COPY public.mail_templates (id, hashtag, lang, subject, description, contents) FROM stdin;
1	#NewMembreshipRecommender	default	{{appName}}: Welcome as a recommender!	Mail to user to acknowledge their status of recommender	<p>Dear {{destPerson}},</p>\r\n<p>Congratulations on passing the PCI RR recommender test! I just added the role of recommender to your profile so you now appear at our <a href="https://rr.peercommunityin.org/about/recommenders" target="_blank" rel="noopener">website</a>&nbsp;and can be invited to handle submissions.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<div>\r\n<div>If you are new to RRs and/or to PCI RR and would like help from an experienced recommender on the first submission you handle (if you have already handled a submission(s), you can still ask for this), you can contact any of the following recommenders to see if they would be willing to be a co-recommender with you. The co-recommender would take a back seat, be available to answer questions, and offer feedback as needed throughout the process. Chris did this for me on the first submission I handled and I felt reassured that he wouldn’t let me do anything wrong (I was nervous I was going to mess up). I found it really useful to ask a few questions and then emailed him to ask him to look over the submission at the website when I was ready to submit a decision.</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>Here is the list of experienced recommenders you can ask to be co-recommenders (after you accept an invitation to be a recommender for a particular submission):</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;-&nbsp;<a href="https://rr.peercommunityin.org/public/user_public_page?userId=5">Zoltan Dienes</a>&nbsp;(<a href="mailto:zoltan.dienes@googlemail.com">zoltan.dienes@googlemail.com</a>)</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;-&nbsp;<a href="https://rr.peercommunityin.org/public/user_public_page?userId=232">Rob McIntosh</a>&nbsp;(<a href="mailto:r.d.mcintosh@ed.ac.uk">r.d.mcintosh@ed.ac.uk</a>)</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;-&nbsp;<a href="https://rr.peercommunityin.org/public/user_public_page?userId=163">moin syed</a>&nbsp;(<a href="mailto:moin@umn.edu">moin@umn.edu</a>)</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;- <a href="https://rr.peercommunityin.org/public/user_public_page?userId=198" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Charlotte Pennington</a> (<a href="mailto:c.pennington@aston.ac.uk">c.pennington@aston.ac.uk</a>)</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;-&nbsp;<a href="https://rr.peercommunityin.org/public/user_public_page?userId=346">Matti Karhulahti</a>&nbsp;(<a href="mailto:vmmkar@utu.fi">vmmkar@utu.fi</a>) - qualitative research</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;-&nbsp;<a href="https://rr.peercommunityin.org/public/user_public_page?userId=233">Sam Schwarzkopf</a>&nbsp;(<a href="mailto:s.schwarzkopf@auckland.ac.nz">s.schwarzkopf@auckland.ac.nz</a>)</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>\r\n<div>Of course, the PCI RR Managing Board is always available to support you with all of your submissions, so just write to us at this email address and/or join our Mattermost group for recommenders if you have any questions at any time. <em>If you are interested in joining the Mattermost group, respond to this email and we will send you an email invitation.</em></div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<p>Below are a few details about the recommender role that apply to all PCIs...</p>\r\n<p>The role of a recommender is very similar to that of a journal editor (finding reviewers, collecting reviews, making editorial decisions based on reviews), with the possibility of recommending the reports you have chosen to handle after one or after several rounds of reviews. The evaluation process is designed to guide decisions as to whether to ‘Revise’, ‘Recommend’ or ‘Reject’ the report.</p>\r\n<p>A report recommended by {{appName}} is an article that may be used and cited like any ‘traditional’ article published in a peer-reviewed journal. If you decide to recommend a report, you will need to write a “recommendation”, which will have its own DOI and be published by {{appName}} under the license CC-BY. The recommendation is a short article, similar to a News &amp; Views piece. It has its own title, contains between about 300 and 1500 words, describes the context and explains why the preprint is particularly interesting. The limitations of the report can also be discussed. This text also contains references (citing, at least, the report being recommended). All of the editorial correspondence (reviews, your decisions, authors’ replies) will also be published by {{appName}}.</p>\r\n<p>As a recommender for {{appName}},</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>You will be expected to comply with the code of conduct of {{appName}}, which can be found there (<a href="https://rr.peercommunityin.org/about/ethics">https://rr.peercommunityin.org/about/ethics</a>).</li>\r\n<li>You are eligible for selection as a member of the Managing Board for a period of two years.</li>\r\n<li>You will be notified about new articles recommended by {{appName}}, according to your requested notification frequency and fields of interest.</li>\r\n<li>You will also receive requests to initiate preprint evaluations in your fields of interest with a view to recommending them.</li>\r\n<li>You can propose the nomination of new recommenders to the Managing Board.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>There is also a guide for PCI RR recommenders (<a href="https://rr.peercommunityin.org/help/guide_for_recommenders">https://rr.peercommunityin.org/help/guide_for_recommenders</a>). Details about the recommendation process can be found here (<a href="https://rr.peercommunityin.org/about/full_policies">https://rr.peercommunityin.org/about/full_policies</a>) and in this short <a href="https://youtu.be/u5greO-q8-M" target="_blank" rel="noopener">video</a>.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Thank you so much for your time and support! It's great to have you on board!</p>\r\n<p>All our best,</p>\r\n<p>The Managing Board of {{appName}}</p>
2	#AdminNewUser	default	{{appName}}: A new user has signed up	Mail to MB to indicate the registration of new user	<p>Dear administrators,</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: left;">A new user has joined {{appName}}: {{userTxt}} ({{userMail}}).</p>\r\n<p>If this user can act as a recommender, you should change their status.</p>\r\n<p>Have a nice day!</p>
3	#NewsLetterWeekly	default	{{appName}}: Newsletter	Mail to users that choose to receive the newsletter every week	<p>Dear {{destPerson}},</p>\r\n<p>Here is some news from {{appName}}.</p>\r\n<p>Best regards,</p>\r\n<p>The Managing Board of {{appName}}<br>&nbsp;</p>
4	#CoRecommenderAddedOnArticleAlreadyPublishedStage1	default	{{appName}}: Your co-recommendation of a {{articlePrePost}}	Mail to co-recommender to inform them that they have been declared as a co-recommender of a postprint	<p>Dear {{destPerson}},</p>\r\n<p>A recommendation text for the {{articlePrePost}} by {{articleAuthors}} and entitled <strong>{{articleTitle}}</strong> (DOI <a href="{{articleDoi}}">{{articleDoi}}</a>) is under consideration. You have been declared as a co-recommender of this {{articlePrePost}}. You can view the recommendation by following this link <a href="{{linkTarget}}">{{linkTarget}}</a> or by logging onto the {{appName}} website and going to 'For recommenders —&gt; Your recommendations of posprints' in the top menu.</p>\r\n<p>We are currently handling this recommendation; it will probably be rapidly posted on the {{appName}} website.</p>\r\n<p>If you do not wish to co-author this recommendation, please contact us as soon as possible. Otherwise, we thank you for co-writing this recommendation.</p>\r\n<p>Yours sincerely,</p>\r\n<p>The Managing Board of {{appName}}</p>
5	#CoRecommenderAddedOnArticleStage1	default	{{appName}}: Your co-recommendation of a {{articlePrePost}}	Mail to co-recommender to inform them that they have been declared as a co-recommender of a preprint	<p>Dear {{destPerson}},</p>\r\n<p>A peer-review evaluation of a Stage 1 submission by {{articleAuthors}} and entitled <strong>{{articleTitle}}</strong> (DOI <a href="{{articleDoi}}">{{articleDoi}}</a>) is currently being handled by the recommender {{recommenderPerson}}. This recommender declared you as a co-recommender and, as such, as a co-author of the recommendation if they decide to recommend this submission. The reviews and the recommendation text can be viewed by clicking on this link: <a href="{{linkTarget}}">{{linkTarget}}</a> or by logging onto the {{appName}} website and going to 'For recommenders —&gt; Preprint you are co-handling' in the top menu.</p>\r\n<p>If you do not wish to be a co-recommender of this preprint, please contact us as soon as possible. Otherwise, we thank you for this contribution to {{appName}}.</p>\r\n<p>Yours sincerely,</p>\r\n<p>The Managing Board of {{appName}}</p>
6	#CoRecommenderRemovedFromArticleStage1	default	{{appName}}: Your co-recommendation of a {{articlePrePost}}	Mail to co-recommender to inform them that they have been removed as a co-recommender of a preprint	<p>Dear {{destPerson}},</p>\r\n<p>A recommendation text for the {{articlePrePost}} by {{articleAuthors}} and entitled <strong>{{articleTitle}}</strong> (DOI <a href="{{articleDoi}}">{{articleDoi}}</a>) is under consideration.</p>\r\n<p>You have been removed from co-recommender of this {{articlePrePost}}.</p>\r\n<p>Yours sincerely,</p>\r\n<p>The Managing Board of {{appName}}</p>
7	#CoRecommendersArticleRecommendedStage1	default	{{appName}}: Your co-recommendation of a {{articlePrePost}}	Mail to co-recommenders to indicate them that the preprint is now recommended	<p>Dear {{destPerson}},</p>\n<p>The recommendation for the {{articlePrePost}} by {{articleAuthors}} and entitled <strong>{{articleTitle}}</strong> (doi {{articleDoi}}) is now published on {{appName}} website.</p>\n<p>You can find it there: <a href="{{recommDOI}}">{{recommDOI}}</a></p>\n<p>And there: <a href="{{linkRecomm}}">{{linkRecomm}}</a></p>\n<p>Do not hesitate to share the news as much as possible: social networks if you are on them, mailing, websites, CV, quotation, etc...</p>\n<p>We thank you for co-writing this recommendation.</p>\n<p>Yours sincerely,</p>\n<p>The Managing Board of {{appName}}</p>
8	#CoRecommendersArticleStatusChangedStage1	default	{{appName}}: Your co-recommendation of a {{articlePrePost}}	Mail to co-recommenders to indicate the change of the status of the preprint	<p>Dear {{destPerson}},</p>\n<p>You are co-recommender of the article by {{articleAuthors}} entitled <strong>{{articleTitle}}</strong> (DOI <a href="{{articleDoi}}">{{articleDoi}}</a>).</p>\n<p>The status of this article has changed from "{{tOldStatus}}" to "{{tNewStatus}}".</p>\n<p>You can view the evaluation process by following this link: <a href="{{linkTarget}}">{{linkTarget}}</a> or by logging onto the {{appName}} website and going to 'For recommenders —&gt; Your recommendation of posprints (if it is a posprint) or —&gt; Preprints you are co-handling (if it is a preprint)' in the top menu.</p>\n<p>Yours sincerely,</p>\n<p>The Managing Board of {{appName}}</p>
9	#ManagersArticleCancelledStage1	default	{{appName}}: Article cancelled	Mail to MB to indicate that the submitter cancelled their submission	<p>Dear members of the Managing Board,</p>\r\n<p>The submission of the article entitled "{{articleTitle}}" has been cancelled by the author.</p>\r\n<p>To manage this recommendation, please follow this link <a href="{{linkTarget}}">{{linkTarget}}</a>.</p>\r\n<p>Have a nice day!</p>
10	#ManagersArticleConsideredForRecommendationStage1	default	{{appName}}: Stage 1 submission considered for recommendation	Mail to MB to indicate that a recommender agreed to handle a Stage 1 submission	<p>Dear members of the Managing Board,</p>\r\n<p>A new recommendation is under consideration by {{recommenderPerson}} for {{appName}}.</p>\r\n<p>To manage this recommendation, please follow this link <a href="{{linkTarget}}">{{linkTarget}}</a>.</p>\r\n<p>Have a nice day!</p>
11	#ManagersArticleResubmitedStage1	default	{{appName}}: Article resubmitted	Mail to MB to indicate that a revised version has been submitted and is under consideration by the recommender	<p>Dear members of the Managing Board,</p>\n<p>A new version of the article entitled "{{articleTitle}}" is under consideration by {{recommenderPerson}} for {{appName}}.</p>\n<p>To manage this recommendation, please follow this link <a href="{{linkTarget}}">{{linkTarget}}</a>.</p>\n<p>Have a nice day!</p>
12	#ManagersArticleStatusChangedStage1	default	{{appName}}: Article status changed	Mail to MB to indicate the change of a status of the preprint 	<p>Dear members of the Managing Board,</p>\n<p>The status of the article entitled "{{articleTitle}}" changed from "{{tOldStatus}}" to "{{tNewStatus}}".</p>\n<p>To manage this recommendation, please follow this link <a href="{{linkTarget}}">{{linkTarget}}</a>.</p>\n<p>Have a nice day!</p>
13	#ManagersPreprintSubmissionStage1	default	{{appName}}: Stage 1 submission requiring validation	Mail to MB to indicate a Stage 1 submission	<p>Dear members of the Managing Board,</p>\r\n<p>{{appName}} has received a Stage 1 submission by {{submitterPerson}}.</p>\r\n<p>To validate or delete this submission, please follow this link <a href="{{linkTarget}}">{{linkTarget}}</a> and use the following instructions.</p>\r\n<h3><span style="font-weight: 400;">Does the submission need changes to be submission-ready? Send it to the pre-submission stage</span></h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><span style="font-weight: 400;">An article in the </span><em><span style="font-weight: 400;">For managers &gt; Pending validations</span></em><span style="font-weight: 400;"> needs changes before it will be ready to be validated. Any articles in the Pending validations section can be sent to the pre-submission stage by clicking View/Edit, scroll to bottom, click the black button: </span><em><span style="font-weight: 400;">Put in pre-submission list</span></em><span style="font-weight: 400;">.</span></li>\r\n<li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Then go to: </span><em><span style="font-weight: 400;">For managers &gt; X Articles in the pre-submission stage</span></em><span style="font-weight: 400;">. Find the article here &gt; click View/Edit &gt; edit the email template to the authors to request further changes so it is ready to be validated and click Send.&nbsp;</span></li>\r\n<li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><span style="font-weight: 400;">When the authors make a change, the submission automatically goes back to the </span><em><span style="font-weight: 400;">Pending validations</span></em><span style="font-weight: 400;"> section.&nbsp;</span></li>\r\n<li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><span style="font-weight: 400;">You can do this loop as many times as you want with an article</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3><span style="font-weight: 400;">Validation instructions: Stage 1 (1 page snapshot)</span></h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Read the cover letter and snapshot, make sure they followed the </span><a href="https://rr.peercommunityin.org/help/guide_for_authors#h_61998243643551613309672490"><span style="font-weight: 400;">snapshot instructions</span></a></li>\r\n<li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Check that the submission checklist is complete</span></li>\r\n<li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Check that the link to the manuscript points directly to the snapshot</span></li>\r\n<li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Check that it is a scientifically valid topic</span><span style="font-weight: 400;">&nbsp;</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3><span style="font-weight: 400;">Validation instructions: Stage 1 (full submission)</span></h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Read the cover letter and abstract</span></li>\r\n<li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Check that the submission checklist is complete (click </span><strong><em>Report</em></strong><span style="font-weight: 400;"> and </span><strong><em>Report Survey</em></strong><span style="font-weight: 400;"> links near the top left)</span></li>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="2"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Report Survey</span><span style="font-weight: 400;">: Note for question 18: for private submissions, it is ok if they list the embargo period to go beyond the estimated Stage 2 submission date because question 17 states that this will be the case.&nbsp;</span><span style="font-weight: 400;">Note: you can see if it is private or public in question 5</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Check that the link to the manuscript points directly to the manuscript file (and not to the general OSF project). If there is any supplementary material, check that the manuscript file includes a URL to this/these file(s)</span></li>\r\n<li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Run the abstract through a </span><a href="https://plagiarismdetector.net"><span style="font-weight: 400;">plagiarism checker</span></a></li>\r\n<li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Check that the manuscript uses the study design template (mandatory for full Stage 1s that include hypothesis tests) and that it is scientifically sound; check also that the study design template is integrated within the manuscript, not as an isolated document on an OSF project (it can be in the main text or the supplemental material)</span></li>\r\n<li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Check that it is a scientifically valid topic</span></li>\r\n<li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><span style="font-weight: 400;">See which recommenders were suggested and add/delete as desired and make sure no conflicts of interest</span></li>\r\n<li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><span style="font-weight: 400;">See if a </span><a href="https://rr.peercommunityin.org/about/full_policies#h_4322855162061613307340646"><span style="font-weight: 400;">managing board member with admin rights</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;"> is a co-author - if so, they have to choose signed reviews only</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>Have a nice day!</p>
14	#ManagersRecommendationOrDecisionStage1	default	{{appName}}: Decision or recommendation requiring validation	Mail to MB to indicate that a decision or a recommendation has been posted by a recommender	<p>Dear members of the Managing Board,</p>\n<p>A decision or a recommendation has been written by {{recommenderPerson}} for {{appName}}.</p>\n<p>To validate and/or manage this recommendation or decision, please follow this link <a href="{{linkTarget}}">{{linkTarget}}</a>.</p>\n<p>Have a nice day!</p>
15	#NewMembreshipManager	default	{{appName}}: Welcome to the Managing Board	Mail to recommender to acknowledge their status of manager	<p>Dear {{destPerson}},</p>\r\n<p>You recently joined the Managing Board of {{appName}}. We thank you warmly for agreeing to join the Board and for your time and support for this community.</p>\r\n<p>The members of the Managing Board of {{appName}} are responsible for accepting/rejecting new recommenders. They also deal with any problems arising between authors and the recommenders who have evaluated/recommended their articles. They detect and deal with dysfunctions of {{appName}}, and may exclude recommenders, if necessary. They also rapidly check the quality of formatting and deontology for the reviews and recommendations published by {{appName}}. Finally, members of the Managing Board of {{appName}} are members of the non-profit organization Peer Community in. This non-profit organization is responsible for the creation and functioning of the various Peer Communities in….</p>\r\n<p>Yours sincerely,</p>\r\n<p>The Managing Board of {{appName}}</p>
16	#NewUser	default	{{appName}}: Welcome new PCI RR user	Mail to user to acknowledge their registration	<p>Dear {{destPerson}},</p>\r\n<p>You have recently joined {{appName}}. Thank you for your interest and for registering with us.</p>\r\n<p>More information about {{appName}} can be found here <a href="{{baseurl}}">{{baseurl}}</a> and in this <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=4PZhpnc8wwo">video</a>.</p>\r\n<p>As a user, you can submit your reports {{appName}} for evaluation and recommendation - and find five good reasons to do so in this short <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=jMhVl__gupg">video</a>. Briefly, your reports must first be deposited on a server, such as bioRxiv, and must not already be under review for publication in a traditional journal.</p>\r\n<p>When submitting your reports, you are allowed to suggest recommenders. A recommender is very similar to a journal editor (responsible for finding reviewers, collecting reviews, and making editorial decisions based on reviews), and may eventually recommend your preprint after one or several rounds of reviews. A report recommended by {{appName}} is an article that may be used and cited like any ‘traditional’ article published in a peer-reviewed journal.</p>\r\n<p>Once you have submitted your report, one of the recommenders you suggest, or any other recommender from the community may express an interest in initiating the evaluation process for your report, which will involve sending your report out for peer review.</p>\r\n<p>If you wish to submit a report, please click on the "Submit a report" button on the home page of the {{appName}} website.</p>\r\n<p>As a user, you will also receive alerts every {{days}} concerning recommendations in the following fields published on the {{appName}} web site: {{thematics}}.</p>\r\n<p>Finally, if you are interested in becoming a recommender for {{appName}} - <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=2BDrPoHGkn0">see video</a> - please see details at our website (https://rr.peercommunityin.org/help/become_a_recommenders).</p>\r\n<p>Thanks again for your interest and for joining {{appName}}.</p>\r\n<p>Yours sincerely,</p>\r\n<p>The Managing Board of {{appName}}</p>
18	#RecommenderArticleStatusChangedStage1	default	{{appName}}: Change in article status	Mail to recommender to indicate the change of the status of the preprint	<p>Dear {{destPerson}},</p>\n<p>You have initiated the evaluation of the article entitled <strong>{{articleTitle}}</strong> by {{articleAuthors}} (DOI <a href="{{articleDoi}}">{{articleDoi}}</a>).</p>\n<p>The status of this article has changed from "{{tOldStatus}}" to "{{tNewStatus}}".</p>\n<p>You can view and manage your evaluation process by following this link: <a href="{{linkTarget}}">{{linkTarget}}</a> or by logging onto the {{appName}} website and going to 'For recommenders —&gt; Preprints you are handling' in the top menu.</p>\n<p>We thank you for managing this evaluation.</p>\n<p>Yours sincerely,</p>\n<p>The Managing Board of {{appName}}</p>
19	#RecommenderPostprintStatusChanged	default	{{appName}}: Change in article status	Mail to recommender to indicate a change in the status of their recommendation of a postprint	<p>Dear {{destPerson}},</p>\r\n<p>You have submitted your recommendation of the postprint article entitled <strong>{{articleTitle}}</strong> by {{articleAuthors}} (DOI {{articleDoi}}).</p>\r\n<p>The status of this article has changed from "{{tOldStatus}}" to "{{tNewStatus}}".</p>\r\n<p>You can view and manage your evaluation process by following this link: <a href="{{linkTarget}}">{{linkTarget}}</a> or by logging onto the {{appName}} website and going to 'For recommenders —&gt; Your recommendations of postprints' in the top menu.</p>\r\n<p>We thank you for managing this evaluation.</p>\r\n<p>Yours sincerely,</p>\r\n<p>The Managing Board of {{appName}}</p>
20	#RecommenderStatusChangedToUnderConsiderationStage1	default	{{appName}}: Revised version	Mail to recommender to indicate that a revised version has been submitted and that they must make a decision	<p>Dear {{destPerson}},</p>\r\n<p>The authors of the Stage 1 submission entitled <strong>{{articleTitle}}</strong> and submitted by {{articleAuthors}} have posted their revised version and their replies to your comments and those of the reviewers. They may also have uploaded (as a PDF or Word file) a revised version of their preprint, with the modifications indicated in Track Changes mode and a clean version of their PDF at this address <a href="{{linkTarget}}">{{linkTarget}}</a> (see also attachments in this email).</p>\r\n<p>For this new round of evaluation, please reach a decision to ‘Revise’, ‘Recommend’ or ‘Reject’ the article.</p>\r\n<p>Feel free to contact the authors directly (either via email while cc’ing contact@rr.peercommunityin.org or at the online system by making a Revise decision before sending it to the reviewers) to request any clarifications necessary to be able to make your assessment, including ensuring the authors have responded to all comments in a point-by-point format and revised the manuscript accordingly.</p>\r\n<p>We look forward to your decision. Thanks in advance!</p>\r\n<p>Yours sincerely,</p>\r\n<p>The Managing Board of {{appName}}</p>
21	#RecommenderStatusChangedUnderToRecommendedStage1	default	{{appName}}: Article recommended	Mail to recommender to indicate that the preprint is now recommended	<p>Dear {{destPerson}},</p>\r\n<p>Your recommendation - along with the reviews - is now posted on the {{appName}} website.</p>\r\n<p>You can find it here: <a href="{{linkRecomm}}">{{linkRecomm}}</a></p>\r\n<p>You will find the reference to your recommendation and that of the recommended article.</p>\r\n<p>Do not hesitate to share the news via social networks (if you are on them), emails, websites, CVs, quotes, etc.</p>\r\n<p>Thanks again for recommending this article for {{appName}}.</p>\r\n<p>Yours sincerely,</p>\r\n<p>The Managing Board of {{appName}}</p>
22	#RecommenderSuggestedArticleStage1	default	{{appName}}: Request to act as a recommender for a Stage 1 submission	Mail to suggested recommenders to ask them to act as recommender of a submitted Stage 1 manuscript	<p>Dear {{destPerson}},</p>\r\n<p>You have been suggested as a recommender for a Stage 1 manuscript entitled <strong>{{articleTitle}}</strong> by {{articleAuthors}} (DOI <a href="{{articleDoi}}">{{articleDoi}}</a>). You can obtain information about this request and accept or decline the invitation by following this link <a href="{{linkTarget}}">{{linkTarget}}</a> or by logging in to the {{appName}} website and going to 'For recommenders —&gt; Request(s) to handle a report' in the top menu.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Important information before accepting the invitation to be the recommender for this report:</strong> The role of a recommender is very similar to that of a journal editor (finding reviewers, collecting reviews, taking editorial decisions based on reviews), and may lead to the recommendation of the report after several rounds of reviews. The evaluation forms the basis of the decision to ‘Revise’, ‘Recommend’ or ‘Reject’ the report. A report recommended by {{appName}} is an article that may be used and cited like the ‘traditional’ articles published in peer-reviewed journals. Please see the <a href="https://rr.peercommunityin.org/help/guide_for_recommenders" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Guidelines for recommenders</a>&nbsp;for detailed information. There is also a PCI short video on&nbsp;<a href="https://youtu.be/u5greO-q8-M">How to start and manage a preprint recommendation</a>.</p>\r\n<p>Agreeing to become the recommender for this report means that <strong>you agree to consider this submission for in-depth review</strong>.<strong> Y</strong><strong>ou will then need to perform the following actions: </strong></p>\r\n<div><span style="font-weight: 400;">1. If you judge that the manuscript fails to sufficiently meet the <a href="https://rr.peercommunityin.org/help/guide_for_recommenders#h_6759646236401613643390905">Stage 1 criteria</a> in order to be sent for in-depth review, then</span> you can <strong>desk reject the manuscript outright </strong>or<strong> invite a revision</strong> prior to in-depth review.</div>\r\n<div>2. If you judge the submission to be <a href="https://rr.peercommunityin.org/help/guide_for_recommenders#h_1245019342271613643227798">review-ready</a><span style="font-weight: 400;"><strong> then please </strong></span><strong>send invitations to </strong><strong>5-10 potential reviewers within the next few days</strong><span style="font-weight: 400;"> and then send new invitations until you find at least two (and ideally three) reviewers willing to review the submission.</span><br>3. <strong>post your decision</strong> or write your recommendation text <strong>within 10 days</strong> of receiving the reviews.<br>4. <strong>write the recommendation text</strong> if you decide to recommend this report for {{appName}} at the end of the evaluation process. If after one or more rounds of review, you decide to recommend this report for Stage 1 in-principle acceptance, you will need to write a “<a href="https://rr.peercommunityin.org/help/guide_for_recommenders#h_68746834114021613643858842" target="_blank" rel="noopener">recommendation</a>” that will have its own DOI and be published by {{appName}} under the license CC-BY 4.0. The recommendation is a short summary (of a few hundred words or less), similar to a News &amp; Views piece, describing the context of the study and explaining why the article was accepted and is expected to make a valuable contribution. The limitations of the report can also be discussed. This text also contains references (citing, at least, the report being recommended). All the editorial correspondence (reviews, your decisions, authors’ replies) will also be published by {{appName}}.<br>5. <strong>declare that you have no conflict of interest with the authors or the content of the article.</strong> You <span style="font-weight: 400;">should not handle reports written by close colleagues, including people belonging to the same laboratory/unit/department in the last four years, people with whom you have published in the last four years, with whom you have received joint funding in the last four years, or with whom you are currently writing a manuscript or submitting a grant proposal.</span><a href="https://rr.peercommunityin.org/about/ethics"><span style="font-weight: 400;"> </span></a></div>\r\n<div>\r\n<p>We ask our recommenders to reflect on their potential biases to help make academia more equitable. Please read the <a href="https://zenodo.org/record/5484052#.YVDePS-B1I1">Bias Reflection Guide</a> (Foster et al. 2021) before deciding whether to accept an invitation to be a recommender for a registered report, before writing a response to the authors, and before writing the recommendation text.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n<p>Thank you very much for your assistance.</p>\r\n<p>Yours sincerely,</p>\r\n<p>The Managing Board of {{appName}}</p>
23	#RecommenderSuggestionNotNeededAnymoreStage1	default	{{appName}}: About our request to act as a recommender	Mail to suggested recommenders to indicate that another recommender took the submission in charge	<p>Dear {{destPerson}},</p>\r\n<p>For this submission, your help as a recommender is no longer needed.</p>\r\n<p>You had been suggested as a recommender for a submission entitled <strong>{{articleTitle}}</strong> by {{articleAuthors}} (DOI <a href="{{articleDoi}}">{{articleDoi}}</a>) but another recommender has accepted the assignment and has initiated the evaluation. Consequently, this submission no longer appears in your list of requests to act as a recommender on the {{appName}} webpage.</p>\r\n<p>If you would still like to participate in the evaluation of this submission, please send us an e-mail at {{appContactLink}}. We will inform the recommender handling the evaluation process of your willingness to participate as a co-recommender and they may then contact you.</p>\r\n<p>We hope that, in the near future, you will have the opportunity to initiate the evaluation of another submission.</p>\r\n<p>Thank you for your support.</p>\r\n<p>Yours sincerely,</p>\r\n<p>The Managing Board of {{appName}}</p>
24	#RecommenderThankForPostprint	default	{{appName}}: Thank you for initiating a recommendation!	Mail to recommender to acknowledge its willingness to recommend a postprint	<p>Dear {{destPerson}},</p>\n<p>You have decided to recommend a postprint entitled <strong>{{articleTitle}}</strong>. To view and/or manage your recommendation, please follow this link <a href="{{linkTarget}}">{{linkTarget}}</a> or logging onto the {{appName}} website and going to 'For recommenders —&gt; Your recommendations of postprints' in the top menu.</p>\n<p>We thank you in advance for writing this recommendation.</p>\n<p>Yours sincerely,</p>\n<p>The Managing Board of {{appName}}</p>
25	#RecommenderThankForPreprintStage1	default	{{appName}}: Thank you for handling the evaluation of this Stage 1 submission 	Mail to recommender to thank them for agreeing to handle a Stage 1 submission	<p>Dear {{destPerson}},</p>\r\n<p>You have agreed to be the recommender handling the report entitled <strong>{{articleTitle}}</strong> by {{articleAuthors}} (DOI <a href="{{articleDoi}}">{{articleDoi}}</a>). Thank you very much for your contribution.</p>\r\n<p>Please decide as soon as possible<strong> <span style="font-weight: 400;">whether the manuscript sufficiently meets the <a href="https://rr.peercommunityin.org/help/guide_for_recommenders#h_6759646236401613643390905" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Stage 1 review criteria</a> to merit further consideration. If not, you can invite a revision prior to review or desk reject the submission outright. If you judge it to be review-ready then please</span> send out 5-10 invitations to review this report within the next 7 days</strong>, and then new invitations until you find at least two reviewers willing to review this report. Thank you in advance for your commitment.</p>\r\n<p>Invitations to review can be sent using this link <a href="{{linkTarget}}">{{linkTarget}}</a>. You can also log on to the {{appName}} website and go to 'For recommenders —&gt; Preprint(s) you are handling' in the top menu, and click on the 'choose a reviewer' button.</p>\r\n<p>The reviews you receive should guide your decision – <strong>within 10 days of receiving the last review</strong> – as to whether to ‘Revise’, ‘Recommend’ or ‘Reject’ the report.</p>\r\n<p>If your decision is to ‘Recommend’ this report, you will need to write a “recommendation”, which will have its own DOI and be published by {{appName}} under the license CC-BY-ND. The recommendation is a short article, similar to a News &amp; Views piece. It has its own title, contains between about 300 and 1500 words, describes the context and explains why the report is suitable for Stage 1 in-principle acceptance. The limitations of the report can also be discussed. This text also contains references (citing, at least, the report being recommended). All editorial correspondence (reviews, your decisions, authors' replies) relating to the report will also be published by {{appName}}.</p>\r\n<p>Feel free to contact the authors directly (either via email while cc’ing contact@rr.peercommunityin.org or at the online system by making a Revise decision before sending it to the reviewers) to request any clarifications necessary to be able to make your assessment.</p>\r\n<p>If you need assistance in any way do not hesitate to ask us.</p>\r\n<p>We thank you again for initiating and managing this evaluation.</p>\r\n<p>Yours sincerely,</p>\r\n<p>The Managing Board of {{appName}}</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>
27	#RecommenderReviewConsideredStage1	default	{{appName}}: Request to review accepted	Mail to recommender to indicate that a reviewer agreed to review a preprint they are handling	<p>Dear {{destPerson}},</p>\r\n<p>{{reviewerPerson}} has accepted your invitation to review the preprint entitled <strong>{{articleTitle}}</strong> by {{articleAuthors}} (DOI <a href="{{articleDoi}}">{{articleDoi}}</a>), and has been sent a message indicating that this review must be posted or uploaded on the {{appName}} website before {{dueTime}}.</p>\r\n<p>You will receive a message notifying you of the posting of this review. If the review is not posted by the deadline, you can send the reviewer a reminder by following this link <a href="{{linkTarget}}">{{linkTarget}}</a> or by logging on to the {{appName}} website and going to 'For recommenders —&gt; Preprint(s) you are handling' in the top menu.</p>\r\n<p>We thank you again for managing this evaluation.</p>\r\n<p>Yours sincerely,</p>\r\n<p>The Managing Board of {{appName}}</p>
28	#RecommenderReviewDeclinedStage1	default	{{appName}}: Request to review declined	Mail to recommender to indicate that a reviewer declined to review a preprint they are handling	<p>Dear {{destPerson}},</p>\r\n<p>{{reviewerPerson}} has declined your invitation to review the preprint entitled <strong>{{articleTitle}}</strong> by {{articleAuthors}} (DOI<a href="{{articleDoi}}"> {{articleDoi}}</a>).</p>\r\n<p>You will need to find another reviewer to obtain the two high-quality reviews required. You can invite additional reviewers by following this link <a href="{{linkTarget}}">{{linkTarget}}</a> or by logging onto the {{appName}} website and going to 'For recommenders —&gt; Preprint(s) you are handling' in the top menu.</p>\r\n<p>We thank you again for managing this evaluation.</p>\r\n<p>Yours sincerely,</p>\r\n<p>The Managing Board of {{appName}}</p>
29	#RecommenderReviewerReviewCompletedStage1	default	{{appName}}: Review completed	Mail to recommender to indicate that a review has been completed	<p>Dear {{destPerson}},</p>\r\n<p>The review by {{reviewerPerson}} of the Stage 1 submission entitled <strong>{{articleTitle}}</strong> is now available.</p>\r\n<p>You can view and/or download this review and manage your recommendation by following this link <a href="{{linkTarget}}">{{linkTarget}}</a> or by logging onto the {{appName}} website and going to 'For recommenders —&gt; Preprint(s) you are handling' in the top menu.</p>\r\n<p><strong>If all of the reviews have now been completed</strong> and returned, <strong>we now expect you</strong>, according to your commitment as a recommender of the preprint, <strong>to make a decision within a few days</strong>. If you need more time, please let us know by return mail.</p>\r\n<p>We remind you that this decision must be: ‘Revise’, ‘Recommend’ or ‘Reject’ the preprint.</p>\r\n<p>If you are ready to recommend,&nbsp;<strong>you do not need to submit an “Acceptation” decision</strong>. You should directly post your recommendation.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>The "recommendation" is a short article, similar to a News &amp; Views piece; it has its own DOI and will be published by {{appName}} under the license CC-BY.&nbsp;It has its own title, contains between about 300 and 1500 words, describes the context and explains why the preprint is particularly interesting. The limitations of the preprint can also be discussed. This text also contains references (citing, at least, the preprint being recommended). All the editorial correspondence (reviews, your decisions, authors’ replies) relating to the preprint will also be published by {{appName}}.</p>\r\n<p>We thank you again for managing this evaluation.</p>\r\n<p>Yours sincerely,</p>\r\n<p>The Managing Board of {{appName}}</p>
30	#ReviewerReviewReopenedStage1	default	{{appName}}: You can now modify your review	Mail to reviewer if recommender reopen the review of a reviewer	<p>Dear {{destPerson}},</p>\r\n<p>{{recommenderPerson}}, the recommender managing the evaluation process for the Stage 1 submission entitled <strong>{{articleTitle}}</strong> by {{articleAuthors}} has made your review concerning this preprint available for modification.</p>\r\n<p>You can now access this review, and edit it if necessary.</p>\r\n<p>You can view and edit your reviews by following this link <a href="{{linkTarget}}">{{linkTarget}}</a> or by logging onto the {{appName}} website and going to 'For contributors —&gt; My reviews' in the top menu.</p>\r\n<p>We thank you again for agreeing to review this preprint.</p>\r\n<p>Yours sincerely,</p>\r\n<p>The Managing Board of {{appName}}</p>
31	#ReviewerThankForReviewAcceptationStage1	default	{{appName}}: Thank you for agreeing to review	Mail to a reviewer to thank them for agreeing to review a Stage 1 manuscript	<p>Dear {{destPerson}},</p>\r\n<p>Thank you very much for agreeing to review the Stage 1 Registered Report entitled <strong>{{articleTitle}}</strong> by {{articleAuthors}} (DOI <a href="{{articleDoi}}">{{articleDoi}}</a>).</p>\r\n<p>To view, write, upload and manage your review, please follow this link <a href="{{linkTarget}}">{{linkTarget}}</a> or log onto the {{appName}} website and go to ‘For contributors —&gt; Your reviews’ in the top menu.</p>\r\n<p>When you have written or uploaded your review, you can:</p>\r\n<p>1) save a draft version of your review for future modification by clicking on the ‘Save’ button; this allows you to make changes or to complete your review later;</p>\r\n<p>or</p>\r\n<p>2) save and submit your review by clicking on the ‘Save &amp; submit your review’ button.</p>\r\n<p>If you have saved a draft version of your review, you can come back to it for modification or completion by clicking on ‘For contributors&nbsp;—&gt; Your reviews’ in the top menu, and then on the black ‘View/Edit’ button to the right on the corresponding line. Don’t forget to click on the ‘Save &amp; submit your review’ button to send your completed review to me.</p>\r\n<p>On the PCI RR website you can find an <a href="https://rr.peercommunityin.org/help/guide_for_reviewers#h_6720026472751613309075757" target="_blank" rel="noopener">expanded description of the review criteria</a>, additional <a href="https://rr.peercommunityin.org/help/guide_for_reviewers#h_7586915642301613635089357" target="_blank" rel="noopener">tips for reviewing a RR</a>, and <a href="https://rr.peercommunityin.org/help/guide_for_reviewers" target="_blank" rel="noopener">complete reviewer guidelines</a>.&nbsp;We ask our reviewers to reflect on their potential biases to help make academia more equitable. Please read the <a href="https://zenodo.org/record/5484052#.YVDePS-B1I1">Bias Reflection Guide</a> (Foster et al. 2021) before deciding whether to accept a review invitation and before writing a review. There is also guidance on how to write a fair and respectful review by Foster et al. (<a href="https://zenodo.org/record/5484072#.YVDePy-B1I1">2021</a>).</p>\r\n<p>Thanks in advance for the time spent evaluating this submission. If you have any questions, please feel free to contact us by replying to this message. The recommender handling this submission is {{recommenderPerson}}.</p>\r\n<p>Yours sincerely,</p>\r\n<p>The Managing Board of {{appName}}</p>
32	#ReviewerThankForReviewDoneStage1	default	{{appName}}: Thank you for your Stage 1 evaluation	Mail to reviewer to thank them for their review	<p>Dear {{destPerson}},</p>\r\n<p>Thank you for evaluating the Stage 1 submission entitled <strong>{{articleTitle}}</strong> by {{articleAuthors}}. Your evaluation has been sent to the recommender ({{recommenderPerson}}) handling this manuscript. Your contribution is greatly appreciated.</p>\r\n<p>You can use this message as proof of your work for {{appName}} and you can view your review at <a href="{{linkTarget}}">{{linkTarget}}</a>. Your review, together with the other reviews of this preprint, will guide the decision of the recommender ({{recommenderPerson}}) as to whether to ‘Revise’, ‘Recommend’ or ‘Reject’ this preprint.</p>\r\n<p>Remember that if the recommender eventually comes to a favorable conclusion, all of the editorial correspondence (reviews, including yours, the decisions reached by the recommender, and the authors’ replies) and a recommendation text will be published by {{appName}}, under the license CC-BY. If, after one or several rounds of review, the recommender eventually rejects the preprint, the editorial correspondence will be sent to the authors but will NOT be published. You will be notified by e-mail at each stage in the procedure.</p>\r\n<p>If the recommender asks the authors to revise their preprint, they may invite you to evaluate their responses and the changes they have made to the preprint. If required, we therefore hope that you will be willing to take part in a second round of review.</p>\r\n<p>If you decided NOT to remain anonymous, your name will be passed on to the authors and, if the recommender decides to recommend this preprint, your name will be visible and associated with your review on the {{appName}} website. If you wish to change your mind and remain anonymous, please send a message to {{appContactMail}}, to let the members of the Managing Board know (they will make the necessary changes).</p>\r\n<p>In the meantime, thank you again for conducting this evaluation.</p>\r\n<p>Best wishes,</p>\r\n<p>The Managing Board of {{appName}}</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>
33	#ReviewersArticleRecommendedStage1	default	{{appName}}: Decision on a Stage 1 Registered Report you reviewed	Mail to reviewers to indicate them that the Stage 1 RR they reviewed is now recommended	<p>Dear {{destPerson}},</p>\r\n<p>The Stage 1 Registered Report that you kindly reviewed for {{appName}} has now received in-principle acceptance. If the authors opted for a public recommendation then you will find the approved Stage 1 article - along with your reviews - now posted on PCI RR website: https://rr.peercommunityin.org/</p>\r\n<p>If the authors opted for a private IPA decision then the Stage 1 manuscript, recommendation, and reviews are temporarily embargoed and will be made publicly available following Stage 2 review acceptance.</p>\r\n<p>Many thanks again for taking the time to support this important initiative. Once the authors have completed their research, we will likely invite you to re-evaluate the final article.</p>\r\n<p>Yours sincerely,</p>\r\n<p>The Managing Board of {{appName}}</p>
34	#ReviewersArticleStatusChangedStage1	default	{{appName}}: Decision on a Stage 1 manuscript you reviewed	Mail to reviewers to indicate the change of the status of the preprint they reviewed	<div>Dear {{destPerson}},</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>Thank you for agreeing to review the Stage 1 Registered Report entitled <strong>{{articleTitle}}</strong>. The status of this preprint is now: {{articleStatus}}. To view your review, the reviews of the other referees and the decision taken by the recommender, please follow this link <a href="{{linkTarget}}">{{linkTarget}}</a> or login to the {{appName}} website and go to 'For contributors —&gt; Your reviews' in the top menu, and then click the blue "VIEW/EDIT" button associated with the submission.</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div><span style="font-weight: 400;"><strong>Your feedback matters.</strong> If this is a final decision (Reject or In Principle Acceptance), then please take 5 minutes to leave anonymous feedback about your experience of the completed Stage 1 review process for this submission:</span> <a href="https://registeredreports.cardiff.ac.uk/feedback/feedback/decision_letter.php"><span style="font-weight: 400;">https://registeredreports.cardiff.ac.uk/feedback/feedback/decision_letter.php</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;"> Feedback from reviewers</span> helps us understand what we’re doing well, what we could do better, and how we can improve and innovate the evaluation of Registered Reports. <span style="font-weight: 400;">This feedback is collected by the </span><a href="https://registeredreports.cardiff.ac.uk/feedback/dashboards/"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Registered Reports Community Feedback</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;"> website which is an independent service and research project being undertaken by Cardiff University.</span></div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>We thank you for the time spent evaluating this preprint.</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>Yours sincerely,</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>The Managing Board of {{appName}}</div>
35	#ReviewersArticleCancellationStage1	default	{{appName}}: About our request to act as reviewer for a preprint	Mail to reviewers to indicate that the submitter cancelled their submission	<p>Dear {{destPerson}},</p>\r\n<p>The submission of the Stage 1 manuscript entitled <strong>{{articleTitle}}</strong> by {{articleAuthors}} has been cancelled by the author. Therefore, the recommendation process is closed and a review is no longer required. Thank you for considering this review request.</p>\r\n<p>Yours sincerely,</p>\r\n<p>The Managing Board of {{appName}}</p>
36	#SubmitterAwaitingSubmissionStage1	default	{{appName}}: Decision concerning your submission	Mail to submitter to indicate the need to revise their preprint	<p>Dear {{destPerson}},</p>\r\n<p>Thank you for submitting your Stage 1 Registered Report entitled <strong>{{articleTitle}} </strong>to {{appName}}. Your manuscript has now been reviewed, and the reviewers' comments and the recommender’s decision may be found below.</p>\r\n<p>On the basis of these comments, we cannot accept your manuscript in its present form but would like to invite you to revise your article, taking into account the issues raised by the reviewers. Please note that in-principle acceptance (IPA) and progression to Stage 2 is not guaranteed and any revision may be sent back to the reviewers for further evaluation. You should, therefore, include a point-by-point response to the reviewers' comments, outlining each change made in your manuscript or providing a suitable rebuttal.</p>\r\n<p>When your revised article is ready, please:</p>\r\n<p>1) Upload the new version of your manuscript onto your preferred open archive;</p>\r\n<p>2) Follow this link <a href="{{linkTarget}}">{{linkTarget}}</a> or log onto the {{appName}} website and go to 'For Contributors -&gt; Your submitted reports' in the top menu;</p>\r\n<p>3) Make your changes to the title, summary, link to the article (or its DOI) and keywords if necessary by clicking on the 'Edit Article' button. If you haven't already, you may also upload a picture or an illustration for which you own the rights – this picture will be used to illustrate your article, if recommended;</p>\r\n<p>4) Write, copy/paste, or upload (as a PDF file) your reply to the recommender's and reviewers' comments by clicking on the 'Write, edit or upload your reply to recommender' button. You must also upload (as a PDF file) a revised version of your article, with all modifications indicated in Track Changes;</p>\r\n<p>5) When you are ready to submit your new version, click on the 'Save &amp; submit your reply' button.</p>\r\n<p>As a reminder: if, in the Stage 1 submission checklist, you chose the option to publish the Stage 1 reviews at the point of IPA, then, if IPA is awarded, the editorial correspondence (reviews, recommender’s decisions, authors’ replies) and a recommendation text will be published immediately at the {{appName}} website under a CC-BY license. Alternatively, if you chose to delay the publication of the Stage 1 recommendation and reviews until final Stage 2 acceptance then IPA will be awarded privately. In either case, depending on your checklist selections, the current list of <a href="https://rr.peercommunityin.org/about/pci_rr_interested_journals" target="_blank" rel="noopener">PCI RR-interested journals</a> may then be alerted to the IPA, and we will inform you as to which among the set of <a href="https://rr.peercommunityin.org/about/pci_rr_friendly_journals" target="_blank" rel="noopener">PCI RR-friendly journals</a> is an eligible outlet that automatically offers IPA.</p>\r\n<p>In the event that your revised submission is rejected, the reviews and decision will be sent to you, but they will not be published or publicly released by {{appName}}. They will be safely stored in our database, to which only the Managing Board has access. You will be notified by e-mail at each stage in the procedure.</p>\r\n<p>There is no particular deadline for submitting your revised manuscript, but we encourage authors to revise manuscripts promptly to ensure that, in cases where Stage 1 re-review is necessary, the same reviewers will be available.</p>\r\n<p>We look forward to receiving your revised manuscript. Should you decide not revise your manuscript for PCI RR then we would be grateful if you could let us know so that we can cancel your submission on the system.</p>\r\n<p>Yours sincerely,</p>\r\n<p>The Managing Board of {{appName}}</p>\r\n<div>{{recommendationProcess}}</div>
37	#SubmitterCancelledSubmissionStage1	default	{{appName}}: Cancellation of your submission	Mail to author to acknowledge the cancellation of their Stage 1 submission	<div>Dear {{destPerson}},</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>Your Stage 1 submission entitled <strong>{{articleTitle}}</strong> has been cancelled at your request.</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div><span style="font-weight: 400;"><strong>Your feedback matters.</strong> If you are cancelling your submission following at least some evaluation by the PCI RR Managing Board, a recommender, or reviewers, please take 5 minutes to leave anonymous feedback about your experience of the Stage 1 review process for this submission:</span> <a href="https://registeredreports.cardiff.ac.uk/feedback/feedback/decision_letter.php"><span style="font-weight: 400;">https://registeredreports.cardiff.ac.uk/feedback/feedback/decision_letter.php</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;"> Feedback from authors</span> helps us understand what we’re doing well, what we could do better, and how we can improve and innovate the review process for Registered Reports. <span style="font-weight: 400;">This feedback is collected by the </span><a href="https://registeredreports.cardiff.ac.uk/feedback/dashboards/"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Registered Reports Community Feedback</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;"> website which is an independent service and research project, being undertaken by Cardiff </span><span style="font-weight: 400;">University.</span></div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>Yours sincerely,</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>The Managing Board of {{appName}}</div>
38	#SubmitterNotConsideredSubmission	default	{{appName}}: Decision concerning your submission	Mail to submitter to indicate that their preprint has not been considered for evaluation	<p>Dear {{destPerson}},<br><br>Thank you for your submission entitled <strong>{{articleTitle}}</strong> to {{appName}}.</p>\r\n<p>Unfortunately, we are canceling this submission either because it does not meet the PCI RR criteria or because no recommender has initiated the evaluation of your submission since the request was made {{unconsider_limit_days}} days ago.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Yours sincerely,</p>\r\n<p>The Managing Board of {{appName}}</p>
41	#SubmitterPreprintStatusChangedStage1	default	{{appName}}: Change in the status of your preprint	Mail to submitter if there is a change in the status of their preprint	<p>Dear {{destPerson}},</p>\r\n<p>The status of your preprint entitled <strong>{{articleTitle}}</strong> has changed from "{{tOldStatus}}" to "{{tNewStatus}}".</p>\r\n<p>You can view, edit, or cancel your submission by following this link <a href="{{linkTarget}}">{{linkTarget}}</a> or by logging onto the {{appName}} website and going to 'For contributors —&gt; Your submitted preprints' in the top menu.</p>\r\n<p>We thank you again for your submission.</p>\r\n<p>Yours sincerely,</p>\r\n<p>The Managing Board of {{appName}}</p>
42	#SubmitterPreprintUnderConsiderationStage1	default	{{appName}}: Consideration of your Stage 1 submission	Mail to submitter that a recommender has agreed to handle their submission	<p>Dear {{destPerson}},</p>\r\n<p>You have submitted your report entitled <strong>{{articleTitle}}</strong> to {{appName}}. We are pleased to inform you that a recommender has initiated the evaluation process.</p>\r\n<p>At this stage in the process, your article will be evaluated by the recommender. Prior to specialist review, the recommender may desk reject your submission or invite you to submit a revised manuscript. If the recommender judges that the manuscript sufficiently meets the Stage 1 criteria to be suitable for in-depth evaluation, it will be sent to several referees who will provided specialist reviews. Based on these assessments, the recommender will reject, recommend, or ask you to modify your article and to respond to the questions and points raised by the reviewers.</p>\r\n<p>We remind you that this report must not be submitted for publication elsewhere until its evaluation by {{appName}} is complete.</p>\r\n<p>If after one or several rounds of reviews, the recommender handling your report awards Stage 1 in-principle acceptance, then the editorial correspondence (reviews, recommender’s decisions, authors’ replies) and a recommendation text will be published by {{appName}} under a CC-BY 4.0 license. Depending on your checklist selections, publication of these records will occur either at the point of Stage 1 in-principle acceptance or following Stage 2 acceptance.</p>\r\n<p>Alternatively, if the recommender decides to reject your submission, the reviews and the decision will be sent to you, but they will not be published or publicly released by {{appName}}. They will be safely stored in our database, to which only the Managing Board has access. You will be notified by e-mail at each stage in this process.</p>\r\n<p>To view or cancel your submission, please follow this link <a href="{{linkTarget}}">{{linkTarget}}</a> or log in at the {{appName}} website and go to 'For contributors —&gt; Your submitted reports' in the top menu. You can also monitor the progress of your submission any time by navigating to 'For contributors' &gt; 'Your submitted reports' &gt; 'VIEW/EDIT' &gt; and then scroll down and expand the <em>Timeline</em> section.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>We thank you again for your submission.</p>\r\n<p>Yours sincerely,</p>\r\n<p>The Managing Board of {{appName}}</p>
43	#SubmitterRecommendedPreprintStage1	default	{{appName}}: Stage 1 in-principle acceptance of your manuscript	Mail to author containing notification of a Stage 1 IPA decision	<div>Dear {{destPerson}},</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>Thank you for submitting your manuscript to PCI RR for consideration as a Registered Report (Stage 1). After careful consideration, we are pleased to award in-principle acceptance (IPA) of your submission.</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>Please read the following letter carefully.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div><strong>Preregistration of the Stage 1 manuscript</strong>. As noted in the <a href="https://rr.peercommunityin.org/help/guide_for_authors#h_2238970114821613309509575" target="_blank" rel="noopener">author guidelines</a>, PCI RR has now registered your approved Stage 1 manuscript on the OSF, and the URL to this protocol is provided in the Stage 1 recommendation text. Depending on the selections you made in the Stage 1 submission checklist, your approved Stage 1 manuscript has been registered either publicly or under a private embargo. If you opted for a private embargo, note that the embargo will be released and the registered protocol made public when any one of the following conditions are met: submission of the Stage 2 manuscript; withdrawal of the submission and consequent triggering of a Withdrawn Registration; or natural expiry of the embargo at the end of the period you selected in the Stage 1 submission checklist.</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div><strong>Progressing to Stage 2.</strong> You may now move to Stage 2 and complete the study as approved. We would be grateful if you could now update the PCI RR Managing board (<a href="mailto:contact@rr.peercommunityin.org">contact@rr.peercommunityin.org</a>) as to the anticipated completion date of your study. This deadline can be readily altered in consultation with the Managing Board (e.g. in case of delays requiring additional time to complete the research). However, in the event that you should fail to submit the Stage 2 manuscript within 6 months of the mutually agreed deadline and also become non-responsive during this period to enquiries, then the manuscript will be considered by PCI RR to be de facto withdrawn, triggering publication of a Withdrawn Registration.</div>\r\n<div>Following completion of your study, we invite you to resubmit one or more Stage 2 Registered Reports, depending on whether this IPA applies to a regular RR (involving one Stage 2 output) or a programmatic RR (involving multiple Stage 2 outputs). If you are receiving IPA for a programmatic RR then please familiarise yourself with the <a href="https://rr.peercommunityin.org/help/guide_for_authors#h_52492857233251613309610581" target="_blank" rel="noopener">reporting requirements for programmatic RRs at Stage 2</a>.</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div><strong>Stage 2 review criteria (see <a href="https://rr.peercommunityin.org/help/guide_for_authors#h_6720026472751613309075757" target="_blank" rel="noopener">here</a>)</strong>. Please note that a Stage 2 manuscript can be rejected by PCI RR if the recommender and Managing Board consider any of the following conditions to be met:</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>The results were unable to test the authors' proposed hypotheses (or answer the proposed research question) by failing to meet any approved outcome-neutral criteria, such as the absence of floor and ceiling effects, success of positive controls or other quality checks</li>\r\n<li>The authors altered the Introduction, rationale, or hypotheses, as approved in the Stage 1 submission</li>\r\n<li>The authors failed to adhere to the registered study procedures or preregistered analyses (and see below concerning necessary deviations from protocol)</li>\r\n<li>Any <em>post hoc</em> (unregistered) analyses are either unjustified, insufficiently caveated, or overly dominant in shaping the authors' conclusions</li>\r\n<li>The authors' conclusions were not justified given the data obtained</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div><strong>Deviations from protocol.</strong> Please note that any deviation from the registered study procedures that is not approved in advance by the recommender and Managing Board could lead to rejection at Stage 2. In cases where the preregistered protocol must be altered after IPA due to unforeseen circumstances (e.g. change of equipment or unanticipated technical error), it is imperative that you consult the recommender immediately and prior to the completion of data collection, regardless of how minor the deviation may seem. Minor changes to the protocol that do not increase risk of bias are likely to be swiftly approved. In such cases, IPA would be preserved and the deviation reported in the Stage 2 submission.</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div><strong>Notification of PCI RR-interested journals.</strong> If you consented to notifying PCI RR-interested journals about your IPA then the complete list of <a href="https://rr.peercommunityin.org/about/pci_rr_interested_journals" target="_blank" rel="noopener">PCI RR-interested journals</a> will now be given access to the author names, stated contact details, Stage 1 reviews and recommendation text (provided you also consented to publish the reviews and recommendation at the point of IPA), as well as the URL to the Stage 1 manuscript that has been registered by PCI RR (even if preregistered under a private embargo).</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div><strong>Recommendation text</strong>. The recommender handling your submission has written a Stage 1 recommendation to accompany this decision letter. The recommendation is a short summary describing the context of the study and explaining why the article was accepted and is expected to make a valuable contribution. The recommendation will also state the URL to the registered Stage 1 manuscript on the OSF, the <a href="https://rr.peercommunityin.org/help/guide_for_authors#h_95790490510491613309490336" target="_blank" rel="noopener">level of bias control</a> that was reached in your submission, and will list all eligible <a href="https://rr.peercommunityin.org/about/pci_rr_friendly_journals" target="_blank" rel="noopener">PCI RR-friendly journals</a> that endorse this IPA decision and will later accept your approved Stage 2 manuscript(s) without further peer review. As noted in the author guidelines, the PCI RR Managing Board determines which PCI RR-friendly journals are eligible based on the disciplinary fit, word limit requirements, minimum pre-planned strength of evidence (e.g. level of statistical power), level of bias control achieved, and any other listed journal requirements (such as the acceptance of signed reviews only). <strong>If you opted for the Stage 1 recommendation to be made public at the point of IPA then you will find it now published on the <a href="https://rr.peercommunityin.org/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">PCI RR website under the heading "Latest Recommendations"</a>. </strong>However, if you opted to keep the Stage 1 recommendation and reviews private until Stage 2 acceptance, then they will not appear on the PCI RR website until the completion of Stage 2. For further information, please see <a href="https://osf.io/dcvj7/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">this tutorial </a>on how to interpret the different sections of the Stage 1 recommendation.</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div><span style="font-weight: 400;"><strong>Your feedback matters.</strong> Please take 5 minutes to leave anonymous feedback about your experience of the Stage 1 review process for this submission:</span> <a href="https://registeredreports.cardiff.ac.uk/feedback/feedback/decision_letter.php"><span style="font-weight: 400;">https://registeredreports.cardiff.ac.uk/feedback/feedback/decision_letter.php</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;"> Feedback from authors</span> helps us understand what we’re doing well, what we could do better, and how we can improve and innovate the review process for Registered Reports. <span style="font-weight: 400;">This feedback is collected by the </span><a href="https://registeredreports.cardiff.ac.uk/feedback/dashboards/"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Registered Reports Community Feedback</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;"> website which is an independent service and research project being undertaken by Cardiff University.</span></div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>Congratulations on achieving Stage 1 in-principle acceptance and thank you for using PCI RR.</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>Yours sincerely,</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>The PCI RR Managing Board</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>{{recommendationProcess}}</div>
44	#SubmitterRejectedSubmissionStage1	default	{{appName}}: Decision concerning your Stage 1 manuscript	Mail to author to indicate the rejection of their Stage 1 manuscript	<div>Dear {{destPerson}},</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>Your Stage 1 manuscript entitled <strong>{{articleTitle}}</strong> has now been evaluated by {{appName}} and we regret to inform you that the recommender has decided to reject your submission.</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>The recommender’s decision is below, along with any reviews, where applicable. Reviews and recommendations for rejected submissions are not published or publicly released by {{appName}}. They will be safely stored in our database, to which only the Managing Board has access.</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div><span style="font-weight: 400;"><strong>Your feedback matters.</strong> Please take 5 minutes to leave anonymous feedback about your experience of the Stage 1 review process for this submission:</span> <a href="https://registeredreports.cardiff.ac.uk/feedback/feedback/decision_letter.php"><span style="font-weight: 400;">https://registeredreports.cardiff.ac.uk/feedback/feedback/decision_letter.php</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;"> Feedback from authors</span> helps us understand what we’re doing well, what we could do better, and how we can improve and innovate the review process for Registered Reports. <span style="font-weight: 400;">This feedback is collected by the </span><a href="https://registeredreports.cardiff.ac.uk/feedback/dashboards/"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Registered Reports Community Feedback</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;"> website which is an independent service and research project, being undertaken by Cardiff University.</span></div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>Thank you for your submission.</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>Yours sincerely,</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>The Managing Board of {{appName}}<br>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>{{recommendationProcess}}</div>\r\n</div>
45	#SubmitterPreprintSubmittedStage1	default	{{appName}}: Your submission	Mail to submitter to indicate the validation of their submission	<p>Dear {{destPerson}},</p>\r\n<p>Thank you for submitting your Stage 1 manuscript to {{appName}}. Your submission has now been validated by the Managing Board and recommenders have been invited to take the assignment. You will be notified by email when a recommender agrees to handle your submission. If none of the invited recommenders is able to act as a recommender, you may receive an email inviting you to suggest additional recommenders.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<div>We remind you that this report must not be published or submitted for publication elsewhere. If this report is taken on by a recommender, and therefore sent out for review, you must not submit it to a journal until the evaluation process is complete (i.e., until it has been rejected or received its Stage 2 recommendation by {{appName}}).</div>\r\n<p>To view or cancel your submission, please follow this link {{linkTarget}} or log into the {{appName}} website and go to 'For contributors —&gt; Your submitted reports' in the top menu. You can also monitor the progress of your submission any time by navigating to 'For contributors' &gt; 'Your submitted reports' &gt; 'VIEW/EDIT' &gt; and then scroll down and expand the <em>Timeline</em> section.&nbsp;<br><br>We thank you again for your submission.<br><br>Yours sincerely,<br><br>The Managing Board of {{appName}}</p>
46	#TestMail	default	{{appName}}: Test Mail	Mail test	<p>Dear {{destPerson}},</p>\r\n<p>This is a test message; please ignore.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Test url :&nbsp;<a href="https://rr.peercommunityin.org/help/guide_for_recommenders">https://rr.peercommunityin.org/help/guide_for_recommenders</a></p>
48	#DefaultReviewCancellationStage1	default	{{appName}}: Cancellation of a review request	Mail to reviewer to indicate cancellation of a Stage 1 review invitation	<p>Dear {{destPerson}},</p>\r\n<div>We recently invited you to review a Stage 1 Registered Report entitled "{{art_title}}".&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>We are writing to let you know that we have now found sufficient reviewers for this submission and your evaluation is no longer requested. Many thanks for your consideration.</div>\r\n<p>Best regards,</p>\r\n<p>The Managing Board of {{appName}}</p>
49	#DefaultReviewInvitationRegisteredUserStage1	default	Invitation to review for Peer Community in Registered Reports	Mail to user already registered to invite them to review a Stage 1 manuscript	<div>Dear {{destPerson}},&nbsp;&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>A Registered Report entitled "<strong>{{art_title}}</strong>", has been submitted for potential recommendation by {{description}} (PCI RR) and I am writing to ask if you would kindly consider reviewing it for us. The manuscript can be viewed and downloaded at the following address: <a href="{{art_doi}}">{{art_doi}}</a></div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>Registered Reports (RRs) are a form of empirical research article in which manuscripts containing a study proposal are reviewed prior to data collection or analysis. The aim of this initiative is to minimise publication bias and reporting bias, while also allowing the flexibility to conduct exploratory (unregistered) analyses and report serendipitous findings. Submitted manuscripts can propose novel studies or direct replications of previous studies.</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>PCI RR is a free, non-commercial platform dedicated to the peer review of RR preprints. Once a preprint is reviewed and positively recommended by PCI RR, authors then have the option to submit their manuscript to a traditional journal, and the reviews are published on the PCI RR website. A growing <a href="https://eur03.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=https%3A%2F%2Frr.peercommunityin.org%2Fabout%2Fpci_rr_friendly_journals&amp;data=04%7C01%7Cchambersc1%40cardiff.ac.uk%7C3b0bd2172d19499a650008d934ba39af%7Cbdb74b3095684856bdbf06759778fcbc%7C1%7C0%7C637598796701743675%7CUnknown%7CTWFpbGZsb3d8eyJWIjoiMC4wLjAwMDAiLCJQIjoiV2luMzIiLCJBTiI6Ik1haWwiLCJXVCI6Mn0%3D%7C1000&amp;sdata=JXBq1vVpf1%2FrbMY0RB9K55orGA%2ByyWDd7mduvA7qQvc%3D&amp;reserved=0" target="_blank" rel="noopener">list of PCI RR-friendly journals</a> now immediately accept submissions recommended by PCI RR without further peer review.</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>The peer review process for RRs happens in two stages. Stage 1 submissions include an Introduction, Method, and Pilot Data (where applicable). In evaluating these manuscripts, we ask reviewers to assess:</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>1A. The scientific validity of the research question(s)</div>\r\n<div>1B. The logic, rationale, and plausibility of the proposed hypotheses (where a submission proposes hypotheses)</div>\r\n<div>1C. The soundness and feasibility of the methodology and analysis pipeline (including statistical power analysis or alternative sampling plans where applicable)</div>\r\n<div>1D. Whether the clarity and degree of methodological detail is sufficient to closely replicate the proposed study procedures and analysis pipeline and to prevent undisclosed flexibility in the procedures and analyses</div>\r\n<div>1E. Whether the authors have considered sufficient outcome-neutral conditions (e.g. absence of floor or ceiling effects; positive controls; other quality checks) for ensuring that the obtained results are able to test the stated hypotheses or answer the stated research question(s).</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>The PCI RR website includes an <a href="https://rr.peercommunityin.org/help/guide_for_reviewers#h_6720026472751613309075757" target="_blank" rel="noopener">expanded description of these review criteria</a>, additional <a href="https://rr.peercommunityin.org/help/guide_for_reviewers#h_7586915642301613635089357" target="_blank" rel="noopener">tips for reviewing a RR</a>, and <a href="https://rr.peercommunityin.org/help/guide_for_reviewers" target="_blank" rel="noopener">complete reviewer guidelines</a>. To ensure swift handling of submissions, the requested review time is <strong>{{reviewDuration}}</strong>, but if you are unable to review the manuscript within this time then please let me know by reply email and we can extend the timeframe.</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>Submissions that pass Stage 1 review are issued an in-principle acceptance (IPA), which guarantees a positive recommendation of the completed study if the authors adhere to the approved procedures and propose a defensible interpretation of the results. Completed manuscripts are then peer reviewed again at Stage 2, ideally by the same reviewers as Stage 1.</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div><span style="font-weight: 400;">{{programmaticRR_invitation_text}}</span></div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>In the event of a favourable outcome, all editorial correspondence (reviews, recommender’s decisions, authors’ replies) and a recommendation text will be published by PCI RR under a CC-BY 4.0 license. If, after one or several rounds of review, the preprint is rejected, the editorial correspondence (and specifically your review) will NOT be published. You will be notified by e-mail at each stage in the procedure.</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>Stage 1 manuscripts may be submitted with author names either revealed or masked, and may be published as preprints or embargoed in a recognised repository (such as the OSF) with a private viewable link. Note that to avoid any conflict of interests, where you know the identity of the submitting authors you should not accept to evaluate this submission if the authors are close colleagues (people belonging to the same laboratory/unit/department in the last four years, people with whom you have published in the last four years, with whom you have received joint funding in the last four years, or with whom you are currently writing a manuscript, or submitting a grant proposal).</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>{{signedreview_invitation_text}}</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>I would be grateful if you could let me know as soon as possible whether you are willing to accept my invitation to review this article, or whether you would prefer to decline, by clicking on the link below or by logging onto the PCI RR website and going to 'For contributors —&gt; Invitation(s) to review a report' in the top menu. If you are a new user, you will be asked to create a password before being logged in. If you are reviewing a revised manuscript, you will find the authors' response to reviewers linked on the website.</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>Many thanks for considering this review request.</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>Best wishes,</div>\r\n<div>{{sender}}</div>
50	#DefaultReviewInvitationNewUserStage1	default	Invitation to review for Peer Community in Registered Reports	Mail to user not yet registered to invite them to review a Stage 1 manuscript	<div>Dear {{destPerson}},&nbsp;&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>A Registered Report entitled <strong>"{{art_title}}"</strong>, has been submitted for potential recommendation by {{description}} (PCI RR) and I am writing to ask if you would kindly consider reviewing it for us. The manuscript can be viewed and downloaded at the following address: <a href="{{art_doi}}">{{art_doi}}</a></div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>Registered Reports (RRs) are a form of empirical research article in which manuscripts containing a study proposal are reviewed prior to data collection or analysis. The aim of this initiative is to minimise publication bias and reporting bias, while also allowing the flexibility to conduct exploratory (unregistered) analyses and report serendipitous findings. Submitted manuscripts can propose novel studies or direct replications of previous studies.</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>PCI RR is the next generation of Registered Reports: a free, non-commercial platform dedicated to the peer review of RR preprints. Once a preprint is reviewed and positively recommended by PCI RR, authors then have the option to submit their manuscript to a traditional journal, and the reviews are published on the PCI RR website. A growing <a href="https://eur03.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=https%3A%2F%2Frr.peercommunityin.org%2Fabout%2Fpci_rr_friendly_journals&amp;data=04%7C01%7Cchambersc1%40cardiff.ac.uk%7C3b0bd2172d19499a650008d934ba39af%7Cbdb74b3095684856bdbf06759778fcbc%7C1%7C0%7C637598796701743675%7CUnknown%7CTWFpbGZsb3d8eyJWIjoiMC4wLjAwMDAiLCJQIjoiV2luMzIiLCJBTiI6Ik1haWwiLCJXVCI6Mn0%3D%7C1000&amp;sdata=JXBq1vVpf1%2FrbMY0RB9K55orGA%2ByyWDd7mduvA7qQvc%3D&amp;reserved=0" target="_blank" rel="noopener">list of PCI RR-friendly journals</a> now immediately accept submissions recommended by PCI RR without further peer review.</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>The peer review process for RRs happens in two stages. Stage 1 submissions include an Introduction, Method, and Pilot Data (where applicable). In evaluating these manuscripts, we ask reviewers to assess:</div>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>1A. The scientific validity of the research question(s)</li>\r\n<li>1B. The logic, rationale, and plausibility of the proposed hypotheses (where a submission proposes hypotheses)</li>\r\n<li>1C. The soundness and feasibility of the methodology and analysis pipeline (including statistical power analysis or alternative sampling plans where applicable)</li>\r\n<li>1D. Whether the clarity and degree of methodological detail is sufficient to closely replicate the proposed study procedures and analysis pipeline and to prevent undisclosed flexibility in the procedures and analyses</li>\r\n<li>1E. Whether the authors have considered sufficient outcome-neutral conditions (e.g. absence of floor or ceiling effects; positive controls; other quality checks) for ensuring that the obtained results are able to test the stated hypotheses or answer the stated research question(s).</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<div>The PCI RR website includes an <a href="https://rr.peercommunityin.org/help/guide_for_reviewers#h_6720026472751613309075757" target="_blank" rel="noopener">expanded description of these review criteria</a>, additional <a href="https://rr.peercommunityin.org/help/guide_for_reviewers#h_7586915642301613635089357" target="_blank" rel="noopener">tips for reviewing a RR</a>, and <a href="https://rr.peercommunityin.org/help/guide_for_reviewers" target="_blank" rel="noopener">complete reviewer guidelines</a>. To ensure swift handling of submissions, the requested review time is <strong>{{reviewDuration}}</strong>, but if you are unable to review the manuscript within this time then please let me know by reply email and we can extend the timeframe.</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>Submissions that pass Stage 1 review are issued an in-principle acceptance (IPA), which guarantees a positive recommendation of the completed study if the authors adhere to the approved procedures and propose a defensible interpretation of the results. Completed manuscripts are then peer reviewed again at Stage 2, ideally by the same reviewers as Stage 1.</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div><span style="font-weight: 400;">{{programmaticRR_invitation_text}}</span></div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>In the event of a favourable outcome, all editorial correspondence (reviews, recommender’s decisions, authors’ replies) and a recommendation text will be published by PCI RR under a CC-BY 4.0 license. If, after one or several rounds of review, the preprint is rejected, the editorial correspondence (and specifically your review) will NOT be published. You will be notified by e-mail at each stage in the procedure.</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>Stage 1 manuscripts may be submitted with author names either revealed or masked, and may be published as preprints or embargoed in a recognised repository (such as the OSF) with a private viewable link. Note that to avoid any conflict of interests, where you know the identity of the submitting authors you should not accept to evaluate this submission if the authors are close colleagues (people belonging to the same laboratory/unit/department in the last four years, people with whom you have published in the last four years, with whom you have received joint funding in the last four years, or with whom you are currently writing a manuscript, or submitting a grant proposal).</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>{{signedreview_invitation_text}}</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>I would be grateful if you could let me know as soon as possible whether you are willing to accept my invitation to review this article, or whether you would prefer to decline, by clicking on the link below or by logging onto the PCI RR website and going to 'For contributors —&gt; Invitation(s) to review a report in the top menu. If you are a new user, you will be asked to create a password before being logged in. If you are reviewing a revised manuscript, you will find the authors' response to reviewers linked on the website.</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>Many thanks for considering this review request.</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>Best wishes,</div>\r\n<div>{{sender}}</div>
51	#ReminderSubmitterSuggestedRecommenderNeededStage1	default	{{appName}}: Please, suggest some recommenders for handling your preprint	Mail to submitter if they have not suggested any recommender	<p>Dear {{destPerson}},<br><br>Thank you very much for submitting your preprint to {{appName}}. Before we validate this submission, could you suggest 5 to 10 recommenders:<br><br>1) Go to <a href="{{siteUrl}}">{{siteUrl}}</a> and log in<br>2) Go to 'FOR CONTRIBUTORS —&gt; YOUR SUBMITTED PREPRINTS' in the top menu.<br>3) Click on the black 'ADD/REMOVE' button in the middle of the line referring to the preprint in question and add or remove suggested recommenders.<br>4) Click on the green 'COMPLETE YOUR SUBMISSION' button when you have finished.<br><br>We remind you that you must not suggest a recommender who might have a conflict of interest - see the PCI code of ethical conduct: {{ethicsLink}}.<br><br>If you need any help suggesting recommenders or for using the {{appName}} website, let us know.<br><br>Best regards</p>\r\n<p>The Managing Board of {{appName}}</p>
52	#ReminderSubmitterNewSuggestedRecommenderNeededStage1	default	{{appName}}: Please suggest additional recommenders	Mail to submitter suggest more recommenders bc no one has agreed yet and it has been 10 days	<p>Dear {{destPerson}},</p>\r\n<p><br>Thank you again for submitting your report to {{appName}}. Despite follow up invitations, none of the suggested recommenders have decided to handle the evaluation of your report. We encourage you to suggest additionnal recommenders as follows:<br><br>1) Go to <a href="{{siteUrl}}">{{siteUrl}}</a>&nbsp;and log in<br>2) Go to 'FOR CONTRIBUTORS —&gt; YOUR SUBMITTED REPORTS' in the top menu.<br>3) Click on the black 'ADD/REMOVE' button in the middle of the line referring to the report in question and add or remove suggested recommenders.<br>4) Click on the green 'COMPLETE YOUR SUBMISSION' button when you are finished.<br><br>Thanks in advance<br>All the best</p>\r\n<p>The managing board of {{appName}}</p>
53	#ReminderSubmitterCancelSubmissionStage1	default	{{appName}}: Please, cancel your submission	Mail to submitter if the preprint is not taken in charge after 20 days	<p>Dear {{destPerson}},</p>\r\n<p>You have submitted your preprint entitled&nbsp;<strong>{{articleTitle}}</strong>&nbsp;to {{appName}}.</p>\r\n<p>Unfortunately, no recommender has initiated the evaluation of your preprint since the submission of this preprint &gt; 20 days ago. This does not mean that your preprint is not of sufficient quality and/or interest. However, we suggest that you do not wait any longer for a return from us at this stage and therefore to cancell your submission by:</p>\r\n<p>1) Logging onto the {{appName}} website.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>2) Go to 'FOR CONTRIBUTORS' —&gt; 'YOUR SUBMITTED PREPRINTS' in the top menu.</p>\r\n<p>3) Click on the black 'VIEW/EDIT' button at the right end of the line referring to the preprint in question.</p>\r\n<p>4) Click on the orange 'I WISH TO CANCEL MY SUBMISSION’ button.</p>\r\n<p>We are sorry to bring disappointing news and hope that that you will consider submitting other preprints to {{appName}} in the future.</p>\r\n<p>Yours sincerely,</p>\r\n<p>The Managing Board of {{appName}}</p>
54	#ReminderSuggestedRecommenderInvitationStage1	default	{{appName}}: Request to act as a recommender for a report - reminder	Mail to suggested recommenders to remind them to act as recommender of a submitted report	<p>Dear {{destPerson}},</p>\r\n<p>A few days ago, you were suggested as a recommender for a report entitled&nbsp;<strong>{{articleTitle}}</strong>&nbsp;by {{articleAuthors}} (DOI <a href="{{articleDoi}}">{{articleDoi}}</a>). You can obtain information about this request and accept or decline this invitation by following this link&nbsp;<a href="{{linkTarget}}">{{linkTarget}}</a> or by logging in to the {{appName}} website and going to 'For recommenders —&gt; Request(s) to handle a report' in the top menu.</p>\r\n<p>The role of a recommender is very similar to that of a journal editor (finding reviewers, collecting reviews, taking editorial decisions based on reviews), and may lead to the recommendation of the report after several rounds of reviews. The evaluation forms the basis of the decision to ‘Revise’, ‘Recommend’ or ‘Reject’ the report. A report recommended by {{appName}} is an article that may be used and cited like &nbsp;‘traditional’ articles published in peer reviewed journals.</p>\r\n<p>If, after one or several rounds of review, you decide to recommend this report, you will need to write a “recommendation” that will have its own DOI and be published by {{appName}} under a CC-BY 4.0 license. The recommendation is a short article, similar to a News &amp; Views piece. It has its own title, is 300-1500 words, describes the context, and explains why the report is particularly interesting. The limitations of the report can also be discussed. This text also contains references (citing, at least, the report being recommended). All the editorial correspondence (reviews, your decisions, authors’ replies) will also be published by {{appName}}.</p>\r\n<p>If you agree to handle this report, you will be responsible for managing the evaluation process until you reach a final decision (i.e., to recommend or reject this report). You will be able to invite, through the {{appName}} website, reviewers included in the {{appName}} database or from your own network.</p>\r\n<p>Details about the recommendation process can be found here&nbsp;<a href="{{helpUrl}}">{{helpUrl}}</a>. You can also watch this short video made by PCI:&nbsp;<a href="https://youtu.be/u5greO-q8-M">How to start and manage a preprint recommendation</a>.</p>\r\n<p>Thanks again for your help.</p>\r\n<p>Yours sincerely,</p>\r\n<p>The Managing Board of {{appName}}</p>
55	#ReminderRecommenderReviewersNeededStage1	default	{{appName}}: Please decide on course of action for Stage 1 manuscript you are handling	Mail to recommender to remind them of the process for handling a Stage 1 manuscript	<p>Dear {{destPerson}},</p>\r\n<p>Thanks again for taking in charge entitled <strong>{{articleTitle}}</strong> by {{articleAuthors}}. We remind you that you have agreed to send out 5-10 invitations to review this report within the next 7 days, and to send out reminders and/or new invitations, over a period of one week if necessary, until you manage to find at least two reviewers willing to review this report within {{reviewDuration}}. Thanks in advance for sending those invitation which would avoid delaying the reviewing process. To invite reviewer, please:</p>\r\n<p>1) Go to <a href="{{siteUrl}}">{{siteUrl}}</a> and log in</p>\r\n<p>2) Go to 'FOR RECOMMENDERS —&gt; REPORT(S) YOU ARE HANDLING' in the top menu.</p>\r\n<p>3) Click on the black 'INVITE A REVIEWER' button in the line corresponding to the report considered.</p>\r\n<p>-To invite a reviewer not included in the database of {{appName}}: click on the black ‘CHOOSE A REVIEWER OUTSIDE {{appName}} DATABASE’ button and complete the form (first name, last name and e-mail address of the reviewer). You can change the subject and/or the message if you wish. Then, click on the blue 'SEND E-MAIL' button at the end of the form.</p>\r\n<p>-To invite a reviewer from the {{appName}} database: click on the green ‘CHOOSE A REVIEWER FROM {{appName}} DATABASE’ button. A search engine and a filter based on thematic fields may be used. Select a reviewer by clicking on the black ‘ADD’ button at the right end of the corresponding line. You can modify the subject and/or the message of the e-mail before sending it. Then, click on the blue 'SEND E-MAIL' button at the end of the form.</p>\r\n<p>4) When you have sent invitations to all your chosen reviewers, click on the blue 'DONE 'button.</p>\r\n<p>If you need assistance in any way do not hesitate to ask us.</p>\r\n<p>Thanks in advance.</p>\r\n<p>Best regards</p>\r\n<p>The Managing Board of {{appName}}</p>
56	#ReminderRecommenderNewReviewersNeededStage1	default	{{appName}}: Please invite additional Stage 1 reviewers	Mail to recommender to ask them to send new referee invitations if <2 reviewers have accepted the review invitation	<p>Dear {{destPerson}},</p>\r\n<p>Thanks for sending invitations to review the Stage 1 submission by {{articleAuthors}}. All invited reviewers have already received a reminder, but you still need to secure two agreed reviewers. Hence, we encourage you to invite further reviewers as follows:</p>\r\n<p>1) Go to&nbsp;<a href="{{siteUrl}}">{{siteUrl}}</a>&nbsp;and log in</p>\r\n<p>2) Go to 'FOR RECOMMENDERS —&gt; PREPRINT(S) YOU ARE HANDLING' in the top menu.</p>\r\n<p>3) Click on the black 'INVITE A REVIEWER' button in the line corresponding to the preprint considered.</p>\r\n<p>-To invite a reviewer not included in the database of {{appName}}: click on the black ‘CHOOSE A REVIEWER OUTSIDE {{appName}} DATABASE’ button and complete the form (first name, last name and e-mail address of the reviewer). You can change the subject and/or the message if you wish. Then, click on the blue 'SEND E-MAIL' button at the end of the form.</p>\r\n<p>-To invite a reviewer from the {{appName}} database: click on the green ‘CHOOSE A REVIEWER FROM {{appName}} DATABASE’ button. A search engine and a filter based on thematic fields may be used. Select a reviewer by clicking on the black ‘ADD’ button at the right end of the corresponding line. You can modify the subject and/or the message of the e-mail before sending it. Then, click on the blue 'SEND E-MAIL' button at the end of the form.</p>\r\n<p>4) When you have sent invitations to all of your chosen reviewers, click on the blue 'DONE 'button.</p>\r\n<p>If you need assistance in any way do not hesitate to ask us.</p>\r\n<p>Thanks in advance and thanks again for handling this preprint.</p>\r\n<p>Best regards</p>\r\n<p>The Managing Board of {{appName}}</p>
60	#ReminderRecommenderRevisedDecisionSoonDueStage1	default	{{appName}}: Editorial decision	Mail to recommender to indicate a decision soon due about the revised version	<div>Dear {{destPerson}},<br><br>A few days ago, you should have received the authors' response, a tracked changes version and the link to a revised version of their article on the {{articleTitle}} by {{articleAuthors}}. <br><br></div>\r\n<div>You can reinvite the reviewers for another round of in-depth evaluation or you can issue a decision without further review.</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>To issue a decision:</div>\r\n<div>\r\n<div dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-position: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">1) Go to <a href="{{siteUrl}}">{{siteUrl}}</a></span><span style="font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-position: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;"> and log in&nbsp;</span></div>\r\n<div dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-position: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">2) Go to '<strong>For Recommenders</strong>'—&gt; '<strong>Reports(s) you are handling</strong>' in the top menu. </span></div>\r\n<div dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-position: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">3) Click the '<strong>View/Edit</strong>' button. </span></div>\r\n<div dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-position: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">4) Click '<strong>Write or edit your decision / recommendation</strong>’. </span></div>\r\n<div dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-position: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">5) Indicate your decision (<strong>revise</strong>, <strong>reject</strong>, <strong>recommend</strong>, <strong>recommend but keep private until Stage 2</strong>).</span></div>\r\n<div dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-position: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">6) Choose a decision or recommendation title (this is of particular importance only for decisions to recommend the preprint concerned) and write or copy/paste your decision or recommendation text.&nbsp;</span></div>\r\n<div dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-position: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">-You can save a draft version of your decision or recommendation text by clicking 'Save' (you will then have to go through steps 1 to 5 to complete your decision or recommendation). </span></div>\r\n<div dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-position: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">7) To send your decision or recommendation to the managing board for validation, click on the green 'Save and submit' button. This will result in your decision or recommendation being sent to the Managing Board for validation.</span></div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div><br>Thank you for handling this submission.</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>The Managing Board of {{appName}}</div>
61	#ReminderRecommenderRevisedDecisionDueStage1	default	{{appName}}: Editorial decision - reminder	Mail to recommender to indicate a decision due about the revised version	<p>Dear {{destPerson}},</p>\r\n<p>This is reminder for your decision on the revised version of the submission by {{articleAuthors}}. </p>\r\n<div>You can reinvite the reviewers for another round of in-depth evaluation or you can issue a decision without further review.</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>To issue a decision:</div>\r\n<div>\r\n<div dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-position: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">1) Go to <a href="{{siteUrl}}">{{siteUrl}}</a></span><span style="font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-position: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;"> and log in&nbsp;</span></div>\r\n<div dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-position: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">2) Go to '<strong>For Recommenders</strong>'—&gt; '<strong>Reports(s) you are handling</strong>' in the top menu. </span></div>\r\n<div dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-position: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">3) Click the '<strong>View/Edit</strong>' button. </span></div>\r\n<div dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-position: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">4) Click '<strong>Write or edit your decision / recommendation</strong>’. </span></div>\r\n<div dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-position: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">5) Indicate your decision (<strong>revise</strong>, <strong>reject</strong>, <strong>recommend</strong>, <strong>recommend but keep private until Stage 2</strong>).</span></div>\r\n<div dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-position: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">6) Choose a decision or recommendation title (this is of particular importance only for decisions to recommend the preprint concerned) and write or copy/paste your decision or recommendation text.&nbsp;</span></div>\r\n<div dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-position: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">-You can save a draft version of your decision or recommendation text by clicking 'Save' (you will then have to go through steps 1 to 5 to complete your decision or recommendation). </span></div>\r\n<div dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-position: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">7) To send your decision or recommendation to the managing board for validation, click on the green 'Save and submit' button. This will result in your decision or recommendation being sent to the Managing Board for validation.</span></div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div><br>Thank you for handling this submission.</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>The Managing Board of {{appName}}</div>
62	#ReminderRecommenderRevisedDecisionOverDueStage1	default	{{appName}}: Editorial decision overdue	Mail to recommender to indicate an overdue decision about the revised version	<p>Dear {{destPerson}},</p>\r\n<p>This is a further reminder for your decision on the revised version of the submission <strong>{{articleTitle}} </strong>by {{articleAuthors}}. </p>\r\n<div>You can reinvite the reviewers for another round of in-depth evaluation or you can issue a decision without further review.</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>To issue a decision:</div>\r\n<div>\r\n<div dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-position: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">1) Go to <a href="{{siteUrl}}">{{siteUrl}}</a></span><span style="font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-position: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;"> and log in&nbsp;</span></div>\r\n<div dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-position: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">2) Go to '<strong>For Recommenders</strong>'—&gt; '<strong>Reports(s) you are handling</strong>' in the top menu. </span></div>\r\n<div dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-position: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">3) Click the '<strong>View/Edit</strong>' button. </span></div>\r\n<div dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-position: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">4) Click '<strong>Write or edit your decision / recommendation</strong>’. </span></div>\r\n<div dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-position: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">5) Indicate your decision (<strong>revise</strong>, <strong>reject</strong>, <strong>recommend</strong>, <strong>recommend but keep private until Stage 2</strong>).</span></div>\r\n<div dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-position: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">6) Choose a decision or recommendation title (this is of particular importance only for decisions to recommend the preprint concerned) and write or copy/paste your decision or recommendation text.&nbsp;</span></div>\r\n<div dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-position: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">-You can save a draft version of your decision or recommendation text by clicking 'Save' (you will then have to go through steps 1 to 5 to complete your decision or recommendation). </span></div>\r\n<div dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-position: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">7) To send your decision or recommendation to the managing board for validation, click on the green 'Save and submit' button. This will result in your decision or recommendation being sent to the Managing Board for validation.</span></div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div><br>Thank you for handling this submission.</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>The Managing Board of {{appName}}</div>
63	#ReminderSubmitterRevisedVersionWarningStage1	default	{{appName}}: Revised version - reminder	Mail to submitter to remind them that they received an interim Stage 1 decision	<p>Dear {{destPerson}},</p>\r\n<p>Thanks again for submitting your Stage 1 Registered Report to {{appName}}.</p>\r\n<p>By now you should have received the decision of the recommender and the accompanying reviews. We hope you found this feedback useful and constructive. If for any reason you did not receive the decision letter, please let us know as soon as possible.</p>\r\n<p>There is no particular deadline for submitting your revised manuscript, but we encourage authors to revise manuscripts as promptly as possible to ensure that, in cases where Stage 1 re-review is necessary, the same reviewers will be available.</p>\r\n<p>We await your revised submission in due course, and please don't hesitate to contact us via email if you have any questions in the meantime.</p>\r\n<p>Sincerely</p>\r\n<p>The Managing Board of {{appName}}</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>
64	#ReminderSubmitterRevisedVersionNeededStage1	default	{{appName}}: Revised version?	Mail to submitter to verify that they received the decision and if they intend to resubmit	<p>Dear {{destPerson}},</p>\r\n<p>Thanks again for submitting your Stage 1 Registered Report to {{appName}}.</p>\r\n<p>By now you should have received the decision of the recommender and the accompanying reviews. We hope you found this feedback useful and constructive. If for any reason you did not receive the decision letter, please let us know as soon as possible.</p>\r\n<p>There is no particular deadline for submitting your revised manuscript, but we encourage authors to revise manuscripts as promptly as possible to ensure that, in cases where Stage 1 re-review is necessary, the same reviewers will be available. If you have decided not revise your manuscript for PCI RR then we would be grateful if you could let us know.</p>\r\n<p>We await your revised submission in due course, and please don't hesitate to contact us via email if you have any questions.</p>\r\n<p>All the best,</p>\r\n<p>The Managing Board of {{appName}}</p>
65	#ReminderRecommenderDecisionSoonDueStage1	default	{{appName}}: Editorial decision	Mail to recommender to indicate a decision soon due	<div dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-position: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">Dear </span><span style="font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-position: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">{{destPerson}}</span><span style="font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-position: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">,</span></div>\r\n<div dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-position: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">All reviewers of <strong>{{articleTitle}} </strong>by {{articleAuthors}} have posted their reviews some days ago. Please </span><span style="font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-position: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">check to see if there are any outstanding review invitations and, if so, decide whether to wait for further review(s) or cancel the remaining review invitations so you can proceed with a decision.</span></div>\r\n<div dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-position: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">To proceed with your decision, please write your decision text (as an Editor would do) and choose between the 3 decisions: Reject, Revise or Recommend. </span></div>\r\n<div dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-position: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">To post your decision on the {{appName}} website, please:</span></div>\r\n<div dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-position: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">1) Go to <a href="{{siteUrl}}">{{siteUrl}}</a></span><span style="font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-position: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;"> and log in&nbsp;</span></div>\r\n<div dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-position: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">2) Go to '<strong>For Recommenders</strong>'—&gt; '<strong>Reports(s) you are handling</strong>' in the top menu. </span></div>\r\n<div dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-position: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">3) Click the '<strong>View/Edit</strong>' button. </span></div>\r\n<div dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-position: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">4) Click '<strong>Write or edit your decision / recommendation</strong>’. </span></div>\r\n<div dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-position: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">5) Indicate your decision (<strong>revise</strong>, <strong>reject</strong>, <strong>recommend</strong>, <strong>recommend but keep private until Stage 2</strong>).</span></div>\r\n<div dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-position: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">6) Choose a decision or recommendation title (this is of particular importance only for decisions to recommend the preprint concerned) and write or copy/paste your decision or recommendation text.&nbsp;</span></div>\r\n<div dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-position: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">-You can save a draft version of your decision or recommendation text by clicking 'Save' (you will then have to go through steps 1 to 5 to complete your decision or recommendation). </span></div>\r\n<div dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-position: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">7) To send your decision or recommendation to the managing board for validation, click on the green 'Save and submit' button. This will result in your decision or recommendation being sent to the Managing Board for validation.</span></div>\r\n<div dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-position: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">Many thanks in advance.</span></div>\r\n<div dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-position: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">The Managing Board of </span><span style="font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-position: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">{{appName}}</span></div>\r\n<p><span id="docs-internal-guid-7d7c062e-7fff-1d1b-f9f2-a4f242c7a5bf"></span></p>
66	#ReminderRecommenderDecisionDueStage1	default	{{appName}}: Editorial decision - reminder	Mail to recommender to indicate a decision due	<div dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-position: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">Dear </span><span style="font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-position: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">{{destPerson}}</span><span style="font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-position: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">,</span></div>\r\n<div dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-position: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">All reviewers of <strong>{{articleTitle}} </strong>by {{articleAuthors}} posted and completed their reviews 10 days ago or more. This means that it's now time to write a decision text and choose between the 3 decisions: Reject, Revise or Recommend. Note: </span>please check to see if there are any outstanding review invitations and, if so, decide whether to wait for further review(s) or cancel the remaining review invitations so you can proceed with a decision.</div>\r\n<div dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-position: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">To post your decision on the PCI <span style="white-space: normal;">{{appName}}</span> website, please:</span></d