div>\r\n<div dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-position: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">6) Choose a decision or recommendation title (this is of particular importance only for decisions to recommend the preprint concerned) and write or copy/paste your decision or recommendation text.&nbsp;</span></div>\r\n<div dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-position: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">-You can save a draft version of your decision or recommendation text by clicking 'Save' (you will then have to go through steps 1 to 5 to complete your decision or recommendation). </span></div>\r\n<div dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-position: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">7) To send your decision or recommendation to the managing board for validation, click on the green 'Save and submit' button. This will result in your decision or recommendation being sent to the Managing Board for validation.</span></div>\r\n<div dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-position: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">Many thanks in advance.</span></div>\r\n<div dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-position: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">The Managing Board of </span>{{appName}}</div>\r\n<p><span id="docs-internal-guid-7d7c062e-7fff-1d1b-f9f2-a4f242c7a5bf"></span></p>
67	#ReminderRecommenderDecisionOverDueStage1	default	{{appName}}: Editorial decision overdue	Email sent to recommender to remind them to issue a Stage 1 decision	<div dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-position: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">Dear </span><span style="font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-position: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">{{destPerson}}</span><span style="font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-position: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">,</span></div>\r\n<div dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-position: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">All reviewers of <strong>{{articleTitle}} </strong>by {{articleAuthors}} have posted and completed their reviews more than 10 days ago. This means that it's now time to write a decision text and choose between the 3 decisions: Reject, Revise or Recommend. </span>Note: please check to see if there are any outstanding review invitations and, if so, decide whether to wait for further review(s) or cancel the remaining review invitations so you can proceed with a decision.</div>\r\n<div dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-position: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">To post your decision on the PCI {{appName}} website, please:</span></div>\r\n<div dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-position: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">1) Go to <a href="{{siteUrl}}">{{siteUrl}}</a></span><span style="font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-position: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;"> and log in&nbsp;</span></div>\r\n<div dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-position: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">2) Go to '<strong>For Recommenders</strong>'—&gt; '<strong>Reports(s) you are handling</strong>' in the top menu. </span></div>\r\n<div dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-position: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">3) Click the '<strong>View/Edit</strong>' button. </span></div>\r\n<div dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-position: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">4) Click '<strong>Write or edit your decision / recommendation</strong>’. </span></div>\r\n<div dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-position: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">5) Indicate your decision (<strong>revise</strong>, <strong>reject</strong>, <strong>recommend</strong>, <strong>recommend but keep private until Stage 2</strong>).</span></div>\r\n<div dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-position: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">6) Choose a decision or recommendation title (this is of particular importance only for decisions to recommend the preprint concerned) and write or copy/paste your decision or recommendation text.&nbsp;</span></div>\r\n<div dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-position: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">-You can save a draft version of your decision or recommendation text by clicking 'Save' (you will then have to go through steps 1 to 5 to complete your decision or recommendation). </span></div>\r\n<div dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-position: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">7) To send your decision or recommendation to the managing board for validation, click on the green 'Save and submit' button. This will result in your decision or recommendation being sent to the Managing Board for validation.</span></div>\r\n<div dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-position: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">Many thanks in advance.</span></div>\r\n<div dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-position: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">The Managing Board of </span><span style="font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-position: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">{{appName}}</span></div>\r\n<p><span id="docs-internal-guid-7d7c062e-7fff-1d1b-f9f2-a4f242c7a5bf"></span></p>
68	#ReminderReviewerReviewInvitationRegisteredUserStage1	default	{{appName}}: Invitation to review a preprint - reminder	Mail to user already registered to remind them that they have been invited as a reviewer of a Stage 1 manuscript	<p>Dear {{destPerson}},&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>This is a kind reminder about the following invitation to review a preprint for the Peer Community in Registered Reports (PCI RR).</p>\r\n<p>A Registered Report entitled "<strong>{{articleTitle}}</strong>", has been submitted for potential recommendation. The manuscript can be viewed and downloaded at the following address: <a href="{{articleDoi}}">{{articleDoi}}</a></p>\r\n<p>Registered Reports (RRs) are a form of empirical research article in which manuscripts containing a study proposal are reviewed prior to data collection or analysis. The aim of this initiative is to minimise publication bias and reporting bias, while also allowing the flexibility to conduct exploratory (unregistered) analyses and report serendipitous findings. Submitted manuscripts can propose novel studies or direct replications of previous studies.</p>\r\n<p>PCI RR is a free, non-commercial platform dedicated to the peer review of RR preprints. Once a preprint is reviewed and positively recommended by PCI RR, authors then have the option to submit their manuscript to a traditional journal, and the reviews are published on the PCI RR website. A growing <a href="https://eur03.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=https%3A%2F%2Frr.peercommunityin.org%2Fabout%2Fpci_rr_friendly_journals&amp;data=04%7C01%7Cchambersc1%40cardiff.ac.uk%7C3b0bd2172d19499a650008d934ba39af%7Cbdb74b3095684856bdbf06759778fcbc%7C1%7C0%7C637598796701743675%7CUnknown%7CTWFpbGZsb3d8eyJWIjoiMC4wLjAwMDAiLCJQIjoiV2luMzIiLCJBTiI6Ik1haWwiLCJXVCI6Mn0%3D%7C1000&amp;sdata=JXBq1vVpf1%2FrbMY0RB9K55orGA%2ByyWDd7mduvA7qQvc%3D&amp;reserved=0" target="_blank" rel="noopener">list of PCI RR-friendly journals</a> now immediately accept submissions recommended by PCI RR without further peer review.</p>\r\n<p>The peer review process for RRs happens in two stages. Stage 1 submissions include an Introduction, Method, and Pilot Data (where applicable). In evaluating these manuscripts, we ask reviewers to assess:</p>\r\n<p>1A. The scientific validity of the research question(s)</p>\r\n<p>1B. The logic, rationale, and plausibility of the proposed hypotheses (where a submission proposes hypotheses)</p>\r\n<p>1C. The soundness and feasibility of the methodology and analysis pipeline (including statistical power analysis or alternative sampling plans where applicable)</p>\r\n<p>1D. Whether the clarity and degree of methodological detail is sufficient to closely replicate the proposed study procedures and analysis pipeline and to prevent undisclosed flexibility in the procedures and analyses</p>\r\n<p>1E. Whether the authors have considered sufficient outcome-neutral conditions (e.g. absence of floor or ceiling effects; positive controls; other quality checks) for ensuring that the obtained results are able to test the stated hypotheses or answer the stated research question(s).</p>\r\n<p>The PCI RR website includes an <a href="https://rr.peercommunityin.org/help/guide_for_reviewers#h_6720026472751613309075757" target="_blank" rel="noopener">expanded description of these review criteria</a>, additional <a href="https://rr.peercommunityin.org/help/guide_for_reviewers#h_7586915642301613635089357" target="_blank" rel="noopener">tips for reviewing a RR</a>, and <a href="https://rr.peercommunityin.org/help/guide_for_reviewers" target="_blank" rel="noopener">complete reviewer guidelines</a>. To ensure swift handling of submissions, the requested review time is <strong>{{reviewDuration}}</strong>, but if you are unable to review the manuscript within this time then please let me know by reply email and we can extend the timeframe.</p>\r\n<p>Submissions that pass Stage 1 review are issued an in-principle acceptance (IPA), which guarantees a positive recommendation of the completed study if the authors adhere to the approved procedures and propose a defensible interpretation of the results. Completed manuscripts are then peer reviewed again at Stage 2, ideally by the same reviewers as Stage 1.</p>\r\n<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">{{programmaticRR_invitation_text}}</span></p>\r\n<p>In the event of a favourable outcome, all editorial correspondence (reviews, recommender’s decisions, authors’ replies) and a recommendation text will be published by PCI RR under a CC-BY 4.0 license. If, after one or several rounds of review, the preprint is rejected, the editorial correspondence (and specifically your review) will NOT be published. You will be notified by e-mail at each stage in the procedure.</p>\r\n<p>Stage 1 manuscripts may be submitted with author names either revealed or masked, and may be published as preprints or embargoed in a recognised repository (such as the OSF) with a private viewable link. Note that to avoid any conflict of interests, where you know the identity of the submitting authors you should not accept to evaluate this submission if the authors are close colleagues (people belonging to the same laboratory/unit/department in the last four years, people with whom you have published in the last four years, with whom you have received joint funding in the last four years, or with whom you are currently writing a manuscript, or submitting a grant proposal).</p>\r\n<p>{{signedreview_invitation_text}}</p>\r\n<p>We would be grateful if you could let us know whether you are willing to accept this invitation to review this article, or whether you would prefer to decline, by clicking on the link below or by logging onto the PCI RR website and going to 'For contributors —&gt; Invitation(s) to review a report' in the top menu. If you are reviewing a revised manuscript, you will find the authors' response to reviewers linked on the website.</p>\r\n<p>Thanks in advance for your help.</p>\r\n<p>Yours sincerely,</p>\r\n<p>The Managing Board of {{appName}} on behalf of {{recommenderName}}</p>
69	#ReminderReviewerReviewInvitationNewUserStage1	default	Invitation to review for Peer Community in Registered Reports - Reminder	Mail to user not yet registered to remind them that they have been invited as a reviewer of a Stage 1 manuscript	<p>Dear {{destPerson}},&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>This is a kind reminder about the following invitation to review a Stage 1 manuscript for the Peer Community in Registered Reports (PCI RR).</p>\r\n<p>A Registered Report entitled "<strong>{{articleTitle}}</strong>", has been submitted for potential recommendation. The manuscript can be viewed and downloaded at the following address: <a href="{{articleDoi}}">{{articleDoi}}</a></p>\r\n<p>Registered Reports (RRs) are a form of empirical research article in which manuscripts containing a study proposal are reviewed prior to data collection or analysis. The aim of this initiative is to minimise publication bias and reporting bias, while also allowing the flexibility to conduct exploratory (unregistered) analyses and report serendipitous findings. Submitted manuscripts can propose novel studies or direct replications of previous studies.</p>\r\n<p>PCI RR is a free, non-commercial platform dedicated to the peer review of RR preprints. Once a preprint is reviewed and positively recommended by PCI RR, authors then have the option to submit their manuscript to a traditional journal, and the reviews are published on the PCI RR website. A growing <a href="https://eur03.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=https%3A%2F%2Frr.peercommunityin.org%2Fabout%2Fpci_rr_friendly_journals&amp;data=04%7C01%7Cchambersc1%40cardiff.ac.uk%7C3b0bd2172d19499a650008d934ba39af%7Cbdb74b3095684856bdbf06759778fcbc%7C1%7C0%7C637598796701743675%7CUnknown%7CTWFpbGZsb3d8eyJWIjoiMC4wLjAwMDAiLCJQIjoiV2luMzIiLCJBTiI6Ik1haWwiLCJXVCI6Mn0%3D%7C1000&amp;sdata=JXBq1vVpf1%2FrbMY0RB9K55orGA%2ByyWDd7mduvA7qQvc%3D&amp;reserved=0" target="_blank" rel="noopener">list of PCI RR-friendly journals</a> now immediately accept submissions recommended by PCI RR without further peer review.</p>\r\n<p>The peer review process for RRs happens in two stages. Stage 1 submissions include an Introduction, Method, and Pilot Data (where applicable). In evaluating these manuscripts, we ask reviewers to assess:</p>\r\n<p>1A. The scientific validity of the research question(s)</p>\r\n<p>1B. The logic, rationale, and plausibility of the proposed hypotheses (where a submission proposes hypotheses)</p>\r\n<p>1C. The soundness and feasibility of the methodology and analysis pipeline (including statistical power analysis or alternative sampling plans where applicable)</p>\r\n<p>1D. Whether the clarity and degree of methodological detail is sufficient to closely replicate the proposed study procedures and analysis pipeline and to prevent undisclosed flexibility in the procedures and analyses</p>\r\n<p>1E. Whether the authors have considered sufficient outcome-neutral conditions (e.g. absence of floor or ceiling effects; positive controls; other quality checks) for ensuring that the obtained results are able to test the stated hypotheses or answer the stated research question(s).</p>\r\n<p>The PCI RR website includes an <a href="https://rr.peercommunityin.org/help/guide_for_reviewers#h_6720026472751613309075757" target="_blank" rel="noopener">expanded description of these review criteria</a>, additional <a href="https://rr.peercommunityin.org/help/guide_for_reviewers#h_7586915642301613635089357" target="_blank" rel="noopener">tips for reviewing a RR</a>, and <a href="https://rr.peercommunityin.org/help/guide_for_reviewers" target="_blank" rel="noopener">complete reviewer guidelines</a>. To ensure swift handling of submissions, the requested review time is <strong>{{reviewDuration}}</strong>, but if you are unable to review the manuscript within this time then please let us know by reply email and we can extend the timeframe.</p>\r\n<p>Submissions that pass Stage 1 review are issued an in-principle acceptance (IPA), which guarantees a positive recommendation of the completed study if the authors adhere to the approved procedures and propose a defensible interpretation of the results. Completed manuscripts are then peer reviewed again at Stage 2, ideally by the same reviewers as Stage 1.</p>\r\n<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">{{programmaticRR_invitation_text}}</span></p>\r\n<p>In the event of a favourable outcome, all editorial correspondence (reviews, recommender’s decisions, authors’ replies) and a recommendation text will be published by PCI RR under a CC-BY 4.0 license. If, after one or several rounds of review, the preprint is rejected, the editorial correspondence (and specifically your review) will NOT be published. You will be notified by e-mail at each stage in the procedure.</p>\r\n<p>Stage 1 manuscripts may be submitted with author names either revealed or masked, and may be published as preprints or embargoed in a recognised repository (such as the OSF) with a private viewable link. Note that to avoid any conflict of interests, where you know the identity of the submitting authors you should not accept to evaluate this submission if the authors are close colleagues (people belonging to the same laboratory/unit/department in the last four years, people with whom you have published in the last four years, with whom you have received joint funding in the last four years, or with whom you are currently writing a manuscript, or submitting a grant proposal).</p>\r\n<p>{{signedreview_invitation_text}}</p>\r\n<p>I would be most grateful if you could let me know using the link below whether you are willing to accept our invitation to review this article, or whether you would prefer to decline. If you accept the assignment then once you have entered a new password and logged onto the website, please go to 'For contributors —&gt; Invitation(s) to review a report' in the top menu. If you are reviewing a revised manuscript, you will find the authors' response to reviewers linked on the website.</p>\r\n<p>Thanks in advance for your help.</p>\r\n<p>Best wishes,</p>\r\n<p>The Managing Board of {{appName}} on behalf of {{recommenderName}}</p>
70	#UserChangeMail	default	{{appName}}: validate your new email address	Mail to user to validate its new email address	<p>Dear {{destPerson}},</p>\r\n<p>Please validate your new e-mail address by clicking on this link:<br><a href="{{verifyMailUrl}}">{{verifyMailUrl}}</a></p>\r\n<p>Thanks in avance</p>\r\n<p>The Managing board of {{appName}}</p>
71	#UserRecoverMail	default	{{appName}}: Your email address has been changed	Mail to user that he might revert the change of their email address	<p>Dear {{destPerson}},</p>\r\n<p>You recently asked to change your email address.</p>\r\n<p>If you want to cancel this email address change please follow this link :<br><a href="{{recoverMailUrl}}">{{recoverMailUrl}}</a></p>\r\n<p>Thanks</p>
72	#RecommenderPendingReviewRequestStage1	default	{{appName}}: A putative reviewer for a preprint you are handling	Mail to recommender to indicate that a user is willing to review a preprint they are handling	<p>Dear {{destPerson}},</p>\r\n<p>You have initiated the evaluation of the article entitled&nbsp;<strong>{{articleTitle}}</strong>&nbsp;by {{articleAuthors}} (DOI <a href="{{articleDoi}}">{{articleDoi}}</a>).</p>\r\n<p>A user {{reviewerPerson}} is willing to review this preprint.</p>\r\n<p>You can accept or decline this offer by following this link:&nbsp;<a href="{{linkTarget}}">{{linkTarget}}</a> or by logging onto the {{appName}} website and going to 'For recommenders —&gt; Preprints you are handling' in the top menu.</p>\r\n<p>We thank you for managing this evaluation.</p>\r\n<p>Yours sincerely,</p>\r\n<p>The Managing Board of {{appName}}</p>
73	#ReviewerReviewRequestAcceptedStage1	default	{{appName}}: Your offer to review an article has been accepted	Mail to user to indicate that the recommender has accepted their proposal to review the preprint	<p>Dear {{destPerson}},</p>\r\n<p>Thank you very much for agreeing to review the Stage 1 Registered Report entitled <strong>{{articleTitle}}</strong> by {{articleAuthors}} (DOI <a href="{{articleDoi}}">{{articleDoi}}</a>).</p>\r\n<p>If you are reviewing a submission via the Scheduled Review track, then please complete your review by the date agreed with the recommender.</p>\r\n<p>If you are reviewing a submission via the Standard track, please complete your review within {{reviewDuration}}, hence before <strong>{{dueTime}}</strong>. If this deadline is too short, please let me know as soon as possible. Otherwise, thank you in advance for respecting this deadline.</p>\r\n<p>To view, write, upload, and manage your review, please follow this link <a href="{{linkTarget}}">{{linkTarget}}</a> or log onto the {{appName}} website and go to ‘For contributors —&gt; Your reviews’ in the top menu.</p>\r\n<p>When you have written or uploaded your review, you can:</p>\r\n<p>1) save a draft version of your review for future modification by clicking on the ‘Save’ button; this allows you to make changes or to complete your review later;</p>\r\n<p>or</p>\r\n<p>2) save and submit your review by clicking on the ‘Save &amp; submit your review’ button.</p>\r\n<p>If you have saved a draft version of your review, you can come back to it for modification or completion by clicking on ‘For contributors&nbsp;—&gt; Your reviews’ in the top menu, and then on the black ‘View/Edit’ button to the right on the corresponding line. Don’t forget to click on the ‘Save &amp; submit your review’ button to send your completed review to me.</p>\r\n<p>On the PCI RR website you can find an <a href="https://rr.peercommunityin.org/help/guide_for_reviewers#h_6720026472751613309075757" target="_blank" rel="noopener">expanded description of the review criteria</a>, additional <a href="https://rr.peercommunityin.org/help/guide_for_reviewers#h_7586915642301613635089357" target="_blank" rel="noopener">tips for reviewing a RR</a>, and <a href="https://rr.peercommunityin.org/help/guide_for_reviewers" target="_blank" rel="noopener">complete reviewer guidelines</a>.&nbsp;We ask our reviewers to reflect on their potential biases to help make academia more equitable. Please read the <a href="https://zenodo.org/record/5484052#.YVDePS-B1I1">Bias Reflection Guide</a> (Foster et al. 2021) before deciding whether to accept a review invitation and before writing a review. There is also guidance on how to write a fair and respectful review by Foster et al. (<a href="https://zenodo.org/record/5484072#.YVDePy-B1I1">2021</a>).</p>\r\n<p>Thanks in advance for the time spent evaluating this submission. If you have any questions, please feel free to contact us by replying to this message. The recommender handling this submission is {{recommenderPerson}}.</p>\r\n<p>Yours sincerely,</p>\r\n<p>The Managing Board of {{appName}}</p>
74	#ReviewerReviewRequestDeclinedStage1	default	{{appName}}: Your request to review an article has been declined	Mail to user to indicate that the recommender decline their proposal to review the preprint	<p>Dear {{destPerson}},<br><br>You kindly indicated your willingness to review the preprint entitled {{articleTitle}} by {{articleAuthors}} (DOI <a href="{{articleDoi}}">{{articleDoi}}</a>). However, the recommender of this preprint has declined your offer - they probably already found enough reviewers to evaluate this preprint.<br><br>We hope that you won't be too disappointed and that you'll still be interested in giving input to {{appName}} in the near future. <br><br>Yours sincerely,<br><br>The Managing Board of {{appName}}</p>
75	#NewsLetterMonthly	default	{{appName}}: Newsletter	Mail to users that choose to receive the newsletter once a month	<p>Dear {{destPerson}},</p>\r\n<p>Here is some news from {{appName}}.</p>\r\n<p>Best regards</p>\r\n<p>The Managing Board of {{appName}}<br>&nbsp;</p>
76	#NewsLetterEveryTwoWeeks	default	{{appName}}: Newsletter	Mail to users that choose to receive the newsletter every two weeks	<p>Dear {{destPerson}},</p>\r\n<p>Here is some news from {{appName}}.</p>\r\n<p>Best regards</p>\r\n<p>The Managing Board of {{appName}}<br>&nbsp;</p>
77	#SubmitterAcknowledgementSubmissionStage1	default	{{appName}}: Thank you for your Stage 1 submission	Mail to submitter to acknowledge their submission	<p>Dear {{destPerson}},</p>\r\n<p>Thank you for your Stage 1 submission entitled {{articleTitle}}, to {{appName}}.</p>\r\n<p>If you have not already done so, please suggest recommenders who could initiate the evaluation of your manuscript or snapshot. A recommender is very similar to a journal editor (responsible for finding reviewers, collecting reviews, and making editorial decisions based on reviews), and may eventually recommend your report after one or several rounds of reviews.</p>\r\n<p>Your submission will now undergo preliminary evaluation by the Managing Board. We will contact you soon with further news.</p>\r\n<p>Thank you again for your submission,</p>\r\n<p>The Managing Board of {{appName}}</p>
78	#AdminTwoReviewersInStage1	default	{{appName}}: {{recommenderPerson}} found two reviewers	Mail to administrators to indicate that 2 reviewers agreed to review the preprint	<p>Dear Administrators of {{appName}},</p>\r\n<p>A second reviewer agreed to review the Stage 1 submission "{{articleTitle}}" by {{articleAuthors}}. Other invitations to referee might be in progress but {{recommenderPerson}} could make their editorial decision based on these two reviews.</p>\r\n<p>To manage this recommendation, please follow this link <a href="{{linkTarget}}">{{linkTarget}}</a>.</p>\r\n<p>Have a nice day!</p>
79	#AdminAllReviewsCompletedStage1	default	{{appName}}: All reviews completed	Mail to administrators to indicate them that all reviews have been completed	<p>Dear Administrators of {{appName}},</p>\r\n<p>All reviews of the Stage 1 submission "{{articleTitle}}" by {{articleAuthors}} are completed. {{recommenderPerson}}, the recommender of this preprint can now make their editorial decision.</p>\r\n<p>To manage this recommendation, please follow this link <a href="{{linkTarget}}">{{linkTarget}}</a>.</p>\r\n<p>Have a nice day!</p>
81	#SubmitterPreprintSubmittedStage2	default	{{appName}}: Your submission	Mail to submitter to indicate the validation of their submission	<p>Dear {{destPerson}},<br><br>We have validated your submission to ({{appName}}).</p>\r\n<div>We have sent a message to all recommenders of {{appName}} you may have suggested to let them know about this submission. You will be notified by e-mail if a recommender decides to start the peer-review process for your report. If none of them decide to act as a recommender, you'll receive an e-mail inviting you to suggest additional recommenders (we can also make suggestions if you wish).&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div><br>We remind you that this report must not be published or submitted for publication elsewhere. If this report is taken on by a recommender, and therefore sent out for review, you must not submit it to a journal until the evaluation process is complete (i.e., until it has been rejected or recommended by {{appName}}).</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<p>To view or cancel your submission, please follow this link {{linkTarget}} or log into the {{appName}} website and go to 'For contributors —&gt; Your submitted reports' in the top menu. As long as a recommender has not picked up your submitted article, you can also suggest additional recommenders.​<br><br>We thank you again for your submission.<br><br>Yours sincerely,<br><br>The Managing Board of {{appName}}</p>
83	#SubmitterPreprintUnderConsiderationStage2	default	{{appName}}: Consideration of your preprint	Mail to submitter that a recommender took their preprint in charge	<p>Dear {{destPerson}},</p>\r\n<p>You have submitted your preprint entitled <strong>{{articleTitle}}</strong> to {{appName}}. We are pleased to inform you that a {{appName}} recommender has initiated the evaluation process.</p>\r\n<p>At this stage of the process, your article will be sent to several referees, to ensure that at least two high-quality reviews are obtained. Based on this review, the recommender will reject, recommend or ask you to modify your article and to respond to the questions and points raised by the reviewers. The mean time to this first decision is about {{recomm_limit_days}} days.</p>\r\n<p>We remind you that this preprint must not be submitted for publication elsewhere until its evaluation by {{appName}} is complete.</p>\r\n<p>If after one or several rounds of reviews, the recommender handling your preprint reaches a favorable conclusion, all the editorial correspondence (reviews, recommender’s decisions, authors’ replies) and a recommendation text will be published by {{appName}} under the license CC-BY. If recommended by {{appName}} your preprint will become an article that may be used and cited like any ‘classic’ article published in a peer-reviewed journal.</p>\r\n<p>Alternatively, if the recommender decides not to recommend your article, the reviews and the decision will be sent to you, but they will not be published or publicly released by {{appName}}. They will be safely stored in our database, to which only the Managing Board has access. You will be notified by e-mail at each stage in the procedure.</p>\r\n<p>To view or cancel your submission, please follow this link <a href="{{linkTarget}}">{{linkTarget}}</a> or log onto the {{appName}} website and go to 'For contributors —&gt; Your submitted preprints' in the top menu.</p>\r\n<p>We thank you again for your submission.</p>\r\n<p>Yours sincerely,</p>\r\n<p>The Managing Board of {{appName}}</p>
84	#SubmitterCancelledSubmissionStage2	default	{{appName}}: Cancellation of your submission	Mail to author to acknowledge the cancellation of their Stage 2 submission	<div>Dear {{destPerson}},</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>Your Stage 2 manuscript entitled <strong>{{articleTitle}}</strong> has been cancelled at your request.</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>\r\n<div><span style="font-weight: 400;"><strong>Your feedback matters.</strong> If you are cancelling your submission following at least some evaluation by the PCI RR Managing Board, a recommender, or reviewers, please take 5 minutes to leave anonymous feedback about your experience of the review process for this submission:</span> <a href="https://registeredreports.cardiff.ac.uk/feedback/feedback/decision_letter.php"><span style="font-weight: 400;">https://registeredreports.cardiff.ac.uk/feedback/feedback/decision_letter.php</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;"> Feedback from authors</span> helps us understand what we’re doing well, what we could do better, and how we can improve and innovate the review process for Registered Reports. <span style="font-weight: 400;">This feedback is collected by the </span><a href="https://registeredreports.cardiff.ac.uk/feedback/dashboards/"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Registered Reports Community Feedback</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;"> website which is an independent service and research project, being undertaken by Cardiff </span><span style="font-weight: 400;">University.</span></div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>Yours sincerely,</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>The Managing Board of {{appName}}</div>
85	#SubmitterRejectedSubmissionStage2	default	{{appName}}: Decision concerning your submission	Mail to submitter to indicate the rejection of their preprint	<div>Dear {{destPerson}},</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>Your preprint entitled <strong>{{articleTitle}}</strong> has been evaluated by at least two referees. On the basis of these reviews, we regret to inform you that the {{appName}} recommender in charge of this evaluation has decided not to recommend it.</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>The reviews and the recommender’s decision are shown below. These reviews and the decision will not be published or publicly released by {{appName}}. They will be safely stored in our database, to which only the Managing Board has access.</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>We are sorry to bring disappointing news and hope that you will consider submitting to {{appName}} in the future.</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div><span style="font-weight: 400;"><strong>Your feedback matters.</strong> Please take 5 minutes to leave anonymous feedback about your experience of the Stage 2 review process for this submission:</span> <a href="https://registeredreports.cardiff.ac.uk/feedback/feedback/decision_letter.php"><span style="font-weight: 400;">https://registeredreports.cardiff.ac.uk/feedback/feedback/decision_letter.php</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;"> Feedback from authors</span> helps us understand what we’re doing well, what we could do better, and how we can improve and innovate the review process for Registered Reports.<span style="font-weight: 400;">This feedback is collected by the </span><a href="https://registeredreports.cardiff.ac.uk/feedback/dashboards/"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Registered Reports Community Feedback</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;"> website which is an independent service and research project, being undertaken by Cardiff University.</span></div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>We thank you again for your submission.</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>Yours sincerely,</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>The Managing Board of {{appName}}<br>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>{{recommendationProcess}}</div>\r\n</div>
87	#SubmitterAwaitingSubmissionStage2	default	{{appName}}: Decision concerning your submission	Mail to submitter to indicate the need to revise their preprint	<p>Dear {{destPerson}},</p>\r\n<p>Your article, entitled <strong>{{articleTitle}}</strong>, has now been reviewed. The referees' comments and the recommender’s decision are shown below. As you can see, the recommender suggests revisions.</p>\r\n<p>We shall, in principle, be happy to recommend your article as soon as it has been revised in response to the points raised by the referees.</p>\r\n<p>When revising your article, we remind you that:</p>\r\n<p>1) Data must be available to readers, either in the text or through an open data repository such as Zenodo (free), Dryad (pay) or some other institutional repository. Data must be reusable, thus metadata or accompanying text must carefully describe the data;</p>\r\n<p>2) Details on quantitative analyses (e.g., data treatment and statistical scripts in R, bioinformatic pipeline scripts, etc.) and details concerning simulations (scripts, code) must be available to readers in the text, as appendices, or through an open data repository, such as Zenodo, Dryad or some other institutional repository. The scripts or code must be carefully described so that they can be reused;</p>\r\n<p>3) Details on experimental procedures must be available to readers in the text or as appendices;</p>\r\n<p>4) Authors must have no financial conflict of interest relating to the article. The article must contain a "Conflict of interest disclosure" paragraph before the reference section containing this sentence: "The authors of this article declare that they have no financial conflict of interest with the content of this article.";</p>\r\n<p>5) This disclosure has to be completed by a sentence indicating, if appropriate, that some of the authors are PCI recommenders: “X is a recommender at {{appName}}.”.</p>\r\n<p>When your revised article is ready, please:</p>\r\n<p>1) Upload the new version of your manuscript onto your favorite open archive;</p>\r\n<p>2) Follow this link <a href="{{linkTarget}}">{{linkTarget}}</a> or log onto the {{appName}} website and go to 'For Contributors -&gt; Your submitted preprints' in the top menu;</p>\r\n<p>3) Make your changes to the title, summary, link to the article (or its DOI) and keywords if necessary by clicking on the 'Edit Article' button. If you haven't already, you may also upload a picture or an illustration for which you own the rights – this picture will be used to illustrate your article, if recommended;</p>\r\n<p>4) Write, copy/paste or upload (as a PDF file) your point-by-point response to all comments (outline each change made in your manuscript or providing a suitable rebuttal reply to the recommender's and reviewers' comments) by clicking on the 'Write, edit or upload your reply to recommender' button. You must also upload (as a PDF file) a revised version of your article, with all modifications indicated in Track Changes mode;</p>\r\n<p>5) When you are ready to submit your new version, click on the 'Save &amp; submit your reply' button.</p>\r\n<p>Once the recommender has read the revised version, they may decide to recommend it directly, in which case the editorial correspondence (reviews, recommender’s decisions, authors’ replies) and a recommendation text will be published by {{appName}} under the license CC-BY.</p>\r\n<p>Alternatively, other rounds of reviews may be needed before the recommender reaches a favorable conclusion. They may also reject your article, in which case the reviews and decision will be sent to you, but they will not be published or publicly released by {{appName}}. They will be safely stored in our database, to which only the Managing Board has access. You will be notified by e-mail at each stage in the procedure.</p>\r\n<p>We thank you in advance for submitting your revised version.</p>\r\n<p>Yours sincerely,</p>\r\n<p>The Managing Board of {{appName}}</p>\r\n<div>{{recommendationProcess}}</div>
88	#SubmitterRecommendedPreprintStage2	default	{{appName}}: Final recommendation of your Stage 2 Registered Report	Mail to authors to indicate a final positive Stage 2 recommendation	<div>Dear {{destPerson}},</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>We are pleased to inform you that the peer-review process concerning your Stage 2 Registered Report entitled<strong> {{articleTitle}} </strong>has reached a favorable conclusion.</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>A recommendation text written by the recommender has been published by PCI RR, along with the final list of eligible PCI RR-friendly journals that will accept your Stage 2 manuscript without further peer review. If you consented to notifying <a href="https://rr.peercommunityin.org/about/pci_rr_interested_journals" target="_blank" rel="noopener">PCI RR-interested journals</a> your recommendation then we will also alert them about the acceptance.</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>The reviews, author responses and recommender decisions associated with the Stage 2 manuscript have&nbsp; also been published on the PCI RR website.</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>The final recommendation may be found at: <a href="{{linkTarget}}">{{linkTarget}}</a></div>\r\n<div>We now kindly ask you to add the {{appName}} badge on the 1st page of your article pdf and upload it to the preprint server as a new version. This will indicate that your article has been peer reviewed and recommended by {{appName}}. Please add a hyperlink to the badge that points to {{doiRecomm}}. This can be done by pasting the badge on the 1st page of your source file, creating a hyperlink, and then saving the file as a pdf. It can also be done directly on the pdf file with pdf editing software.&nbsp;You will find the {{appName}} badge<span style="font-weight: 400;" data-mce-fragment="1">, instructions</span>​ and an example of a PDF here: <a class="theme markdown__link" href="https://peercommunityin.org/badges" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">https://peercommunityin.org/badges</a> (you will need to enter this password to access the page: badges_@PCI).&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div><span style="font-weight: 400;"><strong>Your feedback matters.</strong> Please take 5 minutes to leave anonymous feedback about your experience of the Stage 2 review process for this submission (as well as the previous Stage 1 review process, if you haven't already done so):</span> <a href="https://registeredreports.cardiff.ac.uk/feedback/feedback/decision_letter.php"><span style="font-weight: 400;">https://registeredreports.cardiff.ac.uk/feedback/feedback/decision_letter.php</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;"> Feedback from authors</span> helps us understand what we’re doing well, what we could do better, and how we can improve and innovate the review process for Registered Reports. <span style="font-weight: 400;">This feedback is collected by the </span><a href="https://registeredreports.cardiff.ac.uk/feedback/dashboards/"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Registered Reports Community Feedback</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;"> website which is an independent service and research project, being undertaken by Cardiff University.</span></div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>Thank you for using PCI RR. We looking forward to receiving submissions from you again in future.</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>Yours sincerely,</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>The Managing Board of {{appName}} RR</div>
89	#SubmitterPreprintStatusChangedStage2	default	{{appName}}: Change in the status of your preprint	Mail to submitter if there is a change in the status of their preprint	<p>Dear {{destPerson}},</p>\r\n<p>The status of your preprint entitled <strong>{{articleTitle}}</strong> has changed from "{{tOldStatus}}" to "{{tNewStatus}}".</p>\r\n<p>You can view, edit or cancel your submission by following this link <a href="{{linkTarget}}">{{linkTarget}}</a> or by logging onto the {{appName}} website and going to 'For contributors —&gt; Your submitted preprints' in the top menu.</p>\r\n<p>We thank you again for your submission.</p>\r\n<p>Yours sincerely,</p>\r\n<p>The Managing Board of {{appName}}</p>
90	#SubmitterAcknowledgementSubmissionStage2	default	{{appName}}: thanks for your submission	Mail to submitter to acknowledge their submission	<p>Dear {{destPerson}},</p>\r\n<p>Thank you for your submission, on behalf of all the authors, of your report entitled {{articleTitle}}, to {{appName}}.</p>\r\n<p>If you have not already done so, you need to suggest recommenders who could initiate the evaluation of your report. A recommender is very similar to a journal editor (responsible for finding reviewers, collecting reviews, and making editorial decisions based on reviews), and may eventually recommend your report after one or several rounds of reviews.</p>\r\n<p>We will check that this report is within the scope of {{appName}} and that the data, scripts, codes are publicly available. We will contact you if needed or validate your submission directly.</p>\r\n<p>In any case, we will keep you informed in the next few days.</p>\r\n<p>Thanks again for this submission</p>\r\n<p>The managing board of {{appName}}</p>
91	#RecommenderStatusChangedToUnderConsiderationStage2	default	{{appName}}: Revised version	Mail to recommender to indicate that a revised version has been submitted and they must make a decision	<p>Dear {{destPerson}},</p>\r\n<p>The authors of the preprint entitled <strong>{{articleTitle}}</strong> and submitted by {{articleAuthors}} have posted their revised version and their replies to your comments and those of the reviewers. They may also have uploaded (as a PDF or Word file) a revised version of their preprint, with the modifications indicated in Track Changes mode and a clean version of their PDF at this address <a href="{{linkTarget}}">{{linkTarget}}</a> (see also attachments to this email).</p>\r\n<p>For this new round of evaluation, please reach a decision to ‘Revise’, ‘Recommend’ or ‘Reject’ the article.</p>\r\n<p class="p1">Feel free to contact the authors directly (either via email while cc’ing contact@rr.peercommunityin.org or at the online system by making a Revise decision before sending it to the reviewers) to request any clarifications necessary to be able to make your assessment, including ensuring the authors have responded to all comments in a point-by-point format and revised the manuscript accordingly.</p>\r\n<p>We look forward to your decision. Thanks in advance!</p>\r\n<p>Yours sincerely,</p>\r\n<p>The Managing Board of {{appName}}</p>
92	#RecommenderStatusChangedUnderToRecommendedStage2	default	{{appName}}: Article recommended	Mail to recommender to indicate that the preprint is now recommended	<p>Dear {{destPerson}},</p>\r\n<p>Your recommendation - along with the reviews - is now posted on the {{appName}} website.</p>\r\n<p>You can find it there: <a href="{{doiRecomm}}">{{doiRecomm}}</a></p>\r\n<p>And there: <a href="{{linkRecomm}}">{{linkRecomm}}</a></p>\r\n<p>You will find the reference to your recommendation and that of the recommended article.</p>\r\n<p>Do not hesitate to share the news via social networks (if you are on them), emails, websites, CVs, quotes, etc.</p>\r\n<p>Thanks again for recommending this article for {{appName}}.</p>\r\n<p>Yours sincerely,</p>\r\n<p>The Managing Board of {{appName}}</p>
93	#RecommenderArticleStatusChangedStage2	default	{{appName}}: Change in article status	Mail to recommender to indicate the change of the status of the preprint	<p>Dear {{destPerson}},</p>\n<p>You have initiated the evaluation of the article entitled <strong>{{articleTitle}}</strong> by {{articleAuthors}} (DOI <a href="{{articleDoi}}">{{articleDoi}}</a>).</p>\n<p>The status of this article has changed from "{{tOldStatus}}" to "{{tNewStatus}}".</p>\n<p>You can view and manage your evaluation process by following this link: <a href="{{linkTarget}}">{{linkTarget}}</a> or by logging onto the {{appName}} website and going to 'For recommenders —&gt; Preprints you are handling' in the top menu.</p>\n<p>We thank you for managing this evaluation.</p>\n<p>Yours sincerely,</p>\n<p>The Managing Board of {{appName}}</p>
94	#RecommenderSuggestionNotNeededAnymoreStage2	default	{{appName}}: About our request to act as a recommender for a preprint	Mail to suggested recommenders to indicate that another recommender took the preprint in charge	<p>Dear {{destPerson}},</p>\r\n<p>For this preprint, your help as a recommender is no longer needed.</p>\r\n<p>You were suggested as a recommender for a preprint entitled <strong>{{articleTitle}}</strong> by {{articleAuthors}} (DOI <a href="{{articleDoi}}">{{articleDoi}}</a>). This preprint attracted the attention of another {{appName}} recommender, who has initiated its evaluation. Consequently, this preprint no longer appears in your list of requests to act as a recommender on the {{appName}} webpage.</p>\r\n<p>If you would still like to participate in the evaluation of this preprint, please send us an e-mail at {{appContactLink}}. We will inform the recommender handling the evaluation process of your willingness to participate and they may then contact you.</p>\r\n<p>We hope that, in the near future, you will have the opportunity to initiate the evaluation of another preprint.</p>\r\n<p>Thank you for your support.</p>\r\n<p>Yours sincerely,</p>\r\n<p>The Managing Board of {{appName}}</p>
95	#RecommenderSuggestedArticleStage2	default	{{appName}}: Request to act as a recommender for a Stage 2 submission	Mail to suggested recommenders to ask them to act as recommender of a submitted Stage 2 manuscript	<p>Dear {{destPerson}},</p>\r\n<p>You have been suggested as a recommender for a Stage 2 submission entitled <strong>{{articleTitle}}</strong> by {{articleAuthors}} (DOI <a href="{{articleDoi}}">{{articleDoi}}</a>). You can obtain information about this request and accept or decline this invitation by following this link <a href="{{linkTarget}}">{{linkTarget}}</a> or by logging on to the {{appName}} website and going to 'For recommenders —&gt; Request(s) to handle a preprint' in the top menu.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Important information before accepting to become the recommender for this preprint:</strong> The role of a recommender is very similar to that of a journal editor (finding reviewers, collecting reviews, taking editorial decisions based on reviews), and may lead to the recommendation of the preprint after several rounds of reviews. The evaluation forms the basis of the decision to ‘Revise’, ‘Recommend’ or ‘Reject’ the preprint. A preprint recommended by {{appName}} is an article that may be used and cited like the ‘classic’ articles published in peer-reviewed journals. Details about the recommendation process can be found <a href="{{helpurl}}">here</a>. You can also watch this short video: <a href="https://youtu.be/u5greO-q8-M"> How to start and manage a preprint recommendation</a>.</p>\r\n<p>Agreeing to become the recommender for this report means that <strong>you agree to consider this submission for in-depth review</strong>.<strong> Y</strong><strong>ou will then need to perform the following actions: </strong></p>\r\n<div><span style="font-weight: 400;">1. If you judge that the manuscript fails to sufficiently meet the <a href="https://rr.peercommunityin.org/help/guide_for_recommenders#h_6759646236401613643390905">Stage 2 criteria</a> in order to be sent for in-depth review, then</span> you can <strong>desk reject the manuscript outright </strong>or<strong> invite a revision</strong> prior to in-depth review.</div>\r\n<div>2. If you judge the submission to be <a href="https://rr.peercommunityin.org/help/guide_for_recommenders#h_1245019342271613643227798">review-ready</a><span style="font-weight: 400;"><strong> then please </strong></span><strong>send invitations to </strong><strong>5-10 potential reviewers within the next few days</strong><span style="font-weight: 400;"> and then send new invitations until you find at least two (and ideally three) reviewers willing to review the submission.</span><br>3. <strong>post your decision</strong> or write your recommendation text <strong>within 10 days</strong> of receiving the reviews.<br>4. <strong>write the recommendation text</strong> if you decide to recommend this report for {{appName}} at the end of the evaluation process. If after one or more rounds of review, you decide to recommend this report for Stage 2 acceptance, you will need to write a “<a href="https://rr.peercommunityin.org/help/guide_for_recommenders#h_68746834114021613643858842" target="_blank" rel="noopener">recommendation</a>” that will have its own DOI and be published by {{appName}} under the license CC-BY 4.0. The recommendation is a short summary (of a few hundred words or less), similar to a News &amp; Views piece, describing the context of the study and explaining why the article was accepted and is expected to make a valuable contribution. The limitations of the report can also be discussed. This text also contains references (citing, at least, the report being recommended). All the editorial correspondence (reviews, your decisions, authors’ replies) will also be published by {{appName}}.<br>5. <strong>declare that you have no conflict of interest with the authors or the content of the article.</strong> You <span style="font-weight: 400;">should not handle reports written by close colleagues, including people belonging to the same laboratory/unit/department in the last four years, people with whom you have published in the last four years, with whom you have received joint funding in the last four years, or with whom you are currently writing a manuscript or submitting a grant proposal.</span><a href="https://rr.peercommunityin.org/about/ethics"><span style="font-weight: 400;"> </span></a></div>\r\n<div>\r\n<p>We ask our recommenders to reflect on their potential biases to help make academia more equitable. Please read the <a href="https://zenodo.org/record/5484052#.YVDePS-B1I1">Bias Reflection Guide</a> (Foster et al. 2021) before deciding whether to accept an invitation to be a recommender for a registered report, before writing a response to the authors, and before writing the recommendation text.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n<p>Thank you very much for your assistance.</p>\r\n<p>Yours sincerely,</p>\r\n<p>The Managing Board of {{appName}}</p>
96	#RecommenderReviewerReviewCompletedStage2	default	{{appName}}: Review completed	Mail to recommender to indicate that a review has been completed	<p>Dear {{destPerson}},</p>\r\n<p>The review by {{reviewerPerson}} of the Stage 2 submission entitled <strong>{{articleTitle}}</strong> is now available.</p>\r\n<p>You can view and/or download this review and manage your recommendation by following this link <a href="{{linkTarget}}">{{linkTarget}}</a> or by logging onto the {{appName}} website and going to 'For recommenders —&gt; Preprint(s) you are handling' in the top menu.</p>\r\n<p><strong>If all the reviews have now been completed</strong> and returned, <strong>we now expect you</strong>, according to your commitment as a recommender of the preprint, <strong>to make a decision within a few days</strong>. If you need more time, please let us know by return mail.</p>\r\n<p>We remind you that this decision must be: ‘Revise’, ‘Recommend’ or ‘Reject’ the preprint.</p>\r\n<p>If you are ready to recommend,&nbsp;<strong>you do not need to submit an “Acceptation” decision</strong>. You should directly post your recommendation.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>The "recommendation" is a short article, similar to a News &amp; Views piece; it has its own DOI and will be published by {{appName}} under the license CC-BY.&nbsp;It has its own title, contains between about 300 and 1500 words, describes the context and explains why the preprint is particularly interesting. The limitations of the preprint can also be discussed. This text also contains references (citing, at least, the preprint being recommended). All the editorial correspondence (reviews, your decisions, authors’ replies) relating to the preprint will also be published by {{appName}}.</p>\r\n<p>We thank you again for managing this evaluation.</p>\r\n<p>Yours sincerely,</p>\r\n<p>The Managing Board of {{appName}}</p>
97	#RecommenderReviewConsideredStage2	default	{{appName}}: Request to review accepted	Mail to recommender to indicate that a reviewer agreed to review a preprint they are handling	<p>Dear {{destPerson}},</p>\r\n<p>{{reviewerPerson}} has accepted your invitation to review the preprint entitled <strong>{{articleTitle}}</strong> by {{articleAuthors}} (DOI <a href="{{articleDoi}}">{{articleDoi}}</a>), and has been sent a message indicating that this review must be posted or uploaded on the {{appName}} website before {{dueTime}}.</p>\r\n<p>You will receive a message notifying you of the posting of this review. If the review is not posted by the deadline, you can send the reviewer a reminder by following this link <a href="{{linkTarget}}">{{linkTarget}}</a> or by logging on to the {{appName}} website and going to 'For recommenders —&gt; Preprint(s) you are handling' in the top menu.</p>\r\n<p>We thank you again for managing this evaluation.</p>\r\n<p>Yours sincerely,</p>\r\n<p>The Managing Board of {{appName}}</p>
98	#RecommenderReviewDeclinedStage2	default	{{appName}}: Request to review declined	Mail to recommender to indicate that a reviewer declined to review a preprint they are handling	<p>Dear {{destPerson}},</p>\r\n<p>{{reviewerPerson}} has declined your invitation to review the preprint entitled <strong>{{articleTitle}}</strong> by {{articleAuthors}} (DOI<a href="{{articleDoi}}"> {{articleDoi}}</a>).</p>\r\n<p>You will need to find another reviewer to obtain the two high-quality reviews required. You can invite additional reviewers by following this link <a href="{{linkTarget}}">{{linkTarget}}</a> or by logging onto the {{appName}} website and going to 'For recommenders —&gt; Preprint(s) you are handling' in the top menu.</p>\r\n<p>We thank you again for managing this evaluation.</p>\r\n<p>Yours sincerely,</p>\r\n<p>The Managing Board of {{appName}}</p>
99	#RecommenderPendingReviewRequestStage2	default	{{appName}}: A putative reviewer for a preprint you are handling	Mail to recommender to indicate that a user is willing to review a preprint they are handling	<p>Dear {{destPerson}},</p>\r\n<p>You have initiated the evaluation of the article entitled&nbsp;<strong>{{articleTitle}}</strong>&nbsp;by {{articleAuthors}} (DOI <a href="{{articleDoi}}">{{articleDoi}}</a>).</p>\r\n<p>A user {{reviewerPerson}} is willing to review this preprint.</p>\r\n<p>You can accept or decline this offer by following this link:&nbsp;<a href="{{linkTarget}}">{{linkTarget}}</a> or by logging onto the {{appName}} website and going to 'For recommenders —&gt; Preprints you are handling' in the top menu.</p>\r\n<p>We thank you for managing this evaluation.</p>\r\n<p>Yours sincerely,</p>\r\n<p>The Managing Board of {{appName}}</p>
100	#ReviewerReviewReopenedStage2	default	{{appName}}: You can now modify your review	Mail to reviewer if recommender reopen the review of a reviewer	<p>Dear {{destPerson}},</p>\r\n<p>{{recommenderPerson}}, the recommender managing the evaluation process for the Stage 2 submission entitled <strong>{{articleTitle}}</strong> by {{articleAuthors}} has made your review concerning this preprint available for modification.</p>\r\n<p>You can now access this review, and edit it if necessary.</p>\r\n<p>You can view and edit your reviews by following this link <a href="{{linkTarget}}">{{linkTarget}}</a> or by logging onto the {{appName}} website and going to 'For contributors —&gt; My reviews' in the top menu.</p>\r\n<p>We thank you again for agreeing to review this preprint.</p>\r\n<p>Yours sincerely,</p>\r\n<p>The Managing Board of {{appName}}</p>
101	#ReviewersArticleCancellationStage2	default	{{appName}}: About our request to act as reviewer for a preprint	Mail to reviewers to indicate that them that the submitter cancelled their submission	<p>Dear {{destPerson}},</p>\r\n<p>The submission of the preprint entitled <strong>{{articleTitle}}</strong> by {{articleAuthors}} has been cancelled by the author. Therefore, the recommendation process is closed and a review is no longer required. Thank you for considering the review request.</p>\r\n<p>Yours sincerely,</p>\r\n<p>The Managing Board of {{appName}}</p>
102	#ReviewerReviewRequestAcceptedStage2	default	{{appName}}: Your offer to review an article has been accepted	Mail to user to indicate that the recommender has accepted their proposal to review the preprint	<p>Dear {{destPerson}},<br><br>Thank you very much for indicating your willingness to review the Stage 2 submission entitled {{articleTitle}} by {{articleAuthors}} (DOI <a href="{{articleDoi}}">{{articleDoi}}</a>).<br><br>The recommender ({{recommenderPerson}}) has accepted your offer and would be pleased to receive your review within {{reviewDuration}}, hence before {{dueTime}}. If this deadline is too short, please let the recommender know as soon as possible by reply email. Otherwise, thank you in advance for meeting this deadline.<br><br>To view, write, upload and manage your review, please follow this link <a href="{{linkTarget}}">{{linkTarget}}</a> or log onto the {{appName}} website and go to ‘For contributors —&gt; Your reviews’ in the top menu.<br><br>When you have written or uploaded your review, you can:<br><br>1) save a draft version of your review for future modification by clicking on the ‘Save’ button; this allows you to make changes or to complete your review later;<br><br>or<br><br>2) save and submit your review by clicking on the ‘Save &amp; submit your review’ button.<br><br>If you saved a draft version of your review, you can come back to it for modification or completion by clicking on ‘For contributors —&gt; Your reviews’ in the top menu, and then on the black ‘View/Edit’ button to the right on the corresponding line. Don’t forget to click on the ‘Save &amp; submit your review’ button to send your completed review to me.</p>\r\n<p>The criteria for evaluating Stage 2 Registered Reports may be found <a href="https://rr.peercommunityin.org/help/guide_for_reviewers#h_6720026472751613309075757" target="_blank" rel="noopener">here</a> and specific tips for reviewers at Stage 2 may be found <a href="https://rr.peercommunityin.org/help/guide_for_reviewers#h_5850625547441613635240391" target="_blank" rel="noopener">here</a>.</p>\r\n<p>Many thanks in advance for the time spent evaluating this submission. If you have any questions as you progress, feel free to contact us by replying to this email.<br><br>Yours sincerely,</p>\r\n<p>The Managing Board of {{appName}}</p>
103	#ReviewerReviewRequestDeclinedStage2	default	{{appName}}: Your request to review an article has been declined	Mail to user to indicate that the recommender decline the proposal to review the preprint	<p>Dear {{destPerson}},<br><br>You kindly indicated your willingness to review the preprint entitled {{articleTitle}} by {{articleAuthors}} (DOI <a href="{{articleDoi}}">{{articleDoi}}</a>). However, the recommender of this preprint has declined your offer - they probably found enough reviewers to evaluate this preprint.<br><br>We hope you won't be too disappointed and that you'll still be interested by giving some input to {{appName}} in the near future. <br><br>Yours sincerely,<br><br>The Managing Board of {{appName}}</p>
104	#ReviewerThankForReviewAcceptationStage2	default	{{appName}}: Thank you for agreeing to review	Mail to a reviewer to thank them for agreeing to review a Stage 2 submission	<p>Dear {{destPerson}},</p>\r\n<p>Thank you very much for agreeing to review the Stage 2 Registered Report entitled <strong>{{articleTitle}}</strong> by {{articleAuthors}} (<a href="{{articleDoi}}">{{articleDoi}}</a>). </p>\r\n<p>To view, write, upload and manage your review, please follow this link <a href="{{linkTarget}}">{{linkTarget}}</a> or log onto the {{appName}} website and go to ‘For contributors —&gt; Your reviews’ in the top menu.</p>\r\n<p>When you have written or uploaded your review, you can:</p>\r\n<p>1) save a draft version of your review for future modification by clicking on the ‘Save’ button; this allows you to make changes or to complete your review later;</p>\r\n<p>or</p>\r\n<p>2) save and send me your review by clicking on the ‘Save &amp; submit your review’ button.</p>\r\n<p>If you have saved a draft version of your review, you can come back to it for modification or completion by clicking on ‘For contributors —&gt; Your reviews’ in the top menu, and then on the black ‘View/Edit’ button to the right on the corresponding line. Don’t forget to click on the ‘Save &amp; submit your review’ button to send your completed review to me.</p>\r\n<p>Guidelines for PCI reviewers can be found&nbsp;<a title="guideline for reviewers" href="https://peercommunityin.org/2020/10/22/pci-reviewer-guide/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">here</a>. <span style="font-weight: 400;">We also ask reviewers to&nbsp;</span>reflect on their potential biases to help make academia more equitable. Please read the <a href="https://zenodo.org/record/5484052#.YVDePS-B1I1">Bias Reflection Guide</a> (Foster et al. 2021) before deciding whether to accept a review invitation and before writing a review. There is also guidance on how to write a fair and respectful review by Foster et al. (<a href="https://zenodo.org/record/5484072#.YVDePy-B1I1">2021</a>).</p>\r\n<p>Thanks in advance for the time spent evaluating this submission. If you have any questions, please feel free to contact us by replying to this message. The recommender handling this submission is {{recommenderPerson}}.</p>\r\n<p>Yours sincerely,</p>\r\n<p>The Managing Board of {{appName}}</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>
105	#ReviewerThankForReviewDoneStage2	default	{{appName}}: Thank you for evaluating a Stage 2 submission	Mail to reviewer to thank them for their review	<p>Dear {{destPerson}},</p>\r\n<p>Thank you for evaluating the Stage 2 manuscript entitled <strong>{{articleTitle}}</strong> by {{articleAuthors}}. Your evaluation has been sent to the recommender ({{recommenderPerson}}) handling this preprint. Your contribution is greatly appreciated.</p>\r\n<p>You can use this message as proof of your work for {{appName}} and you can view your review at <a href="{{linkTarget}}">{{linkTarget}}</a>. Your review, together with the other reviews of this preprint, will guide the decision of the recommender ({{recommenderPerson}}) as to whether to ‘Revise’, ‘Recommend’ or ‘Reject’ this preprint.</p>\r\n<p>Remember that if the recommender eventually comes to a favorable conclusion, all of the editorial correspondence (reviews, including yours, the decisions reached by the recommender, and the authors’ replies) and a recommendation text will be published by {{appName}}, under the license CC-BY. If, after one or several rounds of review, the recommender eventually rejects the preprint, the editorial correspondence will be sent to the authors but will NOT be published. You will be notified by e-mail at each stage in the procedure.</p>\r\n<p>If the recommender asks the authors to revise their submission, the recommender may invite you to evaluate their responses and the changes they have made to the manuscript. If required, we therefore hope that you will be willing to take part in a second round of review.</p>\r\n<p>If you decided NOT to remain anonymous, your name will be passed on to the authors and, if the recommender decides to recommend this preprint, your name will be visible and associated with your review on the {{appName}} website. If you wish to change your mind and remain anonymous, please send a message to {{appContactMail}}, to let the members of the Managing Board know (they will make the necessary changes).</p>\r\n<p>In the meantime, thank you again for conducting this evaluation.</p>\r\n<p>Best wishes,</p>\r\n<p>The Managing Board of {{appName}}</p>
106	#AdminTwoReviewersInStage2	default	{{appName}}: {{recommenderPerson}} found two reviewers	Mail to admnistrators to indicate that 2 reviewers agreed to review the preprint	<p>Dear admnistrators of {{appName}},</p>\r\n<p>A second reviewer agreed to review the Stage 2 manuscript "{{articleTitle}}" by {{articleAuthors}}. Other invitations to referee might be in progress but {{recommenderPerson}} could make their editorial decision based on these two reviews.</p>\r\n<p>To manage this recommendation, please follow this link <a href="{{linkTarget}}">{{linkTarget}}</a>.</p>\r\n<p>Have a nice day!</p>
107	#AdminAllReviewsCompletedStage2	default	{{appName}}: All reviews completed	Mail to admnistrators to indicate them that all reviews have been completed	<p>Dear administrators of {{appName}},</p>\r\n<p>All reviews of the preprint "{{articleTitle}}" by {{articleAuthors}} are completed. {{recommenderPerson}}, the recommender of this preprint can now make their editorial decision.</p>\r\n<p>To manage this recommendation, please follow this link <a href="{{linkTarget}}">{{linkTarget}}</a>.</p>\r\n<p>Have a nice day!</p>
108	#ManagersPreprintSubmissionStage2	default	{{appName}}: Stage 2 submission requiring validation	Mail to MB to indicate the submission of a Stage 2 manuscript	<p>Dear members of the Managing Board,</p>\r\n<p>{{appName}} has received a submission of a Stage 2 manuscript by {{submitterPerson}}.</p>\r\n<p>To validate or delete this submission, please follow this link <a href="{{linkTarget}}">{{linkTarget}}</a> and use the following instructions.</p>\r\n<h3><span style="font-weight: 400;">Does the submission need changes to be submission-ready? Send it to the pre-submission stage</span></h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><span style="font-weight: 400;">An article in the </span><em><span style="font-weight: 400;">For managers &gt; Pending validations</span></em><span style="font-weight: 400;"> needs changes before it will be ready to be validated. Any articles in the Pending validations section can be sent to the pre-submission stage by clicking View/Edit, scroll to bottom, click the black button: </span><em><span style="font-weight: 400;">Put in pre-submission list</span></em><span style="font-weight: 400;">.</span></li>\r\n<li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Then go to: </span><em><span style="font-weight: 400;">For managers &gt; X Articles in the pre-submission stage</span></em><span style="font-weight: 400;">. Find the article here &gt; click View/Edit &gt; edit the email template to the authors to request further changes so it is ready to be validated and click Send.&nbsp;</span></li>\r\n<li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><span style="font-weight: 400;">When the authors make a change, the submission automatically goes back to the </span><em><span style="font-weight: 400;">Pending validations</span></em><span style="font-weight: 400;"> section.&nbsp;</span></li>\r\n<li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><span style="font-weight: 400;">You can do this loop as many times as you want with an article</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3><span style="font-weight: 400;">Validation instructions: Stage 2</span></h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Read the cover letter and abstract</span></li>\r\n<li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Check that…</span></li>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="2"><span style="font-weight: 400;">the preprint is at a preprint server and that the lines are numbered</span></li>\r\n<li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="2"><span style="font-weight: 400;">the URL to the registered Stage 1 manuscript is stated</span></li>\r\n<li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="2"><span style="font-weight: 400;">there is a tracked changes version online of the Stage 2 manuscript (e.g., at OSF)</span></li>\r\n<li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="2"><span style="font-weight: 400;">all deviations transparently flagged, and if major, are they clearly explained and justified in the manuscript</span></li>\r\n<li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="2"><span style="font-weight: 400;">the results section clearly distinguishes confirmatory and exploratory analyses</span></li>\r\n<li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="2"><span style="font-weight: 400;">the abstract reasonably reflects the conclusions</span></li>\r\n<li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="2"><span style="font-weight: 400;">the data is publicly available</span></li>\r\n<li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="2"><span style="font-weight: 400;">the submission checklist is complete</span></li>\r\n<li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="2"><span style="font-weight: 400;">the Stage 1 recommender is the only suggested recommender</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><span style="font-weight: 400;">If any of the above is not complete, email the authors directly and have them modify the submission until it is complete. After that, you can validate it</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>Have a nice day!</p>
109	#ManagersRecommendationOrDecisionStage2	default	{{appName}}: Decision or recommendation requiring validation	Mail to MB to indicate that a decision or a recommendation has been posted by a recommender	<p>Dear members of the Managing Board,</p>\n<p>A decision or a recommendation has been written by {{recommenderPerson}} for {{appName}}.</p>\n<p>To validate and/or manage this recommendation or decision, please follow this link <a href="{{linkTarget}}">{{linkTarget}}</a>.</p>\n<p>Have a nice day!</p>
110	#ManagersArticleResubmitedStage2	default	{{appName}}: Article resubmitted	Mail to MB to indicate that a revised version has been submitted and is under consideration by the recommender	<p>Dear members of the Managing Board,</p>\n<p>A new version of the article entitled "{{articleTitle}}" is under consideration by {{recommenderPerson}} for {{appName}}.</p>\n<p>To manage this recommendation, please follow this link <a href="{{linkTarget}}">{{linkTarget}}</a>.</p>\n<p>Have a nice day!</p>
111	#ManagersArticleConsideredForRecommendationStage2	default	{{appName}}: Article considered for recommendation	Mail to MB to indicate that a recommender took a preprint in charge	<p>Dear members of the Managing Board,</p>\n<p>A new recommendation is under consideration by {{recommenderPerson}} for {{appName}}.</p>\n<p>To manage this recommendation, please follow this link <a href="{{linkTarget}}">{{linkTarget}}</a>.</p>\n<p>Have a nice day!</p>
112	#ManagersArticleCancelledStage2	default	{{appName}}: Article cancelled	Mail to MB to indicate that the submitter cancelled their submission	<p>Dear members of the Managing Board,</p>\r\n<p>The submission of the article entitled "{{articleTitle}}" has been cancelled by the author.</p>\r\n<p>To manage this recommendation, please follow this link <a href="{{linkTarget}}">{{linkTarget}}</a>.</p>\r\n<p>Have a nice day!</p>
113	#ManagersArticleStatusChangedStage2	default	{{appName}}: Article status changed	Mail to MB to indicate the change of a status of the preprint 	<p>Dear members of the Managing Board,</p>\n<p>The status of the article entitled "{{articleTitle}}" changed from "{{tOldStatus}}" to "{{tNewStatus}}".</p>\n<p>To manage this recommendation, please follow this link <a href="{{linkTarget}}">{{linkTarget}}</a>.</p>\n<p>Have a nice day!</p>
115	#RecommenderThankForPreprintStage2	default	{{appName}}: Thank you for handling the evaluation of a Stage 2 submission 	Mail to recommender to thank them for agreeing to handle a Stage 2 submission	<p>Dear {{destPerson}},</p>\r\n<p>You have agreed to be the recommender handling the report entitled <strong>{{articleTitle}}</strong> by {{articleAuthors}} (DOI <a href="{{articleDoi}}">{{articleDoi}}</a>). Thank you very much for your contribution.</p>\r\n<p><strong>We remind you that you have agreed to send out 5-10 invitations to review this report within the next 7 days</strong>, and to send out reminders and/or new invitations, over a period of one week if necessary, until you find at least two reviewers willing to review this report within {{reviewDuration}}. We thank you in advance for respecting this commitment.</p>\r\n<p>Invitations to review can be sent using this link <a href="{{linkTarget}}">{{linkTarget}}</a>. You can also log on to the {{appName}} website and go to 'For recommenders —&gt; Preprint(s) you are handling' in the top menu, and click on the 'choose a reviewer' button.</p>\r\n<p>The reviews you receive should guide your decision – <strong>within 10 days of receiving the last review</strong> – as to whether to ‘Revise’, ‘Recommend’ or ‘Reject’ the report.</p>\r\n<p>If your decision is to ‘Recommend’ this report, you will need to write a “recommendation”, which will have its own DOI and be published by {{appName}} under the license CC-BY-ND. The recommendation is a short article, similar to a News &amp; Views piece. It has its own title, contains between about 300 and 1500 words, describes the context and explains why the report is particularly interesting. The limitations of the report can also be discussed. This text also contains references (citing, at least, the report being recommended). All editorial correspondence (reviews, your decisions, authors' replies) relating to the report will also be published by {{appName}}.</p>\r\n<p>Feel free to contact the authors directly (either via email while cc’ing contact@rr.peercommunityin.org or at the online system by making a Revise decision before sending it to the reviewers) to request any clarifications necessary to be able to make your assessment.</p>\r\n<p>If you need assistance in any way do not hesitate to ask us.</p>\r\n<p>We thank you again for initiating and managing this evaluation.</p>\r\n<p>Yours sincerely,</p>\r\n<p>The Managing Board of {{appName}}</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>
116	#CoRecommenderRemovedFromArticleStage2	default	{{appName}}: Your co-recommendation of a {{articlePrePost}}	Mail to co-recommender to inform them that they have been removed as a co-recommender of a preprint	<p>Dear {{destPerson}},</p>\r\n<p>A recommendation text for the {{articlePrePost}} by {{articleAuthors}} and entitled <strong>{{articleTitle}}</strong> (DOI <a href="{{articleDoi}}">{{articleDoi}}</a>) is under consideration.</p>\r\n<p>You have been removed from co-recommender of this {{articlePrePost}}.</p>\r\n<p>Yours sincerely,</p>\r\n<p>The Managing Board of {{appName}}</p>
117	#CoRecommenderAddedOnArticleAlreadyPublishedStage2	default	{{appName}}: Your co-recommendation of a {{articlePrePost}}	Mail to co-recommender to inform them that they have been declared as a co-recommender of a postprint	<p>Dear {{destPerson}},</p>\r\n<p>A recommendation text for the {{articlePrePost}} by {{articleAuthors}} and entitled <strong>{{articleTitle}}</strong> (DOI <a href="{{articleDoi}}">{{articleDoi}}</a>) is under consideration. You have been declared as a co-recommender of this {{articlePrePost}}. You can view the recommendation by following this link <a href="{{linkTarget}}">{{linkTarget}}</a> or by logging onto the {{appName}} website and going to 'For recommenders —&gt; Your recommendations of posprints' in the top menu.</p>\r\n<p>We are currently handling this recommendation; it will probably be rapidly posted on the {{appName}} website.</p>\r\n<p>If you do not wish to co-author this recommendation, please contact us as soon as possible. Otherwise, we thank you for co-writing this recommendation.</p>\r\n<p>Yours sincerely,</p>\r\n<p>The Managing Board of {{appName}}</p>
118	#CoRecommenderAddedOnArticleStage2	default	{{appName}}: Your co-recommendation of a {{articlePrePost}}	Mail to co-recommender to inform them that they have been declared as a co-recommender of a preprint	<p>Dear {{destPerson}},</p>\r\n<p>A peer-review evaluation of a Stage 2 submission by {{articleAuthors}} and entitled <strong>{{articleTitle}}</strong> (DOI <a href="{{articleDoi}}">{{articleDoi}}</a>) is currently being handled by the recommender {{recommenderPerson}}. This recommender declared you as a co-recommender and, as such, as a co-author of the recommendation if they decide to recommend this preprint. The reviews and the recommendation text can be viewed by clicking on this link: <a href="{{linkTarget}}">{{linkTarget}}</a> or by logging onto the {{appName}} website and going to 'For recommenders —&gt; Preprint you are co-handling' in the top menu.</p>\r\n<p>We remind you that a preprint is recommended if, and only if it is scientifically valid and of high quality and the code of conduct has been followed. The decision to recommend a preprint must be based on high-quality reviews. We also remind you that the recommendation text, all the editorial correspondence (reviews, decisions, your recommendation, and authors’ replies) will be published by {{appName}}. Being a co-recommender for this preprint means that you share full responsibility with the recommender for the public recommendation of this preprint.</p>\r\n<p>If you do not wish to be a co-recommender of this preprint, please contact us as soon as possible. Otherwise, we thank you for this contribution to {{appName}}.</p>\r\n<p>Yours sincerely,</p>\r\n<p>The Managing Board of {{appName}}</p>
119	#CoRecommendersArticleRecommendedStage2	default	{{appName}}: Your co-recommendation of a {{articlePrePost}}	Mail to co-recommenders to indicate them that the preprint is now recommended	<p>Dear {{destPerson}},</p>\n<p>The recommendation for the {{articlePrePost}} by {{articleAuthors}} and entitled <strong>{{articleTitle}}</strong> (doi {{articleDoi}}) is now published on {{appName}} website.</p>\n<p>You can find it there: <a href="{{recommDOI}}">{{recommDOI}}</a></p>\n<p>And there: <a href="{{linkRecomm}}">{{linkRecomm}}</a></p>\n<p>Do not hesitate to share the news as much as possible: social networks if you are on them, mailing, websites, CV, quotation, etc...</p>\n<p>We thank you for co-writing this recommendation.</p>\n<p>Yours sincerely,</p>\n<p>The Managing Board of {{appName}}</p>
120	#CoRecommendersArticleStatusChangedStage2	default	{{appName}}: Your co-recommendation of a {{articlePrePost}}	Mail to co-recommenders to indicate the change of the status of the preprint	<p>Dear {{destPerson}},</p>\n<p>You are co-recommender of the article by {{articleAuthors}} entitled <strong>{{articleTitle}}</strong> (DOI <a href="{{articleDoi}}">{{articleDoi}}</a>).</p>\n<p>The status of this article has changed from "{{tOldStatus}}" to "{{tNewStatus}}".</p>\n<p>You can view the evaluation process by following this link: <a href="{{linkTarget}}">{{linkTarget}}</a> or by logging onto the {{appName}} website and going to 'For recommenders —&gt; Your recommendation of posprints (if it is a posprint) or —&gt; Preprints you are co-handling (if it is a preprint)' in the top menu.</p>\n<p>Yours sincerely,</p>\n<p>The Managing Board of {{appName}}</p>
121	#ReviewersArticleRecommendedStage2	default	{{appName}}: Decision on a Stage 2 Registered Report that you reviewed	Mail to reviewers to indicate them that the preprint they review is now recommended	<p>Dear {{destPerson}},</p>\r\n<p>The Stage 2 Registered Report that you kindly reviewed for {{appName}} is now recommended. The recommendation of this article - along with your reviews - is now posted on {{appName}} website.</p>\r\n<p>The final recommendation may be found here: <a href="{{linkRecomm}}">{{linkRecomm}}</a></p>\r\n<p>Many thanks again for reviewing this article for {{appName}}.</p>\r\n<p>Yours sincerely,</p>\r\n<p>The Managing Board of {{appName}}</p>
122	#ReviewersArticleStatusChangedStage2	default	{{appName}}: Decision on a Stage 2 submission you reviewed	Mail to reviewers to indicate the change of the status of the Stage 2 manuscript they reviewed	<div>Dear {{destPerson}},</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>You have agreed to review the preprint entitled <strong>{{articleTitle}}</strong>. The status of this preprint is now: {{articleStatus}}. To view your review, the reviews of the other referees and the decision taken by the recommender, please follow this link <a href="{{linkTarget}}">{{linkTarget}}</a> or login to the {{appName}} website and go to 'For contributors —&gt; My reviews' in the top menu.</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div><span style="font-weight: 400;"><strong>Your feedback matters.</strong> If this is a final Stage 2 decision (Accept or Reject), then please take 5 minutes to leave anonymous feedback about your experience of the completed review process for this submission:</span> <a href="https://registeredreports.cardiff.ac.uk/feedback/feedback/decision_letter.php"><span style="font-weight: 400;">https://registeredreports.cardiff.ac.uk/feedback/feedback/decision_letter.php</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;"> Feedback from reviewers</span> helps us understand what we’re doing well, what we could do better, and how we can improve and innovate the evaluation of Registered Reports. <span style="font-weight: 400;">This feedback is collected by the </span><a href="https://registeredreports.cardiff.ac.uk/feedback/dashboards/"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Registered Reports Community Feedback</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;"> website which is an independent service and research project being undertaken by Cardiff University.</span></div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>We thank you for the time spent evaluating this preprint.</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>Yours sincerely,</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>The Managing Board of {{appName}}</div>
123	#DefaultReviewCancellationStage2	default	{{appName}}: Cancellation of a review request	Mail to reviewer to indicate a cancellation to review a Stage 2 manuscript	<p>Dear {{destPerson}},</p>\r\n<div>\r\n<p>You were invited to act as a reviewer for a preprint entitled "{{art_title}}" by {{art_authors}} (<a href="%7b%7bart_doi%7d%7d">{{art_doi}}</a>).</p>\r\nThis invitation is cancelled either because you did not reply to the invitation, or because we now have enough reviews for this preprint.</div>\r\n<div><br>Consequently, this preprint no longer appears in your list of requests to act as a reviewer on the {{longname}} webpage.</div>\r\n<p>Many thanks,</p>\r\n<p>PCI RR Managing Board</p>
126	#ReminderSubmitterSuggestedRecommenderNeededStage2	default	{{appName}}: Please, suggest some recommenders for handling your preprint	Mail to submitter if they have not suggested any recommender	<p>Dear {{destPerson}},<br><br>Thank you very much for submitting your preprint to {{appName}}. Before we validate this submission, could you suggest 5 to 10 recommenders:<br><br>1) Go to <a href="{{siteUrl}}">{{siteUrl}}</a> and log in<br>2) Go to 'FOR CONTRIBUTORS —&gt; YOUR SUBMITTED PREPRINTS' in the top menu.<br>3) Click on the black 'ADD/REMOVE' button in the middle of the line referring to the preprint in question and add or remove suggested recommenders.<br>4) Click on the green 'COMPLETE YOUR SUBMISSION' button when you have finished.<br><br>We remind you that you must not suggest recommenders who might have a conflict of interest - see the PCI code of ethical conduct: {{ethicsLink}}.<br><br>If you need any help suggesting recommenders or using the {{appName}} website, let us know.<br><br>Best regards</p>\r\n<p>The Managing Board of {{appName}}</p>
127	#ReminderSubmitterNewSuggestedRecommenderNeededStage2	default	{{appName}}: New suggested recommenders needed	Mail to submitter if the preprint is not taken in charge after 10 days	<p>Dear {{destPerson}},</p>\r\n<p><br>Thanks again for submitting your preprint to {{appName}}. Despite some reminders, none of the suggested recommenders has yet decided to start the evaluation of your preprint. At this stage, we strongly suggest you to suggest additionnal recommenders as follow:<br><br>1) Go to <a href="{{siteUrl}}">{{siteUrl}}</a>&nbsp;and log in<br>2) Go to 'FOR CONTRIBUTORS —&gt; YOUR SUBMITTED PREPRINTS' in the top menu.<br>3) Click on the black 'ADD/REMOVE' button in the middle of the line referring to the preprint in question and add or remove suggested recommenders.<br>4) Click on the green 'COMPLETE YOUR SUBMISSION' button when you have finished.<br><br>Thanks in advance<br>All the best</p>\r\n<p>The managing board of {{appName}}</p>
128	#ReminderSubmitterCancelSubmissionStage2	default	{{appName}}: Please, cancel your submission	Mail to submitter if the preprint is not taken in charge after 20 days	<p>Dear {{destPerson}},</p>\r\n<p>You have submitted your preprint entitled&nbsp;<strong>{{articleTitle}}</strong>&nbsp;to {{appName}}.</p>\r\n<p>Unfortunately, no recommender has initiated the evaluation of your preprint since the submission of this preprint &gt; 20 days ago. This does not mean that your preprint is not of sufficient quality and/or interest. However, we suggest that you do not wait any longer for a return from us at this stage and therefore to cancell your submission by:</p>\r\n<p>1) Logging onto the {{appName}} website.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>2) Go to 'FOR CONTRIBUTORS' —&gt; 'YOUR SUBMITTED PREPRINTS' in the top menu.</p>\r\n<p>3) Click on the black 'VIEW/EDIT' button at the right end of the line referring to the preprint in question.</p>\r\n<p>4) Click on the orange 'I WISH TO CANCEL MY SUBMISSION’ button.</p>\r\n<p>We are sorry to bring disappointing news and hope that that you will consider submitting other preprints to {{appName}} in the future.</p>\r\n<p>Yours sincerely,</p>\r\n<p>The Managing Board of {{appName}}</p>
129	#ReminderSuggestedRecommenderInvitationStage2	default	{{appName}}: Request to act as a recommender for a preprint - reminder	Mail to suggested recommenders to remind them to act as recommender of a submitted preprint	<p>Dear {{destPerson}},</p>\r\n<p>A few days ago, you were suggested as a recommender for a preprint entitled&nbsp;<strong>{{articleTitle}}</strong>&nbsp;by {{articleAuthors}} (DOI <a href="{{articleDoi}}">{{articleDoi}}</a>). You can obtain information about this request and accept or decline this invitation by following this link&nbsp;<a href="{{linkTarget}}">{{linkTarget}}</a> or by logging on to the {{appName}} website and going to 'For recommenders —&gt; Request(s) to handle a preprint' in the top menu.</p>\r\n<p>The role of a recommender is very similar to that of a journal editor (finding reviewers, collecting reviews, taking editorial decisions based on reviews), and may lead to the recommendation of the preprint after several rounds of reviews. The evaluation forms the basis of the decision to ‘Revise’, ‘Recommend’ or ‘Reject’ the preprint. A preprint recommended by {{appName}} is an article that may be used and cited like the ‘classic’ articles published in peer-reviewed journals.</p>\r\n<p>If after one or several rounds of review, you decide to recommend this preprint, you will need to write a “recommendation” that will have its own DOI and be published by {{appName}} under the license CC-BY. The recommendation is a short article, similar to a News &amp; Views piece. It has its own title, contains between about 300 and 1500 words, describes the context and explains why the preprint is particularly interesting. The limitations of the preprint can also be discussed. This text also contains references (citing, at least, the preprint being recommended). All the editorial correspondence (reviews, your decisions, authors’ replies) will also be published by {{appName}}.</p>\r\n<p>If you agree to handle this preprint, you will be responsible for managing the evaluation process until you reach a final decision (i.e. to recommend or reject this preprint). You will be able to invite, through the {{appName}} website, reviewers included in the {{appName}} database or from your own network.</p>\r\n<p>Details about the recommendation process can be found here&nbsp;<a href="{{helpUrl}}">{{helpUrl}}</a>. You can also watch this short video:&nbsp;<a href="https://youtu.be/u5greO-q8-M">How to start and manage a preprint recommendation</a>.</p>\r\n<p>Thanks again for your help.</p>\r\n<p>Yours sincerely,</p>\r\n<p>The Managing Board of {{appName}}</p>
130	#ReminderRecommenderReviewersNeededStage2	default	{{appName}}: Please, send invitations to review the preprint you are handling	Mail to recommender to remind them to send invitation to referee	<p>Dear {{destPerson}},</p>\n<p>Thanks again for taking in charge the report submitted by {{articleAuthors}}. We remind you that you have agreed to send out 5-10 invitations to review this report within the next 7 days, and to send out reminders and/or new invitations, over a period of one week if necessary, until you manage to find at least two reviewers willing to review this report within {{reviewDuration}}. Thanks in advance for sending those invitation which would avoid delaying the reviewing process. To invite reviewer, please:</p>\n<p>1) Go to <a href="{{siteUrl}}">{{siteUrl}}</a> and log in</p>\n<p>2) Go to 'FOR RECOMMENDERS —&gt; REPORT(S) YOU ARE HANDLING' in the top menu.</p>\n<p>3) Click on the black 'INVITE A REVIEWER' button in the line corresponding to the report considered.</p>\n<p>-To invite a reviewer not included in the database of {{appName}}: click on the black ‘CHOOSE A REVIEWER OUTSIDE {{appName}} DATABASE’ button and complete the form (first name, last name and e-mail address of the reviewer). You can change the subject and/or the message if you wish. Then, click on the blue 'SEND E-MAIL' button at the end of the form.</p>\n<p>-To invite a reviewer from the {{appName}} database: click on the green ‘CHOOSE A REVIEWER FROM {{appName}} DATABASE’ button. A search engine and a filter based on thematic fields may be used. Select a reviewer by clicking on the black ‘ADD’ button at the right end of the corresponding line. You can modify the subject and/or the message of the e-mail before sending it. Then, click on the blue 'SEND E-MAIL' button at the end of the form.</p>\n<p>4) When you have sent invitations to all your chosen reviewers, click on the blue 'DONE 'button.</p>\n<p>If you need assistance in any way do not hesitate to ask us.</p>\n<p>Thanks in advance.</p>\n<p>Best regards</p>\n<p>The Managing Board of {{appName}}</p>
131	#ReminderRecommenderNewReviewersNeededStage2	default	{{appName}}: Please, invite additional reviewers	Mail to recommender to ask them to send new referee invitations if <2 reviewers have accepted the review invitation	<p>Dear {{destPerson}},</p>\r\n<p>Thanks for sending invitations to review the preprint by {{articleAuthors}}. All invited reviewers have already received a reminder, but you still need to find other reviewers to be sure to obtain two reviews. Hence, we encourage you to invite further reviewers as following:</p>\r\n<p>1) Go to&nbsp;<a href="{{siteUrl}}">{{siteUrl}}</a>&nbsp;and log in</p>\r\n<p>2) Go to 'FOR RECOMMENDERS —&gt; PREPRINT(S) YOU ARE HANDLING' in the top menu.</p>\r\n<p>3) Click on the black 'INVITE A REVIEWER' button in the line corresponding to the preprint considered.</p>\r\n<p>-To invite a reviewer not included in the database of {{appName}}: click on the black ‘CHOOSE A REVIEWER OUTSIDE {{appName}} DATABASE’ button and complete the form (first name, last name and e-mail address of the reviewer). You can change the subject and/or the message if you wish. Then, click on the blue 'SEND E-MAIL' button at the end of the form.</p>\r\n<p>-To invite a reviewer from the {{appName}} database: click on the green ‘CHOOSE A REVIEWER FROM {{appName}} DATABASE’ button. A search engine and a filter based on thematic fields may be used. Select a reviewer by clicking on the black ‘ADD’ button at the right end of the corresponding line. You can modify the subject and/or the message of the e-mail before sending it. Then, click on the blue 'SEND E-MAIL' button at the end of the form.</p>\r\n<p>4) When you have sent invitations to all of your chosen reviewers, click on the blue 'DONE 'button.</p>\r\n<p>If you need assistance in any way do not hesitate to ask us.</p>\r\n<p>Thanks in advance and thanks again for handling this preprint.</p>\r\n<p>Best regards</p>\r\n<p>The Managing Board of {{appName}}</p>
135	#ReminderRecommenderRevisedDecisionSoonDueStage2	default	{{appName}}: Editorial decision	Mail to recommender to indicate a decision soon due about the revised version	<p>Dear {{destPerson}},<br><br>A few days ago, you should have received the authors' response, a tracked changes version and the link to a revised version of their article on the {{articleTitle}} by {{articleAuthors}}. I hope you have received all these documents. Any idea of what you plan to do? Send this new version for review or make a decision based on this feedback from the authors?<br><br>Thanks in advance for your response.</p>\n<p><br>Best regards<br>The Managing Board of {{appName}}</p>
136	#ReminderRecommenderRevisedDecisionDueStage2	default	{{appName}}: Editorial decision - reminder	Mail to recommender to indicate a decision due about the revised version	<p>Dear {{destPerson}},</p>\n<p>This is reminder for your decision on the revised version of the preprint by {{articleAuthors}}. Any idea of what you plan to do? Send this new version for review or make a decision based on this feedback from the authors?</p>\n<p>Thanks in advance for your response or your decision.</p>\n<p>Best regards</p>\n<p>The Managing Board of {{appName}}</p>
137	#ReminderRecommenderRevisedDecisionOverDueStage2	default	{{appName}}: Editorial decision overdue	Mail to recommender to indicate an overdue decision about the revised version	<p>Dear {{destPerson}},</p>\n<p>This is another reminder for your decision on the revised version of the preprint by {{articleAuthors}}. Any idea of what you plan to do? send this new version for review or make a decision based on this feedback from the authors?</p>\n<p>Thanks in advance for your response or your decision.</p>\n<p>Best regards</p>\n<p>The Managing Board of {{appName}}</p>
138	#ReminderSubmitterRevisedVersionWarningStage2	default	{{appName}}: Revised version - reminder	Mail to submitter to have some news about their revised version	<p>Dear {{destPerson}},</p>\r\n<p>Thanks again for submitting your Stage 2 submission to {{appName}}.</p>\r\n<p>You should have received the decision of the recommender and the reviews on which they (the recommender) based their decision. We hope you found this feedback useful and constructive.</p>\r\n<p>We now await your revised submission. There is no rush to resubmit - the purpose of this message is merely to ensure a smooth follow up of the evaluation of your preprint. If you have any questions or concerns as you progress, feel free to contact us or the recommender ({{recommenderPerson}}) by replying to this message.</p>\r\n<p>All the best</p>\r\n<p>The Managing Board of {{appName}}</p>
139	#ReminderSubmitterRevisedVersionNeededStage2	default	{{appName}}: Revised version?	Mail to submitter to verify that they received the decision and if they intend to resubmit	<p>Dear {{destPerson}},</p>\r\n<p>This is an automated reminder that we are following progress of your Stage 2 Registered Report submitted to {{appName}}. As it has been some time, we are wondering if you intend to submit a revised version, and if so when you expect to submit.</p>\r\n<p>Additional time is no problem. However, it would be helpful if you could reply to this email with an approximate resubmisson date and we will adjust any future reminders accordingly.</p>\r\n<p>All the best,</p>\r\n<p>The Managing Board of {{appName}}</p>
140	#ReminderRecommenderDecisionSoonDueStage2	default	{{appName}}: Editorial decision	Mail to recommender to indicate a decision soon due	<div dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-position: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">Dear </span><span style="font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-position: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">{{destPerson}}</span><span style="font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-position: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">,</span></div>\r\n<div dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-position: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">All reviewers of <strong>{{articleTitle}} </strong>by {{articleAuthors}} posted and completed their reviews some days ago. This means that it's now time to write a decision text and choose between the 3 decisions: Reject, Revise or Recommend. Note: </span>please check to see if there are any outstanding review invitations and, if so, decide whether to wait for further review(s) or cancel the remaining review invitations so you can proceed with a decision.</div>\r\n<div dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-position: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">To post your decision on the PCI <span style="white-space: normal;">{{appName}}</span> website, please:</span></div>\r\n<div dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-position: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">1) Go to <a href="{{siteUrl}}">{{siteUrl}}</a></span><span style="font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-position: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;"> and log in&nbsp;</span></div>\r\n<div dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-position: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">2) Go to '<strong>For Recommenders</strong>'—&gt; '<strong>Reports(s) you are handling</strong>' in the top menu. </span></div>\r\n<div dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-position: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">3) Click the '<strong>View/Edit</strong>' button. </span></div>\r\n<div dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-position: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">4) Click '<strong>Write or edit your decision / recommendation</strong>’. </span></div>\r\n<div dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-position: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">5) Indicate your decision (<strong>revise</strong>, <strong>reject</strong>, <strong>recommend</strong>).</span></div>\r\n<div dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-position: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">6) Choose a decision or recommendation title (this is of particular importance only for decisions to recommend the preprint concerned) and write or copy/paste your decision or recommendation text.&nbsp;</span></div>\r\n<div dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-position: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">-You can save a draft version of your decision or recommendation text by clicking 'Save' (you will then have to go through steps 1 to 5 to complete your decision or recommendation). </span></div>\r\n<div dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-position: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">7) To send your decision or recommendation to the managing board for validation, click on the green 'Save and submit' button. This will result in your decision or recommendation being sent to the Managing Board for validation.</span></div>\r\n<div dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-position: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">Many thanks in advance.</span></div>\r\n<div dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-position: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">The Managing Board of </span>{{appName}}</div>\r\n<p><span id="docs-internal-guid-7d7c062e-7fff-1d1b-f9f2-a4f242c7a5bf"></span></p>
141	#ReminderRecommenderDecisionDueStage2	default	{{appName}}: Editorial decision - reminder	Mail to recommender to indicate a decision due	<div dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-position: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">Dear </span><span style="font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-position: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">{{destPerson}}</span><span style="font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-position: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">,</span></div>\r\n<div dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-position: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">All reviewers of <strong>{{articleTitle}} </strong>by {{articleAuthors}} posted and completed their reviews 10 days ago or more. This means that it's now time to write a decision text and choose between the 3 decisions: Reject, Revise or Recommend. Note: </span>please check to see if there are any outstanding review invitations and, if so, decide whether to wait for further review(s) or cancel the remaining review invitations so you can proceed with a decision.</div>\r\n<div dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-position: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">To post your decision on the PCI <span style="white-space: normal;">{{appName}}</span> website, please:</span></