p: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-position: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">6) Choose a decision or recommendation title (this is of particular importance only for decisions to recommend the preprint concerned) and write or copy/paste your decision or recommendation text.&nbsp;</span></div>\r\n<div dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-position: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">-You can save a draft version of your decision or recommendation text by clicking 'Save' (you will then have to go through steps 1 to 5 to complete your decision or recommendation). </span></div>\r\n<div dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-position: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">7) To send your decision or recommendation to the managing board for validation, click on the green 'Save and submit' button. This will result in your decision or recommendation being sent to the Managing Board for validation.</span></div>\r\n<div dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-position: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">Many thanks in advance.</span></div>\r\n<div dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-position: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">The Managing Board of </span>{{appName}}</div>\r\n<p><span id="docs-internal-guid-7d7c062e-7fff-1d1b-f9f2-a4f242c7a5bf"></span></p>
142	#ReminderRecommenderDecisionOverDueStage2	default	{{appName}}: Editorial decision overdue	Mail to recommender to indicate a decision overdue	<div dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-position: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">Dear </span><span style="font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-position: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">{{destPerson}}</span><span style="font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-position: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">,</span></div>\r\n<div dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-position: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">All reviewers of <strong>{{articleTitle}} </strong>by {{articleAuthors}} posted and completed their reviews more than 10 days ago. This means that it's now time to write a decision text and choose between the 3 decisions: Reject, Revise or Recommend. Note: </span>please check to see if there are any outstanding review invitations and, if so, decide whether to wait for further review(s) or cancel the remaining review invitations so you can proceed with a decision.</div>\r\n<div dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-position: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">To post your decision on the PCI <span style="white-space: normal;">{{appName}}</span> website, please:</span></div>\r\n<div dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-position: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">1) Go to <a href="{{siteUrl}}">{{siteUrl}}</a></span><span style="font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-position: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;"> and log in&nbsp;</span></div>\r\n<div dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-position: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">2) Go to '<strong>For Recommenders</strong>'—&gt; '<strong>Reports(s) you are handling</strong>' in the top menu. </span></div>\r\n<div dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-position: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">3) Click the '<strong>View/Edit</strong>' button. </span></div>\r\n<div dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-position: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">4) Click '<strong>Write or edit your decision / recommendation</strong>’. </span></div>\r\n<div dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-position: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">5) Indicate your decision (<strong>revise</strong>, <strong>reject</strong>, <strong>recommend</strong>).</span></div>\r\n<div dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-position: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">6) Choose a decision or recommendation title (this is of particular importance only for decisions to recommend the preprint concerned) and write or copy/paste your decision or recommendation text.&nbsp;</span></div>\r\n<div dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-position: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">-You can save a draft version of your decision or recommendation text by clicking 'Save' (you will then have to go through steps 1 to 5 to complete your decision or recommendation). </span></div>\r\n<div dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-position: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">7) To send your decision or recommendation to the managing board for validation, click on the green 'Save and submit' button. This will result in your decision or recommendation being sent to the Managing Board for validation.</span></div>\r\n<div dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-position: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">Many thanks in advance.</span></div>\r\n<div dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-position: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">The Managing Board of </span>{{appName}}</div>\r\n<p><span id="docs-internal-guid-7d7c062e-7fff-1d1b-f9f2-a4f242c7a5bf"></span></p>
143	#ReminderReviewerReviewInvitationRegisteredUserStage2	default	Invitation to review a Stage 2 submission that you previously reviewed at Stage 1 - reminder	Mail to user already registered to remind about a Stage 2 review invitation	<p>Dear {{destPerson}},</p>\r\n<p>This is a kind reminder concerning the following message, which you should already have received:</p>\r\n<p>Following in-principle acceptance (IPA) of a Stage 1 submission that you reviewed, the authors have submitted a follow-up Stage 2 manuscript entitled "<strong>{{art_title}}</strong>". The Stage 2 manuscript contains the content from Stage 1 plus the results and conclusions, and I am writing to ask if you would kindly consider reviewing it for us. A clean version of the Stage 2 manuscript can be viewed and downloaded at the following address: <a href="{{art_doi}}">{{art_doi}}</a></p>\r\n<p>In evaluating Stage 2 manuscripts, we ask reviewers to assess:</p>\r\n<p>2A. Whether the data are able to test the authors’ proposed hypotheses (or answer the proposed research question) by passing the approved outcome-neutral criteria, such as absence of floor and ceiling effects or success of positive controls or other quality checks.</p>\r\n<p>2B. Whether the introduction, rationale and stated hypotheses (where applicable) are the same as the approved Stage 1 submission.</p>\r\n<p>2C. Whether the authors adhered precisely to the registered study procedures.</p>\r\n<p>2D. Where applicable, whether any unregistered exploratory analyses are justified, methodologically sound, and informative.</p>\r\n<p>2E. Whether the authors’ conclusions are justified given the evidence.</p>\r\n<p>The PCI RR website includes an <a href="https://rr.peercommunityin.org/help/guide_for_reviewers#h_6720026472751613309075757" target="_blank" rel="noopener">expanded description of these review criteria</a>, additional <a href="https://rr.peercommunityin.org/help/guide_for_reviewers#h_7586915642301613635089357" target="_blank" rel="noopener">tips for reviewing a RR</a>, and <a href="https://rr.peercommunityin.org/help/guide_for_reviewers" target="_blank" rel="noopener">complete reviewer guidelines</a>. To ensure swift handling of submissions, the requested review time is <strong>{{reviewDuration}}</strong>, but if you are unable to review the manuscript within this time then please let me know by reply email and we can extend the timeframe. Where possible, it is important that the same reviewers evaluate submissions at Stage 1 and Stage 2.</p>\r\n<p>Please note that the statistical significance, novelty, or perceived importance of findings will not factor into editorial decisions.</p>\r\n<p>In the event of a favourable outcome, all editorial correspondence (Stage 2 reviews, recommender’s decisions, authors’ replies) and a recommendation text will be published by PCI RR under a CC-BY 4.0 license. If, after one or several rounds of review, the Stage 2 manuscript is rejected, the editorial correspondence (and specifically your Stage 2 review) will NOT be published. You will be notified by e-mail at each stage in the procedure.</p>\r\n<p>Note that to avoid any conflict of interests, where you know the identity of the submitting authors you should not accept to evaluate this submission if the authors are close colleagues (people belonging to the same laboratory/unit/department in the last four years, people with whom you have published in the last four years, with whom you have received joint funding in the last four years, or with whom you are currently writing a manuscript, or submitting a grant proposal).</p>\r\n<p>Please let me know as soon as possible whether you are willing to accept my invitation to review this article, or whether you would prefer to decline, by clicking on the link below or by logging onto the {{longname}} website and going to 'For contributors —&gt; Invitation(s) to review a preprint' in the top menu.</p>\r\n<p>Thanks in advance for your help.</p>\r\n<p>Yours sincerely,</p>\r\n<p>{{recommenderName}}</p>
145	#SubmitterRecommendedPreprintPrivateStage1	default	{{appName}}: Stage 1 in-principle acceptance of your manuscript	Mail to author containing notification of an embargoed Stage 1 IPA decision	<div>Dear {{destPerson}},</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>Thank you for submitting your manuscript to PCI RR for consideration as a Registered Report (Stage 1). After careful consideration, we are pleased to award in-principle acceptance (IPA) of your submission.</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>Please read the following letter carefully.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div><strong>Preregistration of the Stage 1 manuscript</strong>. As noted in the <a href="https://rr.peercommunityin.org/help/guide_for_authors#h_2238970114821613309509575" target="_blank" rel="noopener">author guidelines</a>, PCI RR has now registered your approved Stage 1 manuscript on the OSF, and the URL to this protocol is provided in the Stage 1 recommendation text. Depending on the selections you made in the Stage 1 submission checklist, your approved Stage 1 manuscript has been registered either publicly or under a private embargo. If you opted for a private embargo, note that the embargo will be released and the registered protocol made public when any one of the following conditions are met: submission of the Stage 2 manuscript; withdrawal of the submission and consequent triggering of a Withdrawn Registration; or natural expiry of the embargo at the end of the period you selected in the Stage 1 submission checklist.</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div><strong>Progressing to Stage 2.</strong> You may now move to Stage 2 and complete the study as approved. We would be grateful if you could now update the PCI RR Managing board (<a href="mailto:contact@rr.peercommunityin.org">contact@rr.peercommunityin.org</a>) as to the anticipated completion date of your study. This deadline can be readily altered in consultation with the Managing Baord (e.g. in case of delays requiring additional time to complete the research). However, in the event that you should fail to submit the Stage 2 manuscript within 6 months of the mutually agreed deadline and also become non-responsive during this period to enquiries, then the manuscript will be considered by PCI RR to be de facto withdrawn, triggering publication of a Withdrawn Registration.</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>Following completion of your study, we invite you to resubmit one or more Stage 2 Registered Reports, depending on whether this IPA applies to a regular RR (involving one Stage 2 output) or a programmatic RR (involving multiple Stage 2 outputs). If you are receiving IPA for a programmatic RR then please familiarise yourself with the <a href="https://rr.peercommunityin.org/help/guide_for_authors#h_52492857233251613309610581" target="_blank" rel="noopener">reporting requirements for programmatic RRs at Stage 2</a>.</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div><strong>Stage 2 review criteria (see <a href="https://rr.peercommunityin.org/help/guide_for_authors#h_6720026472751613309075757" target="_blank" rel="noopener">here</a>)</strong>. Please note that a Stage 2 manuscript can be rejected by PCI RR if the recommender and Managing Board consider any of the following conditions to be met:</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>The results were unable to test the authors' proposed hypotheses (or answer the proposed research question) by failing to meet any approved outcome-neutral criteria, such as the absence of floor and ceiling effects, success of positive controls or other quality checks</li>\r\n<li>The authors altered the Introduction, rationale, or hypotheses, as approved in the Stage 1 submission</li>\r\n<li>The authors failed to adhere to the registered study procedures or preregistered analyses (and see below concerning necessary deviations from protocol)</li>\r\n<li>Any <em>post hoc</em> (unregistered) analyses are either unjustified, insufficiently caveated, or overly dominant in shaping the authors' conclusions</li>\r\n<li>The authors' conclusions were not justified given the data obtained</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div><strong>Deviations from protocol.</strong> Please note that any deviation from the registered study procedures that is not approved in advance by the recommender and Managing Board could lead to rejection at Stage 2. In cases where the preregistered protocol must be altered after IPA due to unforeseen circumstances (e.g. change of equipment or unanticipated technical error), it is imperative that you consult the recommender immediately and prior to the completion of data collection, regardless of how minor the deviation may seem. Minor changes to the protocol that do not increase risk of bias are likely to be swiftly approved. In such cases, IPA would be preserved and the deviation reported in the Stage 2 submission.</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div><strong>Notification of PCI RR-interested journals.</strong> If you consented to notifying PCI RR-interested journals about your IPA then the complete list of <a href="https://rr.peercommunityin.org/about/pci_rr_interested_journals" target="_blank" rel="noopener">PCI RR-interested journals</a> will now be given access to the author names, stated contact details, Stage 1 reviews and recommendation text (provided you also consented to publish the reviews and recommendation at the point of IPA), as well as the URL to the Stage 1 manuscript that has been registered by PCI RR (even if preregistered under a private embargo).</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div><strong>Recommendation text</strong>. The recommender handling your submission has written a Stage 1 recommendation to accompany this decision letter. The recommendation will state the URL to the registered Stage 1 manuscript on the OSF, the <a href="https://rr.peercommunityin.org/help/guide_for_authors#h_95790490510491613309490336" target="_blank" rel="noopener">level of bias control</a> that was reached in your submission, and will list all eligible <a href="https://rr.peercommunityin.org/about/pci_rr_friendly_journals" target="_blank" rel="noopener">PCI RR-friendly journals</a> that endorse this IPA decision and will later accept your approved Stage 2 manuscript(s) without further peer review. As noted in the author guidelines, the PCI RR Managing Board determines which PCI RR-friendly journals are eligible based on the disciplinary fit, word limit requirements, minimum pre-planned strength of evidence (e.g. level of statistical power), level of bias control achieved, and any other listed journal requirements (such as the acceptance of signed reviews only). Note that if you opted to keep the Stage 1 recommendation and reviews private until Stage 2 acceptance, then they will not appear on the PCI RR website until the completion of Stage 2. For further information, please see <a href="https://osf.io/dcvj7/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">this tutorial </a>on how to interpret the different sections of the Stage 1 recommendation.</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div><span style="font-weight: 400;"><strong>Your feedback matters.</strong> Please take 5 minutes to leave anonymous feedback about your experience of the Stage 1 review process for this submission:</span> <a href="https://registeredreports.cardiff.ac.uk/feedback/feedback/decision_letter.php"><span style="font-weight: 400;">https://registeredreports.cardiff.ac.uk/feedback/feedback/decision_letter.php</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;"> Feedback from authors</span> helps us understand what we’re doing well, what we could do better, and how we can improve and innovate the review process for Registered Reports. <span style="font-weight: 400;">This feedback is collected by the </span><a href="https://registeredreports.cardiff.ac.uk/feedback/dashboards/"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Registered Reports Community Feedback</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;"> website which is an independent service and research project being undertaken by Cardiff University.</span></div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>Congratulations on achieving Stage 1 in-principle acceptance and thank you for using PCI RR.</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>Yours sincerely,</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>The PCI RR Managing Board</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>{{recommendationProcess}}</div>
146	#RecommenderStatusChangedUnderToRecommendedPrivateStage1	default	{{appName}}: Stage 1 manuscript now recommended privately	Mail to recommender to indicate that the preprint is now recommended privately	<p>Dear {{destPerson}},</p>\r\n<p>The article by {{articleAuthors}} entitled {{articleTitle}} (DOI {{articleDoi}}) that you are the recommender for {{appName}} has now been recommended privately.</p>\r\n<p>Yours sincerely,</p>\r\n<p>The Managing Board of {{appName}}</p>
147	#CoRecommendersArticleRecommendedPrivateStage1	default	{{appName}}: article you are co-recommending has been recommended privately	Mail to co-recommenders to indicate them that the preprint is now recommended privately	<p>Dear {{destPerson}},</p>\r\n<p>The article {{articlePrePost}} by {{articleAuthors}} and entitled {{articleTitle}} (DOI {{articleDoi}}) that you have been co-recommending has now been recommended privately.</p>\r\n<p>Yours sincerely,</p>\r\n<p>The Managing Board of {{appName}}</p>
148	#ReviewersArticleRecommendedPrivateStage1	default	{{appName}}: Stage 1 submission now recommended privately	Mail to reviewers to indicate them that the preprint they review is now recommended privately	<div>Dear {{destPerson}},</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>The article that you kindly reviewed for {{appName}} is now recommended. The recommendation of this article - along with your reviews - will remain private until Stage 2 acceptance.</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>\r\n<div><span style="font-weight: 400;"><strong>Your feedback matters.</strong> Please take 5 minutes to leave anonymous feedback about your experience of the Stage 1 review process for this submission:</span> <a href="https://registeredreports.cardiff.ac.uk/feedback/feedback/decision_letter.php"><span style="font-weight: 400;">https://registeredreports.cardiff.ac.uk/feedback/feedback/decision_letter.php</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;"> Feedback from reviewers</span> helps us understand what we’re doing well, what we could do better, and how we can improve and innovate the evaluation of Registered Reports. <span style="font-weight: 400;">This feedback is collected by the </span><a href="https://registeredreports.cardiff.ac.uk/feedback/dashboards/"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Registered Reports Community Feedback</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;"> website which is an independent service and research project being undertaken by Cardiff University.</span></div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>Thanks again for reviewing this article for {{appName}}.</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>Yours sincerely,</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>The Managing Board of {{appName}}</div>
157	#AdminArticleResubmitedStage1	default	{{appName}}: Article resubmitted	Mail to MB to indicate that a revised version has been submitted and is under consideration by the recommender	<p>Dear members of the Managing Board,</p>\r\n<p>A new version of the article entitled "{{articleTitle}}" is under consideration by {{recommenderPerson}} for {{appName}}.</p>\r\n<p>To manage this recommendation, please follow this link <a href="{{linkTarget}}">{{linkTarget}}</a>.</p>\r\n<p>Have a nice day!</p>
158	#AdminArticleResubmitedStage2	default	{{appName}}: Article resubmitted	Mail to MB to indicate that a revised version has been submitted and is under consideration by the recommender	<p>Dear members of the Managing Board,</p>\r\n<p>A new version of the article entitled "{{articleTitle}}" is under consideration by {{recommenderPerson}} for {{appName}}.</p>\r\n<p>To manage this recommendation, please follow this link <a href="{{linkTarget}}">{{linkTarget}}</a>.</p>\r\n<p>Have a nice day!</p>
210	#EmailFooterTemplate	default	\N	Editable email footer that is attached to all emails	<p><em>PCI Registered Reports</em> is one of the communities of the parent project Peer Community In. It is a community of researchers across all research areas dedicated to the recommendation of registered reports that are publicly available in open archives (such as bioRxiv, arXiv, PaleorXiv, etc.) based on a high quality peer review process. This project was driven by a desire to establish a free, transparent, and public scientific publication system based on the review and recommendation of preprints. More information can be found on the website of <em>PCI Registered Reports&nbsp;</em>(<a href="https://rr.peercommunityin.org/about/about" target="_blank" rel="noopener">https://rr.peercommunityin.org/about/about</a>).</p>\r\n<p>In case you have any questions or queries, please email us at: <a href="mailto:contact@rr.peercommunityin.org" target="_blank" rel="noopener">contact@rr.peercommunityin.org</a>.</p>\r\n<p>If you wish to modify your profile or the fields and frequency of alerts, please click on your user name in the top right corner of the website, then click on 'Profile' or follow this link: <a href="https://rr.peercommunityin.org/default/user/login?_next=%2Fdefault%2Fuser%2Fprofile" target="_blank" rel="noopener">https://rr.peercommunityin.org/default/user/login?_next=%2Fdefault%2Fuser%2Fprofile</a>.</p>
212	#RecommenderSuggestedReviewersStage1	default	{{appName}}: suggested reviewers	Mail to recommender to notify reviewer declined invitation and suggests alternative reviewers	<p>Dear {{destPerson}},</p>\r\n<p>The reviewer {{reviewerPerson}} that just declined your invitation to review the report entiled <strong>{{articleTitle}}</strong> suggests the following reviewers:</p>\r\n<p><strong>{{suggestedReviewersText}}</strong></p>\r\n<p>You can invite these reviewers by following this link <a href="{{linkTarget}}">{{linkTarget}}</a> or by logging onto the {{appName}} website and going to 'For recommenders —&gt; Report(s) you are handling’ in the top menu.</p>\r\n<p>We thank you again for managing this evaluation.</p>\r\n<p>All the best,<br>The Managing Board of {{appName}}</p>
213	#RecommenderSuggestedReviewersStage2	default	{{appName}}: suggested reviewers	Mail to recommender to notify reviewer declined invitation and suggests alternative reviewers	<p>Dear {{destPerson}},</p>\r\n<p>The reviewer {{reviewerPerson}} that just declined your invitation to review the report entiled <strong>{{articleTitle}}</strong> suggests the following reviewers:</p>\r\n<p><strong>{{suggestedReviewersText}}</strong></p>\r\n<p>You can invite these reviewers by following this link <a href="{{linkTarget}}">{{linkTarget}}</a> or by logging onto the {{appName}} website and going to 'For recommenders —&gt; Report(s) you are handling’ in the top menu.</p>\r\n<p>We thank you again for managing this evaluation.</p>\r\n<p>All the best,<br>The Managing Board of {{appName}}</p>
216	#RecommenderDecisionSentBackStage1	default	{{appName}}: You can edit your decision	Mail to recommender to indicate that the decision is now reopened (decision modifications, reviewers invitations...)	<p>Dear {{destPerson}},</p>\r\n<p>We have changed the status of your decision on the report <span style="font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-position: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">by {{articleAuthors}} (<a href="{{articleDoi}}">{{articleDoi}}</a>). Y</span>ou can now change or edit this decision. Before doing so, you can also invite more reviewers if needed.</p>\r\n<p><span style="font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-position: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">T</span><span style="font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-position: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">o post your new decision on the PCI {{appName}} website, please:</span></p>\r\n<p dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-position: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">1) Go to <a href="{{linkTarget}}">{{linkTarget}}</a> or go to <a href="{{siteUrl}}">{{siteUrl}}</a></span><span style="font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-position: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">, log in and g</span><span style="font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-position: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">o to 'For recommenders'—&gt; 'Report(s) you are handling' in the top menu. </span></p>\r\n<p dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-position: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">2) Click on the black 'View/Edit' button at the right end of the corresponding line. </span></p>\r\n<p dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-position: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">3) Click on the green 'WRITE OR EDIT YOUR DECISION / RECOMMENDATION’ button. </span></p>\r\n<p dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-position: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">4) Indicate your decision by selecting the corresponding button. </span></p>\r\n<p dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-position: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">5) Choose a decision or recommendation title (this is of particular importance only for decisions to recommend the preprint concerned) and write or copy/paste your decision or recommendation text. </span></p>\r\n<p dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-position: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">-You can save a draft version of your decision or recommendation text by clicking on the blue 'SAVE' button (you will then have to go through steps 0 to 5 to complete your decision or recommendation).&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-position: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">6) To send your decision or recommendation to the managing board for validation, click on the green 'SAVE AND COMPLETE' button. This will result in your decision or recommendation being sent to the managing board for validation.</span></p>\r\n<p dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-position: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">Thanks in advance.</span></p>\r\n<p dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-position: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">Best regards</span></p>\r\n<p dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-position: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">The Managing Board of {{appName}} </span><span style="font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-position: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">{{appName}}</span></p>
217	#RecommenderDecisionSentBackStage2	default	{{appName}}: You can edit your decision	Mail to recommender to indicate that the decision is now reopened (decision modifications, reviewers invitations...)	<p>Dear {{destPerson}},</p>\r\n<p>We have changed the status of your decision on the report <span style="font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-position: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">by {{articleAuthors}} (<a href="{{articleDoi}}">{{articleDoi}}</a>). Y</span>ou can now change or edit this decision. Before doing so, you can also invite more reviewers if needed.</p>\r\n<p><span style="font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-position: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">T</span><span style="font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-position: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">o post your new decision on the PCI {{appName}} website, please:</span></p>\r\n<p dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-position: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">1) Go to <a href="{{linkTarget}}">{{linkTarget}}</a> or go to <a href="{{siteUrl}}">{{siteUrl}}</a></span><span style="font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-position: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">, log in and g</span><span style="font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-position: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">o to 'For recommenders'—&gt; 'Report(s) you are handling' in the top menu. </span></p>\r\n<p dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-position: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">2) Click on the black 'View/Edit' button at the right end of the corresponding line. </span></p>\r\n<p dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-position: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">3) Click on the green 'WRITE OR EDIT YOUR DECISION / RECOMMENDATION’ button. </span></p>\r\n<p dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-position: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">4) Indicate your decision by selecting the corresponding button. </span></p>\r\n<p dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-position: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">5) Choose a decision or recommendation title (this is of particular importance only for decisions to recommend the preprint concerned) and write or copy/paste your decision or recommendation text. </span></p>\r\n<p dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-position: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">-You can save a draft version of your decision or recommendation text by clicking on the blue 'SAVE' button (you will then have to go through steps 0 to 5 to complete your decision or recommendation).&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-position: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">6) To send your decision or recommendation to the managing board for validation, click on the green 'SAVE AND COMPLETE' button. This will result in your decision or recommendation being sent to the managing board for validation.</span></p>\r\n<p dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-position: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">Thanks in advance.</span></p>\r\n<p dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-position: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">Best regards</span></p>\r\n<p dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-position: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">The Managing Board of {{appName}} </span><span style="font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-position: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">{{appName}}</span></p>
249	#ReviewerGenericMail	default	{{appName}}: about your peer review	Generic mail to reviewers for recommender/managers to notify any additional information	<p>Dear {{destPerson}},</p>\r\n<p>Regarding your review of the submission entitled <strong>{{articleTitle}}</strong>,<br><br><br><strong><em>**You can edit/write your message to the referee**</em></strong><br><br><br></p>\r\n<p>We thank you again for evaluating this preprint.</p>\r\n<p>All the best,<br>{{recommenderPerson}} at {{appName}}</p>
252	#DefaultReviewAlreadyAcceptedCancellation	default	{{appName}}: About your review	Mail to reviewer to indicate a cancellation to review a report	<p>Dear {{destPerson}},</p>\r\n<div>Thank you for kindly agreeing to review the report entitled "{{art_title}}" by {{art_authors}} (DOI <a href="{{art_doi}}">{{art_doi}}</a>).</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>I am writing to let you know that we have decided to move ahead with an editorial decision on this manuscript without your evaluation.</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>If you have any questions and if you have already written your review, please feel free to reply by return email and we will include it in the evaluation. Thank you in advance.</div>\r\n<p>Best regards,</p>\r\n<p>{{sender}}</p>
267	#DefaultReviewCancellation	default	{{appName}}: Cancellation of a review request	Mail to reviewer to indicate cancellation of a Stage 1 review invitation	<p>Dear {{destPerson}},</p>\r\n<div>We recently invited you to review a Stage 1 Registered Report entitled "{{art_title}}".&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>We are writing to let you know that we have now found sufficient reviewers for this submission and your evaluation is no longer requested. Many thanks for your consideration.</div>\r\n<p>Best regards,</p>\r\n<p>The Managing Board of {{appName}}</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">&nbsp;#DefaultReviewCancellation</span></p>
268	#DefaultReviewInvitationNewRoundRegisteredUserStage2	default	Invitation to review a revised Stage 2 manuscript for Peer Community in Registered Reports	Mail to registered user to invite them to re-review a revised Stage 2 manuscript that they previously reviewed	<div>Dear {{destPerson}},</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>Thank you for your previous review of the Stage 2 Registered Report entitled "<strong>{{art_title}}</strong>", which was submitted for potential recommendation by Peer Community in Registered Reports (PCI RR). The authors have now submitted a revision and I am writing to ask if you would kindly consider reviewing it for us. A clean version of the revised manuscript can be viewed and downloaded at the following address: <a href="{{art_doi}}">{{art_doi}}</a></div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>The authors have also supplied a tracked changes version of the manuscript and a response to reviewers. You will find these files linked on the PCI RR website once you accept the review request and they can also be downloaded directly from the links below:</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>Response to reviewers: {{r2r_url}}</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>Tracked changes manuscript: {{trackchanges_url}}</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>To ensure swift handling of submissions, the requested review time is <strong>{{reviewDuration}}</strong>, but if you are unable to review the manuscript within this time then please let me know by reply email and we can extend the timeframe.</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>Submissions that pass Stage 1 review are issued an in-principle acceptance (IPA), which guarantees a positive recommendation of the completed study if the authors adhere to the approved procedures and propose a defensible interpretation of the results. Completed manuscripts are then peer reviewed again at Stage 2, ideally by the same reviewers as Stage 1.</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>In the event of a favourable outcome, all editorial correspondence (reviews, recommender’s decisions, authors’ replies) and a recommendation text will be published by PCI RR under a CC-BY 4.0 license. If, after one or several rounds of review, the preprint is rejected, the editorial correspondence (and specifically your review) will NOT be published. You will be notified by e-mail at each stage in the procedure.</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>I would be grateful if you could let me know as soon as possible whether you are willing to accept my invitation to review this revised manuscript, or whether you would prefer to decline, by clicking on the link below or by logging onto the PCI RR website and going to 'For contributors —&gt; Invitation(s) to review a report' in the top menu. You will find the authors' response to reviewers and manuscript with the tracked changes manuscript linked on the website.</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>Many thanks for considering this re-review request and for helping to support PCI RR.</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>Best wishes,</div>\r\n<div>{{sender}}</div>
269	#ReminderReviewerInvitationNewRoundRegisteredUserStage2	default	Invitation to review a revised Stage 2 manuscript for Peer Community in Registered Reports - reminder	Reminder mail to registered user to invite them to re-review a revised Stage 2 manuscript that they previously reviewed	<p>Dear {{destPerson}},&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>This is a kind reminder.<br><br>Thank you for your previous review of the Stage 2 Registered Report entitled "{{art_title}}", which was submitted for potential recommendation by Peer Community in Registered Reports (PCI RR). The authors have now submitted a revision and I am writing to ask if you would kindly consider reviewing it for us. A clean version of the revised manuscript can be viewed and downloaded at the following address: <a href="{{art_doi}}">{{art_doi}}</a></p>\r\n<p>The authors have also supplied a tracked changes version of the manuscript and a response to reviewers. You will find these files linked on the PCI RR website once you accept the review request and they can also be downloaded directly from the links below:</p>\r\n<p>Response to reviewers: {{r2r_url}}</p>\r\n<p>Tracked changes manuscript: {{trackchanges_url}}</p>\r\n<p>To ensure swift handling of submissions, the requested review time is <strong>{{reviewDuration}}</strong>, but if you are unable to review the manuscript within this time then please let me know by reply email and we can extend the timeframe.</p>\r\n<p>Submissions that pass Stage 1 review are issued an in-principle acceptance (IPA), which guarantees a positive recommendation of the completed study if the authors adhere to the approved procedures and propose a defensible interpretation of the results. Completed manuscripts are then peer reviewed again at Stage 2, ideally by the same reviewers as Stage 1.</p>\r\n<p>In the event of a favourable outcome, all editorial correspondence (reviews, recommender’s decisions, authors’ replies) and a recommendation text will be published by PCI RR under a CC-BY 4.0 license. If, after one or several rounds of review, the preprint is rejected, the editorial correspondence (and specifically your review) will NOT be published. You will be notified by e-mail at each stage in the procedure.</p>\r\n<p>I would be grateful if you could let me know as soon as possible whether you are willing to accept my invitation to review this revised manuscript, or whether you would prefer to decline, by clicking on the link below or by logging onto the PCI RR website and going to 'For contributors —&gt; Invitation(s) to review a preprint' in the top menu. You will find the authors' response to reviewers and manuscript with the tracked changes manuscript linked on the website.</p>\r\n<p>Many thanks for considering this re-review request and for helping to support PCI RR.</p>\r\n<p>Best wishes,</p>\r\n<p>{{sender}}</p>
270	#ReminderReviewerInvitationNewRoundRegisteredUserStage1	default	Invitation to review a revised Stage 1 manuscript for Peer Community in Registered Reports - reminder	Reminder mail to registered user to invite them to re-review a revised Stage 1 manuscript that they previously reviewed	<div>\r\n<p>Dear {{destPerson}},</p>\r\n<p>This is a kind reminder.</p>\r\n<p>Thank you for your previous review of the Stage 1 Registered Report entitled "<strong>{{art_title}}</strong>", which was submitted for potential recommendation by Peer Community in Registered Reports (PCI RR). The authors have now submitted a revision and I am writing to ask if you would kindly consider reviewing it for us. A clean version of the revised manuscript can be viewed and downloaded at the following address: <a href="{{art_doi}}">{{art_doi}}</a></p>\r\n<p>The authors have also supplied a tracked changes version of the manuscript and a response to reviewers. You will find these files linked on the PCI RR website once you accept the review request and they can also be downloaded directly from the links below:</p>\r\n<p>Response to reviewers: {{r2r_url}}</p>\r\n<p>Tracked changes manuscript: {{trackchanges_url}}</p>\r\n<p>To ensure swift handling of submissions, the requested review time is <strong>{{reviewDuration}}</strong>, but if you are unable to review the manuscript within this time then please let me know by reply email and we can extend the timeframe.</p>\r\n<p>Submissions that pass Stage 1 review are issued an in-principle acceptance (IPA), which guarantees a positive recommendation of the completed study if the authors adhere to the approved procedures and propose a defensible interpretation of the results. Completed manuscripts are then peer reviewed again at Stage 2, ideally by the same reviewers as Stage 1.</p>\r\n<p>In the event of a favourable outcome, all editorial correspondence (reviews, recommender’s decisions, authors’ replies) and a recommendation text will be published by PCI RR under a CC-BY 4.0 license. If, after one or several rounds of review, the preprint is rejected, the editorial correspondence (and specifically your review) will NOT be published. You will be notified by e-mail at each stage in the procedure.</p>\r\n<p>I would be grateful if you could let me know as soon as possible whether you are willing to accept my invitation to review this revised manuscript, or whether you would prefer to decline, by clicking on the link below or by logging onto the PCI RR website and going to 'For contributors —&gt; Invitation(s) to review a report' in the top menu. You will find the authors' response to reviewers and manuscript with the tracked changes manuscript linked on the website.</p>\r\n<p>Many thanks for considering this re-review request and for helping to support PCI RR.</p>\r\n<p>Best wishes,</p>\r\n<p>PCI RR Managing Board</p>\r\n</div>
271	#DefaultReviewInvitationNewRoundRegisteredUserStage1	default	Invitation to review a revised Stage 1 manuscript for Peer Community in Registered Reports	Mail to registered user to invite them to re-review a revised Stage 1 manuscript that they previously reviewed	<div>\r\n<p>Dear {{destPerson}},</p>\r\n<p>Thank you for your previous review of the Stage 1 Registered Report entitled "<strong>{{art_title}}</strong>", which was submitted for potential recommendation by Peer Community in Registered Reports (PCI RR). The authors have now submitted a revision and I am writing to ask if you would kindly consider reviewing it for us. The revised manuscript can be viewed and downloaded at the following address: <a href="{{art_doi}}">{{art_doi}}</a></p>\r\n<p>The authors have also supplied a tracked changes version of the manuscript and a response to reviewers. You will find these files linked on the PCI RR website once you accept the review request and they can also be downloaded directly from the links below:</p>\r\n<p>Response to reviewers: {{r2r_url}}</p>\r\n<p>Tracked changes manuscript: {{trackchanges_url}}</p>\r\n<p>To ensure swift handling of submissions, the requested review time is <strong>{{reviewDuration}}</strong>, but if you are unable to review the manuscript within this time then please let me know by reply email and we can extend the timeframe.</p>\r\n<p>Submissions that pass Stage 1 review are issued an in-principle acceptance (IPA), which guarantees a positive recommendation of the completed study if the authors adhere to the approved procedures and propose a defensible interpretation of the results. Completed manuscripts are then peer reviewed again at Stage 2, ideally by the same reviewers as Stage 1.</p>\r\n<p>In the event of a favourable outcome, all editorial correspondence (reviews, recommender’s decisions, authors’ replies) and a recommendation text will be published by PCI RR under a CC-BY 4.0 license. If, after one or several rounds of review, the preprint is rejected, the editorial correspondence (and specifically your review) will NOT be published. You will be notified by e-mail at each stage in the procedure.</p>\r\n<p>I would be grateful if you could let me know as soon as possible whether you are willing to accept my invitation to review this revised manuscript, or whether you would prefer to decline, by clicking on the link below or by logging onto the PCI RR website and going to 'For contributors —&gt; Invitation(s) to review a report' in the top menu. You will find the authors' response to reviewers and manuscript with the tracked changes manuscript linked on the website.</p>\r\n<p>Many thanks for considering this re-review request and for helping to support PCI RR.</p>\r\n<p>Best wishes,</p>\r\n<p>{{sender}}</p>\r\n</div>
272	#SubmitterGenericMail	default	{{appName}}: Revisions required to your submission	Generic mail to submitters to fix errors in their submission	<p>Dear {{destPerson}},</p>\r\n<p>Thank you for submission entitled <strong>{{articleTitle}}</strong>.<br><br>The PCI RR Managing Board routinely evaluates submissions for basic compliance with PCI RR policy.</p>\r\n<p>Before we can progress your submission and assign a recommender (equivalent to action editor), the following points need to be addressed:<br><br><br><strong>[MB member to insert points here]</strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Please follow the steps below to revise your submission:</p>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li>Make the changes to the manuscript or snapshot as instructed. We recommend using version control to keep the same URL to the submitted document, but if you decide to change the URL be sure to update any references to the URL in steps 4 and 5 below.</li>\r\n<li>Once the revisions are made, <a href="https://rr.peercommunityin.org/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">login to the PCI RR website</a> and navigate to: <strong>For contributors</strong> &gt; <strong>Your submitted reports</strong></li>\r\n<li>Find the submission that needs revising and click <strong>VIEW/EDIT</strong></li>\r\n<li>Click on “Edit report”. Update your cover letter to respond to the points raised above and click “Save”.</li>\r\n<li>If you need to make any changes to the submission checklist, click on “Edit report survey” and update the survey where required, then click “Submit”. If no changes to the submission checklist are required then you can skip this step.</li>\r\n<li>Your revision has now been resubmitted for consideration by the PCI RR Managing Board.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p>Thanks again for your submission.</p>\r\n<p>The Managing Board of {{appName}}</p>
274	#SubmitterAcknowledgementSubmissionStage1ScheduledSubmission	default	{{appName}}: Thank you for your Stage 1 submission - scheduled submission	Mail to submitter to acknowledge their submission (for scheduled submission)	<p>Dear {{destPerson}},</p>\n<p>Thank you for your Stage 1 submission entitled {{articleTitle}}, to {{appName}}.</p>\n<p>If you have not already done so, please suggest recommenders who could initiate the evaluation of your manuscript or snapshot. A recommender is very similar to a journal editor (responsible for finding reviewers, collecting reviews, and making editorial decisions based on reviews), and may eventually recommend your report after one or several rounds of reviews.</p>\n<p>Your submission will now undergo preliminary evaluation by the Managing Board. We will contact you soon with further news.</p>\n<p>Thank you again for your submission,</p>\n<p>The Managing Board of {{appName}}</p>
275	#ReminderSubmitterSuggestedRecommenderNeededStage1ScheduledSubmission	default	{{appName}}: Please, suggest some recommenders for handling your preprint - scheduled submission	Mail to submitter if they have not suggested any recommender (for scheduled submission)	<p>Dear {{destPerson}},<br><br>Thanks a lot for submitting your preprint to {{appName}}. Before we validate this submission, could you suggest 5 to 10 recommenders:<br><br>1) Go to <a href="{{siteUrl}}">{{siteUrl}}</a> and log in<br>2) Go to 'FOR CONTRIBUTORS —&gt; YOUR SUBMITTED PREPRINTS' in the top menu.<br>3) Click on the black 'ADD/REMOVE' button in the middle of the line referring to the preprint in question and add or remove suggested recommenders.<br>4) Click on the green 'COMPLETE YOUR SUBMISSION' button when you have finished.<br><br>We remind you that you must not suggest recommender who might be in conflict of interests - see the PCI code of ethical conduct: {{ethicsLink}}.<br><br>If you need any help for suggesting recommenders or/and for using the {{appName}}&nbsp;website, let us know.<br><br>Best regards</p>\r\n<p>The Managing Board of {{appName}}</p>
276	#ReminderSubmitterNewSuggestedRecommenderNeededStage1ScheduledSubmission	default	{{appName}}: Please suggest additional recommenders - scheduled submission	Mail to submitter suggest more recommenders bc no one has agreed yet and it has been 10 days (for scheduled submission)	<p>Dear {{destPerson}},</p>\n<p><br>Thank you again for submitting your report to {{appName}}. Despite follow up invitations, none of the suggested recommenders have decided to handle the evaluation of your report. We encourage you to suggest additionnal recommenders as follows:<br><br>1) Go to <a href="{{siteUrl}}">{{siteUrl}}</a>&nbsp;and log in<br>2) Go to 'FOR CONTRIBUTORS —&gt; YOUR SUBMITTED REPORTS' in the top menu.<br>3) Click on the black 'ADD/REMOVE' button in the middle of the line referring to the report in question and add or remove suggested recommenders.<br>4) Click on the green 'COMPLETE YOUR SUBMISSION' button when you are finished.<br><br>Thanks in advance<br>All the best</p>\n<p>The managing board of {{appName}}</p>
277	#ManagersArticleConsideredForRecommendationStage1ScheduledSubmission	default	{{appName}}: Stage 1 submission considered for recommendation - scheduled submission	Mail to MB to indicate that a recommender agreed to handle a Stage 1 submission (for scheduled submission)	<p>Dear members of the Managing Board,</p>\n<p>A new recommendation is under consideration by {{recommenderPerson}} for {{appName}}.</p>\n<p>To manage this recommendation, please follow this link <a href="{{linkTarget}}">{{linkTarget}}</a>.</p>\n<p>Have a nice day!</p>
278	#ReminderRecommenderReviewersNeededStage1ScheduledSubmission	default	{{appName}}: Please, send invitations to review the Stage 1 submission you are handling - scheduled track	Mail to recommender to remind him/her to handle a Stage 1 scheduled submission	<div>Dear {{destPerson}},</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>Thanks again for serving as the recommender for the Stage 1 snapshot entitled <strong>{{articleTitle}}</strong> by {{articleAuthors}} (DOI <a href="{{snapshotUrl}}">{{snapshotUrl}}</a>). We greatly appreciate your contribution.</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>As a reminder, Stage 1 snapshots are one-page templates submitted by authors in advance of preparing and submitting a complete Stage 1 manuscript. If the snapshot passes an internal evaluation by PCI RR, the review process for the upcoming full Stage 1 manuscript is scheduled for a short range of dates in the future, with the aim to<a href="https://rr.peercommunityin.org/help/guide_for_reviewers#h_61998243643551613309672490"> streamline and accelerate the review process</a>. In this case, the authors have indicated that they would be ready to submit their full Stage 1 manuscript on {{scheduledSubmissionDate}}, and if suitable for if in-depth review, reviewers would be scheduled in advance to assess a full submission during a period of <strong>5 working days</strong> between {{scheduledSubmissionLatestReviewStartDate}} and {{scheduledReviewDueDate}} .</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>Importantly, reviewers use the snapshot to decide if they are willing and able to evaluate a full Stage 1 manuscript during the proposed future dates.<strong> Reviewers do NOT a provide an evaluation of the snapshot itself. </strong></div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>Please now perform the following actions:</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div><span style="font-weight: 400;">1. <strong>Decide within 7 days if the snapshot sufficiently meets the <a href="https://rr.peercommunityin.org/help/guide_for_recommenders#h_6759646236401613643390905" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Stage 1 review criteria</a> to merit further consideration</strong>. This can sometimes be challenging to judge given the brevity of a one-page snapshot, but you should especially assess criteria 1A (scientific validity of the research question), 1B (logic, rationale, and plausibility of any proposed hypotheses), 1C (soundness and feasibility of the proposed methodology), and 1E (appropriate steps in place to ensure data quality). Stage 1 criterion 1D (degree of methodological detail) is generally not possible to assess in a snapshot and, for the purposes of your initial evaluation, can be put aside. If the snapshot is sufficiently promising then you can invite reviewers to evaluate a future full Stage 1 manuscript<strong>, </strong>but if the snapshot falls short then you should either invite authors to revise the snapshot or reject it outright. <strong>Please do not accept the recommender assignment if you cannot perform this triage evaluation within the next 7 days.</strong><br></span></div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>2. If you judge the submission to be suitable for in-depth review <span style="font-weight: 400;"><strong>then please </strong></span><strong>send invitations to </strong><strong>5-10 potential reviewers within 24 hours</strong><span style="font-weight: 400;"> and then send new invitations until you find at least two (and ideally three) reviewers willing to review a full Stage 1 manuscript based on the snapshot between {{scheduledSubmissionLatestReviewStartDate}} and {{scheduledReviewDueDate}}. The review invitation letters will be automatically populated with these dates.</span></div>\r\n<div>\r\n<p>To invite a reviewer:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Go to <a href="{{siteUrl}}">{{siteUrl}}</a> and log in</li>\r\n<li>Go to 'FOR RECOMMENDERS —&gt; REPORT(S) YOU ARE HANDLING' in the top menu.</li>\r\n<li>Click on the black 'INVITE A REVIEWER' button in the line corresponding to the preprint considered.</li>\r\n<li>To invite a reviewer not included in the database of {{appName}}: click on the black ‘CHOOSE A REVIEWER OUTSIDE {{appName}} DATABASE’ button and complete the form (first name, last name and e-mail address of the reviewer). You can change the subject and/or the message if you wish. Then, click on the blue 'SEND E-MAIL' button at the end of the form.</li>\r\n<li>To invite a reviewer from the {{appName}} database: click on the green ‘CHOOSE A REVIEWER FROM {{appName}} DATABASE’ button. A search engine and a filter based on thematic fields may be used. Select a reviewer by clicking on the black ‘ADD’ button at the right end of the corresponding line. You can modify the subject and/or the message of the e-mail before sending it. Then, click on the blue 'SEND E-MAIL' button at the end of the form.</li>\r\n<li>When you have sent invitations to all your chosen reviewers, click on the blue 'DONE 'button.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>3. <strong>Write the recommendation text</strong> if you decide to recommend this report for {{appName}} at the end of the in-depth review process. If after one or more rounds of review, you decide to recommend this report for Stage 1 in-principle acceptance, you will need to write a “<a href="https://rr.peercommunityin.org/help/guide_for_recommenders#h_68746834114021613643858842" target="_blank" rel="noopener">recommendation</a>” that will have its own DOI and be published by {{appName}} under a CC-BY 4.0 license. The recommendation is a short summary (of a few hundred words or less), similar to a News &amp; Views piece, describing the context of the study and explaining why the article was accepted and is expected to make a valuable contribution. The limitations of the report can also be discussed. This text also contains references (citing, at least, the report being recommended). All the editorial correspondence (reviews, your decisions, authors’ replies) will also be published by {{appName}}, either at the point of in-principle acceptance or (if the authors) prefer following later Stage 2 acceptance.</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>4. If a full Stage 1 manuscript is eventually submitted and reviewed, then you agree to <strong>post your decision</strong> or write your recommendation text <strong>within 7 days</strong> of receiving the reviews.</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>If you need assistance in any way do not hesitate to ask us. Thank you again for handling this evaluation.</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>Yours sincerely,</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>The Managing Board of {{appName}}</div>
279	#RecommenderArticleStatusChangedStage1ScheduledSubmission	default	{{appName}}: Change in article status - scheduled submission	Mail to recommender to indicate the change of the status of the preprint (for scheduled submission)	<p>Dear {{destPerson}},</p>\n<p>You have initiated the evaluation of the article entitled <strong>{{articleTitle}}</strong> by {{articleAuthors}} (DOI <a href="{{articleDoi}}">{{articleDoi}}</a>).</p>\n<p>The status of this article has changed from "{{tOldStatus}}" to "{{tNewStatus}}".</p>\n<p>You can view and manage your evaluation process by following this link: <a href="{{linkTarget}}">{{linkTarget}}</a> or by logging onto the {{appName}} website and going to 'For recommenders —&gt; Preprints you are handling' in the top menu.</p>\n<p>We thank you for managing this evaluation.</p>\n<p>Yours sincerely,</p>\n<p>The Managing Board of {{appName}}</p>
280	#RecommenderPreprintSubmittedScheduledSubmission	default	{{appName}} : The author has now submitted a full Stage 1 manuscript for scheduled review	Mail to recommender to thank them for agreeing to handle a full Stage 1 submission for scheduled review	<div>Dear {{destPerson}},</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>You have agreed to be the recommender handling the Stage 1 manuscript entitled <strong>{{articleTitle}}</strong> by {{articleAuthors}} (DOI <a href="{{articleDoi}}">{{articleDoi}}</a>). This submission is a full Stage 1 manuscript for scheduled review following submission of a Stage 1 snapshot (which can viewed at <a href="{{snapshotUrl}}">{{snapshotUrl}}</a>) and the review process has been scheduled to take place between {{scheduledSubmissionLatestReviewStartDate}} and {{scheduledReviewDueDate}}. Thank you very much for your assistance.</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div><span style="font-weight: 400;"><strong>If you judge the submission to be <a href="https://rr.peercommunityin.org/help/guide_for_recommenders#h_1245019342271613643227798">review-ready</a> then please invite the previously agreed reviewers</strong> to assess the full submission as soon as possible. You can do this using the manuscript handling system by logging on on to the {{appName}} website and going to 'For recommenders —&gt; Report(s) you are handling' in the top menu. Then navigate to the submission and click the "Validate" button. When you are ready, then click 'Open submission to reviewers' button to release the submission to the reviewers. If the manuscript is review-ready prior to the start of the scheduled review period then it is fine to release it to the reviewers early as it will give the reviewers even more time to complete their review.<br></span></div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div><span style="font-weight: 400;">If you judge that the full Stage 1 manuscript fails to sufficiently meet the <a href="https://rr.peercommunityin.org/help/guide_for_recommenders#h_6759646236401613643390905">Stage 1 criteria</a> in order to be sent for in-depth review, or differs substantially from the proposal decribed in the snapshot, then</span> you can <strong>desk reject the manuscript without review </strong>or<strong> invite a revision</strong> prior to in-depth review (using the corresponding buttons provided). Please perform this pre-review assessment as quickly as possible (and ideally within the next 24 hours) so that if revisions are required, the authors have time to make them before {{scheduledSubmissionLatestReviewStartDate}}. If you reject the manuscript without review then the scheduled reviews will be automatically and irrevocably cancelled.</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>Please perform this pre-review assessment as quickly as possible so that if revisions are required, the authors have time to make them before<strong> {{scheduledSubmissionLatestReviewStartDate}}.</strong></div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>Should the manuscript proceed to in-depth review, the reviews you eventually receive should guide your decision as to whether to ‘Revise’, ‘Recommend’ or ‘Reject’ the preprint.</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>If your decision is eventually to ‘Recommend’ this preprint, you will need to write a “<a href="https://rr.peercommunityin.org/help/guide_for_recommenders#h_68746834114021613643858842" target="_blank" rel="noopener">recommendation</a>” that will have its own DOI and be published by {{appName}} under the license CC-BY 4.0. The recommendation is a short summary (of a few hundred words or less), similar to a News &amp; Views piece, describing the context of the study and explaining why the article was accepted and is expected to make a valuable contribution. The limitations of the report can also be discussed. This text also contains references (citing, at least, the report being recommended). All the editorial correspondence (reviews, your decisions, authors’ replies) will also be published by {{appName}}.</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>Many thanks for handling this evaluation.</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>Yours sincerely,</div>\r\n<div>The Managing Board of {{appName}}</div>
281	#ReviewersArticleCancellationStage1ScheduledSubmission	default	{{appName}}: Cancellation of our request to act as reviewer for a scheduled Stage 1 Registered Report	Mail to reviewers to indicate that them that the submitter cancelled his/her submission (for scheduled submission)	<p>Dear {{destPerson}},</p>\r\n<p>Thank for you previously agreeing to serve as a reviewer for Peer Community in Registered Reports.</p>\r\n<p>We are writing to let you know that the scheduled submission of the Stage 1 manuscript provisionally entitled <strong>"{{articleTitle}}"</strong> by {{articleAuthors}} has been cancelled by the authors. Therefore, the recommendation process is closed and your review is no longer required.</p>\r\n<div>When authors cancel a scheduled submission they are no longer permitted to submit the same Stage 1 snapshot again, but they may choose to submit a completed Stage 1 manuscript in due course. Under these circumstances, it is possible that the recommender who handles such a submission may invite you again to participate as a reviewer. You are of course free to accept or decline as a completely fresh review invitation, and your previous agreement to provide a scheduled review puts you under no obligation to accept.</div>\r\n<p>Many thanks for supporting Peer Community in Registered Reports.</p>\r\n<p>Yours sincerely,</p>\r\n<p><span style="padding-left: 1in;">The Managing Board on behalf of {{recommenderPerson}}</span></p>
282	#RecommenderReviewConsideredStage1ScheduledSubmission	default	{{appName}}: Request to review accepted - scheduled submission	Mail to recommender to indicate him/her that a reviewer agreed to review a Stage 1 manuscript he/she is handling (for scheduled submission)	<p>Dear {{destPerson}},</p>\r\n<p>{{reviewerPerson}} has accepted your invitation to undertake a scheduled review of a Stage 1 Registered Report, provisionally entitled <strong>{{articleTitle}}</strong> by {{articleAuthors}} (<a href="{{articleDoi}}">{{articleDoi}}</a>).</p>\r\n<p>The full Stage 1 manuscript is due to be submitted no later than <strong>{{scheduledSubmissionDate}}</strong>.</p>\r\n<p>The window for in-depth review opens on <strong>{{scheduledSubmissionLatestReviewStartDate}}</strong> and the review will be due on <strong>{{scheduledReviewDueDate}}</strong>.</p>\r\n<p>You will receive a message notifying you of the posting of this review. If the review is not posted by the deadline, you can send the reviewer a reminder by following this link <a href="{{linkTarget}}">{{linkTarget}}</a> or by logging on to the {{appName}} website and going to 'For recommenders —&gt; Preprint(s) you are handling' in the top menu.</p>\r\n<p>We thank you again for managing this evaluation.</p>\r\n<p>Yours sincerely,</p>\r\n<p>The Managing Board of {{appName}}</p>
283	#SubmitterCancelledSubmissionStage1ScheduledSubmission	default	{{appName}}: Cancellation of your scheduled Stage 1 Registered Report	Mail to submitter to acknowledge the cancellation of his/her Stage 1 manuscript (for scheduled submission)	<p>Dear {{destPerson}},</p>\r\n<p>The submission of your scheduled Stage 1 Registered Report, provisionally entitled <strong>"{{articleTitle}}"</strong> has been cancelled at your request. Any reviews that had been scheduled have also been cancelled.</p>\r\n<div>As noted in&nbsp;<a href="https://rr.peercommunityin.org/help/faq#h_69374630111911617352331293">our policy</a>, the same Stage 1 snapshot cannot be resubmitted again via the scheduled track, but you are welcome to submit a completed Stage 1 manuscript to us in due course. This would be handled as a fresh submission would likely be evaluated by a different recommender and set of reviewers.</div>\r\n<p>Yours sincerely,</p>\r\n<p>The Managing Board of {{appName}}</p>
284	#RecommenderSuggestedArticleStage1ScheduledSubmission	default	{{appName}}: Request to act as a recommender for a Stage 1 snapshot	Mail to suggested recommenders to ask them to act as recommender of a submitted Stage 1 snapshot	<div>Dear {{destPerson}},</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>You have been suggested as a recommender for a Stage 1 snapshot entitled <strong>{{articleTitle}}</strong> by {{articleAuthors}} (DOI <a href="{{snapshotUrl}}">{{snapshotUrl}}</a>). You can obtain information about this request and accept or decline the invitation by following this link <a href="{{linkTarget}}">{{linkTarget}}</a> or by logging in to the {{appName}} website and going to 'For recommenders —&gt; Request(s) to handle a report' in the top menu.</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>Stage 1 snapshots are one-page templates submitted by authors in advance of preparing and submitting a complete Stage 1 manuscript. If the snapshot passes an internal evaluation by PCI RR, the review process for the upcoming full Stage 1 manuscript is scheduled for a short range of dates in the future, with the aim to<a href="https://rr.peercommunityin.org/help/guide_for_reviewers#h_61998243643551613309672490"> streamline and accelerate the review process</a>. In this case, the authors have indicated that they would be ready to submit their full Stage 1 manuscript on {{scheduledSubmissionDate}}, and if suitable for if in-depth review, reviewers would be scheduled in advance to assess a full submission during a period of <strong>5 working days</strong> between {{scheduledSubmissionLatestReviewStartDate}} and {{scheduledReviewDueDate}}.</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>Importantly, reviewers use the snapshot to decide if they are willing and able to evaluate a full Stage 1 manuscript during the proposed future dates.<strong> Reviewers do NOT a provide an evaluation of the snapshot itself. </strong></div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div><strong>Important information before accepting the invitation to be the recommender:</strong> The role of a recommender is very similar to that of a journal editor (finding reviewers, collecting reviews, taking editorial decisions based on reviews), and may lead to the recommendation of the report after several rounds of reviews. The evaluation forms the basis of the decision to ‘Revise’, ‘Recommend’ or ‘Reject’ the report. A full Stage 1 manuscript recommended by {{appName}} is an article that may be used and cited like the ‘traditional’ articles published in peer-reviewed journals. Please see the <a href="https://rr.peercommunityin.org/help/guide_for_recommenders" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Guidelines for recommenders</a> for detailed information.</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>Agreeing to become the recommender for this report means that <strong>you agree to consider this submission for in-depth review</strong> and that in due course you agree to perform a triage evaluation of the full Stage 1 manuscript between the scheduled submission date of {{scheduledSubmissionDate}} and the scheduled start of in-depth review on {{scheduledSubmissionLatestReviewStartDate}}. <strong>Please do not accept the assignment unless you know you will be available between these two dates.</strong></div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>After accepting this assignment you will be asked to perform the following tasks:</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div><span style="font-weight: 400;">1. <strong>Decide within 7 days if the snapshot sufficiently meets the <a href="https://rr.peercommunityin.org/help/guide_for_recommenders#h_6759646236401613643390905" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Stage 1 review criteria</a> to merit further consideration</strong>. This can sometimes be challenging to judge given the brevity of a one-page snapshot, but you should especially assess criteria 1A (scientific validity of the research question), 1B (logic, rationale, and plausibility of any proposed hypotheses), 1C (soundness and feasibility of the proposed methodology), and 1E (appropriate steps in place to ensure data quality). Stage 1 criterion 1D (degree of methodological detail) is generally not possible to assess in a snapshot and, for the purposes of your initial evaluation, can be put aside. If the snapshot is sufficiently promising then you can invite reviewers to evaluate a future full Stage 1 manuscript<strong>, </strong>but if the snapshot falls short then you should either invite authors to revise the snapshot or reject it outright. <strong>Please do not accept the recommender assignment if you cannot perform this triage evaluation within the next 7 days.</strong><br></span></div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>2. If you judge the submission to be suitable for in-depth review <span style="font-weight: 400;"><strong>then please </strong></span><strong>send invitations to </strong><strong>5-10 potential reviewers within 24 hours</strong><span style="font-weight: 400;"> and then send new invitations until you find at least two (and ideally three) reviewers willing to review a full Stage 1 manuscript based on the snapshot between {{scheduledSubmissionLatestReviewStartDate}} and {{scheduledReviewDueDate}}. The review invitation letters will be automatically populated with these dates.</span></div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>3. <strong>Write the recommendation text</strong> if you decide to recommend this report for {{appName}} at the end of the in-depth review process. If after one or more rounds of review, you decide to recommend this report for Stage 1 in-principle acceptance, you will need to write a “<a href="https://rr.peercommunityin.org/help/guide_for_recommenders#h_68746834114021613643858842" target="_blank" rel="noopener">recommendation</a>” that will have its own DOI and be published by {{appName}} under a CC-BY 4.0 license. The recommendation is a short summary (of a few hundred words or less), similar to a News &amp; Views piece, describing the context of the study and explaining why the article was accepted and is expected to make a valuable contribution. The limitations of the report can also be discussed. This text also contains references (citing, at least, the report being recommended). All the editorial correspondence (reviews, your decisions, authors’ replies) will also be published by {{appName}}, either at the point of in-principle acceptance or (if the authors) prefer following later Stage 2 acceptance.</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>4. If a full Stage 1 manuscript is eventually submitted and reviewed, then you agree to <strong>post your decision</strong> or write your recommendation text <strong>within 7 days</strong> of receiving the reviews.</div>\r\n<div><br>5. <strong>Declare that you have no conflict of interest with the authors or the content of the article.</strong> You <span style="font-weight: 400;">should not handle reports written by close colleagues, including people belonging to the same laboratory/unit/department in the last four years, people with whom you have published in the last four years, with whom you have received joint funding in the last four years, or with whom you are currently writing a manuscript or submitting a grant proposal.</span><a href="https://rr.peercommunityin.org/about/ethics"><span style="font-weight: 400;"> </span></a></div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>Thank you very much for your assistance.</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>Yours sincerely,</div>\r\n<div>The Managing Board of {{appName}}</div>
285	#ManagersArticleStatusChangedStage1ScheduledSubmission	default	{{appName}}: Article status changed - scheduled submission	Mail to MB to indicate the change of a status of the preprint  (for scheduled submission)	<p>Dear members of the Managing Board,</p>\n<p>The status of the article entitled "{{articleTitle}}" changed from "{{tOldStatus}}" to "{{tNewStatus}}".</p>\n<p>To manage this recommendation, please follow this link <a href="{{linkTarget}}">{{linkTarget}}</a>.</p>\n<p>Have a nice day!</p>
286	#AdminTwoReviewersInStage1ScheduledSubmission	default	{{appName}}: {{recommenderPerson}} found two reviewers - scheduled submission	Mail to admnistrators to indicate that 2 reviewers agreed to review the preprint (for scheduled submission)	<p>Dear Administrators of {{appName}},</p>\r\n<p>A second reviewer agreed to review the preprint "{{articleTitle}}" by {{articleAuthors}}. Other invitations to referee might be in progress but {{recommenderPerson}} could make their editorial decision based on these two reviews.</p>\r\n<p>To manage this recommendation, please follow this link <a href="{{linkTarget}}">{{linkTarget}}</a>.</p>\r\n<p>Have a nice day!</p>
287	#ReminderSuggestedRecommenderInvitationStage1ScheduledSubmission	default	{{appName}}: Request to act as a recommender for a report - reminder - scheduled submission	Mail to suggested recommenders to remind them to act as recommender of a submitted report (for scheduled submission)	<p>Dear {{destPerson}},</p>\r\n<p>A few days ago, you were suggested as a recommender for a Stage 1 snapshot entitled <strong>{{articleTitle}}</strong> by {{articleAuthors}} (DOI <a href="{{snapshotUrl}}">{{snapshotUrl}}</a>). You can obtain information about this request and accept or decline the invitation by following this link <a href="{{linkTarget}}">{{linkTarget}}</a> or by logging in to the {{appName}} website and going to 'For recommenders —&gt; Request(s) to handle a report' in the top menu.</p>\r\n<p>Stage 1 snapshots are one-page templates submitted by authors in advance of preparing and submitting a complete Stage 1 manuscript. If the snapshot passes an internal evaluation by PCI RR, the review process for the upcoming full manuscript is scheduled for a short range of dates in the future, with the aim to<a href="https://rr.peercommunityin.org/help/guide_for_reviewers#h_61998243643551613309672490"> streamline and accelerate the review process</a>. In this case, the authors have indicated that they would be ready to submit their full Stage 1 manuscript on {{scheduledSubmissionDate}}, and if suitable for if in-depth review, reviewers would be scheduled in advance to assess a full submission during a period of <strong>5 working days</strong> between {{scheduledSubmissionLatestReviewStartDate}} and {{scheduledReviewDueDate}} .</p>\r\n<p>Importantly, reviewers use the snapshot to decide if they are willing and able to evaluate a full manuscript during the proposed future dates.<strong> Reviewers do NOT a provide an evaluation of the snapshot itself. </strong></p>\r\n<p><strong>Important information before accepting the invitation to be the recommender:</strong> The role of a recommender is very similar to that of a journal editor (finding reviewers, collecting reviews, taking editorial decisions based on reviews), and may lead to the recommendation of the report after several rounds of reviews. The evaluation forms the basis of the decision to ‘Revise’, ‘Recommend’ or ‘Reject’ the report. A full manuscript recommended by {{appName}} is an article that may be used and cited like the ‘traditional’ articles published in peer-reviewed journals. Please see the <a href="https://rr.peercommunityin.org/help/guide_for_recommenders" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Guidelines for recommenders</a> for detailed information.</p>\r\n<p>Agreeing to become the recommender for this report means that <strong>you agree to consider this submission for in-depth review</strong>.<strong> Y</strong><strong>ou will then be asked to perform the following tasks: </strong></p>\r\n<div><span style="font-weight: 400;">1. <strong>Decide within 7 days if the snapshot sufficiently meets the <a href="https://rr.peercommunityin.org/help/guide_for_recommenders#h_6759646236401613643390905" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Stage 1 review criteria</a> to merit further consideration</strong>. This can sometimes be challenging to judge given the brevity of a one-page snapshot, but you should especially assess criteria 1A (scientific validity of the research question), 1B (logic, rationale, and plausibility of any proposed hypotheses), 1C (soundness and feasibility of the proposed methodology), and 1E (appropriate steps in place to ensure data quality). Stage 1 criterion 1D (degree of methodological detail) is generally not possible to assess in a snapshot and, for the purposes of your initial evaluation, can be put aside. If the snapshot is sufficiently promising then you can invite reviewers to evaluate a future full manuscript<strong>, </strong>but if the snapshot falls short then you should either invite authors to revise the snapshot or reject it outright. <strong>Please do not accept the recommender assignment if you cannot perform this triage evaluation within the next 7 days.</strong><br></span></div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>2. If you judge the submission to be suitable for in-depth review <span style="font-weight: 400;"><strong>then please </strong></span><strong>send invitations to </strong><strong>5-10 potential reviewers within 24 hours</strong><span style="font-weight: 400;"> and then send new invitations until you find at least two (and ideally three) reviewers willing to review a full Stage 1 manuscript based on the snapshot between {{scheduledSubmissionLatestReviewStartDate}} and {{scheduledReviewDueDate}}. The review invitation letters will be automatically populated with these dates.</span></div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>3. <strong>Write the recommendation text</strong> if you decide to recommend this report for {{appName}} at the end of the in-depth review process. If after one or more rounds of review, you decide to recommend this report for Stage 1 in-principle acceptance, you will need to write a “<a href="https://rr.peercommunityin.org/help/guide_for_recommenders#h_68746834114021613643858842" target="_blank" rel="noopener">recommendation</a>” that will have its own DOI and be published by {{appName}} under a CC-BY 4.0 license. The recommendation is a short summary (of a few hundred words or less), similar to a News &amp; Views piece, describing the context of the study and explaining why the article was accepted and is expected to make a valuable contribution. The limitations of the report can also be discussed. This text also contains references (citing, at least, the report being recommended). All the editorial correspondence (reviews, your decisions, authors’ replies) will also be published by {{appName}}, either at the point of in-principle acceptance or (if the authors) prefer following later Stage 2 acceptance.</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>4. If a full manuscript is eventually submitted and reviewed, then you agree to <strong>post your decision</strong> or write your recommendation text <strong>within 7 days</strong> of receiving the reviews.</div>\r\n<div><br>5. <strong>Declare that you have no conflict of interest with the authors or the content of the article.</strong> You <span style="font-weight: 400;">should not handle reports written by close colleagues, including people belonging to the same laboratory/unit/department in the last four years, people with whom you have published in the last four years, with whom you have received joint funding in the last four years, or with whom you are currently writing a manuscript or submitting a grant proposal.</span></div>\r\n<p>Thanks again for your help.</p>\r\n<p>Yours sincerely,</p>\r\n<p>The Managing Board of {{appName}}</p>
288	#RecommenderSuggestionNotNeededAnymoreStage1ScheduledSubmission	default	{{appName}}: About our request to act as a recommender for a Stage 1 scheduled submission	Mail to suggested recommenders to indicate that another recommender took the preprint in charge (for scheduled submission)	<p>Dear {{destPerson}},</p>\r\n<p>Your help as a recommender is not needed anymore for this submission.</p>\r\n<p>You had been suggested as a recommender for a Stage 1 submission entitled <strong>{{articleTitle}}</strong> by {{articleAuthors}} (DOI <a href="{{articleDoi}}">{{articleDoi}}</a>). This submission has now been handled by another {{appName}} recommender. Consequently, it will no longer appear in your list of requests to act as a recommender on the {{appName}} webpage.</p>\r\n<p>If you would still like to participate in the evaluation of this preprint, please send us an e-mail at {{appContactLink}}. We will inform the recommender handling the evaluation process of your willingness to participate and they may then contact you.</p>\r\n<p>Thank you for your support.</p>\r\n<p>Yours sincerely,</p>\r\n<p>The Managing Board of {{appName}}</p>
289	#ManagersPreprintSubmissionStage1ScheduledSubmission	default	{{appName}}: Stage 1 submission requiring validation - scheduled submission	Mail to MB to indicate a Stage 1 submission (for scheduled submission)	<p>Dear members of the Managing Board,</p>\r\n<p>{{appName}} has received a Stage 1 submission by {{submitterPerson}}.</p>\r\n<p>To validate or delete this submission, please follow this link <a href="{{linkTarget}}">{{linkTarget}}</a> and use the following instructions.</p>\r\n<h3><span style="font-weight: 400;">Does the submission need changes to be submission-ready? Send it to the pre-submission stage</span></h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><span style="font-weight: 400;">An article in the </span><em><span style="font-weight: 400;">For managers &gt; Pending validations</span></em><span style="font-weight: 400;"> needs changes before it will be ready to be validated. Any articles in the Pending validations section can be sent to the pre-submission stage by clicking View/Edit, scroll to bottom, click the black button: </span><em><span style="font-weight: 400;">Put in pre-submission list</span></em><span style="font-weight: 400;">.</span></li>\r\n<li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Then go to: </span><em><span style="font-weight: 400;">For managers &gt; X Articles in the pre-submission stage</span></em><span style="font-weight: 400;">. Find the article here &gt; click View/Edit &gt; edit the email template to the authors to request further changes so it is ready to be validated and click Send.&nbsp;</span></li>\r\n<li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><span style="font-weight: 400;">When the authors make a change, the submission automatically goes back to the </span><em><span style="font-weight: 400;">Pending validations</span></em><span style="font-weight: 400;"> section.&nbsp;</span></li>\r\n<li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><span style="font-weight: 400;">You can do this loop as many times as you want with an article</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3><span style="font-weight: 400;">First submission: RR snapshot</span></h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Read the cover letter and snapshot, make sure they followed the snapshot instructions</span></li>\r\n<li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Check that the submission checklist is complete</span></li>\r\n<li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Check that the link to the manuscript point directly to the snapshot</span></li>\r\n<li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Check that it is a scientifically valid topic</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>Have a nice day!</p>
290	#RecommenderReviewDeclinedStage1ScheduledSubmission	default	{{appName}}: Request to review declined - scheduled submission	Mail to recommender to indicate him/her that a reviewer decline to review a preprint he/she is handling (for scheduled submission)	<p>Dear {{destPerson}},</p>\n<p>{{reviewerPerson}} has declined your invitation to review the preprint entitled <strong>{{articleTitle}}</strong> by {{articleAuthors}} (DOI<a href="{{articleDoi}}"> {{articleDoi}}</a>).</p>\n<p>You will need to find another reviewer to obtain the two high-quality reviews required. You can invite additional reviewers by following this link <a href="{{linkTarget}}">{{linkTarget}}</a> or by logging onto the {{appName}} website and going to 'For recommenders —&gt; Preprint(s) you are handling' in the top menu.</p>\n<p>We thank you again for managing this evaluation.</p>\n<p>Yours sincerely,</p>\n<p>The Managing Board of {{appName}}</p>
291	#DefaultReviewCancellationStage1ScheduledSubmission	default	{{appName}}: Cancellation of a review request - scheduled submission	Mail to reviewer to indicate cancellation of a Stage 1 review invitation (for scheduled submission)	<p>Dear {{destPerson}},</p>\r\n<div>We recently invited you to review a Stage 1 Registered Report entitled "{{articleTitle}}".&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>I am writing to let you know that we have now found sufficient reviewers for this submission and your evaluation is no longer requested. Many thanks for your consideration.</div>\r\n<p>Best regards,</p>\r\n<p>{{sender}}</p>
292	#ManagersRecommendationOrDecisionStage1ScheduledSubmission	default	{{appName}}: Decision or recommendation requiring validation - scheduled submission	Mail to MB to indicate that a decision or a recommendation has been posted by a recommender (for scheduled submission)	<p>Dear members of the Managing Board,</p>\n<p>A decision or a recommendation has been written by {{recommenderPerson}} for {{appName}}.</p>\n<p>To validate and/or manage this recommendation or decision, please follow this link <a href="{{linkTarget}}">{{linkTarget}}</a>.</p>\n<p>Have a nice day!</p>
293	#SubmitterAwaitingSubmissionStage1ScheduledSubmission	default	{{appName}}: Decision concerning your submission - scheduled submission	Mail to submitter to indicate the need to revise his/her preprint (for scheduled submission)	<p>Dear {{destPerson}},</p>\r\n<p>Thank you for submitting your Stage 1 Registered Report entitled <strong>{{articleTitle}} </strong>to {{appName}}. Your manuscript has now been reviewed, and the reviewers' comments and the recommender’s decision may be found below.</p>\r\n<p>On the basis of these comments, we cannot accept your manuscript in its present form but would like to invite you to revise your article, taking into account the issues raised by the reviewers. Please note that in-principle acceptance (IPA) and progression to Stage 2 is not guaranteed and any revision may be sent back to the reviewers for further evaluation. You should, therefore, include a point-by-point response to the reviewers' comments, outlining each change made in your manuscript or providing a suitable rebuttal.</p>\r\n<p>When your revised article is ready, please:</p>\r\n<p>1) Upload the new version of your manuscript onto your preferred open archive;</p>\r\n<p>2) Follow this link <a href="{{linkTarget}}">{{linkTarget}}</a> or logging onto the {{appName}} website and go to 'For Contributors -&gt; Your submitted reports' in the top menu;</p>\r\n<p>3) Make your changes to the title, summary, link to the article (or its DOI) and keywords if necessary by clicking on the 'Edit Article' button. If not already done, you also need to upload a picture or an illustration for which you own the rights – this picture will be used to illustrate your article, if recommended;</p>\r\n<p>4) Write, copy/paste or upload (as a PDF file) your reply to the recommender's and reviewers' comments by clicking on the 'Write, edit or upload your reply to recommender' button. You can also upload (as a PDF file) a revised version of your article, with the modifications indicated in TrackChanges;</p>\r\n<p>5) When you are ready to submit your new version, click on the 'Save &amp; submit your reply' button.</p>\r\n<p>As a reminder: if, in the Stage 1 submission checklist, you chose the option to publish the Stage 1 reviews at the point of IPA, then if IPA is awarded the editorial correspondence (reviews, recommender’s decisions, authors’ replies) and a recommendation text will published immediately at the {{appName}} website under a CC-BY license. Alternatively, if you chose to delay the publication of the Stage 1 recommendation and reviews until final Stage 2 acceptance then IPA will be awarded privately. In either case, depending on your checklist selections, the current list of <a href="https://rr.peercommunityin.org/about/pci_rr_interested_journals" target="_blank" rel="noopener">PCI RR-interested journals</a> may then be alerted to the IPA, and we will inform you as to which among the set of <a href="https://rr.peercommunityin.org/about/pci_rr_friendly_journals" target="_blank" rel="noopener">PCI RR-friendly journals</a> is an eligible outlet that automatically offers IPA.</p>\r\n<p>In the event that your revised submission is rejected, the reviews and decision will be sent to you, but they will not be published or publicly released by {{appName}}. They will be safely stored in our database, to which only the Managing Board has access. You will be notified by e-mail at each stage in the procedure.</p>\r\n<p>We look forward to receiving your revised manuscript.</p>\r\n<p>Yours sincerely,</p>\r\n<p>The Managing Board of {{appName}}</p>\r\n<div>{{recommendationProcess}}</div>
294	#DefaultReviewAlreadyAcceptedCancellationStage1ScheduledSubmission	default	{{appName}}: Cancellation of a review request - scheduled submission	Email sent to reviewer to cancel a scheduled review request AFTER the reviewer has already agreed to review	<div>Dear {{destPerson}},</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>We recently invited you to review a Stage 1 Registered Report entitled "<strong>{{articleTitle}}</strong>"</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>Unfortunately, a review-ready Stage 1 manuscript associated with this submission will not be ready in time for the opening of the review window on <span style="font-weight: 400;">{{scheduledSubmissionLatestReviewStartDate}}</span>. I am therefore cancelling the process and your review is no longer requested.</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>Cancellations are unusual but occasionally arise due to personal circumstances, logistical difficulties experienced by authors, or, rarely, because the full Stage 1 manuscript was submitted but judged to fall so far short of meeting the Stage 1 criteria that a revision prior to review was considered infeasible by the recommender and Managing Board.</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>Once a submission is cancelled, authors are no longer permitted to submit the same snapshot again to PCI RR, but they may choose to submit a completed (or new) Stage 1 manuscript in due course. Under such circumstances, it is possible that the recommender who handles the submission may invite you again to participate as a reviewer. You are of course free to accept or decline this as a fresh review invitation.</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>For now, thank you very much for agreeing to be part of this process and I hope this cancellation doesn’t cause any inconvenience.</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>Best wishes,</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>{{sender}}</div>
295	#SubmitterScheduledSubmissionOpen	default	{{appName}}: Your full Stage 1 submission may now be uploaded at any time	Mail to authors to inform them that their full Stage 1 manuscript can now be submitted any time	<p>Dear {{destPerson}}</p>\r\n<p>Thank you for previously submitting a Stage 1 snapshot entitled "<strong>{{articleTitle}}</strong>" to PCI RR. The recommender handling your submission, {{recommenderPerson}}, has scheduled in-depth peer review to take place between {{scheduledSubmissionLatestReviewStartDate}} and {{scheduledReviewDueDate}}.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Even though your full Stage 1 manuscript is not due until {{scheduledSubmissionDate}}, you may upload it anytime between now and the deadline. </strong>Submitting in advance of the submission deadline is unlikely to result in earlier review of your manuscript.</p>\r\n<p>Please note that the full manuscript must be received no later than {{scheduledSubmissionDate}} (11.59pm <a href="https://www.timeanddate.com/time/zones/cet" target="_blank" rel="noopener">CET</a>/<a href="https://www.timeanddate.com/time/zones/cest" target="_blank" rel="noopener">CEST</a>) to enable the recommender and Managing Board to perform a pre-review <a href="https://rr.peercommunityin.org/help/guide_for_recommenders#h_1245019342271613643227798" target="_blank" rel="noopener">triage assessment</a> of your full submission. This evaluation could require you to make revisions to your Stage 1 manuscript prior to the commencement of in-depth review, so to ensure that the manuscript is review-ready by the scheduled review date, please be prepared to respond quickly to any revision invitations from the recommender between {{scheduledSubmissionDate}} and {{scheduledSubmissionLatestReviewStartDate}}. In rare cases where the full submission differs substantially from the research proposed in the snapshot, or falls a long way short of meeting at least one of the <a href="https://rr.peercommunityin.org/help/guide_for_authors#h_6720026472751613309075757" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Stage 1 review criteria</a>, the full submission could also be rejected outright, in which case scheduled in-depth review would be cancelled.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Please note that missing the submission deadline of {{scheduledSubmissionDate}} could result in cancellation of the scheduled review process. </strong>If you can no longer meet this deadline, please contact the Managing Board as soon as possible by replying to this email.<strong><br></strong></p>\r\n<p>Once you have submitted your full manuscript, and the submission has passed internal triage assessment by the Managing Board and recommender, the review process will commence. If you submit ahead of the submission deadline, reviewers may be informed but there is no guarantee that they will review the manuscript until the specified review period is reached.</p>\r\n<p>---</p>\r\n<p>To help avoid the need for revisions prior to review, here are some common difficulties faced by authors in preparing a Stage 1 manuscript:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>The protocol contains insufficient methodological detail to enable replication and prevent researcher degrees of freedom. One commonly neglected area is the criteria for excluding data, both at the level of participants/samples and at the level of data <em>within</em> participants/samples. In the interests of clarity, we recommend listing these criteria systematically rather than presenting them in prose.</li>\r\n<li>For quantitative studies involving hypothesis testing, a lack of correspondence between the scientific hypotheses and the preregistered statistical tests. This is a very common oversight. To maximize clarity of correspondence between predictions and analyses, authors are encouraged to number their hypotheses in the Introduction and then number the proposed analyses in the Methods to make clear which analysis tests which prediction. Ensure also that power analysis, where applicable, is based on the actual test procedures that will be employed to test those hypotheses; e.g. don’t propose a power analysis based on an ANOVA but then suggest a linear mixed effects model to test the hypothesis.&nbsp;</li>\r\n<li>Lack of a completed study design template (as explained&nbsp;<a href="https://rr.peercommunityin.org/help/guide_for_authors#h_27513965735331613309625021">here</a>). Make sure it is as concise as possible (e.g. including formulae for hypotheses) but complete and exhaustive. There are some examples <a href="https://doi.org/10.1371/journal.pcbi.1010571.s002">here</a> alongside the paper ’<a href="https://journals.plos.org/ploscompbiol/article?id=10.1371/journal.pcbi.1010571">ten simple rules for writing a registered report</a>’.</li>\r\n<li>The statistical sampling (such as power analysis) is over-optimistic (e.g. based on previous literature but not taking into account publication bias) or insufficiently justified (e.g. based on a single point estimate from a pilot experiment or previous study). Proposals should be powered to detect the smallest effect that is plausible and of theoretical value. Pilot data can help inform this estimate but is unlikely to form an acceptable basis, alone, for choosing the target effect size. <a href="https://online.ucpress.edu/collabra/article/8/1/33267/120491/Sample-Size-Justification" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Here is an excellent paper</a> on sample size justification.</li>\r\n<li>Intention to infer support for the null hypothesis from statistically non-significant results, without proposing use of Bayes factors or frequentist equivalence&nbsp;testing (see&nbsp;<a href="https://online.ucpress.edu/collabra/article/7/1/28202/118660/Obtaining-Evidence-for-No-Effect">here</a>&nbsp;for a nice explainer).</li>\r\n<li>Inclusion of exploratory analyses in the analysis plan. Manuscripts proposing exploratory analyses will usually be desk rejected until such analyses are removed because inclusion of exploratory “plans” at Stage 1 blurs the line between confirmatory and exploratory outcomes at Stage 2. Instead, such analyses can be included at Stage 2 and need not be preregistered. Under some circumstances, exploratory analyses can be discussed at Stage 1 where they are necessary to justify study variables or procedures that are included in the design exclusively for exploratory analysis. If so, be sure to justify their inclusion in the manuscript.</li>\r\n<li>Failure to distinguish work that has already been done from work that is planned. Where a proposal contains a mixture of pilot work that has already been undertaken and a proposal for work not yet undertaken, authors commonly use the past tense for pilot work but the future tense for the proposed work. At Stage 2, all descriptions shift to past tense.</li>\r\n<li>Lack of pre-specified positive controls or other quality checks, or an appropriate justification for their absence. Positive controls are not&nbsp;possible with all study designs, in which case authors should discuss why they are not included.</li>\r\n<li>Where applicable, lack of power analysis within proposed positive controls that depend on hypothesis testing.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>---</p>\r\n<p>Follow this link to view your submission on the system: <a href="{{linkTarget}}">{{linkTarget}}</a></p>\r\n<p>When the full Stage 1 manuscript is written and ready to submit, please navigate to your submission on the PCI RR website and proceed as follows:</p>\r\n<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">a) Click the button "CHECK / EDIT REPORT SURVEY". This will take you to the submission checklist.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">b) In the submission checklist, change the response for Q3 to “I PREVIOUSLY SUBMITTED A STAGE 1 SNAPSHOT AND THE FULL MANUSCRIPT IS NOW READY FOR REVIEW”. <strong>Please make this change to the checklist first before changing any other answers.</strong><br></span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">c) Next, leave the URL for the snapshot in Q2 unchanged (to keep it preserved in our records) but change the response to Q1 to “COMPLETE STAGE 1 REPORT FOR REGULAR REVIEW”. The URL for the snapshot will then become fixed and uneditable.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">d) Check all other answers in the checklist (adjusting as necessary) then click the "Submit" button at the bottom of the page.<br></span></p>\r\n<p>e) This will close the submission checklist, but you have not completed your submission. Next, enter or update the URL to the <strong>full Stage 1 manuscript</strong> in the box entitled: "Full web address to most recent version of the manuscript". Then enter the version number in the box entitled: "Most recent version of the manuscript at the above".</p>\r\n<p>f) Finally, click the "Submit" button. <strong>You will have then submitted your full Stage 1 manuscript.</strong></p>\r\n<p>If you have any questions please feel free to contact us via reply email.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Sincerely, the PCI RR Managing Board</p>
296	#ReminderSubmitterRevisedVersionWarningStage1ScheduledSubmission	default	{{appName}}: Revised version - reminder - scheduled submission	Mail to submitter to remind them that they received an interim Stage 1 decision (for scheduled submission)	<p>Dear {{destPerson}},</p>\n<p>Thanks again for submitting your Stage 1 Registered Report to {{appName}}.</p>\n<p>By now you should have received the decision of the recommender and the accompanying reviews. We hope you found this feedback useful and constructive. If for any reason you did not receive the decision letter, please let us know as soon as possible.</p>\n<p>There is no particular deadline for submitting your revised manuscript, but we encourage authors to revise manuscripts as promptly as possible to ensure that, in cases where Stage 1 re-review is necessary, the same reviewers will be available.</p>\n<p>We await your revised submission in due course, and please don't hesitate to contact us via email if you have any questions in the meantime.</p>\n<p>Sincerely</p>\n<p>The Managing Board of {{appName}}</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>
297	#ReminderSubmitterRevisedVersionNeededStage1ScheduledSubmission	default	{{appName}}: Revised version? - scheduled submission	Mail to submitter to verify that they received the decision and if they intend to resubmit (for scheduled submission)	<p>Dear {{destPerson}},</p>\n<p>Thanks again for submitting your Stage 1 Registered Report to {{appName}}.</p>\n<p>By now you should have received the decision of the recommender and the accompanying reviews. We hope you found this feedback useful and constructive. If for any reason you did not receive the decision letter, please let us know as soon as possible.</p>\n<p>There is no particular deadline for submitting your revised manuscript, but we encourage authors to revise manuscripts as promptly as possible to ensure that, in cases where Stage 1 re-review is necessary, the same reviewers will be available. If you have decided not revise your manuscript for PCI RR then we would be grateful if you could let us know.</p>\n<p>We await your revised submission in due course, and please don't hesitate to contact us via email if you have any questions.</p>\n<p>All the best,</p>\n<p>The Managing Board of {{appName}}</p>
298	#AdminArticleResubmitedStage1ScheduledSubmission	default	{{appName}}: Article resubmitted - scheduled submission	Mail to MB to indicate that a revised version has been submitted and is under consideration by the recommender (for scheduled submission)	<p>Dear members of the Managing Board,</p>\n<p>A new version of the article entitled "{{articleTitle}}" is under consideration by {{recommenderPerson}} for {{appName}}.</p>\n<p>To manage this recommendation, please follow this link <a href="{{linkTarget}}">{{linkTarget}}</a>.</p>\n<p>Have a nice day!</p>
299	#ReminderRecommenderRevisedDecisionDueStage1ScheduledSubmission	default	{{appName}}: Editorial decision - reminder - scheduled submission	Mail to recommender to indicate a decision due about the revised version (for scheduled submission)	<p>Dear {{destPerson}},</p>\r\n<p>This is an automated reminder for your decision on the revised version of the Stage 1 submission by {{articleAuthors}}. Please decide as soon as possible whether to send this new version for review or to make a decision based on the response from the authors.</p>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>To issue a decision:</div>\r\n<div>\r\n<div dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-position: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">1) Go to <a href="{{siteUrl}}">{{siteUrl}}</a></span><span style="font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-position: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;"> and log in&nbsp;</span></div>\r\n<div dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-position: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">2) Go to '<strong>For Recommenders</strong>'—&gt; '<strong>Reports(s) you are handling</strong>' in the top menu. </span></div>\r\n<div dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-position: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">3) Click the '<strong>View/Edit</strong>' button. </span></div>\r\n<div dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-position: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">4) Click '<strong>Write or edit your decision / recommendation</strong>’. </span></div>\r\n<div dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-position: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">5) Indicate your decision (<strong>revise</strong>, <strong>reject</strong>, <strong>recommend</strong>, <strong>recommend but keep private until Stage 2</strong>).</span></div>\r\n<div dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-position: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">6) Choose a decision or recommendation title (this is of particular importance only for decisions to recommend the preprint concerned) and write or copy/paste your decision or recommendation text.&nbsp;</span></div>\r\n<div dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-position: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">-You can save a draft version of your decision or recommendation text by clicking 'Save' (you will then have to go through steps 1 to 5 to complete your decision or recommendation). </span></div>\r\n<div dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-position: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">7) To send your decision or recommendation to the managing board for validation, click on the green 'Save and submit' button. This will result in your decision or recommendation being sent to the Managing Board for validation.</span></div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div><br>Thank you for handling this submission.</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>The Managing Board of {{appName}}</div>
300	#ReminderRecommenderRevisedDecisionSoonDueStage1ScheduledSubmission	default	{{appName}}: Editorial decision - scheduled submission	Mail to recommender to indicate a decision soon due about the revised version (for scheduled submission)	<p>Dear {{destPerson}},</p>\r\n<div>A few days ago, you should have received the authors' response, a tracked changes version and the link to a revised version of their article on the {{articleTitle}} by {{articleAuthors}}. <br><br></div>\r\n<div>You can reinvite the reviewers for another round of in-depth evaluation or you can issue a decision without further review.</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>To issue a decision:</div>\r\n<div>\r\n<div dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-position: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">1) Go to <a href="{{siteUrl}}">{{siteUrl}}</a></span><span style="font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-position: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;"> and log in&nbsp;</span></div>\r\n<div dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-position: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">2) Go to '<strong>For Recommenders</strong>'—&gt; '<strong>Reports(s) you are handling</strong>' in the top menu. </span></div>\r\n<div dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-position: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">3) Click the '<strong>View/Edit</strong>' button. </span></div>\r\n<div dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-position: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">4) Click '<strong>Write or edit your decision / recommendation</strong>’. </span></div>\r\n<div dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-position: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">5) Indicate your decision (<strong>revise</strong>, <strong>reject</strong>, <strong>recommend</strong>, <strong>recommend but keep private until Stage 2</strong>).</span></div>\r\n<div dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-position: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">6) Choose a decision or recommendation title (this is of particular importance only for decisions to recommend the preprint concerned) and write or copy/paste your decision or recommendation text.&nbsp;</span></div>\r\n<div dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-position: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">-You can save a draft version of your decision or recommendation text by clicking 'Save' (you will then have to go through steps 1 to 5 to complete your decision or recommendation). </span></div>\r\n<div dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-position: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">7) To send your decision or recommendation to the managing board for validation, click on the green 'Save and submit' button. This will result in your decision or recommendation being sent to the Managing Board for validation.</span></div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div><br>Thank you for handling this submission.</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>The Managing Board of {{appName}}</div>
301	#RecommenderThankForPreprintStage1ScheduledSubmission	default	{{appName}}: Thank you for handling the evaluation of this Stage 1 snapshot 	Mail to recommender thanking them for agreeing to handle a Stage 1 snapshot	<p>Dear {{destPerson}},</p>\r\n<p>You have agreed to be the recommender handling the Stage 1 snapshot entitled <strong>{{articleTitle}}</strong> by {{articleAuthors}} (DOI <a href="{{snapshotUrl}}">{{snapshotUrl}}</a>). Thank you very much for your contribution.</p>\r\n<p>As a reminder, Stage 1 snapshots are one-page templates submitted by authors in advance of preparing and submitting a complete Stage 1 manuscript. If the snapshot passes an internal evaluation by PCI RR, the review process for the upcoming full manuscript is scheduled for a short range of dates in the future, with the aim to<a href="https://rr.peercommunityin.org/help/guide_for_reviewers#h_61998243643551613309672490"> streamline and accelerate the review process</a>. In this case, the authors have indicated that they would be ready to submit their full Stage 1 manuscript on {{scheduledSubmissionDate}}, and if suitable for if in-depth review, reviewers would be scheduled in advance to assess a full submission during a period of <strong>5 working days</strong> between {{scheduledSubmissionLatestReviewStartDate}} and {{scheduledReviewDueDate}} .</p>\r\n<p>Importantly, reviewers use the snapshot to decide if they are willing and able to evaluate a full manuscript during the proposed future dates.<strong> Reviewers do NOT a provide an evaluation of the snapshot itself. </strong></p>\r\n<p>Please now perform the following actions:</p>\r\n<div><span style="font-weight: 400;">1. <strong>Decide within 7 days if the snapshot sufficiently meets the <a href="https://rr.peercommunityin.org/help/guide_for_recommenders#h_6759646236401613643390905" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Stage 1 review criteria</a> to merit further consideration</strong>. This can sometimes be challenging to judge given the brevity of a one-page snapshot, but you should especially assess criteria 1A (scientific validity of the research question), 1B (logic, rationale, and plausibility of any proposed hypotheses), 1C (soundness and feasibility of the proposed methodology), and 1E (appropriate steps in place to ensure data quality). Stage 1 criterion 1D (degree of methodological detail) is generally not possible to assess in a snapshot and, for the purposes of your initial evaluation, can be put aside. If the snapshot is sufficiently promising then you can invite reviewers to evaluate a future full manuscript<strong>, </strong>but if the snapshot falls short then you should either invite authors to revise the snapshot or reject it outright. <strong>Please do not accept the recommender assignment if you cannot perform this triage evaluation within the next 7 days.</strong><br></span></div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>2. If you judge the submission to be suitable for in-depth review <span style="font-weight: 400;"><strong>then please </strong></span><strong>send invitations to </strong><strong>5-10 potential reviewers within 24 hours</strong><span style="font-weight: 400;"> and then send new invitations until you find at least two (and ideally three) reviewers willing to review a full Stage 1 manuscript based on the snapshot between {{scheduledSubmissionLatestReviewStartDate}} and {{scheduledReviewDueDate}}. The review invitation letters will be automatically populated with these dates.</span></div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>3. <strong>Write the recommendation text</strong> if you decide to recommend this report for {{appName}} at the end of the in-depth review process. If after one or more rounds of review, you decide to recommend this report for Stage 1 in-principle acceptance, you will need to write a “<a href="https://rr.peercommunityin.org/help/guide_for_recommenders#h_68746834114021613643858842" target="_blank" rel="noopener">recommendation</a>” that will have its own DOI and be published by {{appName}} under a CC-BY 4.0 license. The recommendation is a short summary (of a few hundred words or less), similar to a News &amp; Views piece, describing the context of the study and explaining why the article was accepted and is expected to make a valuable contribution. The limitations of the report can also be discussed. This text also contains references (citing, at least, the report being recommended). All the editorial correspondence (reviews, your decisions, authors’ replies) will also be published by {{appName}}, either at the point of in-principle acceptance or (if the authors) prefer following later Stage 2 acceptance.</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>4. If a full manuscript is eventually submitted and reviewed, then you agree to <strong>post your decision</strong> or write your recommendation text <strong>within 7 days</strong> of receiving the reviews.</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<p>If you need assistance in any way do not hesitate to ask us. Thank you again for handling this evaluation.</p>\r\n<p>Yours sincerely,</p>\r\n<p>The Managing Board of {{appName}}</p>
302	#ReminderScheduledReviewComingSoon	default	{{appName}}: Stage 1 scheduled review period coming soon	Mail to reviewers indicating that full Stage 1 manuscript associating with a submission is due soon	<p>Dear {{destPerson}}</p>\r\n<p>This message is for information only and requires no action at this time.</p>\r\n<p>Previously you agreed to review a full Stage 1 manuscript for PCI Registered Reports based on a Stage 1 snapshot entitled "<strong>{{articleTitle}}</strong>".</p>\r\n<p>The recommender handling the submission, {{recommenderPerson}}, has scheduled in-depth peer review to commence on {{scheduledSubmissionLatestReviewStartDate}} and you kindly agreed to provide a review no later than {{reviewDueDate}}.</p>\r\n<p>Authors are welcome submit the full Stage 1 manuscript earlier than the submission deadline. Once they have submitted, and the submission has passed internal triage assessment by the Managing Board and recommender, the review process can commence. If authors submit ahead of the submission deadline, you will be given the opportunity to prepare your review early but there is no obligation to review the manuscript until the agreed review period is reached.</p>\r\n<p>We will notify you when the full Stage 1 manuscript is ready for in-depth evaluation.</p>\r\n<p>Many thanks, the PCI RR Managing Board</p>
303	#ReminderRecommenderRevisedDecisionOverDueStage1ScheduledSubmission	default	{{appName}}: Editorial decision overdue - scheduled submission	Mail to recommender to indicate an overdue decision about the revised version (for scheduled submission)	<p>Dear {{destPerson}},</p>\r\n<p>This is a further reminder for your decision on the revised version of the submission <strong>{{articleTitle}} </strong>by {{articleAuthors}}.</p>\r\n<div>You can reinvite the reviewers for another round of in-depth evaluation or you can issue a decision without further review.</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>To issue a decision:</div>\r\n<div>\r\n<div dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-position: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">1) Go to <a href="{{siteUrl}}">{{siteUrl}}</a></span><span style="font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-position: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;"> and log in&nbsp;</span></div>\r\n<div dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-position: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">2) Go to '<strong>For Recommenders</strong>'—&gt; '<strong>Reports(s) you are handling</strong>' in the top menu. </span></div>\r\n<div dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-position: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">3) Click the '<strong>View/Edit</strong>' button. </span></div>\r\n<div dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-position: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">4) Click '<strong>Write or edit your decision / recommendation</strong>’. </span></div>\r\n<div dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-position: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">5) Indicate your decision (<strong>revise</strong>, <strong>reject</strong>, <strong>recommend</strong>, <strong>recommend but keep private until Stage 2</strong>).</span></div>\r\n<div dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-position: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">6) Choose a decision or recommendation title (this is of particular importance only for decisions to recommend the preprint concerned) and write or copy/paste your decision or recommendation text.&nbsp;</span></div>\r\n<div dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-position: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">-You can save a draft version of your decision or recommendation text by clicking 'Save' (you will then have to go through steps 1 to 5 to complete your decision or recommendation). </span></div>\r\n<div dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-position: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">7) To send your decision or recommendation to the managing board for validation, click on the green 'Save and submit' button. This will result in your decision or recommendation being sent to the Managing Board for validation.</span></div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div><br>Thank you for handling this submission.</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>The Managing Board of {{appName}}</div>
304	#RecommenderStatusChangedToUnderConsiderationStage1ScheduledSubmission	default	{{appName}}: Revised version - scheduled submission	Mail to recommender to indicate that a revised version has been submitted and that he/she must make a decision (for scheduled submission)	<p>Dear {{destPerson}},</p>\r\n<p>The authors of the Stage 1 submission entitled <strong>{{articleTitle}}</strong> and submitted by {{articleAuthors}} have posted their revised version and their replies to your comments and those of the reviewers. They may also have uploaded (as a PDF or Word file) a revised version of their preprint, with the modifications indicated in TrackChanges mode and a clean version of their PDF at this address <a href="{{linkTarget}}">{{linkTarget}}</a> (see also attachments in this email).</p>\r\n<p>For this new round of evaluation, you must reach a decision to ‘Revise’, ‘Recommend’ or ‘Reject’ the article.</p>\r\n<p>Please decide as soon as possible whether to<strong> send it out again for peer review or whether to render a decision without further review</strong>.</p>\r\n<p>We look forward to your decision. Thanks in advance!</p>\r\n<p>Yours sincerely,</p>\r\n<p>The Managing Board of {{appName}}</p>
305	#ReminderSubmitterScheduledSubmissionSoonDue	default	{{appName}}: Your full Stage 1 submission is due in 14 days	Mail to authors to remind them that the full Stage 1 manuscript based upon their snapshot submission is due in 14 days	<p>Dear {{destPerson}}</p>\r\n<p>Thank you for previously submitting a Stage 1 snapshot entitled "<strong>{{articleTitle}}</strong>" to PCI RR. The recommender handling your submission has scheduled in-depth peer review to take place between {{scheduledSubmissionLatestReviewStartDate}} and {{scheduledReviewDueDate}}.</p>\r\n<p>This is a kind reminder that the full Stage 1 manuscript associated with your snapshot is due in<strong> 14 days, </strong>and must therefore be received by PCI RR <strong>no later than {{scheduledSubmissionDate}}</strong>.</p>\r\n<p>The earliest your full manuscript can be submitted is 7 days from today. You will receive a further notification at that time.</p>\r\n<p>The full manuscript must be received in advance of the scheduled start of in-depth review to enable the recommender and Managing Board to perform a pre-review <a href="https://rr.peercommunityin.org/help/guide_for_recommenders#h_1245019342271613643227798" target="_blank" rel="noopener">triage assessment</a> of your full submission. This evaluation could require you to make revisions to your Stage 1 manuscript prior to the commencement in-depth review, so to ensure that the manuscript is review-ready by the scheduled review date, please be prepared to respond quickly to any revision invitations from the recommender between {{scheduledSubmissionDate}} and {{scheduledSubmissionLatestReviewStartDate}}. In rare cases where the full submission differs substantially from the research proposed in the snapshot, or falls a long way short of meeting at least one of the <a href="https://rr.peercommunityin.org/help/guide_for_authors#h_6720026472751613309075757" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Stage 1 review criteria</a>, the full submission could also be rejected outright, in which case scheduled in-depth review would be cancelled.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Please note that missing the submission deadline of {{scheduledSubmissionDate}} could result in cancellation of the scheduled review process. </strong>If you can no longer meet this deadline, please contact the Managing Board immediately by replying to this email.</p>\r\n<p>Once you have submitted, and the submission has passed internal triage assessment by the Managing Board and recommender, the review process will commence. If you submit ahead of the submission deadline, reviewers may be informed but there is no guarantee that they will review the manuscript until the specified review period is reached.</p>\r\n<p>---</p>\r\n<p>To help avoid the need for revisions prior to review, here are some common difficulties faced by authors in preparing a Stage 1 manuscript:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>The protocol contains insufficient methodological detail to enable replication and prevent researcher degrees of freedom. One commonly neglected area is the criteria for excluding data, both at the level of participants/samples and at the level of data <em>within</em> participants/samples. In the interests of clarity, we recommend listing these criteria systematically rather than presenting them in prose.</li>\r\n<li>For quantitative studies involving hypothesis testing, a lack of correspondence between the scientific hypotheses and the preregistered statistical tests. This is a very common oversight. To maximize clarity of correspondence between predictions and analyses, authors are encouraged to number their hypotheses in the Introduction and then number the proposed analyses in the Methods to make clear which analysis tests which prediction. Ensure also that power analysis, where applicable, is based on the actual test procedures that will be employed to test those hypotheses; e.g. don’t propose a power analysis based on an ANOVA but then suggest a linear mixed effects model to test the hypothesis.&nbsp;</li>\r\n<li>Lack of a completed study design template (as explained&nbsp;<a href="https://rr.peercommunityin.org/help/guide_for_authors#h_27513965735331613309625021">here</a>). Make sure it is as concise as possible (e.g. including formulae for hypotheses) but complete and exhaustive. There are some examples <a href="https://doi.org/10.1371/journal.pcbi.1010571.s002">here</a> alongside the paper ’<a href="https://journals.plos.org/ploscompbiol/article?id=10.1371/journal.pcbi.1010571">ten simple rules for writing a registered report</a>’.</li>\r\n<li>The statistical sampling (such as power analysis) is over-optimistic (e.g. based on previous literature but not taking into account publication bias) or insufficiently justified (e.g. based on a single point estimate from a pilot experiment or previous study). Proposals should be powered to detect the smallest effect that is plausible and of theoretical value. Pilot data can help inform this estimate but is unlikely to form an acceptable basis, alone, for choosing the target effect size. <a href="https://online.ucpress.edu/collabra/article/8/1/33267/120491/Sample-Size-Justification" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Here is an excellent paper</a> on sample size justification.</li>\r\n<li>Intention to infer support for the null hypothesis from statistically non-significant results, without proposing use of Bayes factors or frequentist equivalence&nbsp;testing (see&nbsp;<a href="https://online.ucpress.edu/collabra/article/7/1/28202/118660/Obtaining-Evidence-for-No-Effect">here</a>&nbsp;for a nice explainer).</li>\r\n<li>Inclusion of exploratory analyses in the analysis plan. Manuscripts proposing exploratory analyses will usually be desk rejected until such analyses are removed because inclusion of exploratory “plans” at Stage 1 blurs the line between confirmatory and exploratory outcomes at Stage 2. Instead, such analyses can be included at Stage 2 and need not be preregistered. Under some circumstances, exploratory analyses can be discussed at Stage 1 where they are necessary to justify study variables or procedures that are included in the design exclusively for exploratory analysis. If so, be sure to justify their inclusion in the manuscript.</li>\r\n<li>Failure to distinguish work that has already been done from work that is planned. Where a proposal contains a mixture of pilot work that has already been undertaken and a proposal for work not yet undertaken, authors commonly use the past tense for pilot work but the future tense for the proposed work. At Stage 2, all descriptions shift to past tense.</li>\r\n<li>Lack of pre-specified positive controls or other quality checks, or an appropriate justification for their absence. Positive controls are not&nbsp;possible with all study designs, in which case authors should discuss why they are not included.</li>\r\n<li>Where applicable, lack of power analysis within proposed positive controls that depend on hypothesis testing.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>---</p>\r\n<p>Follow this link to view your submission on the system: <a href="{{linkTarget}}">{{linkTarget}}</a></p>\r\n<p>When the time comes to submit your full Stage 1 manuscript, please navigate to your submission on the PCI RR website and proceed as follows:</p>\r\n<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">a) Click the button "CHECK / EDIT REPORT SURVEY". This will take you to the submission checklist.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">b) In the submission checklist, change the response for Q3 to “I PREVIOUSLY SUBMITTED A STAGE 1 SNAPSHOT AND THE FULL MANUSCRIPT IS NOW READY FOR REVIEW”. <strong>Please make this change to the checklist first, before changing any other answers.</strong><br></span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">c) Next, leave the URL for the snapshot in Q2 unchanged (to keep it preserved in our records) but change the response to Q1 to “COMPLETE STAGE 1 REPORT FOR REGULAR REVIEW”. The URL for the snapshot will then become fixed and uneditable.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">d) Check all other answers in the checklist (adjusting as necessary) then click the "Submit" button at the bottom of the page.<br></span></p>\r\n<p>e) This will close the submission checklist, but you have not completed your submission. Next, enter or update the URL to the <strong>full Stage 1 manuscript</strong> in the box entitled: "Full web address to most recent version of the manuscript". Then enter the version number in the box entitled: "Most recent version of the manuscript at the above".</p>\r\n<p>f) Finally, click the "Submit" button. <strong>You will have then submitted your full Stage 1 manuscript.</strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Note that the above options will not become available until 7 days from now, which is also <strong>7 days prior to {{scheduledSubmissionDate}}</strong>.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>If you have any questions please feel free to contact us via reply email.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Sincerely, the PCI RR Managing Board</p>
306	#ManagersArticleCancelledStage1ScheduledSubmission	default	{{appName}}: Article cancelled - scheduled submission	Mail to MB to indicate that the submitter cancelled his/her submission (for scheduled submission)	<p>Dear members of the Managing Board,</p>\n<p>The submission of the article entitled "{{articleTitle}}" has been cancelled by the author.</p>\n<p>To manage this recommendation, please follow this link <a href="{{linkTarget}}">{{linkTarget}}</a>.</p>\n<p>Have a nice day!</p>
307	#ReminderSubmitterScheduledSubmissionDue	default	{{appName}}: IMPORTANT -- Your full Stage 1 submission is due TODAY	Mail to authors to remind them that the full Stage 1 manuscript based upon their snapshot submission is due TODAY	<p>Dear {{destPerson}}</p>\r\n<p>Thank you for previously submitting a Stage 1 snapshot entitled "<strong>{{articleTitle}}</strong>" to PCI RR. The recommender handling your submission has scheduled in-depth peer review to take place between {{scheduledSubmissionLatestReviewStartDate}} and {{scheduledReviewDueDate}}.</p>\r\n<p><strong>This is an important reminder that the full Stage 1 manuscript associated with your snapshot is due <span style="text-decoration: underline;">TODAY</span>.</strong></p>\r\n<p>The full manuscript must be received in advance of the scheduled start of in-depth review to enable the recommender and Managing Board to perform a pre-review <a href="https://rr.peercommunityin.org/help/guide_for_recommenders#h_1245019342271613643227798" target="_blank" rel="noopener">triage assessment</a> of your full submission. This evaluation could require you to make revisions to your Stage 1 manuscript prior to the commencement in-depth review, so to ensure that the manuscript is review-ready by the scheduled review date, please be prepared to respond quickly to any revision invitations from the recommender between {{scheduledSubmissionDate}} and {{scheduledSubmissionLatestReviewStartDate}}. In rare cases where the full submission differs substantially from the research proposed in the snapshot, or falls a long way short of meeting at least one of the <a href="https://rr.peercommunityin.org/help/guide_for_authors#h_6720026472751613309075757" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Stage 1 review criteria</a>, the full submission could also be rejected outright, in which case scheduled in-depth review would be cancelled.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Please note that missing today's submission deadline could result in cancellation of the scheduled review process. </strong>If you can no longer meet this deadline, please contact the Managing Board immediately by replying to this email.<strong><br></strong></p>\r\n<p>Once you have submitted, and the submission has passed internal triage assessment by the Managing Board and recommender, the review process will commence. If you submit ahead of the submission deadline, reviewers may be informed but there is no guarantee that they will review the manuscript until the specified review period is reached.</p>\r\n<p>Follow this link to view your submission on the system: <a href="{{linkTarget}}">{{linkTarget}}</a></p>\r\n<p>When the full Stage 1 manuscript is written and ready to submit, please navigate to your submission on the PCI RR website and proceed as follows:</p>\r\n<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">a) Click the button "CHECK / EDIT REPORT SURVEY". This will take you to the submission checklist.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">b) In the submission checklist, change the response for Q3 to “I PREVIOUSLY SUBMITTED A STAGE 1 SNAPSHOT AND THE FULL MANUSCRIPT IS NOW READY FOR REVIEW”. <strong>Please make this change to the checklist first before changing any other answers.</strong><br></span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">c) Next, leave the URL for the snapshot in Q2 unchanged (to keep it preserved in our records) but change the response to Q1 to “COMPLETE STAGE 1 REPORT FOR REGULAR REVIEW”. The URL for the snapshot will then become fixed and uneditable.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">d) Check all other answers in the checklist (adjusting as necessary) then click the "Submit" button at the bottom of the page.<br></span></p>\r\n<p>e) This will close the submission checklist, but you have not completed your submission. Next, enter or update the URL to the <strong>full Stage 1 manuscript</strong> in the box entitled: "Full web address to most recent version of the manuscript". Then enter the version number in the box entitled: "Most recent version of the manuscript at the above".</p>\r\n<p>f) Finally, click the "Submit" button. <strong>You will have then submitted your full Stage 1 manuscript.</strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>If you have any questions please feel free to contact us via reply email.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Sincerely, the PCI RR Managing Board</p>
308	#SubmitterAcknowledgementFullPreprintStage1ScheduledSubmission	default	{{appName}}: Thank you for your full Stage 1 submission	Mail to submitter to acknowledge their full Stage 1 submission for scheduled review	<p>Dear {{destPerson}},</p>\n<p>Thank you for your full Stage 1 manuscript entitled "<strong>{{articleTitle}}</strong>" to {{appName}}.</p>\n<p>The recommender handling your submission, {{recommenderPerson}}, has scheduled in-depth peer review to take place between {{scheduledSubmissionLatestReviewStartDate}} and {{scheduledReviewDueDate}}.</p>\n<p>The Managing Board and recommender will now perform a pre-review <a href="https://rr.peercommunityin.org/help/guide_for_recommenders#h_1245019342271613643227798" target="_blank" rel="noopener">triage assessment</a> of your full submission. This evaluation could require you to make revisions to your Stage 1 manuscript prior to the commencement in-depth review, so to ensure that the manuscript is review-ready by the scheduled review date, <strong>please be prepared to respond quickly to any revision invitations from the recommender between now and {{scheduledSubmissionLatestReviewStartDate}}</strong>. In rare cases where the full submission differs substantially from the research proposed in the snapshot, or falls a long way short of meeting at least one of the <a href="https://rr.peercommunityin.org/help/guide_for_authors#h_6720026472751613309075757" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Stage 1 review criteria</a>, the full submission could be rejected outright, in which case scheduled in-depth review will be cancelled.</p>\n<p>Once you have submitted, and the submission has passed internal triage assessment by the Managing Board and recommender, the review process will commence. If you have submitted ahead of the submission deadline, reviewers may be informed but there is no guarantee that they will review the manuscript until the specified review period is reached.</p>\n<p>Thank you again for your submission.</p>\n<p>The Managing Board of {{appName}}</p>
309	#DefaultReviewInvitationRegisteredUserStage1ScheduledSubmission	default	Invitation to review for Peer Community in Registered Reports at a scheduled future date	Mail to user already registered to invite them to review a Stage 1 snapshot	<div>Dear {{destPerson}},</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>A Registered Report 'snapshot' entitled "<strong>{{articleTitle}}</strong>", has been submitted for consideration by {{description}} (PCI RR) and I am writing to ask if you would kindly consider <span style="font-weight: 400;">serving as a reviewer for a full Stage 1 manuscript that will be ready for in-depth evaluation on</span> {{scheduledSubmissionLatestReviewStartDate}}. The snapshot can be viewed and downloaded at the following address: <a href="{{snapshotUrl}}">{{snapshotUrl}}</a></div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div><span style="font-weight: 400;">Registered Reports (RRs) are a form of empirical research article in which manuscripts containing a study proposal are reviewed prior to data collection or analysis. The aim of this initiative is to minimise publication bias and reporting bias, while also allowing the flexibility to conduct exploratory (unregistered) analyses and report serendipitous findings.&nbsp;</span></div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div><span style="font-weight: 400;">PCI RR is a free, non-commercial platform dedicated to the peer review of RR preprints. Once a preprint is reviewed and positively recommended by PCI RR, authors then have the option to submit their manuscript to a traditional journal, and the reviews are published on the PCI RR website. A growing </span><a href="https://eur03.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=https%3A%2F%2Frr.peercommunityin.org%2Fabout%2Fpci_rr_friendly_journals&amp;data=04%7C01%7Cchambersc1%40cardiff.ac.uk%7C3b0bd2172d19499a650008d934ba39af%7Cbdb74b3095684856bdbf06759778fcbc%7C1%7C0%7C637598796701743675%7CUnknown%7CTWFpbGZsb3d8eyJWIjoiMC4wLjAwMDAiLCJQIjoiV2luMzIiLCJBTiI6Ik1haWwiLCJXVCI6Mn0%3D%7C1000&amp;sdata=JXBq1vVpf1%2FrbMY0RB9K55orGA%2ByyWDd7mduvA7qQvc%3D&amp;reserved=0"><span style="font-weight: 400;">list of PCI RR-friendly journals</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;"> now immediately accept submissions recommended by PCI RR without further peer review.</span></div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div><strong>RR snapshots</strong><span style="font-weight: 400;"> are one-page templates submitted by authors to PCI RR in advance of preparing and submitting a complete Stage 1 manuscript. If the snapshot passes an internal evaluation by PCI RR, as this one has, the review process for the upcoming full Stage 1 manuscript is scheduled for a short range of dates in the future, with the aim to </span><a href="https://rr.peercommunityin.org/help/guide_for_reviewers#h_61998243643551613309672490" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><span style="font-weight: 400;">streamline the review process</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;">. In this case, the authors have indicated that their full Stage 1 manuscript will be ready for review no later than </span><span style="font-weight: 400;"><strong>{{scheduledSubmissionLatestReviewStartDate}}</strong>. </span><strong>We are therefore asking if you would consider reviewing the full Stage 1 manuscript, once submitted, within 5 working days of this date, by {{scheduledReviewDueDate}}. </strong></div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div><span style="font-weight: 400;">Please note that we are </span><strong>not requesting a review of the snapshot itself </strong><span style="font-weight: 400;">-- the snapshot is provided only so that based on its content, you can decide now whether to accept or decline the future review of the full Stage 1 manuscript. Reliable scheduling is vital for this submission pathway to be successful so please do not accept this assignment unless you are certain you would be able to complete the review between </span> {{scheduledSubmissionLatestReviewStartDate}} and {{scheduledReviewDueDate}}.<span style="font-weight: 400;"><br></span></div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div><span style="font-weight: 400;">Once the peer review process for the full Stage 1 manuscript commences, it occurs over two stages. Stage 1 submissions include an Introduction, Method, and Pilot Data (where applicable). In evaluating these manuscripts, we ask reviewers to assess:</span></div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div><span style="font-weight: 400;">1A. The scientific validity of the research question(s)</span></div>\r\n<div><span style="font-weight: 400;">1B. The logic, rationale, and plausibility of the proposed hypotheses (where a submission proposes hypotheses)</span></div>\r\n<div><span style="font-weight: 400;">1C. The soundness and feasibility of the methodology and analysis pipeline (including statistical power analysis or alternative sampling plans where applicable)</span></div>\r\n<div><span style="font-weight: 400;">1D. Whether the clarity and degree of methodological detail is sufficient to closely replicate the proposed study procedures and analysis pipeline and to prevent undisclosed flexibility in the procedures and analyses</span></div>\r\n<div><span style="font-weight: 400;">1E. Whether the authors have considered sufficient outcome-neutral conditions (e.g. absence of floor or ceiling effects; positive controls; other quality checks) for ensuring that the obtained results are able to test the stated hypotheses or answer the stated research question(s).</span></div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div><span style="font-weight: 400;">The PCI RR website includes an</span><a href="https://rr.peercommunityin.org/help/guide_for_reviewers#h_6720026472751613309075757"><span style="font-weight: 400;"> </span><span style="font-weight: 400;">expanded description of these review criteria</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;">, additional</span><a href="https://rr.peercommunityin.org/help/guide_for_reviewers#h_7586915642301613635089357"><span style="font-weight: 400;"> </span><span style="font-weight: 400;">tips for reviewing a RR</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;">, and</span><a href="https://rr.peercommunityin.org/help/guide_for_reviewers"><span style="font-weight: 400;"> </span><span style="font-weight: 400;">complete reviewer guidelines</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;">.</span></div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div><span style="font-weight: 400;">Submissions that pass Stage 1 review are issued an in-principle acceptance (IPA), which guarantees a positive recommendation of the completed study if the authors adhere to the approved procedures and propose a defensible interpretation of the results. Completed manuscripts are then peer reviewed again at Stage 2, ideally by the same reviewers as Stage 1.</span></div>\r\n<div><span style="font-weight: 400;">{{programmaticRR_invitation_text}}</span></div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div><span style="font-weight: 400;">In the event of a favourable outcome, all editorial correspondence (reviews, recommender’s decisions, authors’ replies) and a recommendation text will be published by PCI RR under a CC-BY 4.0 license. If, after one or several rounds of review, the preprint is rejected, the editorial correspondence (and specifically your review) will NOT be published. You will be notified by e-mail at each stage in the procedure.</span></div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div><span style="font-weight: 400;">Stage 1 snapshots and manuscripts may be submitted with author names either revealed or masked, and may be published openly or embargoed in a recognised repository (such as the OSF) with a private viewable link. Note that to avoid any conflict of interests, where you know the identity of the submitting authors you should not accept to participate in the review process if the authors are close colleagues (people belonging to the same laboratory/unit/department in the last four years, people with whom you have published in the last four years, with whom you have received joint funding in the last four years, or with whom you are currently writing a manuscript, or submitting a grant proposal).</span></div>\r\n<div><span style="font-weight: 400;">{{signedreview_invitation_text}}</span></div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div><span style="font-weight: 400;">We would be grateful if you could let us know whether, based on your reading of the snapshot, you would be willing to accept our invitation to review the manuscript within 5 working days of {{scheduledSubmissionLatestReviewStartDate}}, by</span> <strong>{{scheduledReviewDueDate}}. </strong></div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>I would be grateful if you could let me know as soon as possible whether you are willing to accept my invitation to review this article, or whether you would prefer to decline, by clicking on the link below or by logging onto the PCI RR website and going to 'For contributors —&gt; Invitation(s) to review a report' in the top menu. If you are a new user, you will be asked to create a password before being logged in.</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div><span style="font-weight: 400;">Best wishes,</span></div>\r\n<div><span style="font-weight: 400;">{{sender}}</span></div>
310	#ReviewerThankForReviewAcceptationStage1ScheduledSubmission	default	{{appName}}: Thank you for agreeing to review at a scheduled future date	Mail to a reviewer to thank them for agreeing to review a future Stage 1 manuscript based on a snapshot	<p>Dear {{destPerson}},</p>\r\n<p>Thank you very much for agreeing to undertake a scheduled review of a Stage 1 Registered Report, <span style="font-weight: 400;">provisionally entitled "{{articleTitle}}"</span>, which <span style="font-weight: 400;">will be available for review no later than</span> {{scheduledSubmissionLatestReviewStartDate}} and for which your review will be due on <strong>{{scheduledReviewDueDate}}</strong>. For reference, the snapshot can be viewed and downloaded at the following address: <a href="{{snapshotUrl}}">{{snapshotUrl}}</a></p>\r\n<p><strong>Please note that no review of the snapshot itself is requested. </strong>The snapshot was provided only so that you could decide if the manuscript fell sufficiently within your area of interest and expertise to provide a later evaluation of a full Stage 1 manuscript.</p>\r\n<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">There is no further action needed at this time. We will notify you when the full Stage 1 manuscript is received with further instructions. In the meantime, you can</span> learn more about being a reviewer for PCI Registered Reports by reading an <a href="https://rr.peercommunityin.org/help/guide_for_reviewers#h_6720026472751613309075757" target="_blank" rel="noopener">expanded description of the review criteria</a>, additional <a href="https://rr.peercommunityin.org/help/guide_for_reviewers#h_7586915642301613635089357" target="_blank" rel="noopener">tips for reviewing a RR</a>, and our <a href="https://rr.peercommunityin.org/help/guide_for_reviewers" target="_blank" rel="noopener">complete reviewer guidelines</a>.</p>\r\n<p>We will contact you again in due course.</p>\r\n<p>Yours sincerely,</p>\r\n<p><span style="padding-left: 1in;">The recommender, {{recommenderPerson}}</span></p>
311	#DefaultReviewInvitationNewUserStage1ScheduledSubmission	default	Invitation to review for Peer Community in Registered Reports at a scheduled future date	Mail to user not yet registered to invite them to review a future Stage 1 manuscript based on a submitted snapshot	<div>Dear {{destPerson}},</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>A Registered Report 'snapshot' entitled "<strong>{{articleTitle}}</strong>", has been submitted for consideration by {{description}} (PCI RR) and I am writing to ask if you would kindly consider <span style="font-weight: 400;">serving as a reviewer for a full Stage 1 manuscript that will be ready for in-depth evaluation on</span> {{scheduledSubmissionLatestReviewStartDate}}. The snapshot can be viewed and downloaded at the following address: <a href="{{snapshotUrl}}">{{snapshotUrl}}</a></div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div><span style="font-weight: 400;">Registered Reports (RRs) are a form of empirical research article in which manuscripts containing a study proposal are reviewed prior to data collection or analysis. The aim of this initiative is to minimise publication bias and reporting bias, while also allowing the flexibility to conduct exploratory (unregistered) analyses and report serendipitous findings.&nbsp;</span></div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div><span style="font-weight: 400;">PCI RR is a free, non-commercial platform dedicated to the peer review of RR preprints. Once a preprint is reviewed and positively recommended by PCI RR, authors then have the option to submit their manuscript to a traditional journal, and the reviews are published on the PCI RR website. A growing </span><a href="https://eur03.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=https%3A%2F%2Frr.peercommunityin.org%2Fabout%2Fpci_rr_friendly_journals&amp;data=04%7C01%7Cchambersc1%40cardiff.ac.uk%7C3b0bd2172d19499a650008d934ba39af%7Cbdb74b3095684856bdbf06759778fcbc%7C1%7C0%7C637598796701743675%7CUnknown%7CTWFpbGZsb3d8eyJWIjoiMC4wLjAwMDAiLCJQIjoiV2luMzIiLCJBTiI6Ik1haWwiLCJXVCI6Mn0%3D%7C1000&amp;sdata=JXBq1vVpf1%2FrbMY0RB9K55orGA%2ByyWDd7mduvA7qQvc%3D&amp;reserved=0"><span style="font-weight: 400;">list of PCI RR-friendly journals</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;"> now immediately accept submissions recommended by PCI RR without further peer review.</span></div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div><strong>RR snapshots</strong><span style="font-weight: 400;"> are one-page templates submitted by authors to PCI RR in advance of preparing and submitting a complete Stage 1 manuscript. If the snapshot passes an internal evaluation by PCI RR, as this one has, the review process for the upcoming full Stage 1 manuscript is scheduled for a short range of dates in the future, with the aim to </span><a href="https://rr.peercommunityin.org/help/guide_for_reviewers#h_61998243643551613309672490" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><span style="font-weight: 400;">streamline the review process</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;">. In this case, the authors have indicated that their full Stage 1 manuscript be ready for review no later than </span><span style="font-weight: 400;"><strong>{{scheduledSubmissionLatestReviewStartDate}}</strong>. </span><strong>We are therefore asking if you would consider reviewing the full Stage 1 manuscript, once submitted, within 5 working days of this date, by {{scheduledReviewDueDate}}. </strong></div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div><span style="font-weight: 400;">Please note that we are </span><strong>not requesting a review of the snapshot itself </strong><span style="font-weight: 400;">-- the snapshot is provided only so that based on its content, you can decide now whether to accept or decline the future review of the full Stage 1 manuscript. Reliable scheduling is vital for this submission pathway to be successful so please do not accept this assignment unless you are certain you would be able to complete the review between </span> {{scheduledSubmissionLatestReviewStartDate}} and {{scheduledReviewDueDate}}.<span style="font-weight: 400;"><br></span></div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div><span style="font-weight: 400;">Once the peer review process for the full Stage 1 </span><span style="font-weight: 400;">manuscript commences, it occurs over two stages. Stage 1 submissions include an Introduction, Method, and Pilot Data (where applicable). In evaluating these manuscripts, we ask reviewers to assess:</span></div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div><span style="font-weight: 400;">1A. The scientific validity of the research question(s)</span></div>\r\n<div><span style="font-weight: 400;">1B. The logic, rationale, and plausibility of the proposed hypotheses (where a submission proposes hypotheses)</span></div>\r\n<div><span style="font-weight: 400;">1C. The soundness and feasibility of the methodology and analysis pipeline (including statistical power analysis or alternative sampling plans where applicable)</span></div>\r\n<div><span style="font-weight: 400;">1D. Whether the clarity and degree of methodological detail is sufficient to closely replicate the proposed study procedures and analysis pipeline and to prevent undisclosed flexibility in the procedures and analyses</span></div>\r\n<div><span style="font-weight: 400;">1E. Whether the authors have considered sufficient outcome-neutral conditions (e.g. absence of floor or ceiling effects; positive controls; other quality checks) for ensuring that the obtained results are able to test the stated hypotheses or answer the stated research question(s).</span></div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div><span style="font-weight: 400;">The PCI RR website includes an</span><a href="https://rr.peercommunityin.org/help/guide_for_reviewers#h_6720026472751613309075757"><span style="font-weight: 400;"> </span><span style="font-weight: 400;">expanded description of these review criteria</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;">, additional</span><a href="https://rr.peercommunityin.org/help/guide_for_reviewers#h_7586915642301613635089357"><span style="font-weight: 400;"> </span><span style="font-weight: 400;">tips for reviewing a RR</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;">, and</span><a href="https://rr.peercommunityin.org/help/guide_for_reviewers"><span style="font-weight: 400;"> </span><span style="font-weight: 400;">complete reviewer guidelines</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;">.</span></div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div><span style="font-weight: 400;">Submissions that pass Stage 1 review are issued an in-principle acceptance (IPA), which guarantees a positive recommendation of the completed study if the authors adhere to the approved procedures and propose a defensible interpretation of the results. Completed manuscripts are then peer reviewed again at Stage 2, ideally by the same reviewers as Stage 1.</span></div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div><span style="font-weight: 400;">{{programmaticRR_invitation_text}}</span></div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div><span style="font-weight: 400;">In the event of a favourable outcome, all editorial correspondence (reviews, recommender’s decisions, authors’ replies) and a recommendation text will be published by PCI RR under a CC-BY 4.0 license. If, after one or several rounds of review, the preprint is rejected, the editorial correspondence (and specifically your review) will NOT be published. You will be notified by e-mail at each stage in the procedure.</span></div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div><span style="font-weight: 400;">Stage 1 snapshots and manuscripts may be submitted with author names either revealed or masked, and may be published openly or embargoed in a recognised repository (such as the OSF) with a private viewable link. Note that to avoid any conflict of interests, where you know the identity of the submitting authors you should not accept to participate in the review process if the authors are close colleagues (people belonging to the same laboratory/unit/department in the last four years, people with whom you have published in the last four years, with whom you have received joint funding in the last four years, or with whom you are currently writing a manuscript, or submitting a grant proposal).</span></div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div><span style="font-weight: 400;">{{signedreview_invitation_text}}</span></div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div><span style="font-weight: 400;">We would be grateful if you could let us know whether, based on your reading of the snapshot, you would be willing to accept our invitation to review the manuscript within 5 working days of {{scheduledSubmissionLatestReviewStartDate}}, by</span> <strong>{{scheduledReviewDueDate}}</strong><span style="font-weight: 400;">.</span></div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>I would be grateful if you could let me know as soon as possible whether you are willing to accept my invitation to review this article, or whether you would prefer to decline, by clicking on the link below or by logging onto the PCI RR website and going to 'For contributors —&gt; Invitation(s) to review a report in the top menu. If you are a new user, you will be asked to create a password before being logged in. If you are reviewing a revised manuscript, you will find the authors' response to reviewers linked on the website.</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div><span style="font-weight: 400;">Many thanks for considering this prospective review request.</span></div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div><span style="font-weight: 400;">Best wishes,</span></div>\r\n<div><span style="font-weight: 400;">{{sender}}</span></div>
312	#ReminderReviewerReviewInvitationRegisteredUserStage1ScheduledSubmission	default	{{appName}}: Invitation to review at a scheduled future date - reminder	Mail to user already registered to remind them that they have been invited as a reviewer of a Stage 1 snapshot	<p>Dear {{destPerson}},&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>This is a kind reminder about the following invitation to review a <span style="font-weight: 400;">Stage 1 manuscript that will be submitted to</span> {{description}} (PCI RR) at a scheduled future date.</p>\r\n<p>A Registered Report 'snapshot' entitled "{{articleTitle}}", has been submitted for consideration by PCI RR and I am writing to ask if you would kindly consider <span style="font-weight: 400;">serving as a reviewer for a full manuscript that will be submitted on</span> {{scheduledSubmissionLatestReviewStartDate}}. The snapshot can be viewed and downloaded at the following address: <a href="{{snapshotUrl}}">{{snapshotUrl}}</a></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Registered Reports (RRs) are a form of empirical research article in which manuscripts containing a study proposal are reviewed prior to data collection or analysis. The aim of this initiative is to minimise publication bias and reporting bias, while also allowing the flexibility to conduct exploratory (unregistered) analyses and report serendipitous findings.&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">PCI RR is a free, non-commercial platform dedicated to the peer review of RR preprints. Once a preprint is reviewed and positively recommended by PCI RR, authors then have the option to submit their manuscript to a traditional journal, and the reviews are published on the PCI RR website. A growing </span><a href="https://eur03.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=https%3A%2F%2Frr.peercommunityin.org%2Fabout%2Fpci_rr_friendly_journals&amp;data=04%7C01%7Cchambersc1%40cardiff.ac.uk%7C3b0bd2172d19499a650008d934ba39af%7Cbdb74b3095684856bdbf06759778fcbc%7C1%7C0%7C637598796701743675%7CUnknown%7CTWFpbGZsb3d8eyJWIjoiMC4wLjAwMDAiLCJQIjoiV2luMzIiLCJBTiI6Ik1haWwiLCJXVCI6Mn0%3D%7C1000&amp;sdata=JXBq1vVpf1%2FrbMY0RB9K55orGA%2ByyWDd7mduvA7qQvc%3D&amp;reserved=0"><span style="font-weight: 400;">list of PCI RR-friendly journals</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;"> now immediately accept submissions recommended by PCI RR without further peer review.</span></p>\r\n<p><strong>RR snapshots</strong><span style="font-weight: 400;"> are one-page templates submitted by authors to PCI RR in advance of preparing and submitting a complete Stage 1 manuscript. If the snapshot passes an internal evaluation by PCI RR, as this one has, the review process for the upcoming full manuscript is scheduled for a short range of dates in the future, with the aim to </span><a href="https://rr.peercommunityin.org/help/guide_for_reviewers#h_61998243643551613309672490" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><span style="font-weight: 400;">streamline the review process</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;">. In this case, the authors have indicated that they will submit their full manuscript on </span><span style="font-weight: 400;"><strong>{{scheduledSubmissionLatestReviewStartDate}}</strong>. </span><strong>We are&nbsp; asking if you would consider reviewing the full manuscript, once submitted, within 5 working days of this date, by {{scheduledReviewDueDate}}. </strong></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Please note that we are </span><strong>not requesting a review of the snapshot itself </strong><span style="font-weight: 400;">-- the snapshot is provided only so that based on its content, you can decide now whether to accept or decline the future review of the full Stage 1 manuscript. Reliable scheduling is vital for this submission pathway to be successful so please do not accept this assignment unless you are certain you would be able to complete the review between </span> {{scheduledSubmissionLatestReviewStartDate}} and {{scheduledReviewDueDate}}.<span style="font-weight: 400;"><br></span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Once the peer review process for the full manuscript commences, it occurs over two stages. Stage 1 submissions include an Introduction, Method, and Pilot Data (where applicable). In evaluating these manuscripts, we ask reviewers to assess:</span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">1A. The scientific validity of the research question(s)</span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">1B. The logic, rationale, and plausibility of the proposed hypotheses (where a submission proposes hypotheses)</span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">1C. The soundness and feasibility of the methodology and analysis pipeline (including statistical power analysis or alternative sampling plans where applicable)</span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">1D. Whether the clarity and degree of methodological detail is sufficient to closely replicate the proposed study procedures and analysis pipeline and to prevent undisclosed flexibility in the procedures and analyses</span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">1E. Whether the authors have considered sufficient outcome-neutral conditions (e.g. absence of floor or ceiling effects; positive controls; other quality checks) for ensuring that the obtained results are able to test the stated hypotheses or answer the stated research question(s).</span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">The PCI RR website includes an</span><a href="https://rr.peercommunityin.org/help/guide_for_reviewers#h_6720026472751613309075757"><span style="font-weight: 400;"> </span><span style="font-weight: 400;">expanded description of these review criteria</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;">, additional</span><a href="https://rr.peercommunityin.org/help/guide_for_reviewers#h_7586915642301613635089357"><span style="font-weight: 400;"> </span><span style="font-weight: 400;">tips for reviewing a RR</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;">, and</span><a href="https://rr.peercommunityin.org/help/guide_for_reviewers"><span style="font-weight: 400;"> </span><span style="font-weight: 400;">complete reviewer guidelines</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;">.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Submissions that pass Stage 1 review are issued an in-principle acceptance (IPA), which guarantees a positive recommendation of the completed study if the authors adhere to the approved procedures and propose a defensible interpretation of the results. Completed manuscripts are then peer reviewed again at Stage 2, ideally by the same reviewers as Stage 1.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">{{programmaticRR_invitation_text}}</span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">In the event of a favourable outcome, all editorial correspondence (reviews, recommender’s decisions, authors’ replies) and a recommendation text will be published by PCI RR under a CC-BY 4.0 license. If, after one or several rounds of review, the preprint is rejected, the editorial correspondence (and specifically your review) will NOT be published. You will be notified by e-mail at each stage in the procedure.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Stage 1 snapshots and manuscripts may be submitted with author names either revealed or masked, and may be published openly or embargoed in a recognised repository (such as the OSF) with a private viewable link. Note that to avoid any conflict of interests, where you know the identity of the submitting authors you should not accept to participate in the review process if the authors are close colleagues (people belonging to the same laboratory/unit/department in the last four years, people with whom you have published in the last four years, with whom you have received joint funding in the last four years, or with whom you are currently writing a manuscript, or submitting a grant proposal), or family members, friends, or anyone for whom bias might affect the nature of your evaluation.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">{{signedreview_invitation_text}}</span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">We would be grateful if you could let us know whether, based on your reading of the snapshot, you would be willing to accept our invitation to review the manuscript within 5 working days of {{scheduledSubmissionLatestReviewStartDate}}, by</span> {{scheduledReviewDueDate}}<span style="font-weight: 400;">. </span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">You can let us know if you are willing to accept our invitation to review a full Stage 1 article during the dates specified above, or whether you prefer to decline</span>, by clicking on the link below or by logging onto the PCI RR website and going to 'For contributors —&gt; Invitation(s) to review a preprint' in the top menu. If you are reviewing a revised Stage 1 snapshot, you will find the authors' response linked on the website.</p>\r\n<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Best wishes,</span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">{{sender}} and the </span><a href="https://rr.peercommunityin.org/about/full_policies#h_4322855162061613307340646"><span style="font-weight: 400;">PCI RR Managing Board</span></a></p>
313	#RecommenderSuggestedReviewersStage1ScheduledSubmission	default	{{appName}}: suggested reviewers	Mail to recommender indicating the him/her the names of the reviewers suggested by a reviewer who declined an invitation	<p>Dear {{destPerson}},&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>The reviewer {{reviewerPerson}} that just declined your invitation to review the report entiled <strong>{{articleTitle}}</strong> suggests the following reviewers:</p>\r\n<p>{{suggestedReviewersText}}&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>You can invite these reviewers by following this link <a href="{{linkTarget}}">{{linkTarget}}</a> or by logging onto the {{appName}} website and going to ‘For recommenders —&gt; Report(s) you are handling’ in the top menu.</p>\r\n<p>We thank you again for managing this evaluation.</p>\r\n<p>All the best,</p>\r\n<p>The Managing Board of {{appName}}</p>
314	#ManagersFullPreprintStage1ScheduledSubmission	default	{{appName}}: Stage 1 submission requiring validation	Mail to MB to indicate a Stage 1 submission	<p>Dear members of the Managing Board,</p>\n<p>{{appName}} has received a Stage 1 submission by {{submitterPerson}}.</p>\n<p>To validate or delete this submission, please follow this link <a href="{{linkTarget}}">{{linkTarget}}</a>.</p>\n<p>Have a nice day!</p>
315	#SubmitterPreprintSubmittedStage1ScheduledSubmission	default	{{appName}}: Your submission	Mail to submitter to indicate the validation of their Stage 1 snapshot	<p>Dear {{destPerson}},<br><br>Thank you for submitting your Stage 1 snapshot to {{appName}} for consideration via the Scheduled Review track. Your submission has now been validated by the Managing Board and recommenders have been invited to take the assignment. You will be notified by email when a recommender agrees to handle your submission. If none of the invited recommenders is able to act as a recommender, you may receive an email inviting you to suggest additional recommenders.&nbsp;</p>\n<p>To view or cancel your submission, please follow this link {{linkTarget}} or log into the {{appName}} website and go to 'For contributors —&gt; Your submitted reports' in the top menu.<br><br>We thank you again for your submission.<br><br>Yours sincerely,<br><br>The Managing Board of {{appName}}</p>
316	#SubmitterPreprintUnderConsiderationStage1ScheduledSubmission	default	{{appName}}: Consideration of your Stage 1 snapshot	Mail to submitter that a recommender has agreed to handle their snapshot submission	<p>Dear {{destPerson}},</p>\r\n<p>Thank you for submitting your Stage 1 snapshot entitled <strong>{{articleTitle}}</strong> to {{appName}}. We are pleased to inform you that a recommender has initiated the evaluation process.</p>\r\n<p>Prior to specialist review, the recommender may desk reject your submission or invite you to submit a revised snapshot. If deemed suitable for in-depth consideration, reviewers will be invited to evaluate a full manuscript between {{scheduledSubmissionLatestReviewStartDate}} and {{scheduledReviewDueDate}}. The reviewers will use the snapshot to decide whether to eventually review a full manuscript based upon the snapshot. The reviewers do not submit an evaluation of the snapshot itself.</p>\r\n<p>To ensure the effectiveness of this scheduled review process, it is imperative that your complete Stage 1 manuscript is ready to submit <strong>no later than {{scheduledSubmissionDate}}. </strong></p>\r\n<p>You can expect to hear within 7 days if your snapshot has been rejected outright or in need of revision. If you hear nothing within 7 days, you can assume that the process of scheduling the in-depth review process is underway.</p>\r\n<p>To view or cancel your submission, please follow this link <a href="{{linkTarget}}">{{linkTarget}}</a> or log in at the {{appName}} website and go to 'For contributors —&gt; Your submitted reports' in the top menu. You can also monitor the progress of your submission any time by navigating to 'For contributors' &gt; 'Your submitted reports' &gt; 'VIEW/EDIT' &gt; and then scroll down and expand the <em>Timeline</em> section.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>We thank you again for your submission.</p>\r\n<p>Yours sincerely,</p>\r\n<p>The Managing Board of {{appName}}</p>
317	#ReminderReviewerReviewInvitationNewUserStage1ScheduledSubmission	default	Invitation to review for Peer Community in Registered Reports at a scheduled future date - reminder	Mail to user not yet registered to remind them that they have been invited as a reviewer of a Stage 1 snapshot	<div>Dear {{destPerson}},</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>This is a kind reminder about the following invitation to review a <span style="font-weight: 400;">Stage 1 manuscript that will be submitted to</span> {{description}} (PCI RR) at a scheduled future date.</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>A Registered Report 'snapshot' entitled "{{articleTitle}}", has been submitted for consideration by PCI RR and I am writing to ask if you would kindly consider <span style="font-weight: 400;">serving as a reviewer for a full manuscript that will be submitted on</span> {{scheduledSubmissionLatestReviewStartDate}}. The snapshot can be viewed and downloaded at the following address: <a href="{{snapshotUrl}}">{{snapshotUrl}}</a></div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div><span style="font-weight: 400;">Registered Reports (RRs) are a form of empirical research article in which manuscripts containing a study proposal are reviewed prior to data collection or analysis. The aim of this initiative is to minimise publication bias and reporting bias, while also allowing the flexibility to conduct exploratory (unregistered) analyses and report serendipitous findings.&nbsp;</span></div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div><span style="font-weight: 400;">PCI RR is a free, non-commercial platform dedicated to the peer review of RR preprints. Once a preprint is reviewed and positively recommended by PCI RR, authors then have the option to submit their manuscript to a traditional journal, and the reviews are published on the PCI RR website. A growing </span><a href="https://eur03.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=https%3A%2F%2Frr.peercommunityin.org%2Fabout%2Fpci_rr_friendly_journals&amp;data=04%7C01%7Cchambersc1%40cardiff.ac.uk%7C3b0bd2172d19499a650008d934ba39af%7Cbdb74b3095684856bdbf06759778fcbc%7C1%7C0%7C637598796701743675%7CUnknown%7CTWFpbGZsb3d8eyJWIjoiMC4wLjAwMDAiLCJQIjoiV2luMzIiLCJBTiI6Ik1haWwiLCJXVCI6Mn0%3D%7C1000&amp;sdata=JXBq1vVpf1%2FrbMY0RB9K55orGA%2ByyWDd7mduvA7qQvc%3D&amp;reserved=0"><span style="font-weight: 400;">list of PCI RR-friendly journals</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;"> now immediately accept submissions recommended by PCI RR without further peer review.</span></div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div><strong>RR snapshots</strong><span style="font-weight: 400;"> are one-page templates submitted by authors to PCI RR in advance of preparing and submitting a complete Stage 1 manuscript. If the snapshot passes an internal evaluation by PCI RR, as this one has, the review process for the upcoming full manuscript is scheduled for a short range of dates in the future, with the aim to </span><a href="https://rr.peercommunityin.org/help/guide_for_reviewers#h_61998243643551613309672490" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><span style="font-weight: 400;">streamline the review process</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;">. In this case, the authors have indicated that they will submit their full manuscript on </span><span style="font-weight: 400;"><strong>{{scheduledSubmissionLatestReviewStartDate}}</strong>. </span><strong>We are&nbsp; asking if you would consider reviewing the full manuscript, once submitted, within 5 working days of this date, by {{scheduledReviewDueDate}}. </strong></div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div><span style="font-weight: 400;">Please note that we are </span><strong>not requesting a review of the snapshot itself </strong><span style="font-weight: 400;">-- the snapshot is provided only so that based on its content, you can decide now whether to accept or decline the future review of the full Stage 1 manuscript. Reliable scheduling is vital for this submission pathway to be successful so please do not accept this assignment unless you are certain you would be able to complete the review between </span> {{scheduledSubmissionLatestReviewStartDate}} and {{scheduledReviewDueDate}}.<span style="font-weight: 400;"><br></span></div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div><span style="font-weight: 400;">Once the peer review process for the full manuscript commences, it occurs over two stages. Stage 1 submissions include an Introduction, Method, and Pilot Data (where applicable). In evaluating these manuscripts, we ask reviewers to assess:</span></div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div><span style="font-weight: 400;">1A. The scientific validity of the research question(s)</span></div>\r\n<div><span style="font-weight: 400;">1B. The logic, rationale, and plausibility of the proposed hypotheses (where a submission proposes hypotheses)</span></div>\r\n<div><span style="font-weight: 400;">1C. The soundness and feasibility of the methodology and analysis pipeline (including statistical power analysis or alternative sampling plans where applicable)</span></div>\r\n<div><span style="font-weight: 400;">1D. Whether the clarity and degree of methodological detail is sufficient to closely replicate the proposed study procedures and analysis pipeline and to prevent undisclosed flexibility in the procedures and analyses</span></div>\r\n<div><span style="font-weight: 400;">1E. Whether the authors have considered sufficient outcome-neutral conditions (e.g. absence of floor or ceiling effects; positive controls; other quality checks) for ensuring that the obtained results are able to test the stated hypotheses or answer the stated research question(s).</span></div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div><span style="font-weight: 400;">The PCI RR website includes an</span><a href="https://rr.peercommunityin.org/help/guide_for_reviewers#h_6720026472751613309075757"><span style="font-weight: 400;"> </span><span style="font-weight: 400;">expanded description of these review criteria</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;">, additional</span><a href="https://rr.peercommunityin.org/help/guide_for_reviewers#h_7586915642301613635089357"><span style="font-weight: 400;"> </span><span style="font-weight: 400;">tips for reviewing a RR</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;">, and</span><a href="https://rr.peercommunityin.org/help/guide_for_reviewers"><span style="font-weight: 400;"> </span><span style="font-weight: 400;">complete reviewer guidelines</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;">.</span></div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div><span style="font-weight: 400;">Submissions that pass Stage 1 review are issued an in-principle acceptance (IPA), which guarantees a positive recommendation of the completed study if the authors adhere to the approved procedures and propose a defensible interpretation of the results. Completed manuscripts are then peer reviewed again at Stage 2, ideally by the same reviewers as Stage 1.</span></div>\r\n<div><span style="font-weight: 400;">{{programmaticRR_invitation_text}}</span></div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div><span style="font-weight: 400;">In the event of a favourable outcome, all editorial correspondence (reviews, recommender’s decisions, authors’ replies) and a recommendation text will be published by PCI RR under a CC-BY 4.0 license. If, after one or several rounds of review, the preprint is rejected, the editorial correspondence (and specifically your review) will NOT be published. You will be notified by e-mail at each stage in the procedure.</span></div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div><span style="font-weight: 400;">Stage 1 snapshots and manuscripts may be submitted with author names either revealed or masked, and may be published openly or embargoed in a recognised repository (such as the OSF) with a private viewable link. Note that to avoid any conflict of interests, where you know the identity of the submitting authors you should not accept to participate in the review process if the authors are close colleagues (people belonging to the same laboratory/unit/department in the last four years, people with whom you have published in the last four years, with whom you have received joint funding in the last four years, or with whom you are currently writing a manuscript, or submitting a grant proposal), or family members, friends, or anyone for whom bias might affect the nature of your evaluation.</span></div>\r\n<div><span style="font-weight: 400;">{{signedreview_invitation_text}}</span></div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div><span style="font-weight: 400;">We would be grateful if you could let us know whether, based on your reading of the snapshot, you would be willing to accept our invitation to review the manuscript within 5 working days of {{scheduledSubmissionLatestReviewStartDate}}, by</span> {{scheduledReviewDueDate}}<span style="font-weight: 400;">. </span></div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div><span style="font-weight: 400;">You can let us know using the link below whether you are willing to accept our invitation to review this article during the future dates above, or whether you prefer to decline, by clicking on the link below</span>. <span style="font-weight: 400;">If you accept the assignment then you will asked to entered a new password and logged onto the website. No further action is then required until the full Stage 1 manuscript is received, and we will notify you when this happens.</span></div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div><span style="font-weight: 400;">Best wishes,</span></div>\r\n<div><span style="font-weight: 400;">{{sender}} and the </span><a href="https://rr.peercommunityin.org/about/full_policies#h_4322855162061613307340646"><span style="font-weight: 400;">PCI RR Managing Board</span></a></div>
318	#ReminderRecommenderNewReviewersNeededStage1ScheduledSubmission	default	{{appName}}: Please invite additional Stage 1 reviewers - scheduled submission	Mail to recommender to ask him/her to send new referee invitations if <2 reviewers have accepted the review invitation (for scheduled submission)	<p>Dear {{destPerson}},</p>\n<p>Thanks for sending invitations to review the Stage 1 submission by {{articleAuthors}}. All invited reviewers have already received a reminder, but you still need to secure two agreed reviewers. Hence, we encourage you to invite further reviewers as following:</p>\n<p>1) Go to&nbsp;<a href="{{siteUrl}}">{{siteUrl}}</a>&nbsp;and log in</p>\n<p>2) Go to 'FOR RECOMMENDERS —&gt; PREPRINT(S) YOU ARE HANDLING' in the top menu.</p>\n<p>3) Click on the black 'INVITE A REVIEWER' button in the line corresponding to the preprint considered.</p>\n<p>-To invite a reviewer not included in the database of {{appName}}: click on the black ‘CHOOSE A REVIEWER OUTSIDE {{appName}} DATABASE’ button and complete the form (first name, last name and e-mail address of the reviewer). You can change the subject and/or the message if you wish. Then, click on the blue 'SEND E-MAIL' button at the end of the form.</p>\n<p>-To invite a reviewer from the {{appName}} database: click on the green ‘CHOOSE A REVIEWER FROM {{appName}} DATABASE’ button. A search engine and a filter based on thematic fields may be used. Select a reviewer by clicking on the black ‘ADD’ button at the right end of the corresponding line. You can modify the subject and/or the message of the e-mail before sending it. Then, click on the blue 'SEND E-MAIL' button at the end of the form.</p>\n<p>4) When you have sent invitations to all your chosen reviewers, click on the blue 'DONE 'button.</p>\n<p>If you need assistance in any way do not hesitate to ask us.</p>\n<p>Thanks in advance and thanks again for handling this preprint.</p>\n<p>Best regards</p>\n<p>The Managing Board of {{appName}}</p>
319	#ReviewerScheduledReviewCancelled	default	{{appName}}: Cancellation of scheduled review	Mail to reviewers indicating that the scheduled review has been cancelled	<p>Dear {{destPerson}},</p>\n<p>Thank you very much for agreeing to undertake a scheduled review of a Stage 1 Registered Report <span style="font-weight: 400;">provisionally entitled "<strong>{{articleTitle}}</strong>", which was expected be available for review by </span>{{scheduledSubmissionLatestReviewStartDate}}. For reference, the snapshot that you viewed can be&nbsp; downloaded at the following address: <a href="{{snapshotUrl}}">{{snapshotUrl}}</a></p>\n<p><strong>I am writing to let you know that the</strong> <strong>scheduled review process for this submission has been cancelled and your review is no longer required</strong>. This is most likely because the authors failed to submit a full submission before the required deadline, or because the recommender decided to desk reject the full submission without review. Desk rejections prior to in-depth review are rare for full submissions that follow a snapshot, but they can occasionally happen <strong>(a)</strong> where the full manuscript is judged by the recommender / Managing Board to deviate substantially and unexpectedly from the content of the snapshot, or <strong>(b)</strong> where the full manuscript falls a long way short of meeting at least one of the <a href="https://rr.peercommunityin.org/help/guide_for_authors#h_6720026472751613309075757" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Stage 1 review criteria</a> and there is no realistic prospect of the authors being able to revise the manuscript in time for the commencement of the scheduled review window.</p>\n<p>Thank you for your willingness to set aside time for this review, and please accept our apologies if this cancellation causes you any inconvenience.</p>\n<p>Yours sincerely,</p>\n<p>The Managing Board of {{appName}} Registered Reports</p>
320	#ReminderSubmitterScheduledSubmissionOverDue	default	{{appName}}: URGENT -- Your full Stage 1 submission is LATE	Mail to authors to remind them that the full Stage 1 manuscript based upon their snapshot submission is LATE	<p>Dear {{destPerson}}</p>\r\n<p>You previously submitted a Stage 1 snapshot entitled "<strong>{{articleTitle}}</strong>" to PCI RR. The recommender handling your submission has scheduled in-depth peer review to take place between {{scheduledSubmissionLatestReviewStartDate}} and {{scheduledReviewDueDate}}.</p>\r\n<p><strong>This is an URGENT reminder that the full Stage 1 manuscript associated with your snapshot was due yesterday and is now LATE. <span style="text-decoration: underline;">Please submit your manuscript within the next 24 hours to avoid the scheduled review process being cancelled. </span></strong>If you are experiencing difficulties and can no longer meet the original deadline, please contact your recommender immediately for advice by replying to this email.<strong><br></strong></p>\r\n<p>The full manuscript must be received in advance of the scheduled start of in-depth review to enable the recommender and Managing Board to perform a pre-review <a href="https://rr.peercommunityin.org/help/guide_for_recommenders#h_1245019342271613643227798" target="_blank" rel="noopener">triage assessment</a> of your full submission. This evaluation could require you to make revisions to your Stage 1 manuscript prior to the commencement in-depth review, so to ensure that the manuscript is review-ready by the scheduled review date, please be prepared to respond quickly to any revision invitations from the recommender between {{scheduledSubmissionDate}} and {{scheduledSubmissionLatestReviewStartDate}}. In rare cases where the full submission differs substantially from the research proposed in the snapshot, or falls a long way short of meeting at least one of the <a href="https://rr.peercommunityin.org/help/guide_for_authors#h_6720026472751613309075757" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Stage 1 review criteria</a>, the full submission could also be rejected outright, in which case scheduled in-depth review would be cancelled.</p>\r\n<p>Once you have submitted, and the submission has passed internal triage assessment by the Managing Board and recommender, the review process will commence. If you submit ahead of the submission deadline, reviewers may be informed but there is no guarantee that they will review the manuscript until the specified review period is reached.</p>\r\n<p>Follow this link to view your submission on the system: <a href="{{linkTarget}}">{{linkTarget}}</a></p>\r\n<p>When the full Stage 1 manuscript is written and ready to submit, please navigate to your submission on the PCI RR website and proceed as follows:</p>\r\n<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">a) Click the button "CHECK / EDIT REPORT SURVEY". This will take you to the submission checklist.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">b) In the submission checklist, change the response for Q3 to “I PREVIOUSLY SUBMITTED A STAGE 1 SNAPSHOT AND THE FULL MANUSCRIPT IS NOW READY FOR REVIEW”. <strong>Please make this change to the checklist first before changing any other answers.</strong><br></span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">c) Next, leave the URL for the snapshot in Q2 unchanged (to keep it preserved in our records) but change the response to Q1 to “COMPLETE STAGE 1 REPORT FOR REGULAR REVIEW”. The URL for the snapshot will then become fixed and uneditable.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">d) Check all other answers in the checklist (adjusting as necessary) then click the "Submit" button at the bottom of the page.<br></span></p>\r\n<p>e) This will close the submission checklist, but you have not completed your submission. Next, enter or update the URL to the <strong>full Stage 1 manuscript</strong> in the box entitled: "Full web address to most recent version of the manuscript". Then enter the version number in the box entitled: "Most recent version of the manuscript at the above".</p>\r\n<p>f) Finally, click the "Submit" button. <strong>You will have then submitted your full Stage 1 manuscript.</strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Sincerely, the PCI RR Managing Board</p>
321	#ReviewerFullPreprintStage1ScheduledSubmission	default	{{appName}}: Stage 1 manuscript now ready for review	Mail to agreed reviewers indicating the full Stage 1 manuscript associated with a snapshot is now available for scheduled review	<p>Dear {{destPerson}}</p>\r\n<p>Thank you very much for agreeing to undertake a scheduled review of a Stage 1 Registered Report&nbsp;<span style="font-weight: 400;"> entitled "<strong>{{articleTitle}}</strong>". The full Stage 1 manuscript is now available and can be viewed and downloaded from <a href="{{articleDoi}}">{{articleDoi}}</a>. </span></p>\r\n<p>The recommender handling the submission, {{recommenderPerson}}, has scheduled in-depth peer review to commence from {{scheduledSubmissionLatestReviewStartDate}} and you kindly agreed to provide a review no later than {{scheduledReviewDueDate}}. If you are receiving this email prior to the scheduled start of the review period, you are welcome to prepare your review early but please do not feel obliged to submit your review before the agreed deadline of {{scheduledReviewDueDate}}.</p>\r\n<p>For reference, the snapshot that you previously viewed can be also downloaded at the following address: <a href="{{snapshotUrl}}">{{snapshotUrl}}</a>. <strong>Please note that we are requesting a review only of <a href="{{articleDoi}}" target="_blank" rel="noopener">the full Stage 1 manuscript</a>.</strong> No review of the snapshot is required.</p>\r\n<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">The peer review process for Registered Reports occurs over two stages. Stage 1 submissions include an Introduction, Method, and Pilot Data (where applicable). In evaluating these manuscripts, we ask reviewers to assess:</span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">1A. The scientific validity of the research question(s)</span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">1B. The logic, rationale, and plausibility of the proposed hypotheses (where a submission proposes hypotheses)</span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">1C. The soundness and feasibility of the methodology and analysis pipeline (including statistical power analysis or alternative sampling plans where applicable)</span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">1D. Whether the clarity and degree of methodological detail is sufficient to closely replicate the proposed study procedures and analysis pipeline and to prevent undisclosed flexibility in the procedures and analyses</span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">1E. Whether the authors have considered sufficient outcome-neutral conditions (e.g. absence of floor or ceiling effects; positive controls; other quality checks) for ensuring that the obtained results are able to test the stated hypotheses or answer the stated research question(s).</span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">The PCI RR website includes an</span><a href="https://rr.peercommunityin.org/help/guide_for_reviewers#h_6720026472751613309075757"><span style="font-weight: 400;"> </span><span style="font-weight: 400;">expanded description of these review criteria</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;">, additional</span><a href="https://rr.peercommunityin.org/help/guide_for_reviewers#h_7586915642301613635089357"><span style="font-weight: 400;"> </span><span style="font-weight: 400;">tips for reviewing a RR</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;">, and</span><a href="https://rr.peercommunityin.org/help/guide_for_reviewers"><span style="font-weight: 400;"> </span><span style="font-weight: 400;">complete reviewer guidelines</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;">.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Submissions that pass Stage 1 review are issued an in-principle acceptance (IPA), which guarantees a positive recommendation of the completed study if the authors adhere to the approved procedures and propose a defensible interpretation of the results. Completed manuscripts are then peer reviewed again at Stage 2, ideally by the same reviewers as Stage 1.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">{{programmaticRR_invitation_text}}</span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">In the event of a favourable outcome, all editorial correspondence (reviews, recommender’s decisions, authors’ replies) and a recommendation text will be published by PCI RR under a CC-BY 4.0 license. If, after one or several rounds of review, the preprint is rejected, the editorial correspondence (and specifically your review) will NOT be published. You will be notified by e-mail at each stage in the procedure.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Stage 1 snapshots and manuscripts may be submitted with author names either revealed or masked, and may be published openly or embargoed in a recognised repository (such as the OSF) with a private viewable link. <br></span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">{{signedreview_invitation_text}}</span></p>\r\n<p>To submit your review, please login at the <a href="https://rr.peercommunityin.org/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">PCI RR website</a> and go to ‘For contributors —&gt; Your reviews’ in the top menu.</p>\r\n<p>If you have any questions in the meantime, please don't hesitate to contact me.</p>\r\n<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Many thanks,</span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">{{sender}}</span></p>
322	#ReviewersArticleStatusChangedStage1ScheduledSubmission	default	{{appName}}: Decision on a Stage 1 manuscript you reviewed - scheduled submission	Mail to reviewers to indicate the change of the status of the Stage 1 manuscript they reviewed (for scheduled submission)	<div>Dear {{destPerson}},</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>Thank you for agreeing to review the Stage 1 Registered Report entitled <strong>{{articleTitle}}</strong>. The status of this preprint is now: {{articleStatus}}. To view your review, the reviews of the other referees and the decision taken by the recommender, please follow this link <a href="{{linkTarget}}">{{linkTarget}}</a> or login to the {{appName}} website and go to 'For contributors —&gt; Your reviews' in the top menu, and then click the blue "VIEW/EDIT" button associated with the submission.</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div><span style="font-weight: 400;"><strong>Your feedback matters.</strong> If this is a final decision (Reject or In Principle Acceptance), then please take 5 minutes to leave anonymous feedback about your experience of the completed Stage 1 review process for this submission:</span> <a href="https://registeredreports.cardiff.ac.uk/feedback/feedback/decision_letter.php"><span style="font-weight: 400;">https://registeredreports.cardiff.ac.uk/feedback/feedback/decision_letter.php</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;"> Feedback from reviewers</span> helps us understand what we’re doing well, what we could do better, and how we can improve and innovate the evaluation of Registered Reports. <span style="font-weight: 400;">This feedback is collected by the </span><a href="https://registeredreports.cardiff.ac.uk/feedback/dashboards/"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Registered Reports Community Feedback</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;"> website which is an independent service and research project being undertaken by Cardiff University.<br></span></div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>We thank you for the time spent evaluating this preprint.</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>Yours sincerely,</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>The Managing Board of {{appName}}</div>
323	#ReminderRecommender2ReviewsReceivedCouldMakeDecision	default	{{appName}}: Editorial decision possible	Mail to recommender to ask not to wait too long for additional reviews	<p>Dear {{destPerson}},</p>\n<p>\nA few weeks ago, you should have received a notification that two reviews have been received for {{articleTitle}} by {{articleAuthors}}. We require a minimum of two reviews for each submission, so it is possible for you to make your editorial decision now. In the event that you are still waiting for additional reviews, we would like to ask you not to wait too long so as not to delay the article handling time. If you would like to make your decision without waiting for further reviews, please cancel the reviews that are not yet in, and then you will be able to make a decision.\n</p>\n<p>Thank you very much for handling this submission.</p>\n<p>Best regards,</p>\n<p>The Managing Board of {{appName}}</p>\n
324	#RecommenderStatusChangedUnderToRecommendedStage1ScheduledSubmission	default	{{appName}}: Article recommended - scheduled submission	Mail to recommender to indicate that the preprint is now recommended (for scheduled submission)	<p>Dear {{destPerson}},</p>\r\n<p>Your recommendation - along with the reviews - is now posted on the {{appName}} website.</p>\r\n<p>You can find it here: <a href="{{linkRecomm}}">{{linkRecomm}}</a></p>\r\n<p>You will find the reference to your recommendation and that of the recommended article.</p>\r\n<p>Do not hesitate to share the news via social networks (if you are on them), emails, websites, CVs, quotes, etc.</p>\r\n<p>Thanks again for recommending this article for {{appName}}.</p>\r\n<p>Yours sincerely,</p>\r\n<p>The Managing Board of {{appName}}</p>
325	#ReviewersArticleRecommendedStage1ScheduledSubmission	default	{{appName}}: Decision on a Stage 1 Registered Report you reviewed - scheduled submission	Mail to reviewers to indicate them that the Stage 1 manuscript they reviewed is now recommended (for scheduled submission)	<div>Dear {{destPerson}},</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>The Stage 1 Registered Report that you kindly reviewed for {{appName}} has now received in-principle acceptance. If the authors opted for a public recommendation then you will find the approved Stage 1 article - along with your reviews - now posted on PCI RR website: https://rr.peercommunityin.org/</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>If the authors opted for a private IPA decision then the Stage 1 manuscript, recommendation, and reviews are temporarily embargoed and will be made publicly available following Stage 2 review acceptance.</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div><span style="font-weight: 400;"><strong>Your feedback matters.</strong> Please take 5 minutes to leave anonymous feedback about your experience of the Stage 1 review process for this submission:</span> <a href="https://registeredreports.cardiff.ac.uk/feedback/feedback/decision_letter.php"><span style="font-weight: 400;">https://registeredreports.cardiff.ac.uk/feedback/feedback/decision_letter.php</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;"> Feedback from reviewers</span> helps us understand what we’re doing well, what we could do better, and how we can improve and innovate the evaluation of Registered Reports. <span style="font-weight: 400;">This feedback is collected by the </span><a href="https://registeredreports.cardiff.ac.uk/feedback/dashboards/"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Registered Reports Community Feedback</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;"> website which is an independent service and research project being undertaken by Cardiff University.</span></div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>Many thanks again for taking the time to support this important initiative. Once the authors have completed their research, we will likely invite you to re-evaluate the final article.</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>Yours sincerely,</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>The Managing Board of {{appName}}</div>
326	#SubmitterRecommendedPreprintStage1ScheduledSubmission	default	{{appName}}: Stage 1 in-principle acceptance of your manuscript - scheduled submission	Mail to author containing notification of a Stage 1 IPA decision (for scheduled submission)	<div>Dear {{destPerson}},</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>Thank you for submitting your manuscript to PCI RR for consideration as a Registered Report (Stage 1). After careful consideration, we are pleased to award in-principle acceptance (IPA) of your submission.</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>Please read the following letter carefully.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div><strong>Preregistration of the Stage 1 manuscript</strong>. As noted in the <a href="https://rr.peercommunityin.org/help/guide_for_authors#h_2238970114821613309509575" target="_blank" rel="noopener">author guidelines</a>, PCI RR has now registered your approved Stage 1 manuscript on the OSF, and the URL to this protocol is provided in the Stage 1 recommendation text. Depending on the selections you made in the Stage 1 submission checklist, your approved Stage 1 manuscript has been registered either publicly or under a private embargo. If you opted for a private embargo, note that the embargo will be released and the registered protocol made public when any one of the following conditions are met: submission of the Stage 2 manuscript; withdrawal of the submission and consequent triggering of a Withdrawn Registration; or natural expiry of the embargo at the end of the period you selected in the Stage 1 submission checklist.</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div><strong>Progressing to Stage 2.</strong> You may now move to Stage 2 and complete the study as approved. We would be grateful if you could now update the PCI RR Managing board (<a href="mailto:contact@rr.peercommunityin.org">contact@rr.peercommunityin.org</a>) as to the anticipated completion date of your study. This deadline can be readily altered in consultation with the Managing Board (e.g. in case of delays requiring additional time to complete the research). However, in the event that you should fail to submit the Stage 2 manuscript within 6 months of the mutually agreed deadline and also become non-responsive during this period to enquiries, then the manuscript will be considered by PCI RR to be de facto withdrawn, triggering publication of a Withdrawn Registration.</div>\r\n<div>Following completion of your study, we invite you to resubmit one or more Stage 2 Registered Reports, depending on whether this IPA applies to a regular RR (involving one Stage 2 output) or a programmatic RR (involving multiple Stage 2 outputs). If you are receiving IPA for a programmatic RR then please familiarise yourself with the <a href="https://rr.peercommunityin.org/help/guide_for_authors#h_52492857233251613309610581" target="_blank" rel="noopener">reporting requirements for programmatic RRs at Stage 2</a>.</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div><strong>Stage 2 review criteria (see <a href="https://rr.peercommunityin.org/help/guide_for_authors#h_6720026472751613309075757" target="_blank" rel="noopener">here</a>)</strong>. Please note that a Stage 2 manuscript can be rejected by PCI RR if the recommender and Managing Board consider any of the following conditions to be met:</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>The results were unable to test the authors' proposed hypotheses (or answer the proposed research question) by failing to meet any approved outcome-neutral criteria, such as the absence of floor and ceiling effects, success of positive controls or other quality checks</li>\r\n<li>The authors altered the Introduction, rationale, or hypotheses, as approved in the Stage 1 submission</li>\r\n<li>The authors failed to adhere to the registered study procedures or preregistered analyses (and see below concerning necessary deviations from protocol)</li>\r\n<li>Any <em>post hoc</em> (unregistered) analyses are either unjustified, insufficiently caveated, or overly dominant in shaping the authors' conclusions</li>\r\n<li>The authors' conclusions were not justified given the data obtained</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div><strong>Deviations from protocol.</strong> Please note that any deviation from the registered study procedures that is not approved in advance by the recommender and Managing Board could lead to rejection at Stage 2. In cases where the preregistered protocol must be altered after IPA due to unforeseen circumstances (e.g. change of equipment or unanticipated technical error), it is imperative that you consult the recommender immediately and prior to the completion of data collection, regardless of how minor the deviation may seem. Minor changes to the protocol that do not increase risk of bias are likely to be swiftly approved. In such cases, IPA would be preserved and the deviation reported in the Stage 2 submission.</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div><strong>Notification of PCI RR-interested journals.</strong> If you consented to notifying PCI RR-interested journals about your IPA then the complete list of <a href="https://rr.peercommunityin.org/about/pci_rr_interested_journals" target="_blank" rel="noopener">PCI RR-interested journals</a> will now be given access to the author names, stated contact details, Stage 1 reviews and recommendation text (provided you also consented to publish the reviews and recommendation at the point of IPA), as well as the URL to the Stage 1 manuscript that has been registered by PCI RR (even if preregistered under a private embargo).</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div><strong>Recommendation text</strong>. The recommender handling your submission has written a Stage 1 recommendation to accompany this decision letter. The recommendation is a short summary describing the context of the study and explaining why the article was accepted and is expected to make a valuable contribution. The recommendation will also state the URL to the registered Stage 1 manuscript on the OSF, the <a href="https://rr.peercommunityin.org/help/guide_for_authors#h_95790490510491613309490336" target="_blank" rel="noopener">level of bias control</a> that was reached in your submission, and will list all eligible <a href="https://rr.peercommunityin.org/about/pci_rr_friendly_journals" target="_blank" rel="noopener">PCI RR-friendly journals</a> that endorse this IPA decision and will later accept your approved Stage 2 manuscript(s) without further peer review. As noted in the author guidelines, the PCI RR Managing Board determines which PCI RR-friendly journals are eligible based on the disciplinary fit, word limit requirements, minimum pre-planned strength of evidence (e.g. level of statistical power), level of bias control achieved, and any other listed journal requirements (such as the acceptance of signed reviews only). <strong>If you opted for the Stage 1 recommendation to be made public at the point of IPA then you will find it now published on the <a href="https://rr.peercommunityin.org/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">PCI RR website under the heading "Latest Recommendations"</a>. </strong>However, if you opted to keep the Stage 1 recommendation and reviews private until Stage 2 acceptance, then they will not appear on the PCI RR website until the completion of Stage 2. For further information, please see <a href="https://osf.io/dcvj7/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">this tutorial </a>on how to interpret the different sections of the Stage 1 recommendation.</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div><span style="font-weight: 400;"><strong>Your feedback matters.</strong> Please take 5 minutes to leave anonymous feedback about your experience of the Stage 1 review process for this submission:</span> <a href="https://registeredreports.cardiff.ac.uk/feedback/feedback/decision_letter.php"><span style="font-weight: 400;">https://registeredreports.cardiff.ac.uk/feedback/feedback/decision_letter.php</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;"> Feedback from authors</span> helps us understand what we’re doing well, what we could do better, and how we can improve and innovate the review process for Registered Reports. <span style="font-weight: 400;">This feedback is collected by the </span><a href="https://registeredreports.cardiff.ac.uk/feedback/dashboards/"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Registered Reports Community Feedback</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;"> website which is an independent service and research project being undertaken by Cardiff University.</span></div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>Congratulations on achieving Stage 1 in-principle acceptance and thank you for using PCI RR.</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>Yours sincerely,</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>The PCI RR Managing Board</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>{{recommendationProcess}}</div>
327	#DefaultReviewInvitationRegisteredUserNewReviewerStage2	default	{{appName}}: Invitation to review a Stage 2 Registered Report	Invitation to a registered user who did NOT review the Stage 1 manuscript to review the corresponding Stage 2 submission	<div><span style="font-weight: 400;">Dear {{destPerson}},</span></div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div><span style="font-weight: 400;">A Stage 2 Registered Report entitled "<strong>{{articleTitle}}</strong>", has been submitted for potential recommendation by {{description}} (PCI RR) and I am writing to ask if you would kindly consider reviewing it for us. A clean version of the manuscript can be viewed and downloaded at the following address: <a href="{{art_doi}}">{{art_doi}}</a></span></div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div><span style="font-weight: 400;">As you may know, PCI RR is a free, non-commercial platform dedicated to the peer review of RR preprints. Once a preprint is reviewed and positively recommended by PCI RR, authors then have the option to submit their manuscript to a traditional journal, and the reviews are published on the PCI RR website. A growing</span><a href="https://eur03.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=https%3A%2F%2Frr.peercommunityin.org%2Fabout%2Fpci_rr_friendly_journals&amp;data=04%7C01%7Cchambersc1%40cardiff.ac.uk%7C3b0bd2172d19499a650008d934ba39af%7Cbdb74b3095684856bdbf06759778fcbc%7C1%7C0%7C637598796701743675%7CUnknown%7CTWFpbGZsb3d8eyJWIjoiMC4wLjAwMDAiLCJQIjoiV2luMzIiLCJBTiI6Ik1haWwiLCJXVCI6Mn0%3D%7C1000&amp;sdata=JXBq1vVpf1%2FrbMY0RB9K55orGA%2ByyWDd7mduvA7qQvc%3D&amp;reserved=0"><span style="font-weight: 400;"> </span><span style="font-weight: 400;">list of PCI RR-friendly journals</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;"> now immediately accept submissions recommended by PCI RR without further peer review.</span></div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div><span style="font-weight: 400;">The above manuscript previously received Stage 1 in-principle acceptance and is now being considered at Stage 2, which includes the content from Stage 1 plus the results and conclusions. Even though you were not a reviewer at Stage 1, I am writing to ask if you would consider evaluating the Stage 2 manuscript for us.&nbsp;</span></div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div><span style="font-weight: 400;">At Stage 2 we ask reviewers to assess:</span></div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div><span style="font-weight: 400;">2A. Whether the data are able to test the authors’ proposed hypotheses (or answer the proposed research question) by passing the approved outcome-neutral criteria, such as absence of floor and ceiling effects or success of positive controls or other quality checks.</span></div>\r\n<div><span style="font-weight: 400;">2B. Whether the introduction, rationale and stated hypotheses (where applicable) are the same as the approved Stage 1 submission. This can be readily assessed by referring to the </span><a href="{{Stage2vsStage1_trackedchangesURL}}"><strong>tracked-changes manuscript supplied by the authors</strong></a><span style="font-weight: 400;"><a href="{{Stage2vsStage1_trackedchangesURL}}">.</a> </span></div>\r\n<div><span style="font-weight: 400;">{{Stage2_Stage1recommendationtext}}</span></div>\r\n<div><span style="font-weight: 400;">2C. Whether the authors adhered precisely to the registered study procedures. For reference, the registered Stage 1 manuscript, unchanged from the point of in-principle acceptance, may be downloaded </span><a href="{{Stage1_registeredURL}}"><strong>here</strong></a><span style="font-weight: 400;">.</span></div>\r\n<div><span style="font-weight: 400;">2D. Where applicable, whether any unregistered exploratory analyses are justified, methodologically sound, and informative.</span></div>\r\n<div><span style="font-weight: 400;">2E. Whether the authors’ conclusions are justified given the evidence.</span></div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div><span style="font-weight: 400;">The PCI RR website includes an</span><a href="https://rr.peercommunityin.org/help/guide_for_reviewers#h_6720026472751613309075757"><span style="font-weight: 400;"> </span><span style="font-weight: 400;">expanded description of these review criteria</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;">, additional</span><a href="https://rr.peercommunityin.org/help/guide_for_reviewers#h_7586915642301613635089357"><span style="font-weight: 400;"> </span><span style="font-weight: 400;">tips for reviewing a RR</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;">, and</span><a href="https://rr.peercommunityin.org/help/guide_for_reviewers"><span style="font-weight: 400;"> </span><span style="font-weight: 400;">complete reviewer guidelines</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;">. To ensure swift handling of submissions, the requested review time is </span><strong>{{reviewDuration}}</strong><span style="font-weight: 400;">, but if you are unable to review the manuscript within this time then please let me know by reply email and we can extend the timeframe.&nbsp;</span></div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div><span style="font-weight: 400;">Please note that the statistical significance, novelty, or perceived importance of findings will not factor into editorial decisions.</span></div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div><span style="font-weight: 400;">{{signedreview_invitation_text}}&nbsp;</span></div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div><span style="font-weight: 400;">In the event of a favourable outcome, all editorial correspondence (Stage 2 reviews, recommender’s decisions, authors’ replies) and a recommendation text will be published by PCI RR under a CC-BY 4.0 license. If, after one or several rounds of review, the Stage 2 manuscript is rejected, the editorial correspondence (and specifically your Stage 2 review) will NOT be published. You will be notified by e-mail at each stage in the procedure.</span></div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div><span style="font-weight: 400;">{{programmaticRR_invitation_text}}</span></div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div><span style="font-weight: 400;">Note that to avoid any conflict of interests, where you know the identity of the submitting authors you should not accept to evaluate this submission if the authors are close colleagues (people belonging to the same laboratory/unit/department in the last four years, people with whom you have published in the last four years, with whom you have received joint funding in the last four years, or with whom you are currently writing a manuscript, or submitting a grant proposal).</span></div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div><span style="font-weight: 400;">I would be grateful if you could let me know as soon as possible whether you are willing to accept my invitation to review this article, or whether you would prefer to decline, by clicking on the link below or by logging onto the PCI RR website and going to 'For contributors —&gt; Invitation(s) to review a report' in the top menu. If you are a new user, you will be asked to create a password before being logged in. If you are reviewing a revised manuscript, you will find the authors' response to reviewers linked on the website.</span></div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div><span style="font-weight: 400;">Many thanks for considering this review request.</span></div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div><span style="font-weight: 400;">Best wishes,</span></div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div><span style="font-weight: 400;">{{sender}}<br></span></div>
328	#DefaultReviewInvitationRegisteredUserReturningReviewerStage2	default	{{appName}}: Invitation to review a Stage 2 submission that you previously reviewed at Stage 1	Invitation to a registered user who reviewed a Stage 1 manuscript to review the corresponding Stage 2 submission	<div><span style="font-weight: 400;">Dear {{destPerson}},</span></div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div><span style="font-weight: 400;">Thank you for reviewing previously for Peer Community in Registered Reports (PCI RR).</span></div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div><span style="font-weight: 400;">Following in-principle acceptance (IPA) of the Stage 1 submission that you reviewed, the authors have submitted a follow-up Stage 2 manuscript entitled "</span><strong>{{art_title}}</strong><span style="font-weight: 400;">". The Stage 2 manuscript contains the content from Stage 1 plus the results and conclusions, and I am writing to ask if you would kindly consider reviewing it for us. A clean version of the Stage 2 manuscript can be viewed and downloaded at the following address: <a href="{{art_doi}}">{{art_doi}}</a></span></div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div><span style="font-weight: 400;">{{signedreview_invitation_text}}&nbsp;</span></div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div><span style="font-weight: 400;">For reference, the registered Stage 1 manuscript, unchanged from the point of IPA, may be downloaded </span><a title="here" href="{{Stage1_registeredURL}}"><strong>here</strong></a><span style="font-weight: 400;">. To make the review process as easy as possible, a tracked-changes version of the Stage 2 manuscript is also available </span><a title="here" href="{{Stage2vsStage1_trackedchangesURL}}"><strong>here</strong></a><span style="font-weight: 400;"> that shows all text changes between the approved Stage 1 manuscript and the corresponding sections of the Stage 2 manuscript. </span><span style="font-weight: 400;">{{Stage2_Stage1recommendationtext}}</span></div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div><span style="font-weight: 400;">{{programmaticRR_invitation_text}}<br></span></div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div><span style="font-weight: 400;">In evaluating Stage 2 manuscripts, we ask reviewers to assess:</span></div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><span style="font-weight: 400;">2A. Whether the data are able to test the authors’ proposed hypotheses (or answer the proposed research question) by passing the approved outcome-neutral criteria, such as absence of floor and ceiling </span><span style="font-weight: 400;">effects or success of positive controls or other quality checks.</span></li>\r\n<li><span style="font-weight: 400;">2B. Whether the introduction, rationale and stated hypotheses (where applicable) are the same as the approved Stage 1 submission. This can be readily assessed by referring to the </span><a title="tracked-changes manuscript supplied by the authors" href="{{Stage2vsStage1_trackedchangesURL}}"><strong>tracked-changes manuscript supplied by the authors</strong><span style="font-weight: 400;">.</span></a></li>\r\n<li><span style="font-weight: 400;">2C. Whether the authors adhered precisely to the registered study procedures.</span></li>\r\n<li><span style="font-weight: 400;">2D. Where applicable, whether any unregistered exploratory analyses are justified, methodologically sound, and informative.</span></li>\r\n<li><span style="font-weight: 400;">2E. Whether the authors’ conclusions are justified given the evidence.</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div><span style="font-weight: 400;">The PCI RR website includes an</span><a href="https://rr.peercommunityin.org/help/guide_for_reviewers#h_6720026472751613309075757"><span style="font-weight: 400;"> </span><span style="font-weight: 400;">expanded description of these review criteria</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;">, additional</span><a href="https://rr.peercommunityin.org/help/guide_for_reviewers#h_7586915642301613635089357"><span style="font-weight: 400;"> </span><span style="font-weight: 400;">tips for reviewing a RR</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;">, and</span><a href="https://rr.peercommunityin.org/help/guide_for_reviewers"><span style="font-weight: 400;"> </span><span style="font-weight: 400;">complete reviewer guidelines</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;">. To ensure swift handling of submissions, the requested review time is </span><strong>{{reviewDuration}}</strong><span style="font-weight: 400;">, but if you are unable to review the manuscript within this time then please let me know by reply email and we can extend the timeframe. Where possible, it is important that the same reviewers evaluate submissions at Stage 1 and Stage 2.</span></div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div><span style="font-weight: 400;">Please note that the statistical significance, novelty, or perceived importance of findings will not factor into editorial decisions.</span></div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div><span style="font-weight: 400;">In the event of a favourable outcome, all editorial correspondence (Stage 2 reviews, recommender’s decisions, authors’ replies) and a recommendation text will be published by PCI RR under a CC-BY 4.0 license. If, after one or several rounds of review, the Stage 2 manuscript is rejected, the editorial correspondence (and specifically your Stage 2 review) will NOT be published. You will be notified by e-mail at each stage in the procedure.</span></div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div><span style="font-weight: 400;">Note that to avoid any conflict of interests, where you know the identity of the submitting authors you should not accept to evaluate this submission if the authors are close colleagues (people belonging to the same laboratory/unit/department in the last four years, people with whom you have published in the last four years, with whom you have received joint funding in the last four years, or with whom you are currently writing a manuscript, or submitting a grant proposal).</span></div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div><span style="font-weight: 400;">Please let me know as soon as possible whether you are willing to accept my invitation to review this article, or whether you would prefer to decline, by clicking on the link below or by logging onto the {{longname}} website and going to 'For contributors —&gt; Invitation(s) to review a report' in the top menu.</span></div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div><span style="font-weight: 400;">Many thanks for considering this re-review request and for helping to support PCI RR.</span></div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div><span style="font-weight: 400;">Best wishes,</span></div>\r\n<div><span style="font-weight: 400;">{{sender}}</span></div>
329	#DefaultReviewInvitationNewUserStage2	default	{{appName}}: Invitation to review a Stage 2 Registered Report	Invitation to a new user who did NOT review the Stage 1 manuscript to review the corresponding Stage 2 submission	<div><span style="font-weight: 400;">Dear {{destPerson}},</span></div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div><span style="font-weight: 400;">A Stage 2 Registered Report entitled "<strong>{{articleTitle}}</strong>", has been submitted for potential recommendation by {{description}} (PCI RR) and I am writing to ask if you would kindly consider reviewing it for us. A clean version of the manuscript can be viewed and downloaded at the following address: <a href="{{art_doi}}">{{art_doi}}</a></span></div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div><span style="font-weight: 400;">As you may know, Registered Reports (RRs) are a form of empirical research article in which manuscripts containing a study proposal are reviewed prior to data collection or analysis. The aim of this initiative is to minimise publication bias and reporting bias, while also allowing the flexibility to conduct exploratory (unregistered) analyses and report serendipitous findings. Submitted manuscripts can propose novel studies or direct replications of previous studies.</span></div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div><span style="font-weight: 400;">PCI RR is a free, non-commercial platform dedicated to the peer review of RR preprints. Once a preprint is reviewed and positively recommended by PCI RR, authors then have the option to submit their manuscript to a traditional journal, and the reviews are published on the PCI RR website. A growing</span><a href="https://eur03.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=https%3A%2F%2Frr.peercommunityin.org%2Fabout%2Fpci_rr_friendly_journals&amp;data=04%7C01%7Cchambersc1%40cardiff.ac.uk%7C3b0bd2172d19499a650008d934ba39af%7Cbdb74b3095684856bdbf06759778fcbc%7C1%7C0%7C637598796701743675%7CUnknown%7CTWFpbGZsb3d8eyJWIjoiMC4wLjAwMDAiLCJQIjoiV2luMzIiLCJBTiI6Ik1haWwiLCJXVCI6Mn0%3D%7C1000&amp;sdata=JXBq1vVpf1%2FrbMY0RB9K55orGA%2ByyWDd7mduvA7qQvc%3D&amp;reserved=0"><span style="font-weight: 400;"> </span><span style="font-weight: 400;">list of PCI RR-friendly journals</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;"> now immediately accept submissions recommended by PCI RR without further peer review.</span></div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div><span style="font-weight: 400;">The above manuscript previously received Stage 1 in-principle acceptance and is now being considered at Stage 2, which includes the content from Stage 1 plus the results and conclusions. Even though you were not a reviewer at Stage 1, I am writing to ask if you would consider evaluating the Stage 2 manuscript for us.&nbsp;</span></div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div><span style="font-weight: 400;">At Stage 2 we ask reviewers to assess:</span></div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div><span style="font-weight: 400;">2A. Whether the data are able to test the authors’ proposed hypotheses (or answer the proposed research question) by passing the approved outcome-neutral criteria, such as absence of floor and ceiling effects or success of positive controls or other quality checks.</span></div>\r\n<div><span style="font-weight: 400;">2B. Whether the introduction, rationale and stated hypotheses (where applicable) are the same as the approved Stage 1 submission. This can be readily assessed by referring to the </span><a href="{{Stage2vsStage1_trackedchangesURL}}"><strong>tracked-changes manuscript supplied by the authors</strong><span style="font-weight: 400;">. </span></a></div>\r\n<div><span style="font-weight: 400;">{{Stage2_Stage1recommendationtext}}</span></div>\r\n<div><span style="font-weight: 400;">2C. Whether the authors adhered precisely to the registered study procedures. For reference, the registered Stage 1 manuscript, unchanged from the point of in-principle acceptance, may be downloaded </span><a href="{{Stage1_registeredURL}}"><strong>here</strong><span style="font-weight: 400;">.</span></a></div>\r\n<div><span style="font-weight: 400;">2D. Where applicable, whether any unregistered exploratory analyses are justified, methodologically sound, and informative.</span></div>\r\n<div><span style="font-weight: 400;">2E. Whether the authors’ conclusions are justified given the evidence.</span></div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div><span style="font-weight: 400;">The PCI RR website includes an</span><a href="https://rr.peercommunityin.org/help/guide_for_reviewers#h_6720026472751613309075757"><span style="font-weight: 400;"> </span><span style="font-weight: 400;">expanded description of these review criteria</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;">, additional</span><a href="https://rr.peercommunityin.org/help/guide_for_reviewers#h_7586915642301613635089357"><span style="font-weight: 400;"> </span><span style="font-weight: 400;">tips for reviewing a RR</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;">, and</span><a href="https://rr.peercommunityin.org/help/guide_for_reviewers"><span style="font-weight: 400;"> </span><span style="font-weight: 400;">complete reviewer guidelines</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;">. To ensure swift handling of submissions, the requested review time is </span><strong>{{reviewDuration}}</strong><span style="font-weight: 400;">, but if you are unable to review the manuscript within this time then please let me know by reply email and we can extend the timeframe.&nbsp;</span></div>\r\n<div><span style="font-weight: 400;">Please note that the statistical significance, novelty, or perceived importance of findings will not factor into editorial decisions.</span></div>\r\n<div><span style="font-weight: 400;">{{signedreview_invitation_text}}&nbsp;</span></div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div><span style="font-weight: 400;">In the event of a favourable outcome, all editorial correspondence (Stage 2 reviews, recommender’s decisions, authors’ replies) and a recommendation text will be published by PCI RR under a CC-BY 4.0 license. If, after one or several rounds of review, the Stage 2 manuscript is rejected, the editorial correspondence (and specifically your Stage 2 review) will NOT be published. You will be notified by e-mail at each stage in the procedure.</span></div>\r\n<div><span style="font-weight: 400;">{{programmaticRR_invitation_text}}</span></div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div><span style="font-weight: 400;">Note that to avoid any conflict of interests, where you know the identity of the submitting authors you should not accept to evaluate this submission if the authors are close colleagues (people belonging to the same laboratory/unit/department in the last four years, people with whom you have published in the last four years, with whom you have received joint funding in the last four years, or with whom you are currently writing a manuscript, or submitting a grant proposal).</span></div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div><span style="font-weight: 400;">I would be most grateful if you could let me know using the link below whether you are willing to accept our invitation to review this article, or whether you would prefer to decline. If you accept the assignment then once you have entered a new password and logged onto the website, please go to 'For contributors —&gt; Invitation(s) to review a report' in the top menu. If you are a new user, you will be asked to create a password before being logged in. If you are reviewing a revised manuscript, you will find the authors' response to reviewers linked on the website.</span></div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div><span style="font-weight: 400;">Many thanks for considering this review request.</span></div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div><span style="font-weight: 400;">Best wishes,</span></div>\r\n<div><span style="font-weight: 400;">{{sender}}<br></span></div>
330	#ReminderReviewInvitationRegisteredUserNewReviewerStage2	default	{{appName}}: Invitation to review a Stage 2 manuscript - reminder	Reminder invitation to a registered user who did NOT review the Stage 1 manuscript to review the corresponding Stage 2 submission	<div><span style="font-weight: 400;">Dear {{destPerson}},</span></div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>This is a kind reminder about the review invitation below.</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div><span style="font-weight: 400;">A Stage 2 Registered Report entitled "<strong>{{articleTitle}}</strong>", has been submitted for potential recommendation by {{description}} (PCI RR) and I am writing to ask if you would kindly consider reviewing it for us. A clean version of the manuscript can be viewed and downloaded at the following address: <a href="{{art_doi}}">{{art_doi}}</a></span></div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div><span style="font-weight: 400;">As you may know, PCI RR is a free, non-commercial platform dedicated to the peer review of RR preprints. Once a preprint is reviewed and positively recommended by PCI RR, authors then have the option to submit their manuscript to a traditional journal, and the reviews are published on the PCI RR website. A growing</span><a href="https://eur03.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=https%3A%2F%2Frr.peercommunityin.org%2Fabout%2Fpci_rr_friendly_journals&amp;data=04%7C01%7Cchambersc1%40cardiff.ac.uk%7C3b0bd2172d19499a650008d934ba39af%7Cbdb74b3095684856bdbf06759778fcbc%7C1%7C0%7C637598796701743675%7CUnknown%7CTWFpbGZsb3d8eyJWIjoiMC4wLjAwMDAiLCJQIjoiV2luMzIiLCJBTiI6Ik1haWwiLCJXVCI6Mn0%3D%7C1000&amp;sdata=JXBq1vVpf1%2FrbMY0RB9K55orGA%2ByyWDd7mduvA7qQvc%3D&amp;reserved=0"><span style="font-weight: 400;"> </span><span style="font-weight: 400;">list of PCI RR-friendly journals</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;"> now immediately accept submissions recommended by PCI RR without further peer review.</span></div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div><span style="font-weight: 400;">The above manuscript previously received Stage 1 in-principle acceptance and is now being considered at Stage 2, which includes the content from Stage 1 plus the results and conclusions. Even though you were not a reviewer at Stage 1, I am writing to ask if you would consider evaluating the Stage 2 manuscript for us.&nbsp;</span></div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div><span style="font-weight: 400;">At Stage 2 we ask reviewers to assess:</span></div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div><span style="font-weight: 400;">2A. Whether the data are able to test the authors’ proposed hypotheses (or answer the proposed research question) by passing the approved outcome-neutral criteria, such as absence of floor and ceiling effects or success of positive controls or other quality checks.</span></div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div><span style="font-weight: 400;">2B. Whether the introduction, rationale and stated hypotheses (where applicable) are the same as the approved Stage 1 submission. This can be readily assessed by referring to the </span><a href="{{Stage2vsStage1_trackedchangesURL}}"><strong>tracked-changes manuscript supplied by the authors</strong></a><span style="font-weight: 400;"><a href="{{Stage2vsStage1_trackedchangesURL}}">.</a> </span><span style="font-weight: 400;">{{Stage2_Stage1recommendationtext}}</span></div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div><span style="font-weight: 400;">2C. Whether the authors adhered precisely to the registered study procedures. For reference, the registered Stage 1 manuscript, unchanged from the point of in-principle acceptance, may be downloaded </span><a href="{{Stage1_registeredURL}}"><strong>here</strong></a><span style="font-weight: 400;">.</span></div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div><span style="font-weight: 400;">2D. Where applicable, whether any unregistered exploratory analyses are justified, methodologically sound, and informative.</span></div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div><span style="font-weight: 400;">2E. Whether the authors’ conclusions are justified given the evidence.</span></div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div><span style="font-weight: 400;">The PCI RR website includes an</span><a href="https://rr.peercommunityin.org/help/guide_for_reviewers#h_6720026472751613309075757"><span style="font-weight: 400;"> </span><span style="font-weight: 400;">expanded description of these review criteria</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;">, additional</span><a href="https://rr.peercommunityin.org/help/guide_for_reviewers#h_7586915642301613635089357"><span style="font-weight: 400;"> </span><span style="font-weight: 400;">tips for reviewing a RR</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;">, and</span><a href="https://rr.peercommunityin.org/help/guide_for_reviewers"><span style="font-weight: 400;"> </span><span style="font-weight: 400;">complete reviewer guidelines</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;">. To ensure swift handling of submissions, the requested review time is </span><strong>{{reviewDuration}}</strong><span style="font-weight: 400;">, but if you are unable to review the manuscript within this time then please let me know by reply email and we can extend the timeframe.&nbsp;</span></div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div><span style="font-weight: 400;">Please note that the statistical significance, novelty, or perceived importance of findings will not factor into editorial decisions.</span></div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div><span style="font-weight: 400;">{{signedreview_invitation_text}}&nbsp;</span></div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div><span style="font-weight: 400;">In the event of a favourable outcome, all editorial correspondence (Stage 2 reviews, recommender’s decisions, authors’ replies) and a recommendation text will be published by PCI RR under a CC-BY 4.0 license. If, after one or several rounds of review, the Stage 2 manuscript is rejected, the editorial correspondence (and specifically your Stage 2 review) will NOT be published. You will be notified by e-mail at each stage in the procedure.</span></div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div><span style="font-weight: 400;">{{programmaticRR_invitation_text}}</span></div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div><span style="font-weight: 400;">Note that to avoid any conflict of interests, where you know the identity of the submitting authors you should not accept to evaluate this submission if the authors are close colleagues (people belonging to the same laboratory/unit/department in the last four years, people with whom you have published in the last four years, with whom you have received joint funding in the last four years, or with whom you are currently writing a manuscript, or submitting a grant proposal).</span></div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div><span style="font-weight: 400;">I would be grateful if you could let me know as soon as possible whether you are willing to accept my invitation to review this article, or whether you would prefer to decline, by clicking on the link below or by logging onto the PCI RR website and going to 'For contributors —&gt; Invitation(s) to review a report' in the top menu. If you are reviewing a revised manuscript, you will find the authors' response to reviewers linked on the website.</span></div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div><span style="font-weight: 400;">Many thanks for considering this review request.</span></div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div><span style="font-weight: 400;">Best wishes,</span></div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div><span style="font-weight: 400;">{{sender}} and the PCI RR Managing Board</span></div>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>
331	#ReminderReviewInvitationRegisteredUserReturningReviewerStage2	default	{{appName}}: Invitation to review a Stage 2 submission that you previously reviewed at Stage 1 - reminder	Reminder invitation to a registered user who reviewed a Stage 1 manuscript to review the corresponding Stage 2 submission	<div><span style="font-weight: 400;">Dear {{destPerson}},</span></div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div><span style="font-weight: 400;">Thank you for reviewing previously for Peer Community in Registered Reports (PCI RR). This is a kind reminder about the following review invitation.<br></span></div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div><span style="font-weight: 400;">Following in-principle acceptance (IPA) of the Stage 1 submission that you reviewed, the authors have submitted a follow-up Stage 2 manuscript entitled "</span><strong>{{art_title}}</strong><span style="font-weight: 400;">". The Stage 2 manuscript contains the content from Stage 1 plus the results and conclusions, and I am writing to ask if you would kindly consider reviewing it for us. A clean version of the Stage 2 manuscript can be viewed and downloaded at the following address: <a href="{{art_doi}}">{{art_doi}}</a>&nbsp;<br></span></div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div><span style="font-weight: 400;">{{signedreview_invitation_text}}&nbsp;</span></div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div><span style="font-weight: 400;">For reference, the registered Stage 1 manuscript, unchanged from the point of IPA, may be downloaded </span><a title="here" href="{{Stage1_registeredURL}}"><strong>here</strong></a><span style="font-weight: 400;">. To make the review process as easy as possible, a tracked-changes version of the Stage 2 manuscript is also available </span><a title="here" href="{{Stage2vsStage1_trackedchangesURL}}" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><strong>here</strong></a><span style="font-weight: 400;"> that shows all text changes between the approved Stage 1 manuscript and the corresponding sections of the Stage 2 manuscript. </span><span style="font-weight: 400;">{{Stage2_Stage1recommendationtext}}</span></div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div><span style="font-weight: 400;">{{programmaticRR_invitation_text}}<br></span></div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div><span style="font-weight: 400;">In evaluating Stage 2 manuscripts, we ask reviewers to assess:</span></div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div><span style="font-weight: 400;">2A. Whether the data are able to test the authors’ proposed hypotheses (or answer the proposed research question) by passing the approved outcome-neutral criteria, such as absence of floor and ceiling effects or success of positive controls or other quality checks.</span></div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div><span style="font-weight: 400;">2B. Whether the introduction, rationale and stated hypotheses (where applicable) are the same as the approved Stage 1 submission. This can be readily assessed by referring to the </span><a title="tracked-changes manuscript supplied by the authors" href="{{Stage2vsStage1_trackedchangesURL}}"><strong>tracked-changes manuscript supplied by the authors</strong><span style="font-weight: 400;">.</span></a></div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div><span style="font-weight: 400;">2C. Whether the authors adhered precisely to the registered study procedures.</span></div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div><span style="font-weight: 400;">2D. Where applicable, whether any unregistered exploratory analyses are justified, methodologically sound, and informative.</span></div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div><span style="font-weight: 400;">2E. Whether the authors’ conclusions are justified given the evidence.</span></div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div><span style="font-weight: 400;">The PCI RR website includes an</span><a href="https://rr.peercommunityin.org/help/guide_for_reviewers#h_6720026472751613309075757"><span style="font-weight: 400;"> </span><span style="font-weight: 400;">expanded description of these review criteria</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;">, additional</span><a href="https://rr.peercommunityin.org/help/guide_for_reviewers#h_7586915642301613635089357"><span style="font-weight: 400;"> </span><span style="font-weight: 400;">tips for reviewing a RR</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;">, and</span><a href="https://rr.peercommunityin.org/help/guide_for_reviewers"><span style="font-weight: 400;"> </span><span style="font-weight: 400;">complete reviewer guidelines</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;">. To ensure swift handling of submissions, the requested review time is </span><strong>{{reviewDuration}}</strong><span style="font-weight: 400;">, but if you are unable to review the manuscript within this time then please let me know by reply email and we can extend the timeframe. Where possible, it is important that the same reviewers evaluate submissions at Stage 1 and Stage 2.</span></div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div><span style="font-weight: 400;">Please note that the statistical significance, novelty, or perceived importance of findings will not factor into editorial decisions.</span></div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div><span style="font-weight: 400;">In the event of a favourable outcome, all editorial correspondence (Stage 2 reviews, recommender’s decisions, authors’ replies) and a recommendation text will be published by PCI RR under a CC-BY 4.0 license. If, after one or several rounds of review, the Stage 2 manuscript is rejected, the editorial correspondence (and specifically your Stage 2 review) will NOT be published. You will be notified by e-mail at each stage in the procedure.</span></div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div><span style="font-weight: 400;">Note that to avoid any conflict of interests, where you know the identity of the submitting authors you should not accept to evaluate this submission if the authors are close colleagues (people belonging to the same laboratory/unit/department in the last four years, people with whom you have published in the last four years, with whom you have received joint funding in the last four years, or with whom you are currently writing a manuscript, or submitting a grant proposal).</span></div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div><span style="font-weight: 400;">I would be grateful if you could let me know as soon as possible whether you are willing to accept our invitation to review this article, or whether you would prefer to decline, by clicking on the link below or by logging onto the {{longname}} website and going to 'For contributors —&gt; Invitation(s) to review a report' in the top menu.</span></div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div><span style="font-weight: 400;">Many thanks for considering this re-review request and for helping to support PCI RR.</span></div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div><span style="font-weight: 400;">Best wishes,</span></div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div><span style="font-weight: 400;">{{sender}} and the PCI RR Managing Board</span></div>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>
332	#ReminderReviewerReviewInvitationNewUserStage2	default	{{appName}}: Invitation to review a Stage 2 manuscript - reminder	Reminder invitation to a new user who did NOT review the Stage 1 manuscript to review the corresponding Stage 2 submission	<p>Dear <span style="font-weight: 400;">{{destPerson}}</span>,&nbsp;&nbsp;</p><p>This is a kind reminder about the following review invitation.</p><div><span style="font-weight: 400;">A Stage 2 Registered Report entitled "<strong>{{articleTitle}}</strong>", has been submitted for potential recommendation by {{description}} (PCI RR) and I am writing to ask if you would kindly consider reviewing it for us. A clean version of the manuscript can be viewed and downloaded at the following address: <a href="{{art_doi}}" target="_blank" rel="noopener">{{art_doi}}</a></span></div><div>&nbsp;</div><div><span style="font-weight: 400;">As you may know, Registered Reports (RRs) are a form of empirical research article in which manuscripts containing a study proposal are reviewed prior to data collection or analysis. The aim of this initiative is to minimise publication bias and reporting bias, while also allowing the flexibility to conduct exploratory (unregistered) analyses and report serendipitous findings. Submitted manuscripts can propose novel studies or direct replications of previous studies.</span></div><div>&nbsp;</div><div><span style="font-weight: 400;">PCI RR is a free, non-commercial platform dedicated to the peer review of RR preprints. Once a preprint is reviewed and positively recommended by PCI RR, authors then have the option to submit their manuscript to a traditional journal, and the reviews are published on the PCI RR website. A growing</span><a href="https://eur03.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=https%3A%2F%2Frr.peercommunityin.org%2Fabout%2Fpci_rr_friendly_journals&amp;data=04%7C01%7Cchambersc1%40cardiff.ac.uk%7C3b0bd2172d19499a650008d934ba39af%7Cbdb74b3095684856bdbf06759778fcbc%7C1%7C0%7C637598796701743675