f="{{Stage1_registeredURL}}"><strong>here</strong><span style="font-weight: 400;">.</span></a></div><div>&nbsp;</div><div><span style="font-weight: 400;">2D. Where applicable, whether any unregistered exploratory analyses are justified, methodologically sound, and informative.</span></div><div>&nbsp;</div><div><span style="font-weight: 400;">2E. Whether the authors’ conclusions are justified given the evidence.</span></div><div>&nbsp;</div><div><span style="font-weight: 400;">The PCI RR website includes an</span><a href="https://rr.peercommunityin.org/help/guide_for_reviewers#h_6720026472751613309075757"><span style="font-weight: 400;"> </span><span style="font-weight: 400;">expanded description of these review criteria</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;">, additional</span><a href="https://rr.peercommunityin.org/help/guide_for_reviewers#h_7586915642301613635089357"><span style="font-weight: 400;"> </span><span style="font-weight: 400;">tips for reviewing a RR</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;">, and</span><a href="https://rr.peercommunityin.org/help/guide_for_reviewers"><span style="font-weight: 400;"> </span><span style="font-weight: 400;">complete reviewer guidelines</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;">. To ensure swift handling of submissions, the requested review time is </span><strong>{{reviewDuration}}</strong><span style="font-weight: 400;">, but if you are unable to review the manuscript within this time then please let me know by reply email and we can extend the timeframe.&nbsp;</span></div><div>&nbsp;</div><div><span style="font-weight: 400;">Please note that the statistical significance, novelty, or perceived importance of findings will not factor into editorial decisions.</span></div><div>&nbsp;</div><div><span style="font-weight: 400;">{{signedreview_invitation_text}}&nbsp;</span></div><div>&nbsp;</div><div><span style="font-weight: 400;">In the event of a favourable outcome, all editorial correspondence (Stage 2 reviews, recommender’s decisions, authors’ replies) and a recommendation text will be published by PCI RR under a CC-BY 4.0 license. If, after one or several rounds of review, the Stage 2 manuscript is rejected, the editorial correspondence (and specifically your Stage 2 review) will NOT be published. You will be notified by e-mail at each stage in the procedure.</span></div><div>&nbsp;</div><div><span style="font-weight: 400;">{{programmaticRR_invitation_text}}</span></div><div>&nbsp;</div><div><span style="font-weight: 400;">Note that to avoid any conflict of interests, where you know the identity of the submitting authors you should not accept to evaluate this submission if the authors are close colleagues (people belonging to the same laboratory/unit/department in the last four years, people with whom you have published in the last four years, with whom you have received joint funding in the last four years, or with whom you are currently writing a manuscript, or submitting a grant proposal).</span></div><div>&nbsp;</div><div><span style="font-weight: 400;">I would be most grateful if you could let me know using the link below whether you are willing to accept our invitation to review this article, or whether you would prefer to decline. If you accept the assignment then once you have entered a new password and logged onto the website, please go to 'For contributors —&gt; Invitation(s) to review a report' in the top menu. If you are reviewing a revised manuscript, you will find the authors' response to reviewers linked on the website.</span></div><div>&nbsp;</div><div><span style="font-weight: 400;">Many thanks for considering this review request.</span></div><div>&nbsp;</div><div><span style="font-weight: 400;">Best wishes,</span></div><div>&nbsp;</div><div><span style="font-weight: 400;">{{sender}} and the PCI RR Managing Board</span></div><p>&nbsp;</p>
333	#DefaultReviewInvitationNewRoundRegisteredUserStage1ScheduledSubmission	default	Invitation to review a revised Stage 1 manuscript for Peer Community in Registered Reports - scheduled submission	Mail to registered user to invite them to re-review a revised Stage 1 manuscript that they previously reviewed (for scheduled submission)	<div>\r\n<p>Dear {{destPerson}},&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Thank you for your previous review of the Stage 1 Registered Report entitled "{{art_title}}", which was submitted for potential recommendation by Peer Community in Registered Reports (PCI RR). The authors have now submitted a revision and I am writing to ask if you would kindly consider reviewing it for us. The revised manuscript can be viewed and downloaded at the following address: <a href="{{art_doi}}">{{art_doi}}</a></p>\r\n<p>The authors have also supplied a tracked changes version of the manuscript and a response to reviewers. You will find these files linked on the PCI RR website once you accept the review request and they can also be downloaded directly from the links below:</p>\r\n<p>Response to reviewers: {{r2r_url}}</p>\r\n<p>Tracked changes manuscript: {{trackchanges_url}}</p>\r\n<p>To ensure swift handling of submissions, the requested review time is <strong>{{reviewDuration}}</strong>, but if you are unable to review the manuscript within this time then please let me know by reply email and we can extend the timeframe.</p>\r\n<p>Submissions that pass Stage 1 review are issued an in-principle acceptance (IPA), which guarantees a positive recommendation of the completed study if the authors adhere to the approved procedures and propose a defensible interpretation of the results. Completed manuscripts are then peer reviewed again at Stage 2, ideally by the same reviewers as Stage 1.</p>\r\n<p>In the event of a favourable outcome, all editorial correspondence (reviews, recommender’s decisions, authors’ replies) and a recommendation text will be published by PCI RR under a CC-BY 4.0 license. If, after one or several rounds of review, the preprint is rejected, the editorial correspondence (and specifically your review) will NOT be published. You will be notified by e-mail at each stage in the procedure.</p>\r\n<p>I would be grateful if you could let me know as soon as possible whether you are willing to accept my invitation to review this revised manuscript, or whether you would prefer to decline, by clicking on the link below or by logging onto the PCI RR website and going to 'For contributors —&gt; Invitation(s) to review a report' in the top menu. You will find the authors' response to reviewers and manuscript with the tracked changes manuscript linked on the website.</p>\r\n<p>Many thanks for considering this re-review request and for helping to support PCI RR.</p>\r\n<p>Best wishes,</p>\r\n<p>{{sender}}</p>\r\n</div>
334	#ReminderReviewerInvitationNewRoundRegisteredUserStage1ScheduledSubmission	default	Invitation to review a revised Stage 1 manuscript for Peer Community in Registered Reports - reminder - scheduled submission	Reminder mail to registered user to invite them to re-review a revised Stage 1 manuscript that they previously reviewed (for scheduled submission)	<div>\r\n<p>Dear {{destPerson}},</p>\r\n<p>This is a kind reminder.</p>\r\n<p>Thank you for your previous review of the Stage 1 Registered Report entitled "{{art_title}}", which was submitted for potential recommendation by Peer Community in Registered Reports (PCI RR). The authors have now submitted a revision and I am writing to ask if you would kindly consider reviewing it for us. A clean version of the revised manuscript can be viewed and downloaded at the following address: <a href="{{art_doi}}">{{art_doi}}</a></p>\r\n<p>The authors have also supplied a tracked changes version of the manuscript and a response to reviewers. You will find these files linked on the PCI RR website once you accept the review request and they can also be downloaded directly from the links below:</p>\r\n<p>Response to reviewers: {{r2r_url}}</p>\r\n<p>Tracked changes manuscript: {{trackchanges_url}}</p>\r\n<p>To ensure swift handling of submissions, the requested review time is <strong>{{reviewDuration}}</strong>, but if you are unable to review the manuscript within this time then please let me know by reply email and we can extend the timeframe.</p>\r\n<p>Submissions that pass Stage 1 review are issued an in-principle acceptance (IPA), which guarantees a positive recommendation of the completed study if the authors adhere to the approved procedures and propose a defensible interpretation of the results. Completed manuscripts are then peer reviewed again at Stage 2, ideally by the same reviewers as Stage 1.</p>\r\n<p>In the event of a favourable outcome, all editorial correspondence (reviews, recommender’s decisions, authors’ replies) and a recommendation text will be published by PCI RR under a CC-BY 4.0 license. If, after one or several rounds of review, the preprint is rejected, the editorial correspondence (and specifically your review) will NOT be published. You will be notified by e-mail at each stage in the procedure.</p>\r\n<p>I would be grateful if you could let me know as soon as possible whether you are willing to accept my invitation to review this revised manuscript, or whether you would prefer to decline, by clicking on the link below or by logging onto the PCI RR website and going to 'For contributors —&gt; Invitation(s) to review a preprint' in the top menu. You will find the authors' response to reviewers and manuscript with the tracked changes manuscript linked on the website.</p>\r\n<p>Many thanks for considering this re-review request and for helping to support PCI RR.</p>\r\n<p>Best wishes,</p>\r\n<p>PCI RR Managing Board</p>\r\n</div>
335	#RecommenderPendingReviewRequestStage1ScheduledSubmission	default	{{appName}}: A putative reviewer for a preprint you are handling - scheduled submission	Mail to recommender to indicate that a user is willing to review a preprint they are handling (for scheduled submission)	<p>Dear {{destPerson}},</p>\r\n<p>You have initiated the evaluation of the article entitled&nbsp;<strong>{{articleTitle}}</strong>&nbsp;by {{articleAuthors}} (DOI <a href="{{articleDoi}}">{{articleDoi}}</a>).</p>\r\n<p>A user {{reviewerPerson}} is willing to review this preprint.</p>\r\n<p>You can accept or decline this offer by following this link:&nbsp;<a href="{{linkTarget}}">{{linkTarget}}</a> or by logging onto the {{appName}} website and going to 'For recommenders —&gt; Preprints you are handling' in the top menu.</p>\r\n<p>We thank you for managing this evaluation.</p>\r\n<p>Yours sincerely,</p>\r\n<p>The Managing Board of {{appName}}</p>
336	#ReviewerReviewRequestAcceptedStage1ScheduledSubmission	default	{{appName}}: Your offer to review an article has been accepted - scheduled submission	Mail to user to indicate that the recommender has accepted their proposal to review the preprint (for scheduled submission)	<p>Dear {{destPerson}},</p>\r\n<p>Thank you very much for agreeing to review the Stage 1 Registered Report entitled <strong>{{articleTitle}}</strong> by {{articleAuthors}} (DOI <a href="{{articleDoi}}">{{articleDoi}}</a>).</p>\r\n<p>If you are reviewing a submission via the Scheduled Review track, then please complete your review by the date agreed with the recommender.</p>\r\n<p>If you are reviewing a submission via the Standard track, please complete your review within {{reviewDuration}}, hence before <strong>{{dueTime}}</strong>. If this deadline is too short, please let me know as soon as possible. Otherwise, thank you in advance for respecting this deadline.</p>\r\n<p>To view, write, upload, and manage your review, please follow this link <a href="{{linkTarget}}">{{linkTarget}}</a> or log onto the {{appName}} website and go to ‘For contributors —&gt; Your reviews’ in the top menu.</p>\r\n<p>When you have written or uploaded your review, you can:</p>\r\n<p>1) save a draft version of your review for future modification by clicking on the ‘Save’ button; this allows you to make changes or to complete your review later;</p>\r\n<p>or</p>\r\n<p>2) save and submit your review by clicking on the ‘Save &amp; submit your review’ button.</p>\r\n<p>If you have saved a draft version of your review, you can come back to it for modification or completion by clicking on ‘For contributors&nbsp;—&gt; Your reviews’ in the top menu, and then on the black ‘View/Edit’ button to the right on the corresponding line. Don’t forget to click on the ‘Save &amp; submit your review’ button to send your completed review to me.</p>\r\n<p>On the PCI RR website you can find an <a href="https://rr.peercommunityin.org/help/guide_for_reviewers#h_6720026472751613309075757" target="_blank" rel="noopener">expanded description of the review criteria</a>, additional <a href="https://rr.peercommunityin.org/help/guide_for_reviewers#h_7586915642301613635089357" target="_blank" rel="noopener">tips for reviewing a RR</a>, and <a href="https://rr.peercommunityin.org/help/guide_for_reviewers" target="_blank" rel="noopener">complete reviewer guidelines</a>.&nbsp;We ask our reviewers to reflect on their potential biases to help make academia more equitable. Please read the <a href="https://zenodo.org/record/5484052#.YVDePS-B1I1">Bias Reflection Guide</a> (Foster et al. 2021) before deciding whether to accept a review invitation and before writing a review. There is also guidance on how to write a fair and respectful review by Foster et al. (<a href="https://zenodo.org/record/5484072#.YVDePy-B1I1">2021</a>).</p>\r\n<p>Thanks in advance for the time spent evaluating this submission. If you have any questions, please feel free to contact us by replying to this message. The recommender handling this submission is {{recommenderPerson}}.</p>\r\n<p>Yours sincerely,</p>\r\n<p>The Managing Board of {{appName}}</p>
337	#CoRecommenderAddedOnArticleStage1ScheduledSubmission	default	{{appName}}: Your co-recommendation of a {{articlePrePost}} - scheduled submission	Mail to co-recommender to inform them that they have been declared as a co-recommender of a preprint (for scheduled submission)	<p>Dear {{destPerson}},</p>\r\n<p>A peer-review evaluation of a Stage 1 submission by {{articleAuthors}} and entitled <strong>{{articleTitle}}</strong> (DOI <a href="{{articleDoi}}">{{articleDoi}}</a>) is currently being handled by the recommender {{recommenderPerson}}. This recommender declared you as a co-recommender and, as such, as a co-author of the recommendation if they decide to recommend this submission. The reviews and the recommendation text can be viewed by clicking on this link: <a href="{{linkTarget}}">{{linkTarget}}</a> or by logging onto the {{appName}} website and going to 'For recommenders —&gt; Preprint you are co-handling' in the top menu.</p>\r\n<p>If you do not wish to be a co-recommender of this preprint, please contact us as soon as possible. Otherwise, we thank you for this contribution to {{appName}}.</p>\r\n<p>Yours sincerely,</p>\r\n<p>The Managing Board of {{appName}}</p>
338	#ReviewerReviewRequestDeclinedStage1ScheduledSubmission	default	{{appName}}: Your request to review an article has been declined - scheduled submission	Mail to user to indicate that the recommender decline their proposal to review the preprint (for scheduled submission)	<p>Dear {{destPerson}},<br><br>You kindly indicated your willingness to review the preprint entitled {{articleTitle}} by {{articleAuthors}} (DOI <a href="{{articleDoi}}">{{articleDoi}}</a>). However, the recommender of this preprint has declined your offer - they probably already found enough reviewers to evaluate this preprint.<br><br>We hope that you won't be too disappointed and that you'll still be interested in giving input to {{appName}} in the near future. <br><br>Yours sincerely,<br><br>The Managing Board of {{appName}}</p>
339	#SubmitterScheduledSubmissionDeskRevisionsRequired	default	{{appName}}: URGENT -- Revisions required to your submission	Email sent to author requesting urgent updates to a scheduled full Stage 1 submission prior to review.	<div>Dear {{destPerson}},</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>Thank you for your scheduled submission entitled <strong>{{articleTitle}}</strong>, for which the review process has been scheduled to take place between {{scheduledSubmissionLatestReviewStartDate}} and {{scheduledReviewDueDate}}.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<p><strong>**Urgent revisions are required to your full Stage 1 manuscript before we can release it to the reviewers**</strong></p>\r\n<div>Please attend as soon as possible to the following points:<br><br><br><strong>[Recommender to insert points here]</strong></div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>Please follow the steps below to revise your submission:</div>\r\n<div>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li>Make the changes to the manuscript as instructed. We recommend using version control to keep the same URL to the submitted document, but if you decide to change the URL be sure to update any references to the URL in steps 3 and 4 below.</li>\r\n<li>Once the revisions are made, <a href="https://rr.peercommunityin.org/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">login to the PCI RR website</a> and navigate to: <strong>For contributors</strong> &gt; <strong>Your submitted reports</strong></li>\r\n<li>Find the submission that needs revising and click <strong>VIEW/EDIT</strong></li>\r\n<li>Click on “Edit report”. Update your cover letter to respond to the points raised above and click “Save”.</li>\r\n<li>If you need to make any changes to the submission checklist, click on “Edit report survey” and update the survey where required, then click “Submit”. If no changes to the submission checklist are required then you can skip this step.</li>\r\n<li>Your revision has now been resubmitted for consideration by the recommender.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n</div>\r\n<div>Please attend to the above points as soon as possible. In order for the scheduled review process to continue as planned, we must have a complete Stage 1 manuscript ready for the reviewers no later than {{scheduledSubmissionLatestReviewStartDate}}.</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>Thanks again for your submission,</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>{{recommenderName}} on behalf of {{appName}}</div>
340	#SubmitterScheduledSubmissionDeskReject	default	{{appName}}: Final decision concerning your Stage 1 manuscript	Email sent to author explaining that their full Stage 1 submission has been rejected outright prior to review.	<div>Dear {{destPerson}},</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>Thank you for your scheduled submission entitled <strong>{{articleTitle}}</strong>, for which the review process was scheduled to take place between {{scheduledSubmissionLatestReviewStartDate}} and {{scheduledReviewDueDate}}.</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>Following a pre-review evaluation, we regret to inform you that your manuscript has been rejected outright from PCI RR and a revision not invited. Outright rejections of scheduled Stage 1 submissions are rare but can happen where the full Stage 1 manuscript deviates substantially from the content of the submitted snapshot, or where the manuscript fails to meet the Stage 1 criteria so severely that it would not be feasible to revise the manuscript in the short time between now and {{scheduledSubmissionLatestReviewStartDate}}.</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>The specific basis for this rejection is as follows:</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<p><strong>[recommender to add feedback here explaining the reasons for the desk rejection]</strong></p>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>The scheduled review process has now been cancelled. We wish you the best of luck with your future work.</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>{{recommenderName}} on behalf of {{appName}}</div>
341	#RecommenderPreprintValidatedScheduledSubmission	default	{{appName}}: Stage 1 scheduled submission is now ready for review	Email sent to recommender to inform them that a scheduled full Stage 1 manuscript is now ready for review	<p>Dear {{destPerson}},</p>\r\n<p>Thank you for serving as the recommender for the Stage 1 manuscript entitled <strong>{{articleTitle}}</strong> by {{articleAuthors}} (DOI <a href="{{articleDoi}}">{{articleDoi}}</a>). This submission is a full Stage 1 manuscript for scheduled review following submission of a Stage 1 snapshot (which can viewed at <a href="{{snapshotUrl}}">{{snapshotUrl}}</a>) and the review process has been scheduled to take place between {{scheduledSubmissionLatestReviewStartDate}} and {{scheduledReviewDueDate}}.</p>\r\n<p><strong>The submission is now <a href="https://rr.peercommunityin.org/help/guide_for_recommenders#h_1245019342271613643227798">review-ready</a><span style="font-weight: 400;"> so please proceed by navigating to the manuscript on the system and </span>inviting the previously agreed reviewers</strong> to assess the full submission. Please do as soon as possible and no later than {{scheduledSubmissionLatestReviewStartDate}} by clicking "Open submission to reviewers". The reviewers will then be automatically notified.</p>\r\n<p>The reviews you receive should guide your next decision – <strong>within 10 days of receiving the last review</strong> – as to whether to ‘Revise’, ‘Recommend’ or ‘Reject’ the Stage 1 manuscript.</p>\r\n<p>If your decision is to ‘Recommend’ this preprint, you will need to write a “<a href="https://rr.peercommunityin.org/help/guide_for_recommenders#h_68746834114021613643858842" target="_blank" rel="noopener">recommendation</a>” that will have its own DOI and be published by {{appName}} under the license CC-BY 4.0. The recommendation is a short summary (of a few hundred words or less), similar to a News &amp; Views piece, describing the context of the study and explaining why the article was accepted and is expected to make a valuable contribution. The limitations of the report can also be discussed. This text also contains references (citing, at least, the report being recommended). All the editorial correspondence (reviews, your decisions, authors’ replies) will also be published by {{appName}}.</p>\r\n<p>We thank you again for handling this evaluation.</p>\r\n<p>Yours sincerely,</p>\r\n<p>The Managing Board of {{appName}}</p>
342	#ReminderRecommenderPreprintValidatedScheduledSubmission	default	{{appName}}: REMINDER -- Please immediately release a Stage 1 manuscript to reviewers 	Email sent to recommender to remind them that a scheduled full Stage 1 manuscript is now ready for review and they need to open the review window	<p>Dear {{destPerson}},</p>\r\n<p>Thank you for serving as the recommender for the Stage 1 manuscript entitled <strong>{{articleTitle}}</strong> by {{articleAuthors}} (DOI <a href="{{articleDoi}}">{{articleDoi}}</a>). This submission is a full Stage 1 manuscript for scheduled review following submission of a Stage 1 snapshot (which can viewed at <a href="{{snapshotUrl}}">{{snapshotUrl}}</a>) and the review process has been scheduled to take place between {{scheduledSubmissionLatestReviewStartDate}} and {{scheduledReviewDueDate}}.</p>\r\n<p><strong>This is a reminder that the submission will be <a href="https://rr.peercommunityin.org/help/guide_for_recommenders#h_1245019342271613643227798">review-ready</a><span style="font-weight: 400;"> in one day, so please proceed by navigating to the manuscript on the system and </span>inviting the previously agreed reviewers</strong> to assess the full submission. Please do that by clicking "Open submission to reviewers". The reviewers will then be automatically notified.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Please contact the Managing Board if you are experiencing difficulties of any kind.</strong> For the scheduled review track to be sustainable, reviewers must have a review-ready Stage 1 manuscript to evaluate by the start of the review window.</p>\r\n<p>The reviews you receive should guide your next decision – <strong>within 10 days of receiving the last review</strong> – as to whether to ‘Revise’, ‘Recommend’ or ‘Reject’ the Stage 1 manuscript.</p>\r\n<p>If your decision is to ‘Recommend’ this preprint, you will need to write a “<a href="https://rr.peercommunityin.org/help/guide_for_recommenders#h_68746834114021613643858842" target="_blank" rel="noopener">recommendation</a>” that will have its own DOI and be published by {{appName}} under the license CC-BY 4.0. The recommendation is a short summary (of a few hundred words or less), similar to a News &amp; Views piece, describing the context of the study and explaining why the article was accepted and is expected to make a valuable contribution. The limitations of the report can also be discussed. This text also contains references (citing, at least, the report being recommended). All the editorial correspondence (reviews, your decisions, authors’ replies) will also be published by {{appName}}.</p>\r\n<p>We thank you again for handling this evaluation.</p>\r\n<p>Yours sincerely,</p>\r\n<p>The Managing Board of {{appName}}</p>
343	#ReminderRecommenderPreprintValidatedScheduledSubmissionLate	default	{{appName}}: URGENT REMINDER -- Please immediately release a Stage 1 manuscript to reviewers 	Email sent to recommender to remind them that a scheduled full Stage 1 manuscript is now ready for review and they are late at opening the review window	<p>Dear {{destPerson}},</p>\r\n<p>Thank you for serving as the recommender for the Stage 1 manuscript entitled <strong>{{articleTitle}}</strong> by {{articleAuthors}} (DOI <a href="{{articleDoi}}">{{articleDoi}}</a>). This submission is a full Stage 1 manuscript for scheduled review following submission of a Stage 1 snapshot (which can viewed at <a href="{{snapshotUrl}}">{{snapshotUrl}}</a>) and the review process has been scheduled to take place between {{scheduledSubmissionLatestReviewStartDate}} and {{scheduledReviewDueDate}}.</p>\r\n<p><strong>This is an urgent reminder that the submission is now <a href="https://rr.peercommunityin.org/help/guide_for_recommenders#h_1245019342271613643227798">review-ready</a><span style="font-weight: 400;"> and the start date of the review period has passed, so please proceed by navigating to the manuscript on the system and </span>inviting the previously agreed reviewers</strong> to assess the full submission. Please do ASAP and no later than {{scheduledSubmissionLatestReviewStartDate}} by clicking "Open submission to reviewers". The reviewers will then be automatically notified.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Please do this as soon as possible or contact the Managing Board if you are experiencing difficulties of any kind.</strong> For the scheduled review track to be sustainable, reviewers must have a review-ready Stage 1 manuscript to evaluate by the start of the review window.</p>\r\n<p>The reviews you receive should guide your next decision – <strong>within 10 days of receiving the last review</strong> – as to whether to ‘Revise’, ‘Recommend’ or ‘Reject’ the Stage 1 manuscript.</p>\r\n<p>If your decision is to ‘Recommend’ this preprint, you will need to write a “<a href="https://rr.peercommunityin.org/help/guide_for_recommenders#h_68746834114021613643858842" target="_blank" rel="noopener">recommendation</a>” that will have its own DOI and be published by {{appName}} under the license CC-BY 4.0. The recommendation is a short summary (of a few hundred words or less), similar to a News &amp; Views piece, describing the context of the study and explaining why the article was accepted and is expected to make a valuable contribution. The limitations of the report can also be discussed. This text also contains references (citing, at least, the report being recommended). All the editorial correspondence (reviews, your decisions, authors’ replies) will also be published by {{appName}}.</p>\r\n<p>We thank you again for handling this evaluation.</p>\r\n<p>Yours sincerely,</p>\r\n<p>The Managing Board of {{appName}}</p>
344	#RecommenderSuggestedReviewersAccepted	default	{{appName}}: suggested reviewer	Mail to recommender to notify reviewer declined invitation and suggests alternative reviewers	<p>Dear {{destPerson}},</p>\r\n<p>The reviewer {{reviewerPerson}} who just accepted your invitation to review the report entitled <strong>{{articleTitle}}</strong> suggests the following reviewers:</p>\r\n<p>{{suggestedReviewersText}}</p>\r\n<p>You can invite these reviewers by following this link <a href="{{linkTarget}}">{{linkTarget}}</a> or by logging onto the {{appName}} website and going to 'For recommenders —&gt; Report(s) you are handling’ in the top menu.</p>\r\n<p>We thank you again for managing this evaluation.</p>\r\n<p>All the best,<br>The Managing Board of {{appName}}</p>
345	#CoRecommendersArticleStatusChangedStage1ScheduledSubmission	default	{{appName}}: Your co-recommendation of a {{articlePrePost}} - scheduled submission	Mail to co-recommenders to indicate the change of the status of the preprint (for scheduled submission)	<p>Dear {{destPerson}},</p>\n<p>You are co-recommender of the article by {{articleAuthors}} entitled <strong>{{articleTitle}}</strong> (DOI <a href="{{articleDoi}}">{{articleDoi}}</a>).</p>\n<p>The status of this article has changed from "{{tOldStatus}}" to "{{tNewStatus}}".</p>\n<p>You can view the evaluation process by following this link: <a href="{{linkTarget}}">{{linkTarget}}</a> or by logging onto the {{appName}} website and going to 'For recommenders —&gt; Your recommendation of posprints (if it is a posprint) or —&gt; Preprints you are co-handling (if it is a preprint)' in the top menu.</p>\n<p>Yours sincerely,</p>\n<p>The Managing Board of {{appName}}</p>
379	#RecommenderRejectMail	default	{{appName}}: A feedback from a suggested recommender who declined	Recommender mail to managers explaining why they rejected an invite	<p>Dear members of the managing board,</p>\r\n<p>I've been invited to act as a recommender for the report entitled <strong>{{articleTitle}}</strong>, submitted by <strong>{{articleAuthors}}</strong>. I'm declining this invitation because of the following reasons:</p>\r\n<p><br><strong><em>**Please indicate these reasons here**<br><br></em></strong></p>\r\n<p>Best regards,<br>{{recommenderPerson}}</p>
380	#SubmitterPendingSurveyWarning	default	Please complete your submission at {{appName}}	Mail to warn submitters about deletion	<p>Dear author,</p>\r\n<p>Thank you for initiating a submission entitled "<strong>{{articleTitle}}"</strong> to {{appName}}.</p>\r\n<p>Your submission is currently incomplete. Please complete your submission within 14 days by going to <a href="https://rr.peercommunityin.org/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener noreferrer ugc">https://rr.peercommunityin.org/</a>&nbsp;&gt; For contributors &gt; Your submitted reports. If your submission remains incomplete, it will be automatically deleted after 14 days.</p>\r\n<p>Yours sincerely,</p>\r\n<p>The Managing Board of {{appName}}</p>
381	#SubmitterPendingSurveyWarning	default	Please complete your submission at {{appName}}	Mail to warn submitters about deletion	<p>Dear author,</p>\n<p>Thank you for initiating a submission entitled "<strong>{{articleTitle}}"</strong> to {{appName}}.</p>\n<p>Your submission is currently incomplete. Please complete your submission within 14 days by going to&nbsp;<a href="https://rr.peercommunityin.org/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener noreferrer ugc">https://rr.peercommunityin.org/</a>&nbsp;&gt; For contributors &gt; Your submitted reports. If your submission remains incomplete, it will be automatically deleted after 14 days.</p>\n<p>Yours sincerely,</p>\n<p>The Managing Board of {{appName}}</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>
382	#ManagersRecommenderAgreedAndNeedsToTakeAction	default	{{appName}} recommender needs to take action	Mail to MB to indicate that the recommender needs to take action	<p class="p1">Dear members of the Managing Board,</p>\r\n<p class="p1"><strong>{{recommenderPerson}}</strong> has taken on the following submission: {{articleTitle}}, but hasn't yet taken any action and it has been more than a week.</p>\r\n<p class="p1">Please contact the recommender to ask them what their timeline is. If they do not respond, consider assigning a different recommender.</p>\r\n<p class="p1">Have a nice day!</p>
383	#ManagersRecommenderReceivedAllReviewsNeedsToTakeAction	default	{{appName}} recommender needs to take action	Mail to MB to indicate that the recommender needs to take action	<p class="p1">Dear members of the Managing Board,</p>\r\n<p class="p1"><strong>{{recommenderPerson}}</strong> has received all outstanding reviews for the following submission: {{articleTitle}}, but hasn't yet taken any action and it has been more than a week.</p>\r\n<p class="p1">Please contact the recommender to ask them what their timeline is. If they do not respond, consider assigning a different recommender.</p>\r\n<p class="p1">Have a nice day!</p>
384	#ManagersRecommenderReceivedRevisionNeedsToTakeAction	default	{{appName}} recommender needs to take action	Mail to MB to indicate that the recommender needs to take action	<p class="p1">Dear members of the Managing Board,</p>\r\n<p class="p1"><strong>{{recommenderPerson}}</strong> has received a revised version for the following submission: {{articleTitle}}, but hasn't yet taken any action and it has been more than a week.</p>\r\n<p class="p1">Please contact the recommender to ask them what their timeline is. If they do not respond, consider assigning a different recommender.</p>\r\n<p class="p1">Have a nice day!</p>
385	#ManagersRecommenderNotEnoughReviewersNeedsToTakeAction	default	{{appName}} recommender needs to take action	Mail to MB to indicate that the recommender needs to take action	<p class="p1">Dear members of the Managing Board,</p>\r\n<p class="p1"><strong>{{recommenderPerson}}</strong> is recruiting reviewers for the following submission: {{articleTitle}}, but has not yet met the minimum 2 reviewers and has not taken any action in more than a week.</p>\r\n<p class="p1">Please contact the recommender to ask them what their timeline is. If they do not respond, consider assigning a different recommender.</p>\r\n<p class="p1">Have a nice day!</p>
386	#ManagersPreprintResubmissionStage1ScheduledSubmission	default	{{appName}}: Re-submission now ready for validation - scheduled submission	Mail sent to managers to indicate that a Presubmission is completed and ready for validation (for scheduled submission)	<div class="p-rich_text_section">Dear members of the Managing Board,</div><div class="p-rich_text_section"><br></div><div class="p-rich_text_section">The Stage 1 scheduled-track submission by {{submitterPerson}} entitled <strong data-stringify-type="bold">{{articleTitle}}</strong> that was previously in a Pre-submission stage has been resubmitted and is now ready for validation.</div><div class="p-rich_text_section"><br></div><div class="p-rich_text_section">To check this submission, please follow this link <a href="{{linkTarget}}">{{linkTarget}}</a>.</div><div class="p-rich_text_section"><br></div><div class="p-rich_text_section">Have a nice day!</div>
387	#ManagersPreprintResubmissionStage2	default	{{appName}}: Re-submission now ready for validation	Mail sent to managers to indicate that a Presubmission is completed and ready for validation	<div class="p-rich_text_section">Dear members of the Managing Board,</div><div class="p-rich_text_section"><br></div><div class="p-rich_text_section">The Stage 2 submission by {{submitterPerson}} entitled <strong data-stringify-type="bold">{{articleTitle}}</strong> that was previously in a Pre-submission stage has been resubmitted and is now ready for validation.</div><div class="p-rich_text_section"><br></div><div class="p-rich_text_section">To check this submission, please follow this link <a href="{{linkTarget}}">{{linkTarget}}</a>.<br><br></div><div class="p-rich_text_section">Have a nice day!</div><p><br></p>
388	#ManagersPreprintResubmissionStage1	default	{{appName}}: Re-submission now ready for validation	Mail sent to managers to indicate that a Presubmission is completed and ready for validation	<div class="p-rich_text_section">Dear members of the Managing Board,</div><div class="p-rich_text_section"><br></div><div class="p-rich_text_section">The Stage 1 submission by {{submitterPerson}} entitled <strong data-stringify-type="bold">{{articleTitle}}</strong> that was previously in a Pre-submission stage has been resubmitted and is now ready for validation.</div><div class="p-rich_text_section"><br></div><div class="p-rich_text_section">To check this submission, please follow this link <a href="{{linkTarget}}">{{linkTarget}}</a>.</div><div class="p-rich_text_section"><br></div><div class="p-rich_text_section">Have a nice day!</div>
389	#RecommenderChangeReviewDueDate	default	Review deadline updated	RecommenderChangeReviewDueDate	<div>Dear {{destPerson}},</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>Previously you kindly agreed to review the report entitled "<strong>{{articleTitle}}"</strong>&nbsp;(<a href="{{articleDoi}}">{{articleDoi}}</a>), submitted to {{appName}}, Thank you for this contribution and for your support of PCI.</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>The deadline for the review has been changed by the recommender. <strong>Your review is now due on {{dueDate}}</strong>.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>To view, write, upload and manage your review, please follow this link <a href="{{myReviewsLink}}">{{myReviewsLink}}</a> or log onto the {{appName}} website and go to ‘For contributors —&gt; Your reviews’ in the top menu.</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>Thanks in advance for the time and energy spent evaluating this report. We look forward to reading your review in due course.</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>Yours sincerely,</div>\r\n<div>The Managing Moard of {{appName}}</div>
390	#ManagersRecommenderAgreedAndNeedsToTakeAction	default	{{appName}} recommender needs to take action	Mail to MB indicating a recommender needs to take action	<p class="p1">Dear members of the Managing Board,</p>\n<p class="p1"><strong>{{recommenderPerson}}</strong> has taken on the following submission: {{articleTitle}}, but hasn''t yet taken any action and it has been more than a week.</p>\n<p class="p1">Please contact the recommender to ask them what their timeline is. If they do not respond, consider assigning a different recommender.</p>\n<p class="p1">Have a nice day!</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>
391	#ManagersRecommenderReceivedAllReviewsNeedsToTakeAction	default	{{appName}} recommender needs to take action	Mail to MB indicating a recommender needs to take action	<p class="p1">Dear members of the Managing Board,</p>\n<p class="p1"><strong>{{recommenderPerson}}</strong> has received all outstanding reviews for the following submission: {{articleTitle}}, but hasn''t yet taken any action and it has been more than a week.</p>\n<p class="p1">Please contact the recommender to ask them what their timeline is. If they do not respond, consider assigning a different recommender.</p>\n<p class="p1">Have a nice day!</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>
392	#ManagersRecommenderNotEnoughReviewersNeedsToTakeAction	default	{{appName}} recommender needs to take action	Mail to MB indicating a recommender needs to take action	<p class="p1">Dear members of the Managing Board,</p>\n<p class="p1"><strong>{{recommenderPerson}}</strong> is recruiting reviewers for the following submission: {{articleTitle}}, but has not yet met the minimum 2 reviewers and has not taken any action in more than a week.</p>\n<p class="p1">Please contact the recommender to ask them what their timeline is. If they do not respond, consider assigning a different recommender.</p>\n<p class="p1">Have a nice day!</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>
397	#ReminderRecommenderAcceptationReview	default	{{appName}}: A reviewer agrees to review, but asks for more time - reminder	reminder delayReminder to the recommender to tell them that a reviewer agreed to review pending an extra duration time	<p><strong>A friendly reminder</strong><span style="font-weight: 400;">.<br></span><span style="font-weight: 400;">{{message}}</span></p>
398	#RecommenderDeclineReviewNewDelay	default	{{appName}}: Your offer to review with an extended deadline has been declined	Email indicating the reviewer that the recommender has declined their request to have an extra delay to make their review	<div>Dear {{destPerson}},</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>Your offer to review the report entitled "<strong>{{articleTitle}}</strong>" with an extended timeline has been declined by the recommender. Therefore, please do not start reviewing this report.</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>Extended review deadlines are often possible, but sometimes it is necessary for recommenders to recruit reviewers who can evaluate a submission within a specific timeframe.</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>Thank for your consideration and for supporting {{appName}}.</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>Yours sincerely,</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>The Managing Board of {{appName}}</div>
399	#RecommenderAcceptReviewNewDelay	default	{{appName}}: Your offer to review with an extended deadline has been accepted	Mail to a reviewer to tell them that the recommender has accepted their request for an extra review duration time	<div>Dear {{destPerson}},</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>Your offer to evaluate the submission entitled "<strong>{{articleTitle}}</strong>" (<a href="{{articleDoi}}">{{articleDoi}}</a>) with an extended review deadline has been accepted by the recommender. <br><br>Please therefore complete your review within {{reviewDuration}} (i.e. by <strong>{{dueTime}}</strong>).&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>To view, write, upload and manage your review, please follow this link <a href="{{linkTarget}}">{{linkTarget}}</a> or log onto the {{appName}} website and go to ‘For contributors —&gt; Your reviews’ in the top menu.</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>Thank you in advance for evaluating this submission.</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>Yours sincerely,</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>The Managing Board of {{appName}}</div>
400	#ConditionalRecommenderAcceptationReview	default	{{appName}}: A reviewer agrees to review, but asks for more time	Mail to the recommender to tell them that a reviewer agreed to review pending an extra duration time	<p>Dear {{destPerson}},</p>\n<p>You have initiated the evaluation of the article entitled&nbsp;<strong>{{articleTitle}}</strong> by {{articleAuthors}} (<a href="{{articleDoi}}">{{articleDoi}}</a>).</p>\n<p>You invited {{reviewerPerson}} to review this preprint. They accepted your invitation but only if the delay to review the article <strong>can be extended to {{delay}}</strong>.</p>\n<p>You can accept or decline this offer by clicking on the corresponding button below<br><br>Thanks again for managing this evaluation.</p>\n<p>Yours sincerely,</p>\n<p>The Managing Board of {{appName}}</p>
401	#ReminderReviewerReviewDueStage1	default	{{appName}}:  Review due - reminder	Mail to reviewer to indicate that a Stage 1 review is due	<p>Dear {{destPerson}},</p><p>This is an automated reminder that your review of the Stage 1 Registered Report entitled <strong>{{articleTitle}}</strong> by {{articleAuthors}} is due today.</p><p>We fully understand the challenges involved in meeting the huge number of deadlines we face on a daily basis. Because Stage 1 Registered Reports are reviewed prior to research being undertaken, delays in the review process can be particularly challenging for authors, so if you are unable to meet this deadine, we would be extremely grateful if you could let us know by replying to this email. Otherwise, many thanks in advance for writing your review.</p><p>To view, write, upload and manage your review, please follow this link <a href="{{linkTarget}}" data-mce-href="{{linkTarget}}">{{linkTarget}}</a> or log onto the {{appName}} website and go to ‘For contributors —&gt; Your reviews’ in the top menu.</p><p>Guidelines for reviewers of Registered Reports can be found <a href="https://rr.peercommunityin.org/help/guide_for_reviewers" data-mce-href="https://rr.peercommunityin.org/help/guide_for_reviewers">here</a>, including <a href="https://rr.peercommunityin.org/help/guide_for_reviewers#h_7586915642301613635089357" data-mce-href="https://rr.peercommunityin.org/help/guide_for_reviewers#h_7586915642301613635089357">specific tips for reviewing effectively</a>.</p><p>Thank you in advance for the time spent evaluating this submission. Reviewers are vital to the success of the <em>Peer Community In</em> initiative and we greatly appreciate your contribution.</p><p>Best wishes</p><p>The Managing Board of {{appName}}</p>
402	#ReminderReviewerReviewDueStage2	default	{{appName}}:  Review due - reminder	Mail to reviewer to indicate that a Stage 2 review is due	<p>Dear {{destPerson}},</p><p>This is an automated reminder that your review of the Stage 2 Registered Report entitled <strong>{{articleTitle}} </strong>is due today.</p><p>We fully understand the challenges involved in meeting the huge number of deadlines we face on a daily basis. If you are unable to meet this deadline, we would be extremely grateful if you could let us know by replying to this email. Otherwise, many thanks in advance for writing your review.</p><p>To view, write, upload and manage your review, please follow this link <a href="{{linkTarget}}" data-mce-href="{{linkTarget}}">{{linkTarget}}</a> or log onto the {{appName}} website and go to ‘For contributors —&gt; Your reviews’ in the top menu.</p><p>Guidelines for reviewers of Registered Reports can be found <a href="%20https://rr.peercommunityin.org/help/guide_for_reviewers" data-mce-href="%20https://rr.peercommunityin.org/help/guide_for_reviewers">here</a>, including <a href="https://rr.peercommunityin.org/help/guide_for_reviewers#h_7586915642301613635089357" data-mce-href="https://rr.peercommunityin.org/help/guide_for_reviewers#h_7586915642301613635089357">specific tips for reviewing effectively</a>.</p><p>Thank you in advance for the time spent evaluating this submission. Reviewers are vital to the success of the <em>Peer Community In</em> initiative and we greatly appreciate your contribution.</p><p>Best wishes</p><p>The Managing Board of {{appName}}</p>
403	#ReminderReviewerReviewOverDueStage1	default	{{appName}}:  Review overdue	Mail to reviewer to indicate that a Stage 1 review is overdue	<p>Dear {{destPerson}},</p><p>This is an automated reminder for your review of the Stage 1 Registered Report <strong>{{articleTitle}}</strong>&nbsp;by {{articleAuthors}} that was due a few days ago.</p><p>We fully understand the challenges involved in meeting review deadlines. Because Stage 1 Registered Reports are reviewed prior to research being undertaken, delays in the review process can present significant challenges for authors, so if you are unable to meet this deadline - or would prefer to withdraw from the review process - we would be extremely grateful if you could let us know by replying to this email.</p><p>To view, write, upload and manage your review, please follow this link <a href="{{linkTarget}}" data-mce-href="{{linkTarget}}">{{linkTarget}}</a> or log onto the {{appName}} website and go to ‘For contributors —&gt; Your reviews’ in the top menu. In case of any problem or difficulties with the website, please contact <a href="{{appContactMail}}" data-mce-href="{{appContactMail}}">{{appContactMail}}</a>.</p><p>Guidelines for reviewers of Registered Reports can be found <a href="%20https://rr.peercommunityin.org/help/guide_for_reviewers" data-mce-href="%20https://rr.peercommunityin.org/help/guide_for_reviewers">here</a>, including <a href="https://rr.peercommunityin.org/help/guide_for_reviewers#h_7586915642301613635089357" data-mce-href="https://rr.peercommunityin.org/help/guide_for_reviewers#h_7586915642301613635089357">specific tips for reviewing effectively</a>.</p><p>Thank you in advance for the time spent evaluating this submission. Reviewers are vital to the success of the <em>Peer Community In</em> initiative and we greatly appreciate your contribution.</p><p>Best wishes</p><p>The Managing Board of {{appName}}</p>
404	#ReminderReviewerReviewOverDueStage2	default	{{appName}}:  Review overdue	Mail to reviewer to indicate that a Stage 2 review is overdue	<p>Dear {{destPerson}},</p><p>This is an automated reminder that your review of the Stage 2 Registered Report entitled <strong>{{articleTitle}} </strong>was due a few days ago.</p><p>We fully understand the challenges involved in meeting review deadlines. Delays in the review process can present significant challenges for authors, so if you are unable to meet this deadline - or would prefer to withdraw from the review process - we would be extremely grateful if you could let us know by replying to this email.</p><p>To view, write, upload and manage your review, please follow this link <a href="{{linkTarget}}" data-mce-href="{{linkTarget}}">{{linkTarget}}</a> or log onto the {{appName}} website and go to ‘For contributors —&gt; Your reviews’ in the top menu. In case of any problem or difficulties with the website, please contact <a href="{{appContactMail}}" data-mce-href="{{appContactMail}}">{{appContactMail}}</a>.</p><p>Guidelines for reviewers of Registered Reports can be found <a href="%20https://rr.peercommunityin.org/help/guide_for_reviewers" data-mce-href="%20https://rr.peercommunityin.org/help/guide_for_reviewers">here</a>, including <a href="https://rr.peercommunityin.org/help/guide_for_reviewers#h_7586915642301613635089357" data-mce-href="https://rr.peercommunityin.org/help/guide_for_reviewers#h_7586915642301613635089357">specific tips for reviewing effectively</a>.</p><p>Thank you in advance for the time spent evaluating this submission. Reviewers are vital to the success of the <em>Peer Community In</em> initiative and we greatly appreciate your contribution.</p><p>Best wishes</p><p>The Managing Board of {{appName}}</p>
405	#ReminderReviewerReviewSoonDueStage1	default	{{appName}}:  Review due	Mail to reviewer to indicate that a Stage 1 review is soon due	<p>Dear {{destPerson}},</p><p>Thank you very much for agreeing to review the Stage 1 Registered Report by {{articleAuthors}} entitled <strong>{{articleTitle}}</strong> <a href="{{articleDoi}}" data-mce-href="{{articleDoi}}">{{articleDoi}}</a>. As a reminder, the review due date is {{reviewDueDate}}. If you are unable to meet this deadline, we would be very grateful if you could us know by replying to this email. Otherwise, many thanks in advance for writing your review.</p><p>To view, write, upload and manage your review, please follow this link <a href="{{linkTarget}}" data-mce-href="{{linkTarget}}">{{linkTarget}}</a> or log onto the {{appName}} website and go to ‘For contributors —&gt; Your reviews’ in the top menu.</p><p>When you have written or uploaded your review, you can:</p><p>1) save a draft version of your review for future modification by clicking on the ‘Save’ button; this allows you to make changes or to complete your review later;</p><p>or</p><p>2) save and submit your review by clicking on the ‘Save &amp; submit your review’ button.</p><p>If you have saved a draft version of your review, you can come back to it for modification or completion by clicking on ‘For contributors —&gt; Your reviews’ in the top menu, and then on the black ‘View/Edit’ button to the right on the corresponding line. Don’t forget to click on the ‘Save &amp; submit your review’ button to send your completed review to me.</p><p>Guidelines for reviewers of Registered Reports can be found <a href="%20https://rr.peercommunityin.org/help/guide_for_reviewers" data-mce-href="%20https://rr.peercommunityin.org/help/guide_for_reviewers">here</a>, including <a href="https://rr.peercommunityin.org/help/guide_for_reviewers#h_7586915642301613635089357" data-mce-href="https://rr.peercommunityin.org/help/guide_for_reviewers#h_7586915642301613635089357">specific tips for reviewing effectively</a>.</p><p>Thank you in advance for the time spent evaluating this submission. Reviewers are vital to the success of the <em>Peer Community In</em> initiative and we greatly appreciate your contribution.</p><p>Yours sincerely,</p><p>The Managing Board of {{appName}}</p>
406	#ReminderReviewerReviewSoonDueStage2	default	{{appName}}:  Review due	Mail to reviewer to indicate that a Stage 2 review is soon due	<p>Dear {{destPerson}},</p><p>Thank you for kindly agreeing to review the Stage 2 submission entitled <strong>{{articleTitle}}</strong> <a href="{{articleDoi}}" data-mce-href="{{articleDoi}}">{{articleDoi}}</a>. This is an automated reminder that we hope to receive your review before {{reviewDueDate}}. If this deadline is too short, please let us know as soon as possible. Otherwise, thank you in advance for writing your review before this deadline.</p><p>To view, write, upload and manage your review, please follow this link <a href="{{linkTarget}}" data-mce-href="{{linkTarget}}">{{linkTarget}}</a> or log onto the {{appName}} website and go to ‘For contributors —&gt; Your reviews’ in the top menu.</p><p>When you have written or uploaded your review, you can:</p><p>1) save a draft version of your review for future modification by clicking on the ‘Save’ button; this allows you to make changes or to complete your review later;</p><p>or</p><p>2) save and submit your review by clicking on the ‘Save &amp; submit your review’ button.</p><p>If you have saved a draft version of your review, you can come back to it for modification or completion by clicking on ‘For contributors —&gt; Your reviews’ in the top menu, and then on the black ‘View/Edit’ button to the right on the corresponding line. Don’t forget to click on the ‘Save &amp; submit your review’ button to send your completed review.</p><p>Guidelines for PCI reviewers can be found&nbsp;<a title="guideline for reviewers" href="https://peercommunityin.org/2020/10/22/pci-reviewer-guide/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" data-mce-href="https://peercommunityin.org/2020/10/22/pci-reviewer-guide/">here</a>.</p><p>Thanks in advance for the time spent evaluating this submission.</p><p>Yours sincerely,</p><p>The Managing Board of {{appName}}</p>
407	#ArticlePublishedPCJ	default	{{appName}}: An article you evaluated is now published in the Peer Community Journal	Mail to notify recommender and reviewers that the article has been published on PCJ	<p>Dear PCI recommender and reviewers,</p>\n<p>We are pleased to inform you that the article you reviewed and recommended for {{appName}} (<a href="{{articleDoi}}">{{articleDoi}}</a>) has been published in the <a href="https://peercommunityjournal.org">Peer Community Journal</a>&nbsp;(a Diamond Open Access Journal) at the request of the authors.</p>\n<p>Here is the DOI of the article now published in Peer Community Journal: <a href="{{published_doi}}">{{published_doi}}</a></p>\n<p>Please note that links to your recommendation and reviews published by {{appName}} are available on the <a href="{{published_doi}}">webpage</a> and in the pdf of the published article.</p>\n<p>Thank you again for your contribution.</p>\n<p>The Managing Board of {{appName}}</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>
440	#SubmitterAwaitingSubmissionCOAR	default	{{appName}}: Decision concerning your submission	Mail to submitter to indicate the need to revise their preprint and to make this resubmission via COAR in the preprint server	<p>Dear {{destPerson}},</p><p>Your article, entitled <strong>{{articleTitle}}</strong>, has now been reviewed.</p><p>The referees' comments and the recommender’s decision are shown below. As you can see, the recommender found your article very interesting but suggests certain revisions.</p><p>We shall, in principle, be happy to recommend your article as soon as it has been revised in response to the points raised by the referees.</p><p>When revising your article, we remind you that your article must contain the following sections (see our Guide for Authors in the Help section of the {{appName}} website):</p><p>1) <strong>Data, script and code availability (if applicable)</strong></p><ul><li><strong>Data, statistical scripts, command lines and simulation code must be made available to readers</strong>. They should either be included in the article or deposited <strong>in </strong>an open repository such as Zenodo <strong>with a DOI</strong>. A perennial URL can be provided if no DOI is available; please note that GitHub URL are not perennial.</li><li><strong>If deposited in </strong>an open repository, a reference to <strong>Data, statistical scripts, command lines and simulation code</strong>, with a DOI or a perennial URL, must be provided in the reference list and in the "Data, script and code availability" section</li><li>The "Data, script and code availability" section must clearly indicate&nbsp;<strong>where and how</strong>&nbsp;data can be accessed.</li><li>Wherever possible, data, scripts and code should be provided in machine-readable formats. Avoid PDFs other than for textual supplementary information.</li><li>Metadata should accompany the data, to make the data understandable and reusable by the reader.</li></ul><p>&nbsp;2) <strong>Supplementary information (if applicable)</strong></p><ul><li>Supplementary information (text, tables, figures, videos, etc.) can be referred to in the article. It must be available in an open repository (such as Zenodo, Dryad, OSF, Figshare, Morphobank, Morphosource, Github, MorphoMuseuM, Phenome10k, etc. or any institutional repository, etc...) with a DOI. A perennial URL can be provided if no DOI is available.</li><li>A reference to the supplementary information, with a DOI or a perennial URL, must be provided in the reference list and in the "Supplementary information" section.</li><li>List all documents attached to the manuscript as Supplementary Information in the "Supplementary Information" section.</li></ul><p>3) <strong>Funding (mandatory)</strong></p><ul><li>All sources of funding must be listed in a separate “Funding section”. The absence of funding must be clearly indicated in this section.</li></ul><p>4) <strong>Conflict of interest disclosure (mandatory)</strong></p><ul><li>Authors should declare any potential non-financial conflict of interest (financial conflicts of interest are forbidden, see&nbsp;<a href="https://peercommunityin.org/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" data-mce-href="https://peercommunityin.org/">the PCI code of conduct</a>).</li><li>In the absence of competing interests, the authors should add the following sentence to the “Conflict of interest disclosure” section: “The authors declare they have no conflict of interest relating to the content of this article.” If appropriate, this disclosure may be completed by a sentence indicating that some of the authors are PCI recommenders: “XXX is a recommender for PCI XX.”</li></ul><p>5) <strong>Materials and methods (mandatory)</strong></p><ul><li>Details of experimental procedures and quantitative analyses must be made&nbsp;<strong>fully available</strong>&nbsp;to readers, in the text, as appendices, or as Supplementary Information deposited in an open repository, such as Zenodo, Dryad or institutional repositories with a DOI.</li><li>For specimen-based studies,&nbsp;<strong>complete repository information</strong>&nbsp;should be provided and institutional abbreviations should be listed in a dedicated subsection (if applicable). Specimens on which conclusions are based&nbsp;<strong>must be deposited in an accessible and permanent repository</strong>.</li></ul><p>When your revised article is ready, please upload the new version of your manuscript onto the same open archive (or preprint server) in which you deposited the previous version. From this open archive (or preprint server), you could directly resubmit your revised version.&nbsp;<br><br>If you have any questions, please contact us by replying to this email.</p><p>We thank you in advance for submitting your revised version.</p><p>Yours sincerely,</p><p>The Managing Board of {{appName}}</p><p><br></p><p>{{recommendationProcess}}</p>
441	#UserCompleteSubmissionCOAR	default	{{appName}}: Please complete your submission made from a preprint server	Mail to submitter when submission made from a preprint server	<p>Dear {{destPerson}}</p><p>Thank you for your submission made via a preprint server and sent to {{appName}}.</p><p>We have just created an account for you, so you can proceed with the submission.</p><p>Welcome on board!</p><p>Please click on the following link: <a href="{{linkTarget}}">Complete your submission</a></p><p>and complete your submission as follows:</p><ol><li>Complete all the missing information needed.</li><li>Click on “Save”.</li><li>Your revision has now been resubmitted for consideration by the {{appName}} Managing Board.</li></ol><p>Thanks again for your submission.</p><p>The Managing Board of {{appName}}</p>
442	#UserCompleteResubmissionCOAR	default	{{appName}}: Please complete your resubmission made from a preprint server	Mail to submitter when resubmission made from a preprint server via COAR	<p>Dear {{destPerson}}</p><p>Thank you for your resubmission made via a preprint server and sent to {{appName}}.</p><p>Please click on the following link: <a href="{{linkTarget}}" data-mce-href="{{linkTarget}}">Complete your resubmission</a><br data-mce-bogus="1"></p><p>and complete your submission as follows:</p><p>1) Check the title, authors, DOI, abstract, keywords, disciplines, and DOI/URL of data, scripts and code. Do not forget to save your modifications by clicking on the green button.</p><p>2) Click on the blue ‘EDIT YOUR REPLY TO THE RECOMMENDER’ button (mandatory step). You could then write or paste your text, upload your reply as a PDF file, and upload a document with the modifications marked in TrackChange mode. If you are submitting the final formatted version ready to be recommended, you should only add a sentence indicating that you posted the final version on the preprint server. Do not forget to <strong>save your modifications by clicking on the green button</strong>.</p><p>3) Click on the green ‘SEND RESUBMISSION’ button. This will result in your submission being sent to the recommender.</p><p>Once the recommender has read the revised version, they may decide to recommend it directly, in which case the editorial correspondence (reviews, recommender’s decisions, authors’ replies) and a recommendation text will be published by {{appName}} under the license CC-BY.</p><p>Alternatively, other rounds of reviews may be needed before the recommender reaches a favorable conclusion. They may also reject your article, in which case the reviews and decision will be sent to you, but they will not be published or publicly released by {{appName}}. They will be safely stored in our database, to which only the Managing Board has access. You will be notified by e-mail at each stage in the procedure.</p><p>We thank you in advance for submitting your revised version.</p><p>Yours sincerely,</p><p>The Managing Board of {{appName}}</p>
